definition: Fair value of financial asset or other contract with one or more underlyings, notional amount or payment provision or both, and the contract can be net settled by means outside the contract or delivery of an asset, not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Derivative Asset, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement Deduction
definition: Fair value of financial asset or other contract with one or more underlyings, notional amount or payment provision or both, and the contract can be net settled by means outside the contract or delivery of an asset, not subject to a master netting arrangement, deducted from derivative assets.

elementLabel: Derivative Asset, Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Securities Borrowed, Amount Offset Against Collateral
definition: Amount, after effects of master netting arrangements, of derivative assets, securities purchased under agreements to resell and securities borrowed offset against an obligation to return collateral under a master netting arrangement. Includes assets not subject to a master netting arrangement and not elected to be offset.

elementLabel: Derivative Asset, Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Securities Borrowed, Collateral, Obligation to Return Cash
definition: Amount of obligation to return cash collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against derivative assets, securities purchased under agreements to resell and securities borrowed.

elementLabel: Derivative Asset, Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Securities Borrowed, Collateral, Obligation to Return Securities
definition: Amount of obligation to return securities collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against derivative assets, securities purchased under agreements to resell and securities borrowed.

elementLabel: Derivative Asset, Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Securities Borrowed, Gross Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of derivative assets, securities purchased under agreements to resell and securities borrowed. Includes assets not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset.

elementLabel: Derivative Asset, Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Securities Borrowed, Not Offset, Policy Election Deduction
definition: Amount of derivative assets, securities purchased under agreements to resell and securities borrowed, elected not to be offset, deducted from derivative assets, securities purchased under agreements to resell and securities borrowed.

elementLabel: Derivative Asset, Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Securities Borrowed, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement Deduction
definition: Amount of derivative assets, securities purchased under agreements to resell and securities borrowed, not subject to a master netting arrangement, deducted from derivative assets, securities purchased under agreements to resell and securities borrowed.

elementLabel: Derivative Asset, Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Securities Borrowed, Offset Against Collateral, Net of Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement, Policy Election
definition: Amount, after effects of master netting arrangements, deduction of assets not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset, of derivative assets, securities purchased under agreements to resell and securities borrowed, offset against an obligation to return collateral under a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Basis Spread on Variable Rate
definition: The average percentage points added to the reference rate to compute the variable rate on the group of interest rate derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Cap Interest Rate
definition: Average cap rate on a group of interest rate derivatives, such as interest rate caps or collars. If market rates exceed the cap rate, a payment or receipt is triggered on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Cap Price
definition: The average cap rate on a group of price risk derivatives such as caps or collars. A payment or receipt is triggered if the market rate exceeds the cap rate on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Exchange Rate Cap (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Average cap rate on a group of foreign currency derivatives such as caps or collars. A payment or receipt is triggered if the market rate exceeds the cap rate on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Exchange Rate Cap
definition: Average cap rate on a group of foreign currency derivatives for example, but not limited to, caps or collars.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Exchange Rate Floor (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Average floor rate on a group of foreign currency derivatives such as floors or collars. A payment or receipt is triggered if the market rate falls below the floor rate on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Exchange Rate Floor
definition: Average floor rate on a group of foreign currency derivatives for example, but not limited to, floors or collars.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Fixed Interest Rate
definition: Average fixed interest rate related to the group of interest rate derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Floor Interest Rate
definition: Average floor rate on a group of interest rate derivatives, such as interest rate floor or collars. If market rates fall below the floor rate, a payment or receipt is triggered on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Floor Price
definition: The average floor rate on a group of price risk derivatives such as floors or collars. A payment or receipt is triggered if the market rate falls below the floor rate on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Foreign Currency Option Strike Price
definition: The average strike price on a group of foreign currency option contracts such as put options or call options.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Forward Exchange Rate (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The average contractual rate at which a foreign currency can be purchased or sold under the terms of a group of foreign currency derivative contracts.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Forward Exchange Rate
definition: Average contractual rate at which a foreign currency can be purchased or sold.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Forward Interest Rate
definition: Average stated rate on a group of interest rate forward or futures contracts.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Forward Price
definition: The average forward price on the group of price risk forward or futures contracts, such as gas futures contracts.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Price Risk Option Strike Price
definition: The average strike price on the group of price risk option contracts such as put options or call options.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Swaption Interest Rate
definition: Average fixed interest rate that will be received or paid upon exercise of a group of interest rate swaption contracts.

elementLabel: Derivative, Average Variable Interest Rate
definition: Average variable interest rate related to the group of interest rate derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative, Basis Spread on Variable Rate
definition: The percentage points added to the reference rate to compute the variable rate on the interest rate derivative.

elementLabel: Derivative, Cap Interest Rate
definition: Cap rate on an interest rate derivative such as an interest rate cap or collar. If market rates exceed the cap rate, a payment or receipt is triggered on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Cap Price
definition: The cap rate on a price risk derivative such as a cap or collar. A payment or receipt is triggered if the market rate exceeds the cap rate on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Collateral, Right to Reclaim Securities
definition: Amount of right to receive securities collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against derivative liabilities.

elementLabel: Derivative Credit Risk Valuation Adjustment, Derivative Assets
definition: Amount of credit risk valuation adjustment to derivative assets to properly reflect the credit quality of the counterparties.

elementLabel: Derivative Credit Risk Valuation Adjustment, Derivative Liabilities
definition: Amount of credit risk valuation adjustment to derivative liabilities to properly reflect the credit quality of the entity.

elementLabel: Derivative, Exchange Rate Cap (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Cap rate on a foreign currency derivative such as a cap or a collar. A payment or receipt is triggered if the market rate exceeds the cap rate on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Exchange Rate Cap
definition: Cap rate on a foreign currency derivative for example, but not limited to, a cap or a collar.

elementLabel: Derivative, Exchange Rate Floor (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Floor rate on a foreign currency derivative such as a floor or a collar. A payment or receipt is triggered if the market rate falls below the floor rate on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Exchange Rate Floor
definition: Floor rate on a foreign currency derivative for example, but not limited to, a floor or a collar.

elementLabel: Derivative, Fixed Interest Rate
definition: Fixed interest rate related to the interest rate derivative.

elementLabel: Derivative, Floor Interest Rate
definition: Floor rate on an interest rate derivative such as an interest rate floor or collar. If market rates falls below the floor rate, a payment or receipt is triggered on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Floor Price
definition: Floor rate on a price risk derivative such as a floor or a collar. A payment or receipt is triggered if the market rate falls below the floor rate on the contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Foreign Currency Option Strike Price
definition: The strike price on the foreign currency option contract such as a put option or a call option.

elementLabel: Derivative, Forward Exchange Rate (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The contractual rate at which a foreign currency can be purchased or sold under the terms of a foreign currency derivative contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Forward Exchange Rate
definition: Contractual rate at which a foreign currency can be purchased or sold.

elementLabel: Derivative, Forward Interest Rate
definition: Stated rate on an interest rate forward or futures contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Forward Price
definition: The forward price on the price risk forward or futures contract, such as a gas futures contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Gain on Derivative
definition: Amount of increase in the fair value of derivatives recognized in the income statement.

elementLabel: Derivative, Higher Fixed Interest Rate Range
definition: High end of the range of fixed interest rates when a range is presented for a group of interest rate derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative, Higher Range of Basis Spread on Variable Rate
definition: High end of the range of percentage points added to the reference rate to compute the variable rate on the group of interest rate derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative, Higher Variable Interest Rate Range
definition: High end of the range of variable interest rates when a range is presented for a group of interest rate derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative Instruments and Hedges, Liabilities, Noncurrent
definition: Fair value of liability arising from contracts that meet the criteria of being accounted for as derivative instruments, financial instrument or contract used to mitigate a specified risk (hedge), energy marketing activities (trading activities), expected to be settled after one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer. Examples of energy marketing activities include, but are not limited to, trading of electricity, coal, natural gas and oil using financial instruments, including, but not limited to, forward contracts, options and swaps.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Fair Value, Gross Asset and Right to Reclaim Cash, Offset
definition: Fair value of asset associated with financial liability or contract with one or more underlyings, notional amount or payment provision or both, and the contract can be net settled by means outside the contract or delivery of an asset, and right to receive cash collateral under master netting arrangements.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Fair Value, Gross Liability Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Fair value, before effects of master netting arrangements, of a financial liability or contract with one or more underlyings, notional amount or payment provision or both, and the contract can be net settled by means outside the contract or delivery of an asset. Includes liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Fair Value, Net (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Fair value as of the balance sheet date of the gross assets less the gross liabilities of a derivative liability or group of derivative liabilities.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Fair Value, Net (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Fair value of the gross liabilities less the gross assets of a derivative liability or group of derivative liabilities.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Fair Value of Collateral
definition: Fair value of securities pledged as collateral against derivative liabilities.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Not Offset, Policy Election Deduction
definition: Fair value of financial liability or contract with one or more underlyings, notional amount or payment provision or both, and the contract can be net settled by means outside the contract or delivery of an asset, elected not to be offset, deducted from derivative liabilities.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Fair value of financial liability or contract with one or more underlyings, notional amount or payment provision or both, and the contract can be net settled by means outside the contract or delivery of an asset, not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement Deduction
definition: Fair value of financial liability or contract with one or more underlyings, notional amount or payment provision or both, and the contract can be net settled by means outside the contract or delivery of an asset, not subject to a master netting arrangement, deducted from derivative liabilities.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Securities Loaned, Collateral, Right to Reclaim Cash
definition: Amount of right to receive cash collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against derivative liabilities, securities sold under agreements to repurchase and securities loaned.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Securities Loaned, Collateral, Right to Reclaim Securities
definition: Amount of right to receive securities collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against derivative liabilities, securities sold under agreements to repurchase and securities loaned.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Securities Loaned, Gross Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of derivative liabilities, securities sold under agreements to repurchase and securities loaned. Includes liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Securities Loaned, Not Offset, Policy Election Deduction
definition: Amount of derivative liabilities, securities sold under agreements to repurchase and securities loaned, elected not to be offset, deducted from derivative liabilities, securities sold under agreements to repurchase and securities loaned.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Securities Loaned, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement Deduction
definition: Amount of derivative liabilities, securities sold under agreements to repurchase and securities loaned, not subject to a master netting arrangement, deducted from derivative liabilities, securities sold under agreements to repurchase and securities loaned.

elementLabel: Derivative Liability, Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Securities Loaned, Offset Against Collateral, Net of Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement, Policy Election
definition: Amount, after effects of master netting arrangements, deduction of liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset, of derivative liabilities, securities sold under agreements to repurchase and securities loaned, offset against a right to receive collateral.

elementLabel: Derivative, Loss on Derivative
definition: Amount of decrease in the fair value of derivatives recognized in the income statement.

elementLabel: Derivative, Lower Fixed Interest Rate Range
definition: Low end of the range of fixed interest rates when a range is presented for a group of interest rate derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative, Lower Range of Basis Spread on Variable Rate
definition: Low end of the range of percentage points added to the reference rate to compute the variable rate on the group of interest rate derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative, Lower Variable Interest Rate Range
definition: Low end of the range of variable interest rates when a range is presented for a group of interest rate derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative, Nonmonetary Notional Amount, Energy Measure
definition: Nominal energy measure used to calculate payments on a derivative instrument.

elementLabel: Derivative, Nonmonetary Notional Amount, Flow Rate
definition: Nominal flow rate used to calculate payments on a derivative instrument.

elementLabel: Derivative, Nonmonetary Notional Amount, Mass
definition: Nominal mass used to calculate payments on a derivative instrument.

elementLabel: Derivative, Nonmonetary Notional Amount, Volume
definition: Nominal volume used to calculate payments on a derivative instrument.

elementLabel: Derivative, Number of Instruments Held
definition: The number of derivative instruments of a particular group held by the entity.

elementLabel: Derivative, Price Risk Option Strike Price
definition: The strike price on the price risk option contract such as a put option or a call option.

elementLabel: Derivative, Swaption Interest Rate
definition: Fixed interest rate that will be received or paid upon exercise of the interest rate swaption contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Swap Type, Average Fixed Price
definition: Average fixed price related to the group of price risk swap derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative, Swap Type, Average Variable Price
definition: Average variable price rate related to the group of price risk swap derivatives.

elementLabel: Derivative, Swap Type, Fixed Price
definition: Fixed price related to the price risk swap derivative.

elementLabel: Derivative, Swap Type, Variable Price
definition: Variable price rate related to the price risk swap derivative.

elementLabel: Derivative, Variable Interest Rate
definition: Variable interest rate in effect as of the balance sheet date related to the interest rate derivative.

elementLabel: Development Costs, Period Cost
definition: The capitalized costs incurred during the period (excluded from amortization) to obtain access to proved reserves and to provide facilities for extracting, treating, gathering and storing the oil and gas.

elementLabel: Development Wells Drilled, Net Nonproductive
definition: The number of nonproductive development wells (dry wells) drilled in the geographic area. A dry well (hole) is a well found to be incapable of producing either oil or gas in sufficient quantities to justify completion as an oil or gas well. The number of wells drilled refers to the number of wells (holes) completed at any time during the fiscal years, regardless when drilling was initiated.

elementLabel: Development Wells Drilled, Net Productive
definition: The number of productive developmental wells drilled in the geographic area. A productive well is a well that is not a dry well. The number of wells drilled refers to the number of wells (holes) completed at any time during the fiscal years, regardless when drilling was initiated.

elementLabel: Direct Premiums Earned
definition: Amount, before premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of premiums earned.

elementLabel: Direct Premiums, Life Insurance in Force (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount, before premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of life insurance in force premiums.

elementLabel: Discontinued Operation, Amounts of Material Contingent Liabilities Remaining
definition: Amounts of material contingent liabilities, for example, but not limited to, product or environmental liabilities or litigation, that remain with the entity despite the disposal of the disposal group that is classified as a component of the entity.

elementLabel: Discounted Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Entity's Share of Equity Method Investees' Standardized Discounted Future Net Cash Flows (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: The enterprise's share of the investees' standardized measure of discounted future net cash flows for the period, in the aggregate and by each geographic area for which quantities are disclosed. This information is excluded from the enterprise's standardized measure and is disclosed separately if the financial statements of the reporting enterprise include investments that are accounted for by the equity method.

elementLabel: Discounted Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Future Cash Inflows (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of estimated future cash inflows from sale of proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: Discounted Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Future Development Costs (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The future cost of developing oil and gas from proved reserves located in this geographic region.

elementLabel: Discounted Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Future Income Tax Expense (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The estimated future income tax expenses that will be incurred based on the future income less future expenses derived from production and sale of proved oil and gas reserves in this geographic region.

elementLabel: Discounted Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Future Net Cash Flows (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of estimated net future cash inflows, after subtracting future development and production costs and future income tax expenses, from sale of proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: Discounted Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Future Production Costs (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The future cost of producing oil and gas from proved reserves located in this geographic region.

elementLabel: Discounted Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Future Production Costs (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of estimated future cost to be incurred in producing proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Accounts Payable and Accrued Liabilities
definition: Amount classified as accounts payable and accrued liabilities attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Accounts Payable and Accrued Liabilities, Current
definition: Amount classified as accounts payable and accrued liabilities attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Accounts Payable, Current
definition: Amount classified as accounts payable attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Accrued Income Tax Payable
definition: Amount classified as income tax obligations attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Accrued Income Tax Payable, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as income tax obligations attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of beyond one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Accrued Liabilities, Current
definition: Amount classified as accrued liabilities attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Assets, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as assets attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of after one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Cash
definition: Amount of currency on hand, demand deposits with banks or financial institutions, and other kinds of accounts that have the general characteristics of demand deposits, held by a disposal group.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Cash and Cash Equivalents
definition: Amount classified as cash and cash equivalents attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Consideration
definition: Amount of consideration received or receivable for the disposal of assets and liabilities, including discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Costs of Goods Sold
definition: Amount of costs of goods sold attributable to disposal group, including, but not limited to, discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Deferred Revenue
definition: Amount classified as deferred revenue attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Deferred Revenue, Current
definition: Amount classified as deferred revenue attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Deferred Revenue, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as deferred revenue attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of beyond one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Deferred Tax Asset, Current
definition: Amount classified as deferred tax assets attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Deferred Tax Assets, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as deferred tax assets attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of after one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Deferred Tax Liabilities, Current
definition: Amount classified as deferred tax liabilities attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Deferred Tax Liabilities, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as deferred tax liabilities attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of beyond one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Depreciation and Amortization
definition: Amount of depreciation and amortization expense attributable to disposal group, including, but not limited to, discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, General and Administrative Expense
definition: Amount of general and administrative expense attributable to disposal group, including, but not limited to, discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Goodwill
definition: Amount classified as goodwill attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Goodwill, Current
definition: Amount classified as goodwill attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Goodwill, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as goodwill attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of after one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Intangible Assets
definition: Amount classified as intangible assets, excluding goodwill, attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Intangible Assets, Current
definition: Amount classified as intangible assets, excluding goodwill, attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Intangible Assets, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as intangible assets, excluding goodwill, attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of beyond one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Interest Expense
definition: Amount of interest expense attributable to disposal group, including, but not limited to, discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Interest Income
definition: Amount of interest income attributable to disposal group, including, but not limited to, discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Inventory
definition: Amount classified as inventory attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Inventory, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as inventory attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of beyond one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Long Lived Assets (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Amount classified as long lived assets attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Long Lived Assets, Current (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Amount classified as long lived assets attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Long Lived Assets, Noncurrent (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Amount classified as long lived assets attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of after one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Other Liabilities, Current
definition: Amount classified as other liabilities attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Other Expense
definition: Amount of other expense attributable to disposal group, including, but not limited to, discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Other Income
definition: Amount of other income attributable to disposal group, including, but not limited to, discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Other Liabilities, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as other liabilities attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of beyond one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Pension Plan Benefit Obligation, Current
definition: Amount classified as defined benefit plan benefit obligations attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Pension Plan Benefit Obligation, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as defined benefit plan benefit obligations attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of beyond one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Postretirement Plan Benefit Obligation, Current
definition: Amount classified as defined benefit non-pension postretirement plan obligations attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Postretirement Plan Benefit Obligation, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as defined benefit non-pension postretirement plan obligations attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of beyond one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Prepaid and Other Assets
definition: Amount classified as prepaid and other assets attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Prepaid and Other Assets, Current
definition: Amount classified as prepaid and other assets attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Property, Plant and Equipment
definition: Amount classified as property, plant and equipment attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Property, Plant and Equipment, Current
definition: Amount classified as property, plant and equipment attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Property, Plant and Equipment, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as property, plant and equipment attributable to disposal group held for sale or disposed of, expected to be disposed of after one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Rental Income
definition: Amount of rental income attributable to disposal group, including, but not limited to, discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Distributed Earnings
definition: The total amount of dividends declared in the period for each class of stock and the contractual amount of dividends (or interest on participating income bonds) that must be paid for the period (for example, unpaid cumulative dividends). Dividends declared in the current period do not include dividends declared in respect of prior-period unpaid cumulative dividends. Preferred dividends that are cumulative only if earned are deducted only to the extent that they are earned.

elementLabel: Distribution Fees
definition: Amount of fees from providing distribution services, including but not limited to, marketing and selling fund shares, advertising, printing and mailing of prospectuses and sales literature to investors.

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Liability Company (LLC) Member, Cash Distributions Declared
definition: Amount of equity impact of cash distributions declared to unit-holder of limited liability company (LLC).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Liability Company (LLC) Member, Cash Distributions Paid
definition: Amount of cash distribution paid to unit-holder of limited liability company (LLC).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Liability Company (LLC) Member, Distributions Declared, Per Unit
definition: Per unit of ownership amount of cash distributions declared to unit-holder of a limited liability company (LLC).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Liability Company (LLC) Member, Distributions Paid, Per Unit
definition: Per unit of ownership amount of cash distributions paid to unit-holder of a limited liability company (LLC).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Liability Company (LLC) Member, Unit Distribution
definition: Number of units distributed for payment of a unit distribution to unit-holder of a limited liability company (LLC).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Liability Company (LLC) Member, Unit Distribution, Dilution Per Unit
definition: Per unit of ownership amount of dilution resulting from the issuance of additional unit for payment of unit distribution to unit-holder of a limited liability company (LLC).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Partner, Cash Distributions Declared
definition: Amount of equity impact of cash distribution declared to unit-holder of limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Partner, Cash Distributions Paid
definition: Amount of cash distribution paid to unit-holder of limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Partner, Distributions Declared, Per Unit
definition: Per unit of ownership amount of cash distributions declared to unit-holder of a limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Partner, Distributions Paid, Per Unit
definition: Per unit of ownership amount of cash distributions paid to unit-holder of a limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Partner, Unit Distribution
definition: Number of units distributed for payment of a unit distribution to unit-holder of limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Limited Partner, Unit Distribution, Dilution Per Unit
definition: Per unit of ownership amount of dilution resulting from the issuance of additional unit for payment of unit distribution to unit-holder of a limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Member or Limited Partner, Cash Distributions Declared (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The equity impact of cash distributions declared to a common shareholder or unit-holder by a LLC or LP.

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Member or Limited Partner, Cash Distributions Paid (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The amount of cash distributions paid to a common shareholder or unit-holder by a LLC or LP.

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Member or Limited Partner, Distributions Declared, Per Unit (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Per-share or per-unit cash distributions declared to a common shareholder or unit-holder by an LLC or LP.

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Member or Limited Partner, Distributions Paid, Per Unit (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Per-share or per-unit cash distributions paid to a common shareholder or unit-holder by an LLC or LP.

elementLabel: Distribution Made to Member or Limited Partner, Share Distribution, Dilution Per Share (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Per-share or per-unit amount of dilution resulting from the issuance of additional shares or units in payment of stock or unit distribution to common unit-holders of limited liability company (LLC) or limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Dividend Income, Operating
definition: Amount of operating dividend income on securities.

elementLabel: Dividend Income, Securities, Operating, Taxable
definition: Amount of operating dividend income on securities subject to state, federal and other income tax.

elementLabel: Dividend Income, Securities, Operating, Tax Advantaged
definition: Amount of operating dividend income on securities subject to tax benefits. Excludes operating dividend income on securities exempt from state, federal and other income tax.

elementLabel: Dividend Income, Securities, Operating, Tax Exempt
definition: Amount of operating dividend income on securities exempt from state, federal and other income tax.

elementLabel: Dividends and Interest Paid
definition: The contractual amount of dividends (or interest on participating income bonds) that must be paid for the current period (for example, unpaid cumulative dividends).

elementLabel: Dividends, Preferred Stock, Cash
definition: Amount of paid and unpaid preferred stock dividends declared with the form of settlement in cash.

elementLabel: Due from Officers or Stockholders, Current
definition: Amounts due from owners or owners with a beneficial interest of more than 10 percent of the voting interests or officers of the company, which are usually due within 1 year (or 1 business cycle).

elementLabel: Due to Affiliate (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Amount of payable due to an entity that is affiliated with the reporting entity by means of direct or indirect ownership. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: Due to Employees (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Amounts due to employees, not to include stockholders or officers. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: Due to Officers or Stockholders (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Amounts due to recorded owners or owners with a beneficial interest of more than 10 percent of the voting interests or officers of the company. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: Due to Other Related Parties, Current (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: The aggregate obligations owed to related parties other than affiliates, officers or stockholders (for example, owner's immediate families or employee pension trusts) at the financial statement date. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: Effective Income Tax Rate Reconciliation, at Federal Statutory Income Tax Rate, Percent
definition: Percentage of domestic federal statutory tax rate applicable to pretax income (loss).

elementLabel: Electrical Transmission Revenue
definition: Revenue from the bulk transport of high voltage power, typically over longer distances, between generating plants and distribution systems.

elementLabel: Employee Service Share-based Compensation, Estimated Quantity of Shares to be Repurchased in Following Period, Maximum
definition: Maximum number of shares to be repurchased in accordance with a policy to use treasury stock to satisfy share-award conversions.

elementLabel: Employee Service Share-based Compensation, Estimated Quantity of Shares to be Repurchased in Following Period, Minimum
definition: Minimum number of shares to be repurchased in accordance with a policy to use treasury stock to satisfy share-award conversions.

elementLabel: Employee Service Share-based Compensation, Nonvested Awards, Compensation Not yet Recognized, Share-based Awards Other than Options
definition: Unrecognized cost of unvested share-based awards, other than options, awarded to employees as compensation.

elementLabel: Employee Service Share-based Compensation, Nonvested Awards, Compensation Not yet Recognized, Stock Options
definition: Unrecognized cost of unvested options awarded to employees as compensation.

elementLabel: Employee Service Share-based Compensation, Tax Benefit Realized from Exercise of Stock Options
definition: Disclosure of the aggregate tax benefit realized from the exercise of stock options and the conversion of similar instruments during the annual period.

elementLabel: Employee Stock Ownership Plan (ESOP), Weighted Average Purchase Price of Shares Purchased
definition: Weighted average purchase price of capital shares purchased through an employee stock ownership plan.

elementLabel: Energy Marketing Contract Liabilities, Noncurrent
definition: Fair value of liability arising from energy marketing activities (trading activities), expected to be settled after one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer. Examples of energy marketing activities include, but are not limited to, trading of electricity, coal, natural gas and oil using financial instruments, including, but not limited to, forward contracts, options and swaps.

elementLabel: Entity-Wide Revenue, Major Customer, Percentage (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Percentage of revenue generated from a single external customer that accounts for 10 percent or more of an entity's revenues.

elementLabel: Environmental Costs Recognized, Capitalized
definition: Amount of costs recognized in the balance sheet for known or estimated future costs arising from requirements to perform activities to remediate one or more sites.

elementLabel: Environmental Costs Recognized, Capitalized in Period
definition: Amount of environmental remediation costs capitalized. These expenditures may relate to long-lived improvements in operating facilities.

elementLabel: Environmental Costs Recognized, Recovery Credited to Expense
definition: Amount of any recovery from third parties that is credited to environmental remediation costs.

elementLabel: Environmental Exit Costs, Reasonably Possible Additional Loss
definition: Estimate of reasonably possible loss exposure in excess of amount accrued for remediation, site restoration, postclosure, monitoring commitments, or other exit costs associated with the sale, disposal or abandonment of a particular property resulting from unanticipated contamination of the assets.

elementLabel: Equipment Expense
definition: This element represents equipment expense including depreciation, repairs, rentals, and service contract costs. This item also includes equipment purchases which do not qualify for capitalization in accordance with the entity's accounting policy. This item may also include furniture expenses.

elementLabel: Equity Contributions to Finance Leveraged Buyout (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of proceeds of equity contributions, such as contributions from affiliates or members of senior management, used to finance a leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Equity Financing for Leveraged Buyout (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Total equity financing of leveraged buyout transaction including the sale of equity and equity contributions from shareholders.

elementLabel: Equity Issuance, Amount Per Share (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The amount per share assigned to the consideration received for equity securities issued by a development stage enterprise during a specific stock issuance since its inception.

elementLabel: Equity Issuance, Number of Equity Securities Issued for Cash (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The number of equity securities issued for cash by a development stage enterprise during a specific issuance since inception.

elementLabel: Equity Issuance, Number of Equity Securities Issued for Noncash Considerations (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The number of equity securities issued for noncash considerations by a development stage enterprise during a specific issuance since inception.

elementLabel: Development Stage Entities, Equity Issuance, Per Share Amount (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Amount per share or per unit assigned to the consideration received of equity securities issued for development stage entities.

elementLabel: Equity Issuance, Amount (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The total dollar amount assigned to the consideration received for equity securities issued during a specific stock issuance.

elementLabel: Equity Issued in Business Combination, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value of equity issued in a business combination.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Equity Method Investment, Dividends or Distributions
definition: This item represents disclosure of the amount of dividends or other distributions received from unconsolidated subsidiaries, certain corporate joint ventures, and certain noncontrolled corporation; these investments are accounted for under the equity method of accounting. This element excludes distributions that constitute a return of investment, which are classified as investing activities.

elementLabel: Equity Method Investment, Summarized Financial Information, Liabilities
definition: The amount of liabilities reported by an equity method investment of the entity.

elementLabel: Escrow Deposit Disbursements Related to Property Acquisition (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Escrow deposit disbursements related to property acquisition in noncash investing or financing transactions.

elementLabel: Escrow Deposit Disbursements Related to Property Acquisition
definition: Amount of escrow deposit disbursements related to property acquisition in noncash investing or financing transactions.

elementLabel: Excess Capital
definition: The amount by which the company's Total Capital exceeds the minimum required for capital adequacy purposes.

elementLabel: Excess Capital to Risk Weighted Assets
definition: The amount of excess Total Capital divided by risk weighted assets which are assets that are weighted for credit risk according to a formula used by the Reserve Bank.

elementLabel: Excess Stock, Shares Authorized
definition: Maximum number of excess stock shares permitted to be issued.

elementLabel: Excess Stock, Shares Issued
definition: Number of excess stock shares of an entity that have been sold or granted to shareholders.

elementLabel: Excess Stock, Shares Outstanding
definition: Number of shares of excess stock held by shareholders.

elementLabel: Excess Tangible Capital
definition: Tangible Capital, which, generally includes outstanding stock plus retained earnings, in excess of the minimum amount of tangible capital required.

elementLabel: Excess Tangible Capital Required for Capital Adequacy to Tangible Assets
definition: The amount of excess Tangible Capital, which generally includes outstanding stock plus retained earnings, divided by tangible assets (assets with physical existence) as defined in the regulations.

elementLabel: Excess Tier One Leverage Capital
definition: The amount by which the company's Tier 1 Leverage Capital exceeds the minimum required for capital adequacy purposes.

elementLabel: Excess Tier One Leverage Capital to Average Assets
definition: The amount of excess Tier 1 Leverage Capital divided by average assets as defined in the regulations.

elementLabel: Excess Tier One Risk Based Capital
definition: The amount by which the company's Tier 1 Risk Based Capital exceeds the minimum required for capital adequacy purposes.

elementLabel: Excess Tier One Risk Based Capital to Risk Weighted Assets
definition: The amount of excess Tier 1 Risk Based Capital (which consists of the types of financial capital considered the most reliable and liquid, primarily Shareholders' equity. Examples of Tier 1 capital are common stock or unit, preferred stock or unit that is irredeemable and noncumulative, and retained earnings) divided by risk-weighted assets which are assets that are weighted for credit risk according to a formula used by the Reserve Bank.

elementLabel: Exchange Fees
definition: The amount of expense in the period for fees charged by securities exchanges for the privilege of trading securities listed on that exchange. Some fees vary with the related volume, while others are fixed.

elementLabel: Expense Related to Distribution or Servicing and Underwriting Fees
definition: Expense related to distribution, servicing and underwriting fees.

elementLabel: Exploration Costs, Period Cost
definition: The capitalized costs incurred during the period (excluded from amortization) in identifying areas that may warrant examination and in examining specific areas that are considered to have prospects of containing oil and gas reserves, including costs of drilling exploratory wells and exploratory-type stratigraphic test wells. Exploration costs may be incurred both before acquiring the related property (sometimes referred to in part as prospecting costs) and after acquiring the property. Principal types of exploration costs, which include depreciation and applicable operating costs of support equipment and facilities and other costs of exploration activities, are: costs of topographical, geographical and geophysical studies, rights of access to properties to conduct those studies, and salaries and other expenses of geologists, geophysical crews, and others conducting those studies. Collectively, these are sometimes referred to as geological and geophysical or "G&G" costs. Exploration costs also include costs of carrying and retaining undeveloped properties, such as delay rentals, ad valorem taxes on properties, legal costs for title defense, the maintenance of land and lease records, dry hole contributions and bottom hole contributions, costs of drilling and equipping exploratory wells and costs of drilling exploratory-type stratigraphic test wells.

elementLabel: Exploratory Wells Drilled, Net Nonproductive
definition: The number of nonproductive exploratory wells (dry wells) drilled in the geographic area. A dry well (hole) is a well found to be incapable of producing either oil or gas in sufficient quantities to justify completion as an oil or gas well. The number of wells drilled refers to the number of wells (holes) completed at any time during the fiscal years, regardless when drilling was initiated.

elementLabel: Exploratory Wells Drilled, Net Productive
definition: The number of productive exploratory wells drilled in the geographic area. A productive well is a well that is not a dry well. The number of wells drilled refers to the number of wells (holes) completed at any time during the fiscal years, regardless when drilling was initiated.

elementLabel: Extinguishment of Debt, Amount
definition: Gross amount of debt extinguished.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Assets Measured on Recurring Basis, Accounts Receivable (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position asset caption which represents a class of assets, or which may include an individual asset, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Assets Measured on Recurring Basis, Cash and Cash Equivalents (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position asset caption which represents a class of assets, or which may include an individual asset, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Assets Measured on Recurring Basis, Equity Method Investments (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position asset caption which represents a class of assets, or which may include an individual asset, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Assets Measured on Recurring Basis, Federal Funds Sold and Securities Borrowed or Purchased under Agreements to Resell (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position asset caption which represents a class of assets, or which may include an individual asset, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Assets Measured on Recurring Basis, Investment in Federal Home Loan Bank Stock (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position asset caption which represents a class of assets, or which may include an individual asset, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Assets Measured on Recurring Basis, Retained Interest (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position asset caption which represents a class of assets, or which may include an individual asset, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Assets Measured on Recurring Basis, Servicing Rights (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position asset caption which represents a class of assets, or which may include an individual asset, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Assets Measured on Recurring Basis, Trading Account Assets (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position asset caption which represents a class of assets, or which may include an individual asset, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value Assumptions, Exercise Price
definition: Agreed upon price for the exchange of the underlying asset.

elementLabel: Fair Value Assumptions, Expected Dividend Payments
definition: Amount of dividends expected to be paid to holders of the underlying shares or contracted instruments over the term of the instruments life.

elementLabel: Fair Value Assumptions, Expected Dividend Rate
definition: Expected dividends to be paid to holders of the underlying shares or financial instruments (expressed as a percentage of the share or instrument's price).

elementLabel: Fair Value Assumptions, Expected Volatility Rate
definition: Measure of dispersion, in percentage terms (for instance, the standard deviation or variance), for a given stock price.

elementLabel: Fair Value Assumptions, Risk Free Interest Rate
definition: Risk-free interest rate assumption used in valuing an instrument.

elementLabel: Fair Value Assumptions, Weighted Average Expected Dividend
definition: Weighted average expected dividend for an entity using a valuation technique with different dividend rates during the contractual term.

elementLabel: Fair Value Assumptions, Weighted Average Volatility Rate
definition: Weighted average expected volatility of stock price.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Estimate Not Practicable, Accounts Payable
definition: This item represents a financial instrument (as defined) for which it is not practicable to estimate fair value. Such disclosure may be for an individual financial instrument or a class of financial instruments.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Estimate Not Practicable, Accounts Receivable
definition: This item represents a financial instrument (as defined) for which it is not practicable to estimate fair value. Such disclosure may be for an individual financial instrument or a class of financial instruments.

definition: This item represents a financial instrument (as defined) for which it is not practicable to estimate fair value. Such disclosure may be for an individual financial instrument or a class of financial instruments.

definition: This item represents a financial instrument (as defined) for which it is not practicable to estimate fair value. Such disclosure may be for an individual financial instrument or a class of financial instruments.

definition: This item represents a financial instrument (as defined) for which it is not practicable to estimate fair value. Such disclosure may be for an individual financial instrument or a class of financial instruments.

definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position asset caption which represents a class of assets, or which may include an individual asset, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Cap Rate
definition: Ratio of the net operating income produced by an asset and its capital cost (original prices paid to buy the asset), used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Control Premium
definition: Percentage above fair value that an investor seeking to acquire control of an entity will pay, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Counterparty Credit Risk
definition: Risk that one party to the contract will default expressed as a percentage, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Discount for Lack of Marketability
definition: Adjustment to the discount rate used to measure fair value for lack of ability to convert business interests into cash quickly.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Discount Rate
definition: Interest rate used to find the present value of an amount to be paid or received in the future as an input to measure fair value. For example, but not limited to, weighted average cost of capital (WACC), cost of capital, cost of equity and cost of debt.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Entity Credit Risk
definition: Risk associated with risk of default, credit spread risk and downgrade risk, expressed as a percentage, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Long-term Net of Tax Operating Income Margin, Percent
definition: Ratio of an entity's operating income net of tax to its revenue, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Long-term Pre-tax Operating Margin, Percent
definition: Long-term pre-tax operating income as a percentage of net sales, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Loss Severity
definition: Loss, including interest and principal, incurred on a defaulted security, expressed as a percentage of the original principal balance, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Offered Quotes
definition: Price at which a dealer is willing to buy an instrument, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Prepayment Rate
definition: Rate at which loans or a loan portfolio are expected to prepay principal balances, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Price Earnings Ratio Multiple
definition: Ratio of an entity's stock price to its earnings per share. Price earnings (P/E) ratio is used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Price Per Square Foot
definition: Cost of construction of real property stated is a price per square foot, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Price Per Square Meter
definition: Cost of construction of real property stated is a price per square meter, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value Inputs, Probability of Default
definition: Percentage of likelihood a loan will not be repaid and instead default, used as an input to measure fair value.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Liabilities Measured on Recurring Basis, Accounts Payable (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Liabilities Measured on Recurring Basis, Borrowings (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Liabilities Measured on Recurring Basis, Commitments (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Liabilities Measured on Recurring Basis, Federal Funds Purchased (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Liabilities Measured on Recurring Basis, Federal Funds Purchased and Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase (Deprecated 2011-01-31)

elementLabel: Fair Value, Liabilities Measured on Recurring Basis, Federal Home Loan Bank Borrowings (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.
