definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Liabilities Measured on Recurring Basis, Mandatorily Redeemable Preferred Stock (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Obligations, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value of obligations measured on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Liabilities Measured on Recurring Basis, Securities Loaned or Sold under Agreements to Repurchase (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Liabilities Measured on Recurring Basis, Securities Sold, Not yet Purchased (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Subordinated Debt Obligations, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value of subordinated debt obligations including, but not limited to, subordinated loan, subordinated bond, subordinated debenture or junior debt.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Liabilities Measured on Recurring Basis, Trading Liabilities (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents a certain statement of financial position liability caption which represents a class of liabilities, or which may include an individual liability, measured at fair value on a recurring basis.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Measurement with Unobservable Inputs Reconciliation, Liability, Transfers Into Level 3
definition: Amount of transfers of financial instrument classified as a liability into level 3 of the fair value hierarchy.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Measurement with Unobservable Inputs Reconciliation, Recurring Basis, Instruments Classified in Shareholders' Equity, Issuances
definition: Amount of issuances of financial instrument classified in shareholders' equity measured using unobservable inputs that reflect the entity's own assumption about the assumptions market participants would use in pricing.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Measurement with Unobservable Inputs Reconciliation, Recurring Basis, Instruments Classified in Shareholders' Equity, Purchases
definition: Amount of purchases of financial instrument classified in shareholders' equity measured using unobservable inputs that reflect the entity's own assumption about the assumptions market participants would use in pricing.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Measurement with Unobservable Inputs Reconciliation, Recurring Basis, Instruments Classified in Shareholders' Equity, Settlements
definition: Amount of settlements of financial instrument classified in shareholders' equity measured using unobservable inputs that reflect the entity's own assumption about the assumptions market participants would use in pricing.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Measurement with Unobservable Inputs Reconciliation, Recurring Basis, Instruments Classified in Shareholders' Equity, Transfers Into Level 3
definition: Amount of transfers of financial instrument classified in shareholders' equity into level 3 of the fair value hierarchy.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Measurement with Unobservable Inputs Reconciliation, Recurring Basis, Instruments Classified in Shareholders' Equity, Transfers out of Level 3
definition: Amount of transfers of financial instrument classified in shareholders' equity out of level 3 of the fair value hierarchy.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Measurement with Unobservable Inputs Reconciliation, Recurring Basis, Liability, Issuances
definition: Amount of issuances of financial instrument classified as a liability measured using unobservable inputs that reflect the entity's own assumption about the assumptions market participants would use in pricing.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Measurement with Unobservable Inputs Reconciliation, Recurring Basis, Liability, Sales
definition: Amount of sales of financial instrument classified as a liability measured using unobservable inputs that reflect the entity's own assumption about the assumptions market participants would use in pricing.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Measurement with Unobservable Inputs Reconciliation, Recurring Basis, Value of Instruments Classified in Shareholders' Equity
definition: Fair value of financial instrument classified in shareholders' equity measured using unobservable inputs that reflect the entity's own assumption about the assumptions market participants would use in pricing.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Option, Disclosures Related to Election, Items Existing at Effective Date, Derivative Financial Instruments, Assets (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: This element represents a financial asset or liability (as defined) for which the fair value option is elected and which item existed at the effective date (as defined).

elementLabel: Fair Value, Option, Disclosures Related to Election, Items Existing at Effective Date, Derivative Financial Instruments, Liabilities (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: This element represents a financial asset or liability (as defined) for which the fair value option is elected and which item existed at the effective date (as defined).

elementLabel: Fair Value, Option, Disclosures Related to Election, Items Existing at Effective Date, Servicing Rights (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: This element represents a financial asset or liability (as defined) for which the fair value option is elected and which item existed at the effective date (as defined).

elementLabel: Fair Value, Option, Disclosures Related to Election, Items Existing at Effective Date, Trading Account Assets (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: This element represents a financial asset or liability (as defined) for which the fair value option is elected and which item existed at the effective date (as defined).

elementLabel: Fair Value, Option, Disclosures Related to Election, Items Existing at Effective Date, Trading Liabilities (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: This element represents a financial asset or liability (as defined) for which the fair value option is elected and which item existed at the effective date (as defined).

elementLabel: Fair Value, Option, Loans Held as Assets, 90 Days or More Past Due
definition: This item represents the aggregate fair value of loans held as assets that are 90 days or more past due for which the fair value option has been elected.

elementLabel: Fair Value, Option, Loans Held as Assets, Aggregate Amount in Nonaccrual Status
definition: This item represents the aggregate fair value of loans held as assets that are in nonaccrual status for which the fair value option has been elected, if the entity's policy is to recognize interest income separately from other changes in fair value.

elementLabel: FDIC Indemnification Asset
definition: Carrying amount of receivable assets originating from the indemnification agreement with the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC), in which the FDIC is to partially cover losses.

elementLabel: FDIC Indemnification Asset, Accretion of Discount
definition: Increases to the indemnification asset due to accretion of the loan discount relating to loss sharing agreements with the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC).

elementLabel: FDIC Indemnification Asset, Acquisitions
definition: Amount of increases to the indemnification asset due to acquisitions of assets relating to loss sharing agreements with the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC).

elementLabel: FDIC Indemnification Asset, Additional Estimated Losses
definition: Amount of increases to the indemnification asset due to additional estimated losses assumed by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC), relating to loss sharing agreements with the FDIC.

elementLabel: FDIC Indemnification Asset, Cash Payments Received
definition: Amount of decreases to the indemnification asset due to cash payments received relating to loss sharing agreements with the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC).

elementLabel: FDIC Indemnification Asset, Disposals
definition: Amount of decreases to the indemnification asset due to disposals relating to loss sharing agreements with the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC).

elementLabel: Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation Premium Expense
definition: Amount of expense for Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC) insurance.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank Advances
definition: Amount of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) advances to member financial institutions.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Affordable Housing Program, Principal Outstanding
definition: Principal amount outstanding of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) relating to the Affordable Housing Program (AHP).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Branch of FHLB Bank, Amount of Advances
definition: Amount of advances from the Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLB).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Branch of FHLB Bank, Interest Rate
definition: Discloses the single interest rate [if] applicable to the advances from the Federal Home Loan Bank, by branch, as of the Balance Sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Branch of FHLB Bank, Interest Rate, Range from
definition: Discloses the lowest interest rate applicable to any of the advances from the Federal Home Loan Bank, by branch, as of the Balance Sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Branch of FHLB Bank, Interest Rate, Range to
definition: Discloses the highest interest rate applicable to any of the advances from the Federal Home Loan Bank, by branch, as of the Balance Sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Branch of FHLB Bank, Weighted Average Interest Rate
definition: Describes the weighted average interest rate applicable to the specific advances from the Federal Home Loan Bank, by branch, as of the Balance Sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Commitment Fees
definition: Amount of unearned commitment fees on advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Discount
definition: Amount of unamortized discount on outstanding advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Discount on Affordable Housing Program
definition: Amount of unamortized discount on outstanding Affordable Housing Program (AHP) advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Call Date, after Rolling Year Five
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next call date after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Call Date, in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next call date within the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Call Date, in Rolling Year Five
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next call date within the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Call Date, in Rolling Year Four
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next call date within the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Call Date, in Rolling Year Three
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next call date within the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Call Date, in Rolling Year Two
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next call date within the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Put or Convert Date, after Rolling Year Five
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next put or convert date after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Put or Convert Date, in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next put or convert date within the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Put or Convert Date, in Rolling Year Five
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next put or convert date within the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Put or Convert Date, in Rolling Year Four
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next put or convert date within the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Put or Convert Date, in Rolling Year Three
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next put or convert date within the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Earlier of Contractual Maturity or Next Put or Convert Date, in Rolling Year Two
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with the earlier of contractual maturity or next put or convert date within the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Fixed Rate
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with fixed interest rate.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Fixed Rate, after One Year
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with fixed interest rate maturing more than one year after the latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Fixed Rate, under One Year
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with fixed interest rate maturing within one year of the latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Floating Rate
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with floating interest rate.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Floating Rate, after One Year
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with floating interest rate maturing more than one year after the latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Floating Rate, under One Year
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) with floating interest rate maturing within one year after the latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, General Debt Obligations, Disclosures, Collateral Pledged (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: States the amount of the collateral pledged in support of Federal Home Loan Bank advances outstanding as of the Balance Sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, General Debt Obligations, Disclosures, Collateral Pledged
definition: Amount of the collateral pledged in support of federal home loan bank advances outstanding.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, General Debt Obligations, Disclosures, Repayment and Penalties
definition: Amount of repayments and penalties incurred in the satisfaction or roll-over of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLB) advance.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Index Amortizing
definition: Par amount of index amortizing advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Interest Rate on Affordable Housing Program Subsidized Loans
definition: Interest rate of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) on Affordable Housing Program (AHP) subsidized loans.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, after Rolling Year Five
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, Due after Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of advances from Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, Due in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of advances from Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, Due in Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of advances from Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, Due in Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of advances from Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, Due in Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of advances from Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, Due in Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of advances from Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, Due in Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of advances from Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, in Rolling Year Five
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, in Rolling Year Four
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, in Rolling Year Three
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Maturities Summary, in Rolling Year Two
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Outstanding, Greater than One Billion Dollars Per Borrower, Amount
definition: Amount of advances outstanding made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) in excess of one billion U.S. dollars per borrower.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Outstanding, Greater than One Billion Dollars Per Borrower, Number of Borrowers
definition: Number of borrowers with Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) advances outstanding greater than one billion U.S. dollars.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Outstanding, Greater than One Billion Dollars Per Borrower, Percent
definition: Percentage of advances outstanding made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) that are in excess of one billion U.S. dollars per borrower to the total advances outstanding.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Par Value
definition: Par amount of advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Premium
definition: Amount of unearned premiums on outstanding advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Weighted Average Interest Rate
definition: Weighted average interest rate on advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Weighted Average Interest Rate, Index Amortizing
definition: Weighted average interest rate on index amortizing advances made by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Weighted Average Interest Rate, Maturing after Rolling Year Five
definition: Weighted average interest rate on advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Weighted Average Interest Rate, Maturing in Next Twelve Rolling Months
definition: Weighted average interest rate on advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Weighted Average Interest Rate, Maturing in Rolling Year Five
definition: Weighted average interest rate on advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Advances, Weighted Average Interest Rate, Maturing in Rolling Year Four
definition: Weighted average interest rate on advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank Advances, Weighted Average Interest Rate, Maturing in Rolling Year Three
definition: Weighted average interest rate on advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank Advances, Weighted Average Interest Rate, Maturing in Rolling Year Two
definition: Weighted average interest rate on advances made and reported by Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Consolidated Obligations
definition: Amount of joint and several obligations consisting of consolidated obligation bonds and discount notes issued by Federal Home Loan Banks (FHLBanks).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Consolidated Obligations, Bonds
definition: Amount of joint and several obligations consisting of bonds issued by Federal Home Loan Banks (FHLBanks).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Consolidated Obligations, Discount Notes
definition: Amount of joint and several obligations consisting of discount notes issued by Federal Home Loan Banks (FHLBanks).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Leverage Capital, Actual
definition: Amount of leveraged capital of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank), set by the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Leverage Capital, Required
definition: Minimum amount of leverage capital required for Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank), set by the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Leverage Ratio, Actual
definition: Leverage ratio of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank), calculated per regulations of the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Regulatory Capital, Actual
definition: Amount of regulatory capital of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank), set by the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Regulatory Capital Ratio, Actual
definition: Regulatory capital ratio of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank), calculated per regulations of the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Regulatory Capital, Required
definition: Minimum amount of regulatory capital required for Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank), set by the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Risk-Based Capital, Actual
definition: Amount of risk-based capital of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank), set by the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank, Risk-Based Capital, Required
definition: Minimum amount of risk-based capital required for Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank), set by the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA).

elementLabel: Federal Home Loan Bank Stock and Federal Reserve Bank Stock
definition: Amount of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLB) and Federal Reserve Bank stock.

elementLabel: Fees and Commissions, Correspondent Clearing
definition: Service revenue earned by a depository institution that holds the account balances of other financial institutions and provides services thereto. Such services include check collection and item processing.

elementLabel: Fees and Commissions, Credit and Debit Cards
definition: Amount of income earned from credit card services (including late, over limit, and annual fees) and debit card services (including interchange fees, annual fees and other fees). Excludes interest income earned on credit card balances and transactions.

elementLabel: Fees and Commissions, Credit Cards
definition: Income earned from credit card services including late, over limit, and annual fees. This item excludes interest income earned on credit card balances and transactions.

elementLabel: Fees and Commissions, Debit Cards
definition: Amount of income earned from debit card services, including interchange fees, annual fees and other fees.

elementLabel: Fees and Commissions, Depositor Accounts
definition: Includes amounts charged depositors for: (1) maintenance of their accounts (maintenance charges); (2) failure to maintain specified minimum balances on account; (3) exceeding the number of checks or transactions allowed to be processed in a given period; (4) checks drawn on no minimum balance deposit accounts; (5) withdrawals from nontransaction deposit accounts; (6) closing savings accounts before a specified minimum period of time has elapsed; (7) accounts which have remained inactive for extended periods of time or which have become dormant; (8) use of automated teller machines or remote service units; (9) checks drawn against insufficient funds that the bank assesses regardless of whether it decides to pay, return or hold the check; (10) issuing stop payment orders; (11) certifying checks; and (12) accumulating or disbursing funds deposited in IRAs or Keogh Plan accounts when not handled by the bank's trust department. This item does not include penalties assessed on the early withdrawal of time deposits.

elementLabel: Fees and Commissions, Fiduciary and Trust Activities
definition: Income from services rendered by trust departments or by any consolidated subsidiaries acting in a fiduciary capacity, including fees earned for (1) acting as an agent for fiduciary placement and loans and (2) custody or investment advisory services when such fees are not separately billed to the customer. This item excludes commissions and fees received for the accumulation or disbursement of funds deposited to Individual Retirement or Keogh plan accounts when such are not handled by the reporting entity's trust department.

elementLabel: Fees and Commissions, Mortgage Banking
definition: The noninterest income derived from mortgage banking activities (fees and commissions), excluding fees earned from servicing third-party assets.

elementLabel: Fees and Commissions, Mortgage Banking and Servicing
definition: Income from mortgage banking activities (fees and commissions) and servicing real estate mortgages, credit cards, and other financial assets held by others net of any related impairment of capitalized service costs. Also includes any premiums received in lieu of regular servicing fees on such loans only as earned over the life of the loans.

elementLabel: Fees and Commissions, Other
definition: Fee and commission revenue earned from sources not otherwise specified in the existing taxonomy.

elementLabel: Fees and Commissions, Transfer Agent
definition: Revenues from providing transfer agent services to corporations. Such services include maintaining records of investors and account balances and transactions, canceling and issuing certificates, processing investor mailings and dealing with any associated problems (i.e. lost or stolen certificates).

elementLabel: Financial Guarantee Insurance Contracts, Claim Liability, Significant Components of Change, Accretion of Discount
definition: This element represents the amount of the change in the claim liability related to financial guarantee insurance contracts arising from the accretion of the discount of the claim liability.

elementLabel: Financial Guarantee Insurance Contracts, Future Expected Premium Revenue to be Recognized, Fourth Rolling Quarter
definition: Amount of premium revenue under financial guarantee insurance contracts expected to be recognized in the fourth rolling quarter following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Financial Guarantee Insurance Contracts, Future Expected Premium Revenue to be Recognized, Next Rolling Quarter

elementLabel: Financial Guarantee Insurance Contracts, Premium Receivable, Premium Expected to be Collected, Fourth Rolling Quarter

elementLabel: Financial Guarantee Insurance Contracts, Premiums Receivable, New Business Written (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of new business written during the period on financial guarantee insurance contracts where premium is received over the contract period.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Owned and Pledged as Collateral, Amount Eligible to be Repledged by Counterparty
definition: Fair value of financial instrument held by the entity for its own account (proprietary securities) for trading or investment purposes that are carried at fair value and pledged to counterparties as collateral for financing transactions where counterparty has the right to re-pledge such.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Owned and Pledged as Collateral, Amount Not Eligible to be Repledged by Counterparty
definition: Fair value of financial instrument held by the entity for its own account (proprietary securities) for trading or investment purposes that are carried at fair value and pledged to counterparties as collateral for financing transactions where counterparty does not have the right to re-pledge such.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Sold, Not yet Purchased, Derivatives and Other Contracts
definition: Fair value of obligations arising from derivatives and other contracts sold short.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Subject to Mandatory Redemption, Number of Stockholders
definition: Number of stockholders holding financial instruments subject to mandatory redemption.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Subject to Mandatory Redemption, Past Contractual Redemption Date, Due to Outstanding Activity
definition: Amount of mandatorily redeemable capital stock past the contractual redemption date due to outstanding activity.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Subject to Mandatory Redemption, Past Contractual Redemption Date, Due to Regulatory Action
definition: Amount of mandatorily redeemable capital stock past the contractual redemption date due to regulatory action.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Subject to Mandatory Redemption, Redeemable in Year Five
definition: Amount of mandatorily redeemable capital stock maturing in year five following the date of the latest balance sheet.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Subject to Mandatory Redemption, Redeemable in Year Four
definition: Amount of mandatorily redeemable capital stock maturing in year four following the date of the latest balance sheet.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Subject to Mandatory Redemption, Redeemable in Year Three
definition: Amount of mandatorily redeemable capital stock maturing in year three following the date of the latest balance sheet.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Subject to Mandatory Redemption, Redeemable in Year Two
definition: Amount of mandatorily redeemable capital stock maturing in year two following the date of the latest balance sheet.

elementLabel: Financial Instruments Subject to Mandatory Redemption, Redeemable within One year
definition: Amount of mandatorily redeemable capital stock maturing within one year following the date of the latest balance sheet.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Allowance for Credit Losses, Individually Evaluated for Impairment (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The valuation allowance for financing receivables that are expected to be uncollectible that were individually evaluated for impairment.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Allowance for Credit Losses, Individually Evaluated for Impairment
definition: Amount of valuation allowance for financing receivables that are expected to be uncollectible that were individually evaluated for impairment.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Allowance for Credit Losses, Recovery
definition: Amount of recovery of financing receivables doubtful of collection that were previously charged off.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Allowance for Credit Losses, Write-downs
definition: Amount of direct write-downs of financing receivables charged against the allowance.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Modifications, Number of Contracts (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Number of financing receivables that have been modified by troubled debt restructurings.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Modifications, Number of Contracts
definition: Number of financing receivables that have been modified by troubled debt restructurings.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Modifications, Post-Modification Recorded Investment (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of investment in financing receivables (after modification) modified by troubled debt restructurings.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Modifications, Post-Modification Recorded Investment
definition: Post-modification amount of investment in financing receivables modified by troubled debt restructurings.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Modifications, Pre-Modification Recorded Investment (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of investment in financing receivables (before modification) modified by troubled debt restructurings.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Modifications, Pre-Modification Recorded Investment
definition: Pre-modification amount of investment in financing receivables modified by troubled debt restructurings.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Modifications, Subsequent Default, Number of Contracts (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Number of financing receivables that have been modified by troubled debt restructurings within the previous 12 months and for which there was a payment default.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Modifications, Subsequent Default, Number of Contracts
definition: Number of financing receivables that have been modified by troubled debt restructurings within the previous 12 months and for which there was a payment default.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Modifications, Subsequent Default, Recorded Investment (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of investment related to financing receivables modified by troubled debt restructurings within the previous 12 months, for which there was a payment default.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Modifications, Subsequent Default, Recorded Investment
definition: Amount of investment related to financing receivables modified by troubled debt restructurings within the previous 12 months, for which there was a payment default.

elementLabel: Finite-lived Intangible Assets Acquired (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life acquired.

elementLabel: Finite-lived Intangible Assets Acquired
definition: Amount of increase in assets, excluding financial assets, lacking physical substance with a definite life, resulting from a business combination.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, after Year Five
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Next Twelve Months
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized during the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Rolling after Year Five
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Rolling Year Five

For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Year Five
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized during the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Year Four
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized during the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Year Three
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized during the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Amortization Expense, Year Two
definition: Amount of amortization expense for assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life expected to be recognized during the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Finite-lived Intangible Assets, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of assets, excluding financial assets, that lack physical substance, having a limited useful life.

elementLabel: Floor Brokerage
definition: Broker-dealers often use other brokers to execute trades on their behalf. The trading broker-dealer becomes a customer of the executing broker-dealer and pays a floor brokerage fee. Such fees are paid periodically either directly to the executing broker-dealer or through a clearing house.

elementLabel: Floor Brokerage, Exchange and Clearance Fees
definition: The amount of expense during the period for floor brokerage fees paid to other broker-dealers to execute trades on their behalf, stock exchange fees, order flow fees, and clearance fees.

elementLabel: Foreclosed Real Estate Expense
definition: Amount of expense recognized during the period for the foreclosure on real estate assets.

elementLabel: Foreign Currency Exchange Rate, Remeasurement
definition: Foreign exchange rate used to remeasure amounts denominated in a currency other than functional currency into functional currency.

elementLabel: Foreign Currency Exchange Rate, Translation
definition: Foreign exchange rate used to translate amounts denominated in functional currency to reporting currency.

elementLabel: Foreign Currency Transaction Loss, before Tax
definition: Amount before tax of foreign currency transaction realized and unrealized loss recognized in the income statement.

elementLabel: Foreign Earnings Repatriated
definition: Amount of foreign earnings repatriated from subsidiaries outside the country of domicile.

elementLabel: Forward Contract Indexed to Issuer's Equity, Redeemable Stock, Redemption Requirements, Amount (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: For freestanding forward contracts that are indexed to, and potentially settled in an entity's own stock, that has redemption requirements, amount of redemption requirements for all issues of capital stock that are redeemable at fixed or determinable prices on fixed or determinable dates in each of the five years following the date of the latest statement of financial position presented.

elementLabel: Forward Contract Indexed to Issuer's Equity, Settlement Alternatives, Shares, at Fair Value
definition: Number of shares as a settlement alternative for each freestanding forward contract.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Due in Rolling after Year Five
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Due in Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Due in Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Due in Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Due in Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Cash Inflows
definition: Amount of estimated future accumulated cash inflow from the sale of proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Development Costs
definition: Amount of estimated future accumulated cash outflow for costs to be incurred in developing proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Production Costs
definition: Amount of estimated future accumulated cash outflow for costs to be incurred in producing proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: Gain Contingency, Patents Allegedly Infringed upon, Number
definition: Number of entity's patents that another entity has allegedly infringed.

elementLabel: Gain Contingency, Patents Found Infringed upon, Number
definition: Number of entity's patents that another entity was found to have infringed.

elementLabel: Gain Contingency, Patents Found Not Infringed upon, Number
definition: Number of entity's patents that another entity was found not to have infringed.

elementLabel: Gain on Derivative Instruments, Pretax
definition: Aggregate gain on all derivative instruments recognized in earnings during the period, before tax effects.

elementLabel: Gain on Sale of Investments
definition: The difference between the carrying value and the sale price of an investment. A gain would be recognized when the sale price of the investment is greater than the carrying value of the investment. This element refers to the Gain included in earnings and not to the cash proceeds of the sale.

elementLabel: Gas and Oil Acreage, Developed, Gross (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Developed acres are acres spaced or assigned to productive wells. Gross acreage is an acre in which a working interest is owned.

elementLabel: Gas and Oil Acreage, Developed, Net (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Developed acres are acres spaced or assigned to productive wells. Net acres is the sum of the fractional interest owned based on working interests or other economic arrangements.

elementLabel: Gas and Oil Acreage, Undeveloped, Gross (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Undeveloped acreage is considered to be those lease acres on which wells have not been drilled or completed to a point that would permit the production of commercial quantities of oil and gas regardless of whether or not such acreage contains proved reserves. Gross acreage is an acre in which a working interest is owned.

elementLabel: Gas and Oil Acreage, Undeveloped, Net (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Undeveloped acreage is considered to be those lease acres on which wells have not been drilled or completed to a point that would permit the production of commercial quantities of oil and gas regardless of whether or not such acreage contains proved reserves. Net acres is the sum of the fractional interest owned based on working interests or other economic arrangements.

elementLabel: Gas and Oil Area, Developed, Gross
definition: Area spaced or assigned to productive wells in which a working interest is owned.

elementLabel: Gas and Oil Area, Developed, Net
definition: Fractional interest owned based on working interests or other economic arrangements of area spaced or assigned to productive wells.

elementLabel: Gas and Oil Area, Undeveloped, Gross
definition: Lease area in which a working interest is owned and on which wells have not been drilled or completed to a point that would permit the production of commercial quantities of oil and gas regardless of whether or not such area contains proved reserves.

elementLabel: Gas and Oil Area, Undeveloped, Net
definition: Fractional interest owned based on working interests or other economic arrangements of lease area on which wells have not been drilled or completed to a point that would permit the production of commercial quantities of oil and gas regardless of whether or not such area contains proved reserves.

elementLabel: Gas Imbalance Payable (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred and payable to an underproduced working interest owner when an overproduced working interest owner has sold gas in excess of the party's ownership percentage. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: Gas Purchase Contract, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value of contract to purchase gas.

elementLabel: Gas Purchase Payable (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred and payable for purchases of natural gas. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: General and Administrative Expense Ratio
definition: Ratio of non-life general and administrative expenses to non-life net premiums earned.

elementLabel: General Fair Value Hedge Information, Minimum R Square, Percentage
definition: The correlation coefficient between the hypothetical instrument and the hedged item used in determination of the effectiveness of a hedging relationship.

elementLabel: General Partner Distributions
definition: Distributions from earnings to the general partner of a partnership included in the consolidated financial statements.

elementLabel: General Partners' Capital Account, Period Distribution Amount
definition: The total amount of distributions to the general partner during the period.

elementLabel: Goodwill, Acquired During Period
definition: Amount of increase in asset representing future economic benefits arising from other assets acquired in a business combination that are not individually identified and separately recognized resulting from a business combination.

elementLabel: Goodwill, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of asset representing the future economic benefits arising from other assets acquired in a business combination that are not individually identified and separately recognized.

elementLabel: Goodwill, Impaired, Adjustment to Initial Estimate Amount
definition: The amount of an adjustment to a previously reported goodwill impairment charge, which will be recognized in the subsequent reporting period.

elementLabel: Goodwill, Impairment Loss, Net of Tax
definition: Amount after tax of loss recognized that results from the write-down of an asset representing the future economic benefits arising from other assets acquired in a business combination that are not individually identified and separately recognized.

elementLabel: Gross Investment Income, Operating
definition: Amount, before investment expense, of income earned from investments in securities and real estate. Includes, but is not limited to, real estate investment, policy loans, dividends, and interest. Excludes realized gain (loss) on investments.

elementLabel: Ground Leases, Accumulated Amortization
definition: Accumulated amortization on long-term land leases capitalized as part of real property.

elementLabel: Ground Leases, Gross
definition: Gross long-term land leases capitalized as part of real property.

elementLabel: Ground Leases, Net
definition: Net long-term land leases which are capitalized as part of real property.

elementLabel: Guaranteed Benefits Incurred (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Total of amount of guaranteed minimum benefit expense incurred during the period presented, resulting in an increase to the liability for expected guaranteed minimum benefits in excess of projected account values, for all guaranteed benefit types.

elementLabel: Guaranteed Benefits Paid (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Total amount of guaranteed minimum benefit payments to policyholders and contract holders, during the period presented, resulting in a decrease to the liability for expected guaranteed minimum benefits in excess of projected account values, for all guaranteed benefit types.

elementLabel: Guaranty Fee Income
definition: This item represents the portion of monthly guaranty fees collected representing the interest imputed and recognized under the prospective interest method on the present value of the contractually stipulated guarantee payments at inception of the contract.

elementLabel: Health Care Organization, Allowance for Doubtful Accounts, Percentage of Accounts Receivable
definition: Ratio of the allowance for doubtful accounts to accounts receivable, expressed as a percentage, for health care organizations.

elementLabel: Hedging Liabilities, Noncurrent
definition: Fair value of liability arising from a financial instrument or contract used to mitigate a specified risk (hedge), expected to be settled after one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Accumulated Unrecognized Holding Gain
definition: Amount of accumulated unrealized gain on investments in debt securities classified as held-to-maturity.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Accumulated Unrecognized Holding Loss
definition: Amount of accumulated unrealized loss on investments in debt securities classified as held-to-maturity.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, 12 Months or Longer, Accumulated Loss
definition: Amount of accumulated unrealized loss on investments in debt securities classified as held-to-maturity that have been in a continuous loss position for twelve months or longer.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, 12 Months or Longer, Aggregate Loss
definition: Amount of unrealized loss on investments in held-to-maturity securities that have been in a loss position for twelve months or longer.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, Accumulated Loss
definition: Amount of accumulated unrealized loss on investments in debt securities classified as held-to-maturity in a continuous loss position.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, Aggregate Loss
definition: Amount of unrealized loss on investments in held-to-maturity securities.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, Less than 12 Months, Accumulated Loss
definition: Amount of accumulated unrealized loss on investments in debt securities classified as held-to-maturity that have been in a continuous loss position for less than twelve months.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, Less than 12 Months, Aggregate Loss
definition: Amount of unrealized loss before deducting unrealized gain on investments in held-to-maturity securities that have been in a loss position for less than twelve months.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Next Rolling Twelve Months, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of held-to-maturity debt securities maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Remainder of Fiscal Year, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of held-to-maturity debt securities maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Rolling after Ten Years, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of held-to-maturity debt securities maturing after the tenth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Rolling Year Six Through Ten, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of held-to-maturity debt securities maturing in the sixth through tenth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Rolling Year Two Through Five, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of held-to-maturity debt securities maturing in the second through fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Single Maturity Date, Amortized Cost Basis
definition: Amount of investment in held-to-maturity debt securities with a single maturity date, after other than temporary impairment (OTTI) accretion.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Single Maturity Date, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of investment in held-to-maturity debt securities with a single maturity date.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity, Securities in Unrealized Loss Positions, Qualitative Disclosure, Other, Loan to Collateral Value, Ratio
definition: This item represents the loan to collateral ratio of the underlying assets in the security, represented as a percentage, which was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are not other-than-temporarily impaired.

elementLabel: Immediate, Terminal Funding Annuities, Interest Rate, High End
definition: Maximum interest rate in the range of interest rates used to calculate future benefits to be paid to or on behalf of policyholders and related expenses less the present value of future net premiums using assumptions such as estimates of expected investment yields, mortality, morbidity, terminations and expenses, applicable at the time the insurance contracts are made and cost of settling insured claims and cost incurred in the claim settlement process of immediate terminal funding annuities.

elementLabel: Immediate, Terminal Funding Annuities, Interest Rate, Low End
definition: Minimum interest rate in the range of interest rates used to calculate future benefits to be paid to or on behalf of policyholders and related expenses less the present value of future net premiums using assumptions such as estimates of expected investment yields, mortality, morbidity, terminations and expenses, applicable at the time the insurance contracts are made and cost of settling insured claims and cost incurred in the claim settlement process of immediate terminal funding annuities.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, with No Related Allowance, Average Recorded Investment
definition: Amount of average investment of impaired financing receivables for which there is no related allowance for credit losses.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, with No Related Allowance, Interest Income, Accrual Method
definition: Amount of interest income, recognized on accrual basis, on financing receivables that are recognized as impaired, for which there is no related allowance for credit losses.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, with No Related Allowance, Interest Income, Cash Basis Method
definition: Amount of interest income, recognized on cash basis, on financing receivables, for which there is no related allowance for credit losses and are recognized as impaired.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, with No Related Allowance, Recorded Investment
definition: Amount of investment in impaired financing receivables for which there is no related allowance for credit losses.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, with No Related Allowance, Unpaid Principal Balance
definition: Amount of unpaid principal balance of impaired financing receivables for which there is no related allowance for credit losses.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, with Related Allowance, Average Recorded Investment
definition: Amount of average investment of impaired financing receivables for which there is a related allowance for credit losses.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, with Related Allowance, Interest Income, Accrual Method
definition: Amount of interest income, recognized on accrual basis, on financing receivables, for which there is a related allowance for credit losses and are recognized as impaired.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, with Related Allowance, Interest Income, Cash Basis Method
definition: Amount of interest income on financing receivables, for which there is a related allowance for credit losses, recognized on a cash-basis method of accounting that the financing receivables were impaired.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, with Related Allowance, Recorded Investment
definition: Amount of investment in impaired financing receivables for which there is a related allowance for credit losses.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, with Related Allowance, Unpaid Principal Balance
definition: Unpaid principal balance of impaired financing receivables for which there is a related allowance for credit losses.

elementLabel: Impairment Effect on Earnings Per Share, after Tax
definition: After tax earnings per share or per unit impact arising from asset impairment.

elementLabel: Impairment Effect on Earnings Per Share, Pretax
definition: Pretax earnings per share or per unit impact arising from asset impairment.

elementLabel: Incentive Fee, Amount Paid (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount paid to managing member or general partner for incentive rights held.

elementLabel: Incentive Fee Expense
definition: Amount of expense for incentive rights held by the managing member or general partner, of limited liability company (LLC) or limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Income Taxes Paid
definition: The amount of cash paid during the current period to foreign, federal, state, and local authorities as taxes on income.

elementLabel: Income Tax Examination, Estimate of Possible Loss
definition: Estimated amount of loss resulting from an adverse tax position.

elementLabel: Income Tax Examination, Range of Possible Losses (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The estimated range of reasonably possible losses resulting from an adverse position taken by a taxing authority.

elementLabel: Income Tax Holiday, Income Tax Benefits Per Share
definition: Per share amount effect of the income tax benefit resulting from the income tax holidays granted by taxing jurisdictions.

elementLabel: Effective Income Tax Rate Reconciliation, Nondeductible Expense, Research and Development, Amount
definition: Amount of the difference between reported income tax expense (benefit) and expected income tax expense (benefit) computed by applying the domestic federal statutory income tax rates to pretax income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to nondeductible research and development expense.

elementLabel: Effective Income Tax Rate Reconciliation, Tax Credit, Amount
definition: Amount of the difference between reported income tax expense (benefit) and expected income tax expense (benefit) computed by applying the domestic federal statutory income tax rates to pretax income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to tax credits. Including, but not limited to, research credit, foreign tax credit, investment tax credit, and other tax credits.

elementLabel: Increase in Restricted Cash
definition: Amount of cash outflow associated with funds that are not available for withdrawal or use (such as funds held in escrow) and are associated with underlying transactions that are classified as investing activities.

elementLabel: Incremental Effect on Balance Sheet, Asset Line Item Balance, Application of FAS 158 Recognition Provisions
definition: Balances of individual asset line items in the year-end statement of financial position that are incrementally affected by the recognition provisions of FAS 158 in the year of initial application.

elementLabel: Incremental Effect on Balance Sheet, Asset Line Item Balance, before Additional Minimum Pension Liability (AML) Adjustment and Application of FAS 158 Recognition Provisions
definition: Balances of individual asset line items in the year-end statement of financial position that are incrementally affected, before the adjustment to additional minimum pension liability (AML) and before the adjustment to adopt FAS 158, by the recognition provisions of FAS 158 in the year of initial application.

elementLabel: Policyholder Benefits and Claims Incurred, Net, Property, Casualty and Liability
definition: Amount, after effect of policies assumed or ceded, of expense related to provision for policy benefits and costs incurred for property and casualty insurance contracts.

elementLabel: Indefinite-lived Intangible Assets Acquired
definition: Amount of increase in assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with an indefinite life, resulting from a business combination.

elementLabel: Indefinite-lived Intangible Assets (Excluding Goodwill), Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, that lack physical substance, having a projected indefinite period of benefit.

elementLabel: Information Technology and Data Processing
definition: The amount of expenses incurred in the period for information technology and data processing products and services.

elementLabel: Insurance Commissions
definition: The expense incurred by an insurance company to persons or entities for generating or placing insurance or investment contracts with the company, usually determined as a percentage of policy or contract premiums. Excludes advances or draws to be applied against commissions earned.

elementLabel: Insurance Commissions and Fees
definition: Income from agency and brokerage operations (includes sales of annuities and supplemental contracts); service charges, commissions, and fees from the sale of insurance and related services; and management fees from separate accounts, deferred annuities, and universal life products.

elementLabel: Insurance Services Revenue
definition: Revenue from insurance services, including net premiums earned, gain on sale of insurance block, agency management fees and insurance contract fees and commissions.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of amortization expense for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination expected to be recognized in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Next Twelve Months
definition: Amount of amortization expense expected to be recognized during the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of amortization expense expected to be recognized in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year ended for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of amortization expense for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination expected to be recognized in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of amortization expense for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination expected to be recognized in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of amortization expense for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination expected to be recognized in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of amortization expense for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination expected to be recognized in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Year Five
