definition: Amount of amortization expense expected to be recognized during the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Year Four
definition: Amount of amortization expense expected to be recognized during the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Year Three
definition: Amount of amortization expense expected to be recognized during the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Amortization Expense, Year Two
definition: Amount of amortization expense expected to be recognized during the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets, Gross (Excluding Goodwill)
definition: Amount before accumulated amortization of intangible assets, excluding goodwill.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets, Net (Including Goodwill)
definition: Carrying amount of finite-lived intangible assets, indefinite-lived intangible assets and goodwill. Goodwill is an asset representing the future economic benefits arising from other assets acquired in a business combination that are not individually identified and separately recognized. Intangible assets are assets, not including financial assets, lacking physical substance.

elementLabel: Interest Accrual Rate Associated with Amortization Method of Present Value of Future Insurance Profits
definition: States the assumed long-term market interest rate used in the determination of the present value of future profits on long-duration contracts acquired in a business combination.

elementLabel: Interest and Dividend Income, Operating
definition: Represents the total of interest and dividend income, including any amortization and accretion (as applicable) of discounts and premiums, earned from (1) loans and leases whether held-for-sale or held-in-portfolio; (2) investment securities; (3) federal funds sold; (4) securities purchased under agreements to resell; (5) investments in banker's acceptances, commercial paper, or certificates of deposit; (6) dividend income; or (7) other investments not otherwise specified herein.

elementLabel: Interest and Dividend Income, Securities, Operating
definition: Amount of operating dividend and interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securities.

elementLabel: Interest and Dividend Income, Securities, Operating, Available-for-sale
definition: Amount of operating dividend and interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on available-for-sale securities.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities, Operating, Held-to-maturity
definition: Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on held-to-maturity securities.

elementLabel: Interest and Dividend Income, Securities, Operating, Other
definition: Amount of other operating dividend and interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securities.

elementLabel: Interest and Dividend Income, Securities, Operating, Trading or Measured at Fair Value
definition: Amount of operating dividend and interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on trading securities and other forms of securities that provide ownership interests.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans and Leases
definition: The aggregate interest and fee income generated by: (1) loans the Entity has positive intent and ability to hold for the foreseeable future, or until maturity or payoff, including commercial and consumer loans, whether domestic or foreign, which may consist of: (a) industrial and agricultural; (b) real estate; and (c) real estate construction loans; (d) trade financing; (e) lease financing; (f) home equity lines-of-credit; (g) automobile and other vehicle loans; and (h) credit card and other revolving-type loans and (2) loans and leases held-for-sale which may include mortgage loans, direct financing, and sales-type leases.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans and Leases Held-for-sale
definition: The amount of interest and fee income earned from loans held-for-sale, including mortgage loans, and interest earned from direct financing and sales-type leases held-for-sale.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans and Leases Held-in-portfolio
definition: Interest and fee income generated by loans the Entity intends and has the ability to hold for the foreseeable future, or until maturity or payoff, including commercial and consumer loans, whether domestic or foreign, which may consist of: (1) industrial and agricultural; (2) real estate; and (3) real estate construction loans; (4) trade financing; (5) lease financing; (6) home equity lines-of-credit; (7) automobile and other vehicle loans; and (8) credit card and other revolving-type loans. Also includes interest income for leases held by the Entity.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Commercial
definition: Interest and fee income related to commercial loans including industrial and agricultural, real estate (commercial and residential, construction and development), trade financing, and lease financing.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Commercial and Residential, Real Estate
definition: Interest and fee income from commercial and residential real estate loans.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Commercial, Industrial, and Agricultural Loans
definition: Interest and fee income generated from all commercial, industrial, and agricultural loans.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Commercial, Real Estate
definition: Interest and fee income generated from loans secured by commercial properties. Examples of properties commonly securing commercial real estate loans may include office buildings, apartment buildings, shopping centers, industrial property, and hotels.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Consumer
definition: Interest and fee income generated from consumer loans. Consumer loans are loans to individuals for household, family, and other personal expenditures. Such loans include residential mortgages, home equity lines-of-credit, automobiles and marine transport loans, credit card transactions, and others.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Consumer, Home Equity
definition: Interest and fee income from home equity lines-of-credit extended to individuals (borrowers). Such loans are generally secured by the borrower's equity in her or his home.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Consumer Installment, Automobiles, Marine, and Other Vehicles
definition: Interest and fee income generated by automobile, marine, and other vehicle loans made to individuals.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Consumer Installment, Credit Card
definition: Interest and fee income from credit card balances due from individuals. Such loans are considered revolving credit arrangements.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Consumer, Real Estate
definition: Interest and fee income generated from loans secured by one- to four-family residential properties. This item excludes home equity lines-of-credit.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Foreign
definition: Interest and fee income generated by commercial and consumer loans, made by foreign branches of the reporting entity, which may include loans to foreign governments, foreign banks and other financial institutions, commercial and industrial entities, and citizens of not domiciled in the same country as the reporting entity.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans Held-for-sale, Mortgages
definition: Interest and fee income from mortgage loans considered to be held-for-sale.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Lease Financing
definition: Interest and fee income generated by direct lease financing which consists of an institution owning and leasing personal property for the use of its customers at the customers' specific request.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Other Consumer
definition: Interest and fee income from other loans extended to individual consumers.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Real Estate Construction
definition: Interest and fee income from loans used for real estate development and construction costs. Such loans are referred to as "Construction" loans or mortgages.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Loans, Trade Financing
definition: Interest and fee income generated by trade financing. Trade financing is a specialized area of commercial lending frequently used by businesses that engage in international activities. Such financing includes open account financing, sales on consignment, documentary collections, advances against collections, letters of credit, bankers' acceptances, factoring, and forfeiting.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Nonmortgage Loans and Leases Held-for-sale
definition: Amount of interest and fee income earned from loans held-for-sale, including interest earned from direct financing and sales-type leases held-for-sale, but excluding mortgage loans held-for sale.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Other Loans
definition: Interest and fee income derived from loans not otherwise specified in the existing taxonomy.

elementLabel: Interest and Fee Income, Other Loans Held-for-sale
definition: Interest and fee income from other loans considered to be held-for-sale not otherwise specified in the existing taxonomy.

elementLabel: Interest and Other Income
definition: The amount of interest income and other income recognized during the period. Included in this element is interest derived from investments in debt securities, cash and cash equivalents, and other investments which reflect the time value of money or transactions in which the payments are for the use or forbearance of money and other income from ancillary business-related activities (that is, excluding major activities considered part of the normal operations of the business).

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Deposits, at Carrying Value (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Cash on deposit with financial institutions, classified as a cash equivalent, that earns interest, either at a fixed or market rate.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Checking
definition: Amount of interest-bearing domestic checking deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Other
definition: Amount of other interest-bearing domestic deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Costs Capitalized Adjustment
definition: Amount of interest costs capitalized disclosed as an adjusting item to interest costs incurred.

elementLabel: Interest Credited to Policyholders Account Balances
definition: Interest allocated to policyholders holding contracts under which the insurer must provide a guaranteed yield.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Beneficial Interests Issued by Consolidated Variable Interest Entities
definition: Interest expense on beneficial interests issued by consolidated variable interest entities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Borrowings
definition: Aggregate amount of interest expense on all borrowings.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Capital Securities
definition: Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on capital securities issued by the reporting entity.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Commercial Paper
definition: Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on commercial paper.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Demand Deposit Accounts
definition: Interest expense incurred on demand deposit accounts that represent borrowings rather than outstanding drafts.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Domestic Deposits
definition: The aggregate interest expense incurred on all domestic deposits.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Federal Funds Purchased and Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase
definition: The aggregate expense incurred on federal funds purchased and securities sold under agreements to repurchase. If amounts recognized as payables under repurchase agreements have been offset against amounts recognized as receivables under reverse repurchase agreements and reported as a net amount on the balance sheet, the income and expense from these agreements may be reported on a net basis.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Federal Home Loan Bank and Federal Reserve Bank Advances, Long-term
definition: Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on long-term borrowings associated with Federal Home Loan Bank and Federal Reserve Bank advances.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Federal Home Loan Bank and Federal Reserve Bank Advances, Short-term
definition: Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on short-term borrowings associated with Federal Home Loan Bank and Federal Reserve Bank advances.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Foreign Deposits
definition: Interest expense on all foreign deposits.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Junior Subordinated Debentures
definition: Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on junior subordinated debentures. Includes amortization of expenses incurred in the issuance of subordinated notes and debentures.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Long-term Debt
definition: Aggregate amount of interest paid or due on all long-term debt.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Long-term Debt and Capital Securities
definition: Total interest expense on long-term debt and capital securities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Medium-term Notes
definition: Interest expense on medium-Term notes.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Money Market Deposits
definition: Interest expense incurred on all money market deposits.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Negotiable Order of Withdrawal (NOW) Deposits
definition: Interest expense incurred on the amount of Negotiable Order of Withdrawal (NOW). Interest-bearing transaction account that combines the payable on demand feature of checks and investment feature of savings accounts. A NOW account is functionally an interest paying checking account.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, NOW Accounts, Money Market Accounts, and Savings Deposits
definition: The aggregate interest expense incurred on the following for deposits in domestic offices: (1) transaction accounts (NOW, and telephone and preauthorized transfer accounts), (2) money market deposits and (3) savings deposits.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Other Domestic Deposits
definition: Interest expense incurred on other deposits in domestic offices.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Other Long-term Debt
definition: Interest expense incurred on all other long-term debt, which may include (1) interest on long-term notes, and (2) amortization of issuance costs not otherwise separately disclosed.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Other Short-term Borrowings
definition: Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on other short-term borrowings.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Related Party
definition: Amount of interest expense incurred on a debt or other obligation to related party.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Savings Deposits
definition: Interest expense incurred on all savings account deposits.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase
definition: Gross expenses on securities sold coupled with an agreement to repurchase the same from the same counterparty at a fixed or determinable price within a fixed or variable time period.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Short-term Borrowings Excluding Federal Funds and Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase
definition: The aggregate interest expense incurred on short-term borrowings including commercial paper, Federal Home Loan Bank and Federal Reserve Bank advances and other short term borrowings.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Subordinated Notes and Debentures
definition: Interest expense incurred during the reporting period on subordinated notes and debentures. Includes amortization of expenses incurred in the issuance of subordinated notes and debentures.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Time Deposits
definition: The aggregate interest expense incurred on time deposits, including certificates of deposits, in domestic offices.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Time Deposits, $100,000 or More
definition: Interest expense incurred on time deposits, including certificates of deposits, of $100,000 or more in domestic offices.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Time Deposits, Less than $100,000
definition: Interest expense incurred on time deposits, including certificates of deposits, less than $100,000 in domestic offices.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Trading Liabilities
definition: Interest expense incurred on short positions arising from sales of securities and other assets, which the entity does not own, to other parties. Trading liabilities includes the fair value of derivative contracts held for trading that are in loss positions.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Trust Preferred Securities
definition: The amount of interest incurred to a trust which has issued trust-preferred securities. In order to issue trust preferred securities, a sponsor forms a trust by investing a nominal amount of cash to purchase all of the voting common stock of the trust. The trust issues nonvoting, mandatorily redeemable preferred securities to outside investors in exchange for cash. The proceeds received from the issuance of the preferred securities, together with the cash received for issuing the common stock to the sponsor, is then loaned to the sponsor in exchange for a note which has the same terms as the trust preferred securities. Trust preferred securities possesses characteristics of both equity and debt issues and are generally issued by bank holding companies.

elementLabel: Interest Income and Fees, Bankers Acceptances, Certificates of Deposit and Commercial Paper
definition: Interest and fee income derived from banker's acceptances, certificates of deposit and commercial paper.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Domestic Deposits
definition: Interest earned on deposits in United States money market accounts and other United States interest earning accounts.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Federal Funds Sold
definition: Interest income on federal funds sold. Federal funds sold represent the excess federal funds held by one commercial bank which it lends to another commercial bank, usually at an agreed-upon (federal funds) rate of interest. Such loans generally are of short-duration (overnight).

elementLabel: Interest Income, Foreign Deposits
definition: Interest income generated from amounts on deposit with foreign entities located outside the United States of America.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Money Market Deposits
definition: Interest earned on funds deposited in US domestic money market accounts.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Other
definition: Amount of interest income earned from interest bearing assets not separately disclosed.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Other Domestic Deposits
definition: Interest earned on US domestic deposits other than funds deposited in money market accounts.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Purchased Receivables
definition: Interest earned from receivables purchased; for instance, receivables purchased through a factoring arrangement.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Related Party
definition: Amount of interest income earned from interest-bearing assets owed to the entity by related party.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities, Corporate Debt, Operating
definition: Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on corporate debt securities.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities, Mortgage Backed
definition: Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securitized, pass-through debt securities collateralized by real estate mortgage loans.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities, Other US Government
definition: Interest income on securities issued by US government agencies not including US Treasury Securities.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell
definition: Interest income derived from securities purchased under agreements to resell. The difference in the price at which the institution buys the securities and resells the securities represents interest for the use of the funds by the other party. Most repurchase and sale agreements involve obligations of the federal government or its agencies, but other financial instruments, such as commercial paper, banker's acceptances and negotiable certificates of deposits are sometimes used in such transactions.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities, State and Municipal
definition: Interest income, including any amortization and accretion (as applicable) of discounts and premiums, derived from debt securities issued by municipal governments, local taxing districts and US state government agencies.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities, Operating, Taxable
definition: Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securities subject to state, federal and other income tax.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities, Operating, Tax Advantaged
definition: Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securities subject to tax benefits. Excludes operating interest income on securities exempt from state, federal and other income tax.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities, Operating, Tax Exempt
definition: Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on securities exempt from state, federal and other income tax.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities, US Treasury
definition: Interest income on US treasury securities. US treasury securities are negotiable debt obligations of the US government, secured by its full faith and credit and issued at various schedules and maturities. The income from treasury securities is exempt from state and local, but not federal, taxes. There are three types of securities issued by the US treasury (bonds, bills, and notes), which are distinguished by the amount of time from the initial sale of the bond to maturity.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Securities, US Treasury and Other US Government
definition: Amount of operating interest income, including amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts, on U.S. Treasury securities and other U.S. government securities.

elementLabel: Interest Paid
definition: The amount of cash paid for interest during the period.

elementLabel: Interest Receivable and Other Assets
definition: Carrying amount of interest earned but not received (also called accrued interest or accrued interest receivable) and carrying amounts of assets not separately disclosed.

elementLabel: Inventory, Net of Allowances, Customer Advances and Progress Billings
definition: Carrying amount (lower of cost or market) of inventories less all valuation, other allowances, and progress payments or customer advances received on long-term contracts or programs. Excludes noncurrent inventory balances (expected to remain on hand past one year or one operating cycle, if longer).

elementLabel: Inventory, Noncurrent, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of inventory expected to be realized or consumed after one year or normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Inventory, Parts and Components (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date for elements of machinery or equipment held for the purpose of replacing similar parts in the course of repair or maintenance.

elementLabel: Inventory, Raw Materials and Purchased Parts (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of items purchased for use as components of a finished product or pieces of machinery and equipment plus any items in their natural and unrefined state. This element may be used when the reporting entity combines raw materials and purchased parts into an aggregate amount.

elementLabel: Derivative, Nonmonetary Notional Amount
definition: Aggregate notional amount of derivative expressed in nonmonetary units. For example, the number of barrels specified in a fuel oil forward purchase contract.

elementLabel: Derivative, Notional Amount
definition: Aggregate notional amount specified by the derivative(s). Expressed as an absolute value.

elementLabel: Investment Foreign Currency, Contract, Foreign Currency Amount
definition: The amount of foreign currency that the entity has contractually agreed, or for which it has the option, to buy or sell with respect to the contract being described.

elementLabel: Investment Foreign Currency, Contract, Reporting Currency Amount at Date of Origin
definition: The reporting currency amount (for example, US dollars) conversion, as of the date of origin, of the foreign currency amount that the entity is obligated or for which it has the option to buy or sell with respect to the contract being described.

elementLabel: Investment Interest Rate
definition: The interest rate for investments that have an interest rate. For fixed rate investments, this indicates the fixed interest rate. If the investment has a variable interest rate, the rate stated here may be the rate that is currently relevant. In this case the "Investment, Interest Rate is Current Rate for Variable Rate Investment Flag", "Investment, Interest Rate is Discount Rate at Purchase Flag", "Investment, Interest Rate Reflects Current Yield Flag" should be used. If one of these flags are not appropriate to explain the interest rate that is indicated, then a new flag should be added or an explanation should be included in "Investment, Additional Information".

elementLabel: Investment Interest Rate Range End
definition: The highest interest rate in the aggregated short-term debt instruments.

elementLabel: Investment Interest Rate Range Start
definition: The lowest interest rate in the aggregated short-term debt instruments.

elementLabel: Investment Options, Exercise Price
definition: Exercise price of the option.

elementLabel: Investment Repurchase Agreement, Amount to be Received
definition: Amount to be received on the repurchase date.

elementLabel: Investment Advisory, Management and Administrative Fees
definition: Amount of revenue from providing investment advisory, asset management and administrative services, including, but not limited to, distribution and shareholder services, accounting, tax, legal, regulatory filing, share registration, and shareholder correspondence activities.

elementLabel: Investment Income, Dividend
definition: Amount of dividend income on nonoperating securities.

elementLabel: Investment Income, Interest
definition: Amount before accretion (amortization) of purchase discount (premium) of interest income on nonoperating securities.

elementLabel: Investment Income, Interest and Dividend
definition: Amount before accretion (amortization) of purchase discount (premium) of interest income and dividend income on nonoperating securities.

elementLabel: Investment in Physical Commodities, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value of investment held in physical commodities, for example, but not limited to, gold, silver, platinum, crude oil, coal, sugar, rice, wheat.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, at Cost
definition: Cost of the investment.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Balance, Contracts
definition: Balance held at close of period in number of contracts.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Balance, Other Measure
definition: Quantity of the investment. Indicate the measure in the unit of measure. This is commonly used for investments other than securities. For example, if the investment is gold, the balance would be the number of ounces and the unit of measure would indicate "ounces".

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Balance, Principal Amount
definition: For investments which are quantified by principal amount, the principle balance held at close of period.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Balance, Shares
definition: Balance held at close of period in number of shares.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Loaned for Short Sales, at Fair Value
definition: The aggregate value of investments loaned for short sales. This is not required to be disclosed under Regulation S-X but is commonly reported by Funds.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Other than Securities, Loaned for Short Sales, at Fair Value (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: The aggregate value of non-security investments loaned for short sales. This is not required to be disclosed under Regulation S-X but is commonly reported by Funds.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Restricted, Carrying Value Per Unit at Date of Balance Sheet
definition: The carrying value per unit of investment at date of related balance sheet.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Restricted, Cost
definition: The cost of the restricted investment.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Subject to Option, Balance, Other Measure
definition: The quantity of the investment that is subject to option.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Subject to Option, Price
definition: The option price of the investment that is subject to option.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Unrealized Appreciation (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents the excess of the fair value of an investment (security, contract) over its cost (face amount, notional amount) which excess value has not been recognized in earnings of the entity.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Unrealized Depreciation (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents the excess of the cost (face amount, notional amount) of an investment (security, contract) over its fair value which deficiency has not been recognized in earnings of the entity.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Unrestricted, Carrying Value Per Unit at Date of Purchase Price Agreement
definition: The carrying value per unit of investment of unrestricted investment of the same issue as the restricted investment during the preceding year at the date the purchase price was agreed.

elementLabel: Investment Owned, Unrestricted, Carrying Value Per Unit at Date When Enforceable Right to Acquire was Obtained
definition: The carrying value per unit of investment of unrestricted investment of the same issue as the restricted investment during the preceding year at the date on which an enforceable right to acquire the investments was obtained.

elementLabel: Investments in Affiliates, Subsidiaries, Associates, and Joint Ventures, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of investments in an entity not consolidated. Includes, but is not limited to, investments in an entity that is affiliated with the reporting entity by means of direct or indirect ownership, an entity in which the reporting entity shares control of the entity with another party or group, an entity which the company has significant influence, but does not have control and subsidiaries that are not required to be consolidated and are accounted for using the equity or cost method.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, at Fair Value
definition: Value of the investment at close of period. For investment in and advances to affiliates, if operations of any controlled companies are different in character from those of the company, group such affiliates within divisions and by type of activities.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, at Fair Value, Gross Additions
definition: Gross additions to the investment in and advance to the affiliate.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, at Fair Value, Gross Reductions
definition: Gross reductions to the investment in and advance to the affiliate.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, Balance, Contracts (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Balance held at close of period in number of contracts.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, Balance, Contracts
definition: Number of contracts held with affiliates for management investment companies.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, Balance, Other Measure
definition: Mass of investment for management investment companies.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, Balance, Principal Amount
definition: Amount of principal loans outstanding to affiliates for management investment companies.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, Balance, Shares
definition: Number of shares of affiliates held for management investment companies.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, Dividend or Interest Credited to Income
definition: At the close of the period, the dividends or interest included in caption 1 of the statement of operations. In addition, show as the final item the aggregate of dividends and interest included in the statement of operations in respect of investments in affiliates not held at the close of the period. The total of this column would be expected to agree with the correlative amount shown on the related statement of operations.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, Dividend or Interest, Other
definition: All other dividends and interest. Explain in the "Schedule of Investments, Investment Notes" the treatment accorded each item.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advances to Affiliates, Dividends or Interest
definition: Amount of dividends or interest. Give totals for each group. If operations of any controlled companies are different in character from those of the company, group such affiliates (1) within divisions and (2) by type of activities.

elementLabel: Investments in Power and Distribution Projects, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value of investments in power and distribution projects.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, at Fair Value
definition: Value of the short position.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Balance, Other Measure
definition: Quantity of the investment. Indicate the measure in the unit of measure. This is commonly used for investments other than securities. For example, if the investment is gold, the balance would be the number of ounces and the unit of measure would indicate "ounces".

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Balance, Principal Amount
definition: For investments which are quantified by principal amount, the principle balance held at close of period.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Balance, Shares
definition: Number of securities sold short (the short position) as of the end of the period.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Number of Investments of Largest Short Position, Other Measure (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The number of the investments that represents the manager's largest single short position. Indicate the measure in the unit of measure. This is commonly used for investments other than securities. For example, if the investment is gold, the balance would be the number of ounces and the unit of measure would indicate "ounces".

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Number of Investments of Largest Short Position, Principal Amount (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The principal amount of the investment that represents the manager's largest single short position.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Number of Investments of Largest Short Position, Shares (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The number of shares of the investment that represents the manager's largest single short position.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Number of Investments Sold Short, Other Measure (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The aggregate quantity of the investment that the manager sold short during the period. Indicate the measure in the unit of measure. This is commonly used for investments other than securities. For example, if the investment is gold, the balance would be the number of ounces and the unit of measure would indicate "ounces".

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Number of Investments Sold Short, Principal Amount (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The aggregate principal amount of the investment that the manager sold short during the period.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Number of Investments Sold Short, Shares (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The aggregate number of shares of the investment that the manager sold short during the period.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Percent of Net Assets
definition: For schedules of investments sold, not yet purchased (short sales) that are categorized, each category would be expected to have a percent of net assets for the aggregated value of the investments sold short in the category.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Restricted, Carrying Value Per Unit at Date of Balance Sheet
definition: The carrying value per unit of investment at date of related balance sheet.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Restricted, Cost
definition: The cost of the restricted investment.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Sale Proceeds
definition: The amount of proceeds received resulting from the short sale of a security.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Unrestricted, Carrying Value Per Unit at Date of Purchase Price Agreement
definition: The carrying value per unit of investment of unrestricted investment of the same issue as the restricted investment during the preceding year at the date the purchase price was agreed.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Unrestricted, Carrying Value Per Unit at Date When Enforceable Right to Acquire was Obtained
definition: The carrying value per unit of investment of unrestricted investment of the same issue as the restricted investment during the preceding year at the date on which an enforceable right to acquire the investments was obtained.

elementLabel: Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Value of Investments Sold Short (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The market value of the investments sold short indicated in "Investment Sold, Not yet Purchased, Number of Investments Sold Short".

elementLabel: Jointly Owned Utility Plant, Gross Ownership Amount of Plant in Service
definition: The period end amount owned by the reporting utility of a jointly owned utility plant in service.

elementLabel: Jointly Owned Utility Plant, Net Ownership Amount
definition: The total period end amount of plant in service and construction in progress net of accumulated depreciation for the utility's share of jointly owned electricity generation plant.

elementLabel: Jointly Owned Utility Plant, Ownership Amount of Construction Work in Progress
definition: The period end amount of construction work in progress at a jointly owned electricity generation plant.

elementLabel: Jointly Owned Utility Plant, Ownership Amount of Other Assets
definition: The period end ownership amount of other assets in a jointly owned utility plant.

elementLabel: Jointly Owned Utility Plant, Ownership Amount of Plant Accumulated Depreciation
definition: The period end amount of accumulated depreciation in a jointly owned electricity generation plant.

elementLabel: Jointly Owned Utility Plant, Proportionate Ownership Share
definition: The proportionate share of interest (percent) in a jointly owned utility plant.

elementLabel: Land and Land Improvements
definition: Amount before accumulated deprecation and depletion of real estate held for productive use and additions or improvements to real estate held for productive use, examples include, but are not limited to, walkways, driveways, fences, and parking lots. Excludes land held for sale.

elementLabel: Land Subject to Ground Leases
definition: Area of land subject to a ground lease.

elementLabel: Lease Concessions (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of reduction of lease revenue that was offered to induce the lessee to enter into a lease agreement.

elementLabel: Lease Incentive, Payable (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: This item represents an incentive or inducement contractually stipulated between parties to a lease whereby the lessor has committed to provide the entity (lessee) with a cash payment as inducement to enter the lease.

elementLabel: Leasing Commissions Expense
definition: Amount of commissions expense incurred because the lessor of real estate obtained a lessee for a rental property through a real estate agent.

elementLabel: Leveraged Buyout, Closing Fees and Expense (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of cash paid for closing fees, debt issue costs, and other transaction expenses in a leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Leveraged Buyout, Consideration Paid for Outstanding Shares (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of cash paid to stockholders for outstanding shares and warrants in a leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Leveraged Buyout, Prepayment Penalties on Retired Debt (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of cash paid for prepayment penalties on retired debt in a leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Leveraged Buyout, Redemption of Share-based Awards (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of cash paid to settle outstanding management options in a leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Leveraged Buyout, Repayment of Existing Debt (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of cash used to pay off existing debt in a leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Leveraged Buyout, Uses of Cash in Leveraged Buyout Transaction (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Total uses of cash in a leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Income (Loss)
definition: The total recognized during the period for income on leases meeting the criteria for classification as leveraged leases.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Net Investment in Leveraged Leases Disclosure, Deferred Taxes Arising from Leveraged Leases
definition: Taxes arising from arrangements meeting the criteria for classification as leveraged leases due to timing differences between accounting and tax income recognition.

elementLabel: Liabilities and Partners' Capital (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: Total of all partners' capital and liability items in a publicly listed limited partnership or master limited partnership.

elementLabel: Liabilities, Fair Value Disclosure, Nonrecurring
definition: Aggregation of the liabilities reported on the balance sheet measured at fair value on a nonrecurring basis by the entity.

elementLabel: Liabilities, Fair Value Disclosure, Recurring
definition: Aggregation of the liabilities reported on the balance sheet measured at fair value on a recurring basis by the entity.

elementLabel: Liabilities for Guarantees on Long-Duration Contracts, Guaranteed Benefit Liability, Gross
definition: Amount of expected guaranteed benefits in excess of the projected account balances for minimum guaranteed benefit contracts, as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Liabilities for Guarantees on Long-Duration Contracts, Guaranteed Benefit Liability, Net
definition: Amount of expected guaranteed benefits in excess of the projected account balances for minimum guaranteed benefit contracts, net of reinsurance recoverables, as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Liabilities for Guarantees on Long-Duration Contracts, Incurred Benefits (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of guaranteed minimum benefit expense incurred during the period presented, resulting in an increase to the liability for expected guaranteed minimum benefits in excess of projected account values.

elementLabel: Liabilities for Guarantees on Long-Duration Contracts, Incurred Benefits
definition: Amount of guaranteed minimum benefit expense incurred for expected guaranteed minimum benefits in excess of projected account values.

elementLabel: Liabilities for Guarantees on Long-Duration Contracts, Reinsurance Recoverable
definition: Amount of guaranteed minimum benefits the ceding insurer expects to recover on insurance policies ceded to other insurance entities as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise
definition: Total amount of liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Accounts Payable and Accrued Liabilities
definition: The amount of trade accounts payable included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Aircraft Obligations and Deferred Gains
definition: The amount of aircraft obligations and deferred gains included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Asbestos Obligations
definition: The amount of asbestos related liabilities included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Balance at Bankruptcy Effective Date (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of liabilities subject to compromise at the bankruptcy date.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Capital Lease Obligations and Accrued Interest
definition: The amount of capital lease obligations and related accrued interest included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Debt and Accrued Interest
definition: The amount of debt and related accrued interest included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Early Contract Termination Fees
definition: The amount of early contract termination fees included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Employee and Deemed Claims
definition: The amount of employee and related claims included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, End of Period (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of liabilities subject to compromise at the end of the reporting period.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Environmental Contingencies
definition: The amount of environmental remediation liabilities included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Income Tax Contingencies
definition: The amount of income taxes included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Increase (Decrease) in Interest on Prepetition Liabilities
definition: Amount of interest on prepetition liabilities since bankruptcy filing date.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Other Liabilities
definition: The amount of other obligations included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Pension and Other Postretirement Obligations
definition: The amount of pension and other postretirement obligations included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Provision for Expected and Allowed Claims
definition: The amount of the provision for expected and allowed claims included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liabilities Subject to Compromise, Retained Obligation of Divested Businesses
definition: The amount of retained obligations related to divested businesses included in liabilities subject to compromise.

elementLabel: Liability for Asbestos and Environmental Claims, Gross
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of reserves for the costs of settling insured claims and costs incurred in the claims settlement process attributable to asbestos and environmental claims, before estimated recoveries from reinsurers.

elementLabel: Liability for Asbestos and Environmental Claims, Gross, Claims Paid
definition: Amount of asbestos claims paid in the current period, before estimated recoveries from reinsurers.

elementLabel: Liability for Asbestos and Environmental Claims, Gross, Incurred Loss
definition: Increase in asbestos and environmental reserve based on known and estimated costs of settling insured claims and costs incurred in the claims settlement process, before estimated recoveries from reinsurers.

elementLabel: Liability for Asbestos and Environmental Claims, Net
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of reserves for the costs of settling insured claims and costs incurred in the claims settlement process attributable to asbestos and environmental claims, net of estimated reinsurance recoveries.

elementLabel: Liability for Asbestos and Environmental Claims, Net, Claims Paid
definition: Amount of asbestos claims paid in the current period, net of reinsurance recoveries.

elementLabel: Liability for Asbestos and Environmental Claims, Net, Incurred Loss
definition: Increase in asbestos and environmental reserve based on known and estimated costs of settling insured claims and costs incurred in the claims settlement process, net of estimated reinsurance recoveries.

elementLabel: Liability for Catastrophe Claims, Carrying Amount
definition: The amount of estimated liability as of the balance sheet date for the specific conflagration, earthquake, windstorm, explosion, or similar event.

elementLabel: Liability for Future Policy Benefit by Product Segment, Discounted Liability Amount
definition: Monetary amount by product segment of present value of future benefits to be paid to or on behalf of policyholders and related expenses less the present value of future net premiums using assumptions such as estimates of expected investment yields, mortality, morbidity, terminations and expenses, applicable at the time the insurance contracts are made and unpaid claim costs relating to insurance contracts including estimates of costs relating to incurred but not reported claims based on the estimated ultimate cost of settling the claims (including effects of inflation and other societal and economic factors), using past experience adjusted for current trends and any other factors that would modify past experience.

elementLabel: Liability for Future Policy Benefit by Product Segment, Interest Rate, Year of Issue
definition: The assumed interest rate used to determine present value of future benefits to be paid to or on behalf of policyholders and related expenses less the present value of future net premiums using assumptions such as estimates of expected investment yields, mortality, morbidity, terminations and expenses, applicable at the time the insurance contracts are made and unpaid claim costs relating to insurance contracts including estimates of costs relating to incurred but not reported claims based on the estimated ultimate cost of settling the claims (including effects of inflation and other societal and economic factors), using past experience adjusted for current trends and any other factors that would modify past experience in the year the policy went into force.

elementLabel: Liability for Unpaid Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense, Claims Paid, Current Year
definition: Amount of payments to settle claims incurred in the current period and related claims settlement costs.

elementLabel: Liability for Unpaid Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense, Claims Paid, Prior Years
definition: Amount of payments to settle claims incurred in prior periods and related claims settlement costs.

elementLabel: Liability for Unpaid Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense, Reinsurance Recoverables, Deduction (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: The known and estimated amount that is recoverable on unpaid claims through reinsurance as of the beginning of the year.

elementLabel: License Costs
definition: Costs incurred and are directly related to generating license revenue. Licensing arrangements include, but are not limited to, rights to use a patent, copyright, technology, manufacturing process, software or trademark.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force, Assumed
definition: Amount of life insurance issued and outstanding assumed from other entities. Includes, but not limited to, dividends and adjustments to face value.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force, Ceded
definition: Amount of life insurance issued and outstanding ceded to other entities. Includes, but not limited to, dividends and adjustments to face value.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force, Gross
definition: Amount before contracts ceded to other entities and contracts assumed by the entity of life insurance issued and outstanding. Includes, but not limited to, dividends and adjustments to face value.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force, Net
definition: Amount after contracts ceded to other entities and contracts assumed by the entity of life insurance issued and outstanding. Includes, but not limited to, dividends and adjustments to face value.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force, Percentage Assumed to Net
definition: Percentage of assumed life insurance issued and outstanding contracts to life insurance issued and outstanding after contracts ceded to other entities and contracts assumed by the entity. Includes, but not limited to, dividends and adjustments to face value.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force Premiums, Percentage Assumed to Net (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Percentage of assumed life insurance in force premiums to net premiums.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing after Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing after Year Five
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing in Next Twelve Months
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing in Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing in Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing in Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing in Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing in Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing in Year Five
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing in Year Four
definition: Amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the investment method maturing in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Investment Method, Carrying Amount, Maturing in Year Three

elementLabel: Limited Liability Company (LLC) Preferred Unit, Authorized
definition: Maximum number of preferred units of ownership permitted to be issued of a limited liability company (LLC).

elementLabel: Limited Liability Company (LLC) Preferred Unit, Issuance Value
definition: Stated value of preferred units of ownership issued by a limited liability company (LLC).

elementLabel: Limited Liability Company (LLC) Preferred Unit, Issued
definition: Number of preferred units issued of limited liability company (LLC).

elementLabel: Limited Liability Company (LLC) Preferred Unit, Outstanding
definition: Number of preferred units of ownership outstanding of a limited liability company (LLC).

elementLabel: Line of Credit Facility, Decrease, Forgiveness
definition: Amount of decrease in line of credit facility from forgiveness by the holder of the line of credit.

elementLabel: Liquidation Basis of Accounting, Accrued Costs to Dispose of Assets and Liabilities
definition: Amount of estimated accrued costs to dispose of assets or other items expected to be sold in liquidation.

elementLabel: Liquidation Basis of Accounting, Items Previously Not Recognized
definition: Amount of items not previously recognized that are expected to be sold in liquidation.

elementLabel: Loan Processing Fee
definition: Expenses paid for obtaining loans which includes expenses such as application and origination fees.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Allowance, Covered
definition: Amount of allowance for loan and lease losses covered by loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Carrying Amount, Covered
definition: Aggregate gross carrying amount of loans and leases receivable covered by loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Net Reported Amount, Covered
definition: Net carrying amount of loans and leases receivable covered by loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Net Reported Amount, Covered and Not Covered
definition: Amount after allowance and deduction of deferred interest and fees, unamortized costs and premiums over and discounts from face amounts, of loans and leases held in portfolio, including but not limited to, commercial and consumer loans. Includes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Related Parties, Collections
definition: Reflects the amount of collections received from related parties to reduce the carrying amounts of loans and leases receivable due from them.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable with Fixed Rates of Interest
definition: Amount of loan with fixed rate of interest.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable with Variable Rates of Interest
definition: Amount of loan with variable or adjustable rate of interest.

elementLabel: Loans to Finance Leveraged Buyout (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Proceeds from term loans used to finance a leveraged buyout transaction (excludes subordinated notes and shareholder loans).

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Discount Rate
definition: Percentage discount rate used to calculate present value of an expected stream of future payments, which is included in the calculation of the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Discount Rate, High End (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Percentage discount rate at the high end of a range of reasonable estimates used to calculate present value of an expected stream of future payments, which is included in the calculation of the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Discount Rate, Low End (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Percentage discount rate at the low end of a range of reasonable estimates used to calculate present value of an expected stream of future payments, which is included in the calculation of the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Estimated Average Investment Yield
definition: Estimated average rate of return on investments which is included in the calculation of the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Estimated Investment Yield, High End (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Estimated rate of return on investments at the high end of a range of reasonable estimates which is included in the calculation of the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Estimated Investment Yield, Low End (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Estimated rate of return on investments at the low end of a range of reasonable estimates which is included in the calculation of the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Lapse Rate
definition: Anticipated rate of future terminations of contracts in force as of the balance sheet date, which is included in determining the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Lapse Rate, High End (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Anticipated rate of future terminations of contracts in force as of the balance sheet date at the high end of the range of reasonable estimates, which is included in determining the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Lapse Rate, Low End (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Anticipated rate of future terminations of contracts in force as of the balance sheet date at the low end of the range of reasonable estimates, which is included in determining the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Mortality Rate
definition: Actuarially determined death rate of policyholders, which is included in determining the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Mortality Rate, High End (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Actuarially determined death rate of policyholders at the high end of the range of reasonable estimates, which is included in determining the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Mortality Rate, Low End (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Actuarially determined death rate of policyholders at the low end of the range of reasonable estimates, which is included in determining the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Other Rate
definition: Anticipated rate for an assumption not otherwise specified in the taxonomy, which is included in determining the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Volatility Rate
definition: Percentage rate that is indicative of an expected degree of movement against a base line index, and which is included in determining the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Volatility Rate, High End (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Percentage rate at the high end of the range of reasonable estimates that is indicative of an expected degree of movement against a base line index, and which is included in determining the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-Duration Contracts, Assumptions by Product and Guarantee, Volatility Rate, Low End (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Percentage rate at the low end of the range of reasonable estimates that is indicative of an expected degree of movement against a base line index, and which is included in determining the amount of the specified guaranteed benefit obligation as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Contract for Purchase of Electric Power, Amount of Long-term Debt or Lease Obligation Outstanding
definition: Under long-term contracts with public utility districts, cooperatives or other organizations, a utility company receives a portion of the output of a production plant constructed and financed by the district or cooperative. The utility has only a nominal or no investment at all in the plant but pays a proportionate part of the plant's costs, including debt service.

elementLabel: Long-term Contract for Purchase of Electric Power, Annual Minimum Debt Service Payment Required
definition: Under long-term contracts with public utility districts, cooperatives or other organizations, a utility company receives a portion of the output of a production plant constructed and financed by the district or cooperative. The utility has only a nominal or no investment at all in the plant but pays a proportionate part of the plant's costs, including debt service. If the utility is obligated to pay certain minimum amounts which cover debt service requirements whether or not the plant is operating, the amount can be disclosed here.

elementLabel: Long-term Contract for Purchase of Electric Power, Estimated Annual Cost
definition: Estimated annual cost to purchase electricity under a long-term contract from a production plant constructed and financed by a public utility district, cooperative, or other organization.

elementLabel: Long-term Contract for Purchase of Electric Power, Interest Included in Contract Charges
definition: The allocable portion of interest included in charges under a long-term contract to purchase electric power.

elementLabel: Long-term Contract for Purchase of Electric Power, Share of Plant Output Being Purchased
definition: Share of plant output being purchased under a long-term contract to purchase electricity from a production plant constructed and financed by a public utility district, cooperative, or other organization.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt and Capital Lease Obligations, Including Current Maturities
definition: Amount of long-term debt and capital lease obligations including current maturities.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt and Capital Lease Obligations, Maturities, Repayments of Principal after Year Five
definition: Principal amount of long-term debt and capital lease obligation maturing after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt and Capital Lease Obligations, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Year Five

elementLabel: Long-term Debt and Capital Lease Obligations, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Years Two and Three
definition: Principal amount of long-term debt and capital lease obligation maturing in the second and third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt and Capital Lease Obligations, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Year Three

definition: Amount of long-term debt and capital lease obligation maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year ended.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt and Capital Lease Obligations, Repayments of Principal in Next Twelve Months
definition: Principal amount of long-term debt and capital lease obligation maturing in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Bonds Payable (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount of bonds payable as of the balance sheet date, including the current portion, which originally required full repayment more than twelve months after issuance or greater than the normal operating cycle of the company.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Bonds Payable, Current (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Current portion of carrying amount of bonds payable as of the balance sheet date (excluding noncurrent portions).

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Bonds Payable, Noncurrent (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount of bonds payable as of the balance sheet date, net of the amount due in the next twelve months or greater than the normal operating cycle of the company.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Commercial Loans (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount of commercial loans, excluding mortgages and lease obligations, as of the balance sheet date, including the current portion, which originally required full repayment more than twelve months after issuance or greater than the normal operating cycle of the company.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Commercial Loans, Current (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Current portion of carrying amount of commercial loans as of the balance sheet date (excluding noncurrent portions) excluding mortgage loans.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Commercial Loans, Noncurrent (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount of commercial loans as of the balance sheet date excluding mortgage loans and net of the amount due in the next twelve months or greater than the normal operating cycle of the company.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Convertible Debt (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount of convertible debt as of the balance sheet date, including the current portion, which originally required full repayment more than twelve months after issuance or greater than the normal operating cycle of the company.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Credit Facilities (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Amounts outstanding under credit facilities (lines of credit and letters of credit) classified as long-term debt as of the balance sheet date (including both current and noncurrent portions).

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Credit Facilities, Current (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Current portion of amount outstanding under credit facilities (lines of credit and letters of credit) as of the balance sheet date (excluding noncurrent portions).

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Credit Facilities, Noncurrent (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount of amounts outstanding under credit facilities (lines of credit and letters of credit) as of the balance sheet date, net of the amount due in the next twelve months or greater than the normal operating cycle of the company.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Mortgage Loans (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount of mortgage loans as of the balance sheet date, including the current portion, which originally required full repayment more than twelve months after issuance or greater than the normal operating cycle of the company.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Mortgage Loans, Current (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Current portion of carrying amount of mortgage loans as of the balance sheet date (excluding noncurrent portions).

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Mortgage Loans, Noncurrent (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount of mortgage loans as of the balance sheet date, net of the amount due in the next twelve months or greater than the normal operating cycle of the company.

elementLabel: Long-term Notes Payable, Current and Noncurrent (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Including the current and noncurrent portions, aggregate carrying amount of all types of notes payable, as of the balance sheet date, with initial maturities beyond one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Components, Other Debt (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount of other forms of debt classified as long-term as of the balance sheet date (including both current and noncurrent portions).

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of long-term debt payable, sinking fund requirements, and other securities issued that are redeemable by holder at fixed or determinable prices and dates maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Rolling after Year Five

For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Rolling Year Four and Five
definition: Amount of long-term debt payable, sinking fund requirements, and other securities issued that are redeemable by holder at fixed or determinable prices and dates maturing in the fourth and fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of long-term debt payable, sinking fund requirements, and other securities issued that are redeemable by holder at fixed or determinable prices and dates maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. definition: Amount of long-term debt payable, sinking fund requirements, and other securities issued that are redeemable by holder at fixed or determinable prices and dates maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Rolling Year Two and Three
definition: Amount of long-term debt payable, sinking fund requirements, and other securities issued that are redeemable by holder at fixed or determinable prices and dates maturing in the second and third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Maturities, Repayments of Principal, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of long-term debt payable, sinking fund requirements, and other securities issued that are redeemable by holder at fixed or determinable prices and dates maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt of Registrant, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Next Rolling Twelve Months (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of long-term debt of the registrant maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet presented.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt of Registrant, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Remainder of Fiscal Year (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of long-term debt of the registrant maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year ended.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt of Registrant, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Rolling after Year Five (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of long-term debt of the registrant maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet presented.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt of Registrant, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Rolling Year Five (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of long-term debt of the registrant maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet presented.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt of Registrant, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Rolling Year Four (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of long-term debt of the registrant maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet presented.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt of Registrant, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Rolling Year Three (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of long-term debt of the registrant maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet presented.
