elementLabel: Long-term Debt of Registrant, Maturities, Repayments of Principal in Rolling Year Two (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of long-term debt of the registrant maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet presented.

elementLabel: Long-term Purchase Commitment, Minimum Energy Volume Required
definition: Energy volume that must be purchased within the specified time period of the agreement to avoid penalties or unfavorable effects on pricing, among other adverse consequences.

elementLabel: Long-term Purchase Commitment, Minimum Mass Required
definition: Mass of goods that must be purchased within the specified time period of the agreement to avoid penalties or unfavorable effects on pricing, among other adverse consequences.

elementLabel: Long-term Purchase Commitment, Minimum Volume Required
definition: Volume that must be purchased within the specified time period of the agreement to avoid penalties or unfavorable effects on pricing, among other adverse consequences.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency Accrual, Payments
definition: Amount of payments made reducing loss contingency liability.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency Accrual, Product Liability, after Rolling Year Five
definition: Undiscounted amount of the accrual for damages arising from third-party use of the entity's product or process expected to be paid after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency Accrual, Product Liability, Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Undiscounted amount of the accrual for damages arising from third-party use of the entity's product or process expected to be paid in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency Accrual, Product Liability, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Undiscounted amount of the accrual for damages arising from third-party use of the entity's product or process expected to be paid in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency Accrual, Product Liability, Rolling Year Five
definition: Undiscounted amount of the accrual for damages arising from third-party use of the entity's product or process expected to be paid in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency Accrual, Product Liability, Rolling Year Four
definition: Undiscounted amount of the accrual for damages arising from third-party use of the entity's product or process expected to be paid in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency Accrual, Product Liability, Rolling Year Three
definition: Undiscounted amount of the accrual for damages arising from third-party use of the entity's product or process expected to be paid in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency Accrual, Product Liability, Rolling Year Two
definition: Undiscounted amount of the accrual for damages arising from third-party use of the entity's product or process expected to be paid in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Claims Dismissed, Number
definition: Number of claims dismissed.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Claims Settled, Number
definition: Number of claims settled.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Damages Paid, Value
definition: Amount of damages paid to the plaintiff in the legal matter.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Number of Defendants
definition: Number of defendants named in a legal action.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Number of Plaintiffs
definition: Number of plaintiffs that have filed claims pertaining to a loss contingency.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Patents Allegedly Infringed, Number
definition: Number of another entity's patents that the entity has allegedly infringed.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Patents Found Infringed, Number
definition: Number of another entity's patents that the entity was found to have infringed.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Patents Found Not Infringed, Number
definition: Number of another entity's patents that the entity was found not to have infringed.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Receivable
definition: Amount of receivable related to a loss contingency accrual. For example, an insurance recovery receivable.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Receivable, Current
definition: Amount of receivable related to a loss contingency accrual that is expected to be collected within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer. For example, an insurance recovery receivable.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Receivable, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of receivable related to a loss contingency accrual that is expected to be collected after one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer. For example, an insurance recovery receivable.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Receivable, Receipts
definition: Amount of collections of receivables pertaining to a loss contingency.

elementLabel: Loss Contingency, Settlement Agreement, Consideration (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of consideration the entity has agreed to pay to settle a legal matter.

elementLabel: Loss on Sale of Investments
definition: The difference between the carrying value and the sale price of an investment. A loss would be recognized when the sale price of the investment is less than the carrying value of the investment. This element refers to the Loss included in earnings and not to the cash proceeds of the sale.

elementLabel: Loss Ratio
definition: Ratio of non-life losses and loss expenses to non-life net premiums earned.

elementLabel: Malpractice Insurance, Annual Coverage Limit
definition: Annual coverage limit provided by the insurance arrangement for malpractice claims.

elementLabel: Malpractice Insurance, Coverage Floor
definition: Amount at the low end of the range in which the insurance begins to cover losses and costs associated with malpractice claims.

elementLabel: Malpractice Insurance, Deductible (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of risk retained by the entity before the insurance arrangement begins to provide coverage.

elementLabel: Malpractice Insurance, Deductible
definition: Amount of risk retained by the entity before the insurance arrangement begins to provide coverage.

elementLabel: Malpractice Insurance, Maximum Coverage Per Incident
definition: Maximum coverage per malpractice claim provided by the insurance arrangement.

elementLabel: Malpractice Insurance, Percentage of Ownership in Captive Insurer
definition: State the entity's ownership interest in the captive insurer.

elementLabel: Malpractice Insurance, Percentage of Premiums Paid to Captive Insurer
definition: Amount of the premiums paid by the entity to a partially-owned captive insurer. Express as a percentage of total premiums received by the captive insurer from all sources.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Accrual Not Recognized, Estimate of Possible Loss
definition: Amount of estimated possible loss for a loss contingency for malpractice claims that is reasonably possible to occur but does not meet the loss recognition criteria.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Settlement of Claims (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amounts paid during an accounting period for malpractice claims, including costs associated with litigation or claims settlements.

elementLabel: Management Fee, Amount Paid (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount paid to managing member or general partner for management of the day-to-day business functions of the limited liability company (LLC) or limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Management Fee Expense
definition: Amount of expenses related to the managing member or general partner for management of the day-to-day business functions of the limited liability company (LLC) or limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Management Fee Payable
definition: Carrying amount of the unpaid portion of the fee payable to the managing member or general partner for management of the fund or trust.

elementLabel: Market Data Revenue
definition: Amount of revenue from market data services, including, but not limited to, information about current quotes and most recent prices for a specific security.

elementLabel: Maximum Future Earnings from Closed Block Assets and Liabilities (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The carrying amount of closed block liabilities in excess of the carrying amount of closed block assets at the date of demutualization (adjusted to eliminate the impact of related amounts in accumulated other comprehensive income).

elementLabel: Merchant Discount Fees
definition: Amount of earnings on fees charged to merchants for the cardholder's use of a credit card. Excludes interest income earned on credit card balances, transactions and credit card services including late, over limit, and annual fees.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Due in Rolling after Year Five
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Due in Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Due in Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Due in Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Due in Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Net Capital Required (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Total minimum net capital required to be maintained to engage in securities transactions.

elementLabel: Minimum Net Capital Required
definition: Amount of minimum net capital required to be maintained to engage in securities transactions.

elementLabel: Minimum Net Capital Required for Broker-Dealer Subsidiary (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The minimum amount of net capital required to be maintained by the company's broker-dealer subsidiary to engage in securities transactions.

elementLabel: Minimum Net Capital Required for Broker-Dealer Subsidiary
definition: Minimum amount of net capital required to be maintained by entity's broker-dealer subsidiary to engage in securities transactions.

elementLabel: Minimum Net Capital Required for Entity (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The minimum amount of net capital required to be maintained by the entity to engage in securities transactions.

elementLabel: Minimum Net Capital Required for Entity
definition: Minimum amount of net capital required to be maintained by the entity to engage in securities transactions.

elementLabel: Minimum Net Worth Required for Compliance
definition: The lowest amount of net worth (total assets minus total liabilities) required by secondary market investors or state-imposed regulatory mandates.

elementLabel: Minimum Remaining Terms of Leases and Concessions on Undeveloped Acreage (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Information about the leases or concessions that will expire on undeveloped acreage controlled by the enterprise.

elementLabel: Minimum Rents (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: This element represents the minimum amount of rents earned during the period from lessees based on the terms of contractual arrangements.

elementLabel: Noncontrolling Interest, Ownership Percentage by Parent
definition: The parent entity's interest in net assets of the subsidiary, expressed as a percentage.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Carrying Amount of Mortgages
definition: The carrying amount of the outstanding balance due under the mortgage loan.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Delinquent Principal or Interest, Acquired from Affiliates
definition: Amount of principal due on loans that have been delinquent, which may exclude loans having interest delinquent for three months or less, as of the balance sheet date that were acquired from controlled and other affiliates.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Face Amount of Mortgages
definition: Amount of the contractual principal due at the origination of the mortgage loan (face amount).

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Federal Income Tax Basis (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The total amount of the Federal income tax bases of mortgage loans on real estate.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Federal Income Tax Basis
definition: Amount of the federal income tax basis of mortgage loans on real estate.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Interest Rate
definition: The stated interest rate on the mortgage loan receivable or the weighted average interest rate on a group of loans.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Maximum Interest Rate in Range
definition: The highest stated interest rate within the mortgage loans included in the loan grouping.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Minimum Interest Rate in Range
definition: The lowest stated interest rate within the mortgage loans included in the loan grouping.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Number of Loans
definition: Indicates the number of mortgages under each classification.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Periodic Payment Terms, Balloon Payment Amount (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The required large, lump sum payment amount on final maturity date.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Periodic Payment Terms, Balloon Payment to be Received
definition: Amount of large payment to be received at final maturity date of mortgage loans.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Principal Amount of Delinquent Loans
definition: Amount of principal due on loans that have been delinquent, which may exclude loans having interest delinquent for three months or less, as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Prior Liens (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of any prior liens on the real estate that secures the mortgage loan.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Prior Liens
definition: Amount of prior lien on the real estate that secures the mortgage loan.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Renewed and Extended, Amount (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount of mortgage loans on real estate that were renewed or extended.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Renewed and Extended, Amount
definition: Amount of mortgage loan on real estate that was renewed or extended.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Write-down or Reserve, Amount (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The amount of any write-down or reserve provided in the period on a mortgage loan on real estate.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Write-down or Reserve, Amount
definition: Amount of reserve for write-down of a mortgage loan on real estate.

elementLabel: Multiemployer Plans, Accumulated Benefit Obligation
definition: Amount of accumulated benefit obligation attributable to the pension or postretirement benefit plan to which two or more unrelated employers contribute where assets contributed by one participating employer may be used to provide benefits to employees of other participating employers.

elementLabel: Multiemployer Plans, Collective-Bargaining Arrangement, Percentage of Contributions
definition: Percentage of contributions required by a collective bargaining arrangement to contributions required by all collective bargaining arrangements related to a pension or postretirement benefit plan to which two or more unrelated employers contribute where assets contributed by one participating employer may be used to provide benefits to employees of other participating employers.

elementLabel: Multiemployer Plans, Collective-Bargaining Arrangement, Percentage of Employer's Contributions
definition: Percentage of contributions required by a collective bargaining arrangement to all contributions required of an employer related to a pension or postretirement benefit plan to which two or more unrelated employers contribute where assets contributed by one participating employer may be used to provide benefits to employees of other participating employers.

elementLabel: Multiemployer Plans, Collective-Bargaining Arrangement, Percentage of Employer's Participants
definition: Percentage of employee participants subject to a collective bargaining arrangement to all of the employer's participants in a pension or postretirement benefit plan to which two or more unrelated employers contribute where assets contributed by one participating employer may be used to provide benefits to employees of other participating employers.

elementLabel: Multiemployer Plans, Collective-Bargaining Arrangement, Percentage of Participants
definition: Percentage of employee participants subject to a collective bargaining arrangement to all participants in a pension or postretirement benefit plan to which two or more unrelated employers contribute where assets contributed by one participating employer may be used to provide benefits to employees of other participating employers.

elementLabel: Multiemployer Plans, Minimum Contribution
definition: Amount of minimum contribution(s) required for future periods to a multiemployer plan by collective bargaining arrangements, statutory obligations, or other contractual obligations. A multiemployer plan is a pension or postretirement benefit plan to which two or more unrelated employers contribute where assets contributed by one participating employer may be used to provide benefits to employees of other participating employers.

elementLabel: Multiemployer Plans, Plan Assets
definition: Amount of plan assets attributable to the pension or postretirement benefit plan to which two or more unrelated employers contribute where assets contributed by one participating employer may be used to provide benefits to employees of other participating employers.

elementLabel: Multiemployer Plans, Plan Contributions
definition: Amount of contributions made to the multiemployer plan by all employers who participate in the plan. A multiemployer plan is a pension or postretirement benefit plan to which two or more unrelated employers contribute where assets contributed by one participating employer may be used to provide benefits to employees of other participating employers.

elementLabel: Multiemployer Plans, Withdrawal Obligation
definition: Amount of the obligation recognized by withdrawing from a pension or postretirement benefit plan to which two or more unrelated employers contribute where assets contributed by one participating employer may be used to provide benefits to employees of other participating employers.

elementLabel: Net Amount at Risk by Product and Guarantee, General Account Value
definition: Value of the general accounts corresponding to the specified product, guarantee type and subset of the guarantee.

elementLabel: Net Amount at Risk by Product and Guarantee, Net Amount at Risk
definition: Net amount at risk, representing the guaranteed benefit in excess of the current account balance corresponding to the specified product, guarantee type and subset of the guarantee.

elementLabel: Net Amount at Risk by Product and Guarantee, Net Amount at Risk at Annuitization (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Net amount at risk, representing the guaranteed benefit in excess of the current account balance corresponding to the specified product, guarantee type and subset of the guarantee.

elementLabel: Net Amount at Risk by Product and Guarantee, Net Amount at Risk in Event of Death (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: The portion of the specified guaranteed benefit amount in excess of the sum of the current account balance amounts assuming death of the insureds, corresponding to the specified guarantee or subset of the guarantee.

elementLabel: Net Amount at Risk by Product and Guarantee, Separate Account Value
definition: Value of the separate accounts corresponding to the specified product, guarantee type and subset of the guarantee.

elementLabel: Net Amount at Risk by Product and Guarantee, Separate Account Value at Annuitization (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Estimated value of the separate accounts as of the date benefit payments are to commence.

elementLabel: Net Amount at Risk by Product and Guarantee, Separate Account Value in Event of Death (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Value of the separate accounts assuming death of the insured, corresponding to the specified product, guarantee type and subset of the guarantee.

elementLabel: Net Amount at Risk by Product and Guarantee, Weighted Average Attained Age (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Weighted average attained age of all policyholders or contract holders in the specified guarantee type and subset of guarantee class.

elementLabel: Net Amount at Risk by Product and Guarantee, Weighted Average Period Remaining (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Weighted average amount of time in years until annuitization or benefit payment is expected to occur.

elementLabel: Net Credit Losses During Period on Loans Managed or Securitized or Asset-backed Financing Arrangement (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: This is the sum of charge-offs (credit losses) on loans managed or securitized during the period.

elementLabel: Net Credit Loss on Loans Managed or Securitized or Asset-backed Financing Arrangement
definition: Amount of credit loss after recoveries for transferred financial assets that continue to be recognized in the statement of financial position.

elementLabel: Net Rentable Area
definition: Net rentable area for properties owned.

elementLabel: Noncash Commission and Closing Costs
definition: The expense related to real estate commissions and closing costs that are not paid in cash. Is an adjustment to net income when calculating cash provided by or used in operations using the indirect method.

elementLabel: Noncash or Part Noncash Acquisition, Intangible Assets Acquired
definition: The amount of intangibles that an Entity acquires in a noncash (or part noncash) acquisition. Noncash is defined as information about all investing and financing activities of an enterprise during a period that affect recognized assets or liabilities but that do not result in cash receipts or cash payments in the period. "Part noncash" refers to that portion of the transaction not resulting in cash receipts or cash payments in the period.

elementLabel: Noncash or Part Noncash Acquisition, Value of Liabilities Assumed
definition: The total amount of [all] liabilities that an Entity assumes in acquiring a business or in consideration for an asset received in a noncash (or part noncash) acquisition. Noncash is defined as transactions during a period that affect recognized assets or liabilities but that do not result in cash receipts or cash payments in the period. "Part noncash" refers to that portion of the transaction not resulting in cash receipts or cash payments in the period.

elementLabel: Noncash or Part Noncash Divestiture, Amount of Consideration Received
definition: Amount of noncash consideration received for selling an asset or business through a noncash (or part noncash) transaction.

elementLabel: Noncash Project Abandonment Costs
definition: The expense charged against earnings to eliminate the capitalized costs of projects that have been terminated during the reporting period, which is added back to net income when calculating cash provided by (used in) operations using the indirect method.

elementLabel: Noncontrolling Interest, Increase from Sale of Parent Equity Interest
definition: Amount of increase in noncontrolling interest from sale of a portion of the parent's controlling interest.

elementLabel: Noncontrolling Interest, Increase from Subsidiary Equity Issuance
definition: Amount of increase in noncontrolling interest from subsidiary issuance of equity interests to noncontrolling interest holders.

elementLabel: Nonfinancial Liabilities Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value of obligations not classified as financial liabilities. Includes, but is not limited to, accounts payable and accrued liabilities, commitments, obligations, and other liabilities.

elementLabel: Noninterest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Other
definition: Amount of other noninterest-bearing domestic deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Noninterest Expense
definition: Total aggregate amount of all noninterest expense.

elementLabel: Noninterest Expense Commission Expense
definition: Amount of fees incurred for commissions on mutual funds and insurance products.

elementLabel: Noninterest Expense Directors Fees
definition: Noninterest expense related to directors' fees which are fees paid by an Entity to its directors. Directors' fees may be paid in addition to salary and other benefits.

elementLabel: Noninterest Expense Investment Advisory Fees
definition: This represents the company's cost incurred during an accounting period for managing the money in a fund, which will be billed back to the client and is a component of noninterest expenses.

elementLabel: Noninterest Expense Offering Cost
definition: Includes offering costs of open-end investment companies, and closed-end funds with a continuous offering period.

elementLabel: Noninterest Expense Printing and Fulfillment
definition: Amounts expended for printing of marketing and compliance communications and fulfillment services.

elementLabel: Noninterest Expense Related to Performance Fees
definition: Incentive fees which are compensation paid to a trading advisor or to any practitioner who achieves investment results above a specified contractual level.

elementLabel: Noninterest Expense Transfer Agent and Custodian Fees
definition: Fees paid to an agent employed by a corporation or mutual fund to maintain shareholder records, including purchases, sales, and account balances. Also includes custodian fees incurred during an accounting period from an agent, bank, trust company, or other organization that holds and safeguards an individual's, mutual fund's, or investment company's assets for them. These fees will be billed back to the client and are a component of noninterest expense.

elementLabel: Non-Recourse Debt
definition: Amount of debt for which creditor does not have general recourse to the debtor but rather has recourse only to the property used for collateral in the transaction or other specific property.

elementLabel: Notes Payable, Related Parties, Current (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: The amount for notes payable (written promise to pay), due to related parties. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: Notes Receivable by Owner to Limited Liability Company (LLC)
definition: Amount of an agreement for an unconditional promise by an owner to pay limited liability company (LLC) a definite sum of money at a future date.

elementLabel: Notional Amount of Foreign Currency Derivatives (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Aggregate notional amount of foreign currency exchange rate derivatives. Notional amount refers to the number of currency units specified in the foreign currency derivative contract.

elementLabel: Notional Amount of Foreign Currency Derivative Sale Contracts (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Aggregate notional amount of foreign currency derivatives to sell a foreign currency. Notional amount refers to the number of currency units specified in the foreign currency derivative contract.

elementLabel: Notional Amount of Nonderivative Instruments
definition: Nominal or face amount used to calculate payments on a nonderivative instrument.

elementLabel: Number of Aircraft Operated
definition: Number of aircraft operated by the carrier.

elementLabel: Number of Operating Segments
definition: Number of operating segments. An operating segment is a component of an enterprise: (a) that engages in business activities from which it may earn revenues and incur expenses (including revenues and expenses relating to transactions with other components of the same enterprise), (b) whose operating results are regularly reviewed by the enterprise's chief operating decision maker to make decisions about resources to be allocated to the segment and assess its performance, and (c) for which discrete financial information is available. An operating segment may engage in business activities for which it has yet to earn revenues, for example, start-up operations may be operating segments before earning revenues.

elementLabel: Number of Properties Subject to Ground Leases
definition: Number of separate real estate development properties located on land subject to ground leases.

elementLabel: Number of Reportable Segments
definition: Number of segments reported by the entity. A reportable segment is a component of an entity for which there is an accounting requirement to report separate financial information on that component in the entity's financial statements.

elementLabel: Number of Reporting Units
definition: Number of reporting units tested for impairment of goodwill. A reporting unit is an operating segment or one level below an operating segment.

elementLabel: Obligation with Joint and Several Liability Arrangement, Amount Outstanding
definition: Amount outstanding, before the effects of recovery, of obligation under the joint and several liability arrangement.

elementLabel: Obligation with Joint and Several Liability Arrangement, Amount Receivable
definition: Amount of receivable from other entities recognized in the balance sheet resulting from the joint and several liability arrangement.

elementLabel: Obligation with Joint and Several Liability Arrangement, Amount Recognized
definition: Amount of joint and several liability recognized in the balance sheet.

elementLabel: Occupancy, Net
definition: Amount of net occupancy expense that may include items, such as depreciation of facilities and equipment, lease expenses, property taxes and property and casualty insurance expense.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Delivery Commitments and Contracts, Available Amounts to be Received
definition: Total available amounts expected to be received from each oil producing property.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Delivery Commitments and Contracts, Daily Production
definition: Amount of daily production of the applicable energy source.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Delivery Commitments and Contracts, Fixed Price
definition: The delivery price committed to in the contract.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Delivery Commitments and Contracts, Remaining Contractual Volume
definition: Total amount of product committed to be supplied under existing contracts or agreements.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Delivery Commitments and Contracts, Reserves or Supplies Subject to Priorities or Curtailments
definition: Significant oil and gas supplies subject to priorities or curtailments which may affect quantities delivered to certain classes of customers, such as customers receiving services under low priority and interruptible contracts.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Delivery Commitments and Contracts, Significant Supplies Dedicated or Contracted to Entity
definition: Significant oil and gas supplies dedicated or contracted to the enterprise that can be used to fulfill existing contracts or agreements.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Property, Successful Effort Method, Accumulated Depreciation, Depletion Amortization and Impairment
definition: Amount of accumulated depreciation, depletion, amortization and impairment of oil and gas property carried under the successful effort method.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Quantities Received under Long-term Supply Agreements with Governments or Authorities
definition: The net quantity of oil and/or gas received under long-term supply, purchase, or similar agreements and contracts, including such agreements with governments or authorities, as of the end of the period if the enterprise participates in the operation of the properties in which the oil or gas is located or otherwise serves as the "producer" of those reserves, as opposed, for example, to being an independent purchaser, broker, dealer or importer.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Sales Payable (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred and payable to third parties for oil and gas that has been sold but not delivered. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: Open Option Contracts Written, Exercise Price
definition: The exercise price of the open option contracts written on the investment.

elementLabel: Open Option Contracts Written, Number of Contracts
definition: The number of contracts written for the open option contracts written on the investment.

elementLabel: Open Option Contracts Written, Number of Shares
definition: The number of shares for the open option contracts written on the investment.

elementLabel: Open Option Contracts Written, Premiums
definition: Represents the premiums earned on the open option contracts held by the fund. This item is not required to be disclosed in Regulation S-X but is commonly reported by some funds.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Due in Four and Five Years
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due in the fourth and fifth fiscal years following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Due in Rolling after Year Five
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Due in Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Due in Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Due in Rolling Year Four and Five
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due in the fourth and fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Due in Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Due in Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Due in Rolling Year Two and Three
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due in the second and third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Due in Two and Three Years
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due in the second and third fiscal years following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments Receivable, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments receivable in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year ended for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable letter-terms in excess of one year.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Future Minimum Payments, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of required minimum rental payments for operating leases having an initial or remaining non-cancelable lease term in excess of one year due in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Income Statement, Lease Revenue
definition: The total amount of revenue recognized for the period from operating leases, including minimum lease revenue, contingent revenue, percentage revenue and sublease revenue.

elementLabel: Operating Lease, Rent Expense (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Rent expense for each period for which an income statement is presented for minimum lease payments, contingent rentals, and sublease rentals.

elementLabel: Option Indexed to Issuer's Equity, Redeemable Stock, Redemption Requirements, Amount (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: For freestanding option contracts indexed to, and potentially settled in, a company's own stock that has redemption requirements, the amount of redemption requirements for all issues of capital stock that are redeemable at fixed or determinable prices on fixed or determinable dates in each of the five years following the date of the latest statement of financial position presented.

elementLabel: Option Indexed to Issuer's Equity, Redeemable Stock, Redemption Requirements, Amount
definition: Amount of redeemable stock for issue of capital stock that are redeemable at fixed or determinable prices on fixed or determinable dates in each of the five years following the date of the latest statement of financial position presented.

elementLabel: Option Indexed to Issuer's Equity, Strike Price
definition: Exercise or strike price stated in the contract for options indexed to the issuer's equity shares.

elementLabel: Order Flow Fees
definition: The amount of expense in the period for the cost of other broker-dealers' executions of orders.

elementLabel: Origination and Purchases of Mortgage Banking Assets (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The value of mortgage-based securitized assets that were created through the writing and securitizing new loans and through purchasing previously securitized assets.

elementLabel: Origination of Loan to Purchase Common Stock
definition: Cash outflow for origination of loan for purchasing common stock.

elementLabel: Origination of Mortgage Servicing Rights (MSRs) (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The increase during the reporting period in the cumulative value of servicing rights. This increase is the result of new servicing rights that are created when mortgages are sold or transferred.

elementLabel: Other Accrued Liabilities (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred through that date and payable arising from transactions not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: Other Commitment
definition: Minimum amount of other commitment not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. Excludes commitments explicitly modeled in the taxonomy, including but not limited to, long-term and short-term purchase commitments, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, supply commitments, registration payment arrangements, leases, debt, product warranties, guarantees, environmental remediation obligations, and pensions.

elementLabel: Other Commitment, Due after Fifth Year
definition: Minimum amount of other commitment maturing after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for commitments not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. Excludes commitments explicitly modeled in this taxonomy, including but not limited to, long-term and short-term purchase commitments, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, supply commitments, registration payment arrangements, leases, debt, product warranties, guarantees, environmental remediation obligations, and pensions.

elementLabel: Other Commitment, Due in Fifth Year
definition: Minimum amount of other commitment maturing in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for commitments not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. Excludes commitments explicitly modeled in this taxonomy, including but not limited to, long-term and short-term purchase commitments, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, supply commitments, registration payment arrangements, leases, debt, product warranties, guarantees, environmental remediation obligations, and pensions.

elementLabel: Other Commitment, Due in Fourth and Fifth Year
definition: Minimum amount of other commitment maturing in the fourth and fifth fiscal years following the latest fiscal year for commitments not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. Excludes commitments explicitly modeled in this taxonomy, including but not limited to, long-term and short-term purchase commitments, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, supply commitments, registration payment arrangements, leases, debt, product warranties, guarantees, environmental remediation obligations, and pensions.

elementLabel: Other Commitment, Due in Fourth Year
definition: Minimum amount of other commitment maturing in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for commitments not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. Excludes commitments explicitly modeled in this taxonomy, including but not limited to, long-term and short-term purchase commitments, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, supply commitments, registration payment arrangements, leases, debt, product warranties, guarantees, environmental remediation obligations, and pensions.

elementLabel: Other Commitment, Due in Next Twelve Months
definition: Minimum amount of other commitment maturing in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for commitments not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. Excludes commitments explicitly modeled in this taxonomy, including but not limited to, long-term and short-term purchase commitments, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, supply commitments, registration payment arrangements, leases, debt, product warranties, guarantees, environmental remediation obligations, and pensions.

elementLabel: Other Commitment, Due in Second and Third Year
definition: Minimum amount of other commitment maturing in the second and third fiscal years following the latest fiscal year for commitments not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. Excludes commitments explicitly modeled in this taxonomy, including but not limited to, long-term and short-term purchase commitments, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, supply commitments, registration payment arrangements, leases, debt, product warranties, guarantees, environmental remediation obligations, and pensions.

elementLabel: Other Commitment, Due in Second Year
definition: Minimum amount of other commitment maturing in the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for commitments not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. Excludes commitments explicitly modeled in this taxonomy, including but not limited to, long-term and short-term purchase commitments, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, supply commitments, registration payment arrangements, leases, debt, product warranties, guarantees, environmental remediation obligations, and pensions.

elementLabel: Other Commitment, Due in Third Year
definition: Minimum amount of other commitment maturing in the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year for commitments not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. Excludes commitments explicitly modeled in this taxonomy, including but not limited to, long-term and short-term purchase commitments, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, supply commitments, registration payment arrangements, leases, debt, product warranties, guarantees, environmental remediation obligations, and pensions.

elementLabel: Other Commitments, Future Minimum Payments, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of other commitments maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year ended.

elementLabel: Other Comprehensive Income (Loss), Pension and Other Postretirement Benefit Plans, Net Prior Service Costs Arising During Period ,Tax (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: Tax effect on the cost of benefit improvement resulting from a plan amendment that occurred during the period. The cost has not been recognized in net periodic benefit cost pursuant. A plan amendment includes provisions that grant increased benefits based on service rendered in prior periods.

elementLabel: Other Comprehensive Income (Loss), Additional Minimum Pension Liability, Tax Effect (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Tax effect of the change in the additional minimum pension liability.

elementLabel: Other Comprehensive Income (Loss), Reclassification Adjustment for Write-down of Securities Included in Net Income, before Tax (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Before tax amount of the income statement impact of the reclassification adjustment for unrealized (losses) realized upon the write-down of available-for-sale securities.

elementLabel: Other Comprehensive Income (Loss), Reclassification Adjustment for Write-down of Securities Included in Net Income, Net of Tax (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Net of tax amount of the income statement impact of the reclassification adjustment for unrealized (losses) realized upon the write-down of available-for-sale securities.

elementLabel: Other Comprehensive Income (Loss), Reclassification Adjustment for Write-down of Securities Included in Net Income, Tax (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Tax effect of the income statement impact of the reclassification adjustment for unrealized (losses) realized upon the write-down of available-for-sale securities.

elementLabel: Other Comprehensive (Income) Loss, Reclassification Adjustment from AOCI for Write-down of Securities, before Tax
definition: Amount before tax of reclassification adjustment from accumulated other comprehensive income for unrealized loss realized upon the write-down of available-for-sale securities.

elementLabel: Other Comprehensive (Income) Loss, Reclassification Adjustment from AOCI for Write-down of Securities, Net of Tax
definition: Amount after tax of reclassification adjustment from accumulated other comprehensive income for unrealized loss realized upon the write-down of available-for-sale securities.

elementLabel: Other Comprehensive Income (Loss), Reclassification Adjustment for Write-down of Securities Included in Net Income, before Tax (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Pre tax reclassification adjustment for losses realized upon the write-down of securities.

elementLabel: Other Comprehensive Income (Loss), Reclassification Adjustment for Write-down of Securities Included in Net Income, Tax (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Tax effect on the reclassification adjustment for losses realized upon the write-down of securities.

elementLabel: Other Deferred Compensation Arrangements, Liability, Noncurrent (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Aggregate carrying value as of the balance sheet date of the liabilities for deferred compensation arrangements payable after one year (or the operating cycle, if longer) other than those specified elsewhere in the taxonomy. For an unclassified balance sheet, represents the entire liability.

elementLabel: Other Employee Related Liabilities (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred through that date and payable for employer-related costs not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: Other Expense, Capitalization to Deferred Acquisition Cost (DAC) (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Represents the total amount of operating expenses resulting from the amortization or adjustments of amounts capitalized as deferred policy acquisition costs.

elementLabel: Other Expenses
definition: This element represents a sum total of expenses not separately reflected on the income statement for the period.

elementLabel: Other General and Administrative Expense
definition: The sum of expenses not otherwise specified in the taxonomy for managing and administering the affairs of an entity, including affiliates of the reporting entity, which are not directly or indirectly associated with the manufacture, sale or creation of a product or product line.

elementLabel: Other Interest and Dividend Income
definition: Includes all other interest income, net of discount accretion and premium amortization, and dividend income. It may include dividend income from equity securities that do not have readily determinable fair values that are reportable in Other Assets, and interest income on interest-only strips receivable (not in the form of a security) that are included in Other Assets.

elementLabel: Other Investment Not Readily Marketable, Fair Value
definition: Value of the other investment not readily marketable determined by management based upon fair value methods, including pricing of similar securities and valuation techniques, that was used to record the investment for financial reporting purposes.

elementLabel: Other Investment Not Readily Marketable, Quoted Value
definition: Value of the other investments measured by quoted price.

elementLabel: Other Noninterest Expense
definition: Other noninterest expenses that are not separately presented in any other noninterest expense category.

elementLabel: Other Nonoperating Expense
definition: The aggregate amount of other expense amounts, the components of which are not separately disclosed on the income statement, resulting from ancillary business-related activities (that is, excluding major activities considered part of the normal operations of the business) also known as other nonoperating expense recognized during the period. Such amounts may include: (a) unusual costs, (b) loss on foreign exchange transactions, (c) losses on securities (net of profits), and (d) miscellaneous other expense items.

elementLabel: Other Nonoperating Income
definition: The aggregate amount of other income amounts, the components of which are not separately disclosed on the income statement, resulting from ancillary business-related activities (that is, excluding major activities considered part of the normal operations of the business) also known as other nonoperating income recognized for the period. Such amounts may include: (a) dividends, (b) interest on securities, (c) profits on securities (net of losses), and (d) miscellaneous other income items.

elementLabel: Other Nonrecurring Gain
definition: Amount of gain that is infrequent in occurrence or unusual in nature.

elementLabel: Other Postretirement Benefits Payable (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: The total amount of the entity's obligation as of the balance sheet date under any other retirement plan(s), such as one or more defined contribution plans.

elementLabel: Other Premium Revenue, Net (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Premiums recognized as revenue in the period earned on all types of insurance and reinsurance contracts not otherwise specified in the taxonomy after subtracting any amounts ceded to another insurer.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Additions
definition: Additions of other real estate not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations may also be included in real estate owned. This excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Covered
definition: Carrying amount of other real estate covered by loss sharing agreements not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations that may also be included in real estate owned. Excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure by banks.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Covered, Additions
definition: Additions of other real estate covered by loss sharing agreements not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations that may also be included in real estate owned. Excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure by banks.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Covered, Disposals
definition: Disposals of other real estate covered by loss sharing agreements not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations that may also be included in real estate owned. Excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure by banks.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Covered, Improvements
definition: Improvements made to other real estate covered by loss sharing agreements not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations that may also be included in real estate owned. Excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure by banks.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Disposals
definition: Disposals of other real estate not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations may also be included in real estate owned. This excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Improvements
definition: Improvements to other real estate not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations may also be included in real estate owned. This excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Non Covered
definition: Carrying amount of other real estate not covered by loss sharing agreements not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations that may also be included in real estate owned. Excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure by banks.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Non Covered, Additions
definition: Additions of other real estate not covered by loss sharing agreements not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations that may also be included in real estate owned. Excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure by banks.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Non Covered, Disposals
definition: Disposals of other real estate not covered by loss sharing agreements not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations that may also be included in real estate owned. Excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure by banks.

elementLabel: Other Real Estate, Non Covered, Improvements
definition: Improvements made to other real estate not covered by loss sharing agreements not separately disclosed, including, but not limited to, real estate investments, real estate loans that qualify as investments in real estate, and premises that are no longer used in operations that may also be included in real estate owned. Excludes real estate assets taken in settlement of troubled loans through surrender or foreclosure by banks.

elementLabel: Other Research and Development Expense
definition: Amount of other research and development expense.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Available-for-sale Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Loan to Collateral Value
definition: This item represents the loan to collateral ratio of the underlying assets in the security, represented as a percentage, which was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the available-for-sale investments are other than temporarily impaired and only the amount of impairment related to credit loss was recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Held-to-maturity Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Loan to Collateral Value
definition: This item represents the loan to collateral ratio of the underlying assets in the security, represented as a percentage, which was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are other than temporarily impaired and only the amount of impairment related to credit loss was recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Portion in Other Comprehensive Loss, before Tax, Including Portion Attributable to Noncontrolling Interest
definition: Amount before tax of other than temporary impairment (OTTI) loss on investments in available-for-sale and held-to-maturity debt securities, recognized in other comprehensive loss.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Reclassification Adjustment of Noncredit Portion from Held-to-maturity to Available-for-sale Securities, before Tax
definition: Amount before tax of other than temporary impairment (OTTI) related to factors other than credit loss transferred from held-to-maturity to available-for-sale securities.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Reclassification Adjustment of Noncredit Portion Included in Net Income, Availabe-for-sale Securities, before Tax
definition: Amount before tax of reclassification adjustment for other than temporary impairment (OTTI) related to factors other than credit loss on a previously impaired investment in available-for-sale debt security.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Reclassification Adjustment of Noncredit Portion Included in Net Income, Held-to-maturity Securities, before Tax
definition: Amount before tax of reclassification adjustment for other than temporary impairment (OTTI) related to factors other than credit loss on a previously impaired investment on held-to-maturity security.

elementLabel: Other Underwriting Expense
definition: Costs incurred during the period, such as those relating to general administration and policy maintenance that do not vary with and are not primarily related to the acquisition or renewal of insurance contracts.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Contributions
definition: Total contributions made by each class of partners (i.e., general, limited and preferred partners).

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Deferred Compensation
definition: Total change in each class of partners' capital accounts during the year due to deferred compensation. Partners include general, limited and preferred partners.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Distribution Per Unit of Limited Partner Interest
definition: The amount of the distribution per unit of limited partner interest.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Distributions
definition: Total distributions to each class of partners (i.e., general, limited and preferred partners).

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Option Exercise
definition: Total change in each class of partners' capital accounts during the year due to option exercise. All partners include general, limited and preferred partners.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Private Placement of Units
definition: Monetary value of the issuance of new units of limited partnership interest in a private placement.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Public Sale of Units
definition: Monetary value of the issuance of new units of limited partnership interest in a public offering.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Public Sale of Units Net of Offering Costs
definition: Monetary value of the issuance of new units of limited partnership interest in a public offering, net of offering costs. This is a parenthetical disclosure.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Return of Capital
definition: Total change in each class of partners' capital accounts during the year due to the return of partner's capital. That is, excess distributions over earnings to partners. All partners include general, limited and preferred partners.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Sale of Units
definition: Total change in each class of partners' capital accounts during the year due to the sale of units. All partners include general, limited and preferred partners.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Treasury Units, Value (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Cumulative impact on total partners' capital of units issued that have been repurchased.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Units
definition: The number of each class of partnership units outstanding at the balance sheet date. Units represent shares of ownership of the general, limited, and preferred partners.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Units, Contributed
definition: Units contributed by each class of partners during the year. Units represent shares of ownership of the general, limited, and preferred partners.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Units, Redeemed
definition: The number of units redeemed during the year of each class of partners' capital account. Units represent shares of ownership of the general, limited, and preferred partners.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Units, Sale of Units
definition: Total units issued during the year due to the sale of units. All partners include general, limited and preferred partners.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Units, Sold in Private Placement
definition: The number of units sold in a private placement of each class of partners' capital account. Units represent shares of ownership of the general, limited, and preferred partners.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Units, Sold in Public Offering
definition: The number of units sold in a public offering of each class of partners' capital account. Units represent shares of ownership of the general, limited, and preferred partners.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Units, Treasury Units Purchased
definition: Units that were previously issued and have been repurchased during the year.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Units, Treasury Units Reissued
definition: Units that were previously issued and then were repurchased and classified as treasury units. This element represents the number of these units which were reissued during the period.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Account, Units, Unit-based Compensation
definition: The number of units issued due to unit-based compensation.

elementLabel: Patronage Source Earnings
definition: Amount of revenue in excess of cost resulting from transactions for or with patrons.

elementLabel: Payment for Administrative Fees
definition: Amount paid to managing member or general partner, affiliate of managing member or general partner, or affiliate of limited liability company (LLC) or limited partnership (LP) for administrative services provided to the LLC or LP, for example, but not limited to, salaries, rent, or overhead costs.

elementLabel: Payment for Incentive Fee
definition: Amount paid for incentive rights held by the managing member or general partner, of limited liability company (LLC) or limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Payment for Management Fee
definition: Amount paid to managing member or general partner for management of the day-to-day business functions of the limited liability company (LLC) or limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Payments for Brokerage Fees
definition: The amount of cash paid for brokerage fees during the current period. This element is intended to represent the brokerage fees paid by and between financial industry participants.

elementLabel: Payments for Construction in Process
definition: The cash outflow from construction costs to date on capital projects that have not been completed and assets being constructed that are not ready to be placed into service.

elementLabel: Payments for Deposits with Other Institutions
definition: Cash paid to make deposits at other institutions during the period.

elementLabel: Payments for Lease Commissions
definition: Amount of cash outflow for lease commissions incurred.

elementLabel: Payments for Leasing Costs
definition: Amount of cash outflow for costs that are essential to originate the lease and would not otherwise have been incurred without the lease agreement. Amount includes, but is not limited to, cash outflows to evaluate the lessee's credit condition, guarantees, and collateral and cash outflows for costs incurred in negotiating, processing, and executing the lease agreement.

elementLabel: Payments for Loans
definition: Cash payments for and related to principal collection on loans related to operating activities.

elementLabel: Liability for Unpaid Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense, Claims Paid
definition: Amount of payments to settle insured claims and pay costs incurred in the claims settlement process.

elementLabel: Payments for Origination and Purchases of Loans Held-for-sale
definition: The aggregate amount of cash outflow for loans purchased and created with the intention to resell them in the near future.

elementLabel: Payments for Purchase of Other Assets
definition: Amount of cash paid to purchase other assets as part of operating activities.

elementLabel: Payments for Reinsurance
definition: Cash payments made for reinsurance during the current period.

elementLabel: Payments for Repurchase of Common Stock for Employee Tax Withholding Obligations (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of cash outflow for repurchase of common stock to satisfy employee tax withholding obligations for stock issued as part of an employee benefit plan.

elementLabel: Payments for Repurchase of Redeemable Noncontrolling Interest
definition: The cash outflow during the period for redemption of redeemable noncontrolling interests.

elementLabel: Payments for Repurchase of Trust Preferred Securities
definition: The cash outflow to reacquire preferred stocks issued by a business trust or other special purpose entity, mainly established by a bank holding entity, to third party investors. The trust's assets are deeply subordinated debentures of the bank holding entity. Most trust preferred securities are subject to a mandatory redemption upon the repayment of the debentures.

elementLabel: Payments for Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell
definition: The cash outflow associated with agreements to purchase and then resell securities to counterparties (reverse repurchase agreements).

elementLabel: Payments for Software
definition: The cash outflow associated with the development, modification or acquisition of software programs or applications for internal use (that is, not to be sold, leased or otherwise marketed to others) that qualify for capitalization.

elementLabel: Payments for Tenant Improvements
definition: Amount of cash outflow for the allowance granted to lessee and/or direct costs incurred by lessor used to prepare the leased premises for tenant's occupancy.

elementLabel: Payments for Time Deposits
definition: Cash paid to customers who withdraw money in checking and similar accounts at a financial institution.

elementLabel: Payments for Underwriting Expense
definition: Cash paid for expenses incurred during underwriting activities (the process to review insurance applications, evaluate risks, accept or reject applications, and determine the premiums to be charged) for insurance companies.

elementLabel: Payments of Debt Extinguishment Costs
definition: The cash outflow for incremental, external costs directly pertaining to an early extinguishment of debt, including legal costs and prepayment penalties, and excluding interest and repayment of debt principal.

elementLabel: Payments of Derivative Issuance Costs
definition: The cash outflow for cost incurred directly with the issuance of a derivative security.

elementLabel: Payments Related to Tax Withholding for Share-based Compensation
definition: Amount of cash outflow to satisfy an employee's income tax withholding obligation as part of a net-share settlement of a share-based award.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire and Develop Real Estate
definition: The cash outflow from the acquisition of a piece of land and anything permanently fixed to it, including buildings, structures on it and so forth, and payments to develop real estate assets by adding improvements on or to a parcel of land. Such improvements may include drainage, utilities, subdividing, access, buildings, and any combination of these elements. Including real estate intended to generate income for the owner; excluding real estate acquired for use by the owner.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Commercial Real Estate
definition: The cash outflow from the acquisition of property as primarily intended to generate income for its owner.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Federal Home Loan Bank Stock
definition: Amount of cash outflow to acquire Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLB) stock.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Held-for-sale Real Estate
definition: The cash outflow from the acquisition of a piece of land held for sale, anything permanently fixed to it, including buildings, structures on it, and so forth.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Land
definition: The cash outflow from the acquisition of real estate intended to generate income for the owner; excludes land acquired for use by the owner.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Loans Held-for-investment
definition: The cash outflow associated with purchasing loans held for investment purposes during the period.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Management Contract Rights
definition: The cash outflow from amounts paid for the rights to manage the property.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Mortgage Backed Securities (MBS) categorized as Available-for-sale
definition: The cash outflow for the purchase of securities issued by a governmental agency or corporation (for example, GNMA or FHLMC) or by private issuers (for example, banks and mortgage banking enterprises) secured by and repaid from underlying mortgages, which were designated as available for sale when acquired.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Mortgage Backed Securities (MBS) categorized as Held-to-maturity
definition: The cash outflow for the purchase of securities issued by a governmental agency or corporation (for example, GNMA or FHLMC) or by private issuers (for example, banks and mortgage banking enterprises) secured by and repaid from underlying mortgages, which were designated as held to maturity when acquired.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Mortgage Notes Receivable
definition: The cash outflow from the purchase of receivables arising from the mortgage note on real estate.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Mortgage Servicing Rights (MSR)
definition: The cash outflow to obtain servicing rights, which contractually entitle the servicer to receive fees and ancillary revenues for performing billing, collection, disbursement and recordkeeping services in connection with a mortgage portfolio. Rights may be obtained via (1) acquisition or assumption of a servicing obligation that does not relate to financial assets of the servicer or its consolidated affiliates; or (2) by originating mortgage loans and then (a) transferring the loans to a Variable Interest Entity (VIE) in a transaction that meets the necessary transfer and classification requirements, or (b) transferring the loans in a transaction that meets the requirements for sale accounting.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Other Real Estate
definition: The cash outflow associated with the purchase of other real estate investments held by the entity for investment purposes not otherwise defined in the taxonomy.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Partners Interest in Real Estate Partnership, Net of Cash Acquired
definition: The cash outflow from the purchase of ownership in a partnership, the purpose of which is to construct, sell, hold or invest in real estate.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Property, Plant, and Equipment
definition: The cash outflow associated with the acquisition of long-lived, physical assets that are used in the normal conduct of business to produce goods and services and not intended for resale; includes cash outflows to pay for construction of self-constructed assets.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Real Estate
