definition: The cash outflow from the acquisition of a piece of land, anything permanently fixed to it, including buildings, structures on it and so forth; includes real estate intended to generate income for the owner; excludes real estate acquired for use by the owner.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Real Estate Held-for-investment
definition: The cash outflow associated with the purchase of real estate held for investment purposes.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Residential Real Estate
definition: The cash outflow from the acquisition of residential property intended to generate income for the owner.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Trust Preferred Investments
definition: The cash outflow for the purchase of trust preferred securities, which possess characteristics of both equity and debt securities.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire US Government Securities Pledged under Bond Indenture
definition: The cash outflow from the purchase of US Government Securities Pledged Under Bond Indenture.

elementLabel: Payments to Develop Real Estate Assets
definition: Payments to develop real estate assets is the process of adding improvements on or to a parcel of land. Such improvements may include drainage, utilities, subdividing, access, buildings, and any combination of these elements; and are generally classified as cash flow from investing activities.

elementLabel: Payments to Fund Policy Loans
definition: The initial funding or additional funding of loans receivable to policy holders principally secured by the benefits under the policy.

elementLabel: Payments to Purchase Loans Held-for-sale
definition: The aggregate cash outflow used to purchase all loans that are held with the intention to resell in the near future.

elementLabel: Payments to Purchase Mortgage Loans Held-for-sale
definition: The cash outflow used to purchase loans that are secured with real estate mortgage and are held with the intention to resell in the near future.

elementLabel: Payments to Purchase Other Loans Held-for-sale
definition: The cash outflow used to purchase loans (other than mortgage loans) that are held with the intention to resell in the near future.

elementLabel: Pension and Other Postretirement and Postemployment Benefit Plans, Noncurrent Liabilities (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: For classified balance sheets this represents the noncurrent liability recognized in the balance sheet that is associated with the defined benefit pension plans and other postretirement defined benefit plans. (The current liability will be separate, but it will normally be small, if there is even any at all.) For unclassified balance sheets, this represents the entire liability recognized in the balance sheet that is associated with the defined benefit plans.

elementLabel: Planned Major Maintenance Activities, Effect of Change on Prior Period Per Share Amounts, Diluted Earnings Per Share (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: For any periods retrospectively adjusted, the amount of the effect of the change in permitted major maintenance activities on affected diluted earnings per share amounts.

elementLabel: Policy Charges, Insurance (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: An amount that an insurer adds to a policy's premium, or deducts from a policy's cash value or contract holder's account, as compensation for services rendered; may include fees.

elementLabel: Policyholder Benefits and Claims Incurred, Net, Health
definition: Amount, after effect of policies assumed or ceded, of expense related to provision for policy benefits and costs incurred for health insurance contracts.

elementLabel: Policyholder Benefits and Claims Incurred, Net, Life and Annuity
definition: Amount, after effect of policies assumed or ceded, of expense related to provision for policy benefits and costs incurred for life and annuity insurance contracts.

elementLabel: Policyholder Benefits and Claims Incurred, Net, Other
definition: Amount, after effect of policies assumed or ceded, of expense related to provision for benefits and costs incurred for other insurance contracts.

elementLabel: Policyholder Dividends, Expense
definition: Amount of expense for dividends to policyholders.

elementLabel: Policyholders' Surplus
definition: Amount of policyholders' surplus excluded from calculating deferred taxes.

elementLabel: Postage Expense
definition: Amount of expense associated with postage.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Dividend (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Total dividends declared for each class of preferred stock.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock Dividends, Income Statement Impact
definition: The amount of preferred stock dividends that is an adjustment to net income apportioned to common stockholders.

elementLabel: Premiums Earned, Net, Accident and Health
definition: Amount, after premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of accident and health premiums earned.

elementLabel: Premiums Earned, Net, Financial Guarantee Insurance Contracts
definition: Amount, after premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of financial guarantee premiums earned.

elementLabel: Premiums Earned, Net, Life
definition: Amount, after premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of life premiums earned.

elementLabel: Premiums Earned, Net, Property and Casualty
definition: Amount, after premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of property and casualty premiums earned.

elementLabel: Premiums, Net, Life Insurance in Force (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount, after premiums ceded to other entities and premiums assumed by the entity, of life insurance in force premiums.

elementLabel: Premiums, Percentage Assumed to Net
definition: Percentage of assumed premiums earned by the entity to net premiums earned.

elementLabel: Premiums Receivable, Allowance for Doubtful Accounts, Provision Charged to Expense (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The amount charged against earnings during the period to provide for known and estimated losses on collections of premiums receivable.

elementLabel: Premiums Receivable, Allowance for Doubtful Accounts, Provision Charged to Expense
definition: Amount of expense for known and estimated loss on collection of premiums receivable.

elementLabel: Prepaid Expense and Other Assets, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of asset related to consideration paid in advance for costs that provide economic benefits in future periods, and amount of other assets that are expected to be realized or consumed after one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, after Year Five
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Next Twelve Months
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Rolling after Year Five
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Year Five
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Year Four
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Year Three
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prescription Drug Subsidy Receipts, Year Two
definition: Amount of the prescription drug subsidy receipts to be received in the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Decrease (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Amount of decrease in present value of future insurance profits, including but not limited to amortization, impairment and unrealized investment loss.

elementLabel: Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Impairment Write-down
definition: Amount of impairment recognized in the income statement reducing the present value of future profits asset below amortized carrying value.

elementLabel: Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Interest Accrued
definition: Amount of interest earned on present value of future insurance profits.

elementLabel: Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Unrealized Investment Gains
definition: Amount of unrealized investment gains recognized in the income statement from the increase in the present value of future insurance profits asset.

elementLabel: Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Unrealized Investment Losses
definition: Amount of unrealized investment loss recognized in the income statement from the decrease in the present value of future profits asset.

elementLabel: Pressure Maintenance Operations
definition: The number of pressure maintenance operations in each geographic area as of the date listed.

elementLabel: Principal Amount Outstanding on Loans Managed and Securitized or Asset-backed Financing Arrangement
definition: This is the sum of principal amount outstanding for both securitized and unsecuritized loans of all types.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Annuities and Investment Certificates
definition: The cash inflow from an insurance contract under which the policy holder make a lump sum payment or a series of payments in exchange for periodic payments to the policyholder beginning immediately or at some future date.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Bank Debt
definition: The cash inflow from bank borrowing during the year.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Collection of Advance to Affiliate
definition: The cash inflow from the collection of money previously advanced to an entity that is related to it but not strictly controlled.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Collection of Loans Held-for-sale
definition: The cash inflow from collection of repayments from borrowers on loans that are held with the intention to resell in the near future; includes mortgages and other types of loans.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Collection of Long-term Loans to Related Parties
definition: The cash inflow associated with collection, whether partial or full, of long-term loans to a related party. Alternate caption: Proceeds from Advances to Affiliates.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Collection of Other Loans Held-for-sale
definition: The cash inflow from collection of repayments from borrowers on loans that are held with the intention to resell in the near future; includes loans that are not mortgages.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Collection of Policy Loans
definition: The cash inflow associated with the collection of policy loans receivable.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Collection of Retained Interest in Securitized Receivables categorized as Available-for-sale
definition: The cash inflow from the collection of a retained interest in a receivable securitized via a structured process whereby interests in loans and other receivables are packaged, underwritten, and sold in the form of asset-backed securities, categorized as available-for-sale.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Collection of Retained Interest in Securitized Receivables categorized as Held-to-maturity
definition: The cash inflow from the collection of a retained interest in a receivable securitized via a structured process whereby interests in loans and other receivables are packaged, underwritten, and sold in the form of asset-backed securities, categorized as held to maturity.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Construction Loans Payable
definition: The cash inflow from borrowings to finance the cost of construction.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Deposits with Other Institutions
definition: Cash received from refund of deposits with other institutions during the period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Derivative Instrument, Investing Activities
definition: The cash inflow provided by derivative instruments during the period, which are classified as investing activities, excluding those designated as hedging instruments.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Distributions Received from Real Estate Partnerships
definition: The cash inflow from earnings received from real estate partnerships.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Divestiture of Real Estate Partnership
definition: The cash inflow from the sale of interest in partnership during the period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Equity Method Investment, Dividends or Distributions, Return of Capital
definition: Cash dividends or other distributions received from unconsolidated subsidiaries, certain corporate joint ventures, and certain noncontrolled corporations that are returns of capital. Excludes dividends or distributions from equity method investments classified as operating activities.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Federal Home Loan Bank Borrowings
definition: The cash inflow from a borrowing made from Federal Home Loan Bank.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Insurance Premiums Collected
definition: Cash received as payments for insurance premiums during the current period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of Common Stock, Dividend Reinvestment Plan
definition: Amount of cash inflow from capital contributions to an entity associated with a dividend reinvestment plan.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of Debt
definition: The cash inflow during the period from additional borrowings in aggregate debt. Includes proceeds from short-term and long-term debt.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of Preferred Stock, Preference Stock, and Warrants
definition: Proceeds from issuance of capital stock which provides for a specific dividend that is paid to the shareholders before any dividends to common stockholder, which takes precedence over common stockholders in the event of liquidation and from issuance of rights to purchase common shares at a predetermined price.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of Shares under Incentive and Share-based Compensation Plans, Including Stock Options
definition: The total cash inflow associated with the amount received from holders to acquire the entity's shares under incentive and share awards, including stock option exercises. This item inherently excludes any excess tax benefit, which the entity may have realized and reported separately.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of Trust Preferred Securities
definition: The cash inflow from issuance of preferred stocks by a business trust or other special purpose entity, mainly established by a bank holding entity, to third party investors. The trust's assets are deeply subordinated debentures of the bank holding entity. Most trust preferred securities are subject to a mandatory redemption upon the repayment of the debentures.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Loan and Lease Originations and Principal Collections
definition: Cash inflow related to a loan origination (the process when securing a mortgage for a piece of real property), lease origination, and principal collections.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Loan Originations (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The cash inflow associated with loan origination (the process when securing a mortgage for a piece of real property) or lease origination. It is through this process that the terms of the mortgage agreement (amount of loan, interest rate, compounding frequency, and so forth) or lease are established and the involved parties legally bind themselves to the transaction.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Loan Originations
definition: Cash inflow associated with loan origination (the process when securing a mortgage for a piece of real property) or lease origination.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Loans
definition: Cash received from principal payments made on loans related to operating activities.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Maturities, Prepayments and Calls of Mortgage Backed Securities (MBS)
definition: The cash inflow from the maturity (principal due), prepayment and call (request of early payment) of a loan financed by home mortgage payments classified as held to maturity.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Maturities, Prepayments and Calls of Other Investments
definition: The cash inflow associated with the maturity (principal being due), prepayment and call (request of early payment) of other investments not otherwise defined in the taxonomy.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Maturities, Prepayments and Calls of Securities, Operating Activities
definition: Cash received from maturities, prepayments and calls of trading securities and other securities, classified as operating.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Other Deposits
definition: Cash inflow related to receipts of other deposits not otherwise defined in the taxonomy.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Principal Repayments on Loans and Leases Held-for-investment
definition: The cash inflow from repayments of the balance excluding interest (principal) on loans receivable and leases held for investment purposes.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Recoveries of Loans Previously Charged off
definition: The cash inflow from loans reinstated and recovered that were previously deemed uncollectible.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Related Party Debt
definition: The cash inflow from a long-term borrowing made from related parties where one party can exercise control or significant influence over another party; including affiliates, owners or officers and their immediate families, pension trusts, and so forth. Alternate caption: Proceeds from Advances from Affiliates.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Repayment of Loans to Purchase Common Stock
definition: Cash inflow from repayment of loans for purchasing common stock.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale and Collection of Loans Held-for-sale
definition: The cash inflow from sale proceeds and collection of repayments from borrowers on loans classified as held-for-sale, including proceeds from loans sold through mortgage securitization; includes mortgages and other types of loans.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale and Collection of Mortgage Notes Receivable
definition: The cash inflow from proceeds from sale of receivables arising from the mortgage note on real estate; includes collections on mortgage notes receivable that are not classified as operating cash flows.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Donor Restricted Assets
definition: Amount of receipts from contributions and investment income with restrictions stipulated by the donor for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, or improving property, plant, equipment, or other long-lived assets, or establishing, or increasing a permanent endowment or term endowment.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Federal Home Loan Bank Stock
definition: Amount of cash inflow from sale of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLB) stock.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Land (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: The cash inflow from the sale of real estate asset held for productive use.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Land Held-for-investment
definition: The cash inflow from the sale of land held for investment; excludes sales of land held as inventory or productive use.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Loans Held-for-investment
definition: The cash inflow from Sales of Loans Held For Investment.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Loans Held-for-sale
definition: The cash inflow resulting from the sale of loans classified as held-for-sale, including proceeds from loans sold through mortgage securitization.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Mortgage Backed Securities (MBS) categorized as Available-for-sale
definition: The cash inflow from the sale of securities issued by a governmental agency or corporation (for example, GNMA or FHLMC) or by private issuers (for example, banks and mortgage banking enterprises) secured by and repaid from underlying mortgages, which were designated as available for sale when acquired.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Mortgage Servicing Rights (MSR)
definition: The cash inflow from the sale of servicing rights, which contractually entitle the servicer to receive fees and ancillary revenues for performing billing, collection, disbursement and recordkeeping services in connection with a mortgage portfolio. Rights may be obtained via (1) acquisition or assumption of a servicing obligation that does not relate to financial assets of the servicer or its consolidated affiliates; or (2) by originating mortgage loans and then (a) transferring the loans to a Variable Interest Entity (VIE) in a transaction that meets the necessary transfer and classification requirements, or (b) transferring the loans in a transaction that meets the requirements for sale accounting.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Other Assets
definition: Amount of cash inflow from the sale of other assets as part of operating activities.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Other Assets, Investing Activities
definition: Amount of cash inflow from the sale of other assets recognized in investing activities.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Other Investments
definition: The cash inflow associated with the sale of other investments not otherwise defined in the taxonomy.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Other Loans Held-for-sale
definition: The cash inflow resulting from the sale of loans (other than mortgage loans) that are held with the intention to resell in the near future.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Other Real Estate
definition: The cash inflow associated with the sale of other real estate not otherwise defined in the taxonomy.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Other Real Estate Held-for-investment
definition: The cash inflow associated with the sale of other real estate held for investment not otherwise defined in the taxonomy.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Property Held-for-sale
definition: The cash inflow from the sale of formerly productive land held for sale, anything permanently fixed to it, including buildings, structures on it, and so forth.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Property, Plant, and Equipment
definition: The cash inflow from the sale of long-lived, physical assets that are used in the normal conduct of business to produce goods and services and not intended for resale.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Real Estate Held-for-investment
definition: Cash received from the sale of real estate that is held for investment, that is, it is part of an investing activity during the period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Securities, Operating Activities
definition: Cash received from sale of investments in debt and equity securities, classified as operating activities, during the period; includes trading securities and any other investments classified as operating.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Trust Assets to Pay Expenses
definition: Amount of cash inflows from the sale of trust assets to pay trust expenses.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Secured Lines of Credit
definition: The cash inflow from a contractual arrangement with the lender, including letter of credit, standby letter of credit and revolving credit arrangements, under which borrowings can be made up to a specific amount at any point in time with either short term or long term maturity that is collateralized (backed by pledge, mortgage or other lien in the entity's assets).

elementLabel: Proceeds from Secured Notes Payable
definition: The cash inflow from borrowings supported by a written promise to pay an obligation that is collateralized (backed by pledge, mortgage or other lien in the entity's assets).

elementLabel: Proceeds from Securitizations of Loans Held-for-sale
definition: The cash inflow from securitizing loans held with the intention to resell in the near future.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Short-term Capital Lease Obligations
definition: The cash inflow from proceeds received from lessor related to capital lease obligation.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Time Deposits Accepted
definition: Cash received from customers who deposit money in checking and similar accounts at a financial institution.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Unsecured Lines of Credit
definition: The cash inflow from a contractual arrangement with the lender, including letter of credit, standby letter of credit and revolving credit arrangements, under which borrowings can be made up to a specific amount at any point in time with either short term or long term maturity that is uncollateralized (where debt is not backed by the pledge of collateral).

elementLabel: Proceeds from Unsecured Notes Payable
definition: The cash inflow from borrowings supported by a written promise to pay an obligation that is uncollateralized (where debt is not backed by the pledge of collateral).

elementLabel: Production and Distribution Costs
definition: Amount of expense related to the production and distribution of goods or services to customers and clients.

elementLabel: Production, Barrels of Oil Equivalents
definition: Energy measure of oil and natural gas production reserves.

elementLabel: Production Costs, Period Cost
definition: The capitalized costs incurred during the period (excluded from amortization) to operate and maintain wells and related equipment and facilities, including depreciation and applicable operating costs of support equipment and facilities and other costs of operating and maintaining those wells and related equipment and facilities. They become part of the cost of oil and gas produced. Examples of production costs (sometimes called lifting costs) are: costs of labor to operate the wells and related equipment and facilities; repairs and maintenance; materials, supplies, and fuel consumed and supplies utilized in operating the wells and related equipment and facilities; property taxes and insurance applicable to proved properties and wells and related equipment and facilities; severance taxes; some support equipment or facilities may serve two or more oil and gas producing activities and may also serve transportation, refining, and marketing activities. To the extent that the support equipment and facilities are used in oil and gas producing activities, their depreciation and applicable operating costs become exploration, development or production costs, as appropriate. Depreciation, depletion, and amortization of capitalized acquisition, exploration, and development costs are not production costs but also become part of the cost of oil and gas produced along with production (lifting) costs identified above.

elementLabel: Production Tax Expense
definition: A tax assessed on oil and gas production.

elementLabel: Productive Gas Wells, Number of Wells, Gross
definition: The total number of producing gas wells and gas wells capable of production, in which the entity owns an undivided working interest.

elementLabel: Productive Gas Wells, Number of Wells, Net
definition: The total number of producing gas wells and gas wells capable of production, in which the entity owns a fractional working interest.

elementLabel: Productive Gas Wells, Number of Wells with Multiple Completions, Gross
definition: The total number of productive gas wells and gas wells capable of production which access multiple reservoirs through one well bore, in which the entity owns an undivided working interest.

elementLabel: Productive Gas Wells, Number of Wells with Multiple Completions, Net
definition: The total number of productive gas wells and gas wells capable of production which access multiple reservoirs through one well bore, in which the entity owns a fractional working interest.

elementLabel: Productive Oil Wells, Number of Wells, Gross
definition: The total number of producing oil wells and oil wells capable of production, in which the entity owns an undivided working interest.

elementLabel: Productive Oil Wells, Number of Wells, Net
definition: The total number of producing oil wells and oil wells capable of production, in which the entity owns a fractional working interest.

elementLabel: Productive Oil Wells, Number of Wells with Multiple Completions, Gross
definition: The total number of productive oil wells and oil wells capable of production which access multiple reservoirs through one well bore, in which the entity owns an undivided working interest.

elementLabel: Productive Oil Wells, Number of Wells with Multiple Completions, Net
definition: The total number of productive oil wells and oil wells capable of production which access multiple reservoirs through one well bore, in which the entity owns a fractional working interest.

elementLabel: Product Warranty Accrual, Current (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred through that date and payable for estimated claims under standard and extended warranty protection rights granted to customers. For classified balance sheets, represents the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, represents the total liability.

elementLabel: Professional and Contract Services Expense
definition: Professional and contract service expense includes cost reimbursements for support services related to contracted projects, outsourced management, technical and staff support.

elementLabel: Professional Fees
definition: A fee charged for services from professionals such as doctors, lawyers and accountants. The term is often expanded to include other professions, for example, pharmacists charging to maintain a medicinal profile of a client or customer.

elementLabel: Program Rights Obligations
definition: Total amount of obligations related to rights to programming, including, but not limited to, feature films and episodic series, acquired under license agreements.

elementLabel: Program Rights Obligations, Current
definition: Amount of obligations related to rights to programming, including, but not limited to, feature films and episodic series, acquired under license agreements that will be paid within the next twelve months.

elementLabel: Program Rights Obligations, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of obligations related to rights to programming, including, but not limited to, feature films and episodic series, acquired under license agreements that will be paid after one year.

elementLabel: Property, Plant and Equipment, Additions
definition: Amount of acquisition of long-lived, physical assets used in the normal conduct of business and not intended for resale. Examples include, but are not limited to, land, buildings, machinery and equipment, office equipment, furniture and fixtures, and computer equipment.

elementLabel: Property, Plant, and Equipment, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of physical assets used in the normal conduct of business to produce goods and services and not intended for resale. Examples include, but are not limited to, land, buildings, machinery and equipment, office equipment, and furniture and fixtures.

elementLabel: Property, Plant and Equipment, Gross, Excluding Capital Leased Assets
definition: Gross amount of long-lived physical assets excluding assets held under lease agreements used in the normal conduct of business and not intended for resale. Examples include, but are not limited to, land, buildings, machinery and equipment, office equipment, furniture and fixtures, and computer equipment.

elementLabel: Property, Plant and Equipment, Net, Excluding Capital Leased Assets
definition: Amount, net of accumulated depreciation, depletion and amortization, of long-lived physical assets excluding assets held under lease agreements used in the normal conduct of business and not intended for resale. Examples include, but are not limited to, land, buildings, machinery and equipment, office equipment, furniture and fixtures, and computer equipment.

elementLabel: Property Subject to or Available for Operating Lease, Accumulated Depreciation
definition: The amount of accumulated depreciation, by major property class, recorded on property subject to or available for lease as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Property Subject to or Available for Operating Lease, Net
definition: The amount of property, by major property class, net of accumulated depreciation, subject to or available for lease as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserve, Extension and Discovery (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of increase in quantity of proved reserve of oil and gas resulting from the extension of the proved acreage of previously discovered reservoir or discovery of new field with proved reserve or of new reservoir of proved reserve in old field, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserve, Improved Recovery (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of increase in quantity of proved reserve of oil and gas resulting from application of improved recovery techniques, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserve, Net (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of proved reserve of oil and gas, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserve, Production (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of decrease in quantity of proved reserve of oil and gas resulting from production, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserve, Purchase of Mineral in Place (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of increase in quantity of proved reserve of oil and gas resulting from purchase of mineral in place, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Extensions, Discoveries, and Additions
definition: Additions to proved reserves that result from (1) extension of the proved acreage of previously discovered (old) reservoirs through additional drilling in periods after discovery and (2) discovery of new fields with proved reserves or of new reservoirs of proved reserves in old fields.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Improved Recovery
definition: Changes in proved reserve estimates resulting from application of improved recovery techniques.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Net
definition: The net quantity of proved reserves as of the balance sheet date. Proved oil reserves are the estimated quantities of crude oil and natural gas liquids which geological and engineering data demonstrate with reasonable certainty to be recoverable.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Production
definition: Production of proved reserves.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Purchases of Minerals in Place
definition: Purchase of minerals in place.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Sale of Mineral in Place (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of decrease in quantity of proved reserve of oil and gas resulting from sale of mineral in place, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Sales of Minerals in Place
definition: Sales of minerals in place.

elementLabel: Proved Developed Reserves (BOE) (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Net quantities of an enterprise's interests in proved developed reserves of either crude oil (including condensate and natural gas liquids), natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other nonrenewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas as of the beginning and the end of the year. "Net" quantities of reserves include those relating to the enterprise's operating and nonoperating interests in properties. Quantities of reserves relating to royalty interests owned are included in "net" quantities if the necessary information is available to the enterprise. "Net" quantities do not include reserves relating to interests of others in properties owned by the enterprise. Measured in barrel of oil equivalent (BOE).

elementLabel: Proved Developed Reserves (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of interests in proved developed reserves of crude oil, including condensate and natural gas liquids, natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other nonrenewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas.

elementLabel: Proved Developed Reserves (Volume)
definition: Net quantities of an enterprise's interests in proved developed reserves of either crude oil (including condensate and natural gas liquids), natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other nonrenewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas as of the beginning and the end of the year. "Net" quantities of reserves include those relating to the enterprise's operating and nonoperating interests in properties. Quantities of reserves relating to royalty interests owned are included in "net" quantities if the necessary information is available to the enterprise. "Net" quantities does not include reserves relating to interests of others in properties owned by the enterprise. The unit of measure for reserve quantities is defined as "barrels" for oil and synthetic oil reserves or "cubic feet" or "cubic meters" for natural gas and synthetic gas reserves.

elementLabel: Proved Undeveloped Reserve (BOE) (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Net quantities of an enterprise's interests in proved undeveloped reserves of either crude oil (including condensate and natural gas liquids), natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other nonrenewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas as of the beginning and the end of the year. "Net" quantities of reserves include those relating to the enterprise's operating and nonoperating interests in properties. Quantities of reserves relating to royalty interests owned are included in "net" quantities if the necessary information is available to the enterprise. "Net" quantities do not include reserves relating to interests of others in properties owned by the enterprise. Measured in barrel of oil equivalent (BOE).

elementLabel: Proved Undeveloped Reserves (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of proved undeveloped reserves of crude oil, including condensate and natural gas liquids, natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other nonrenewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas.

elementLabel: Proved Undeveloped Reserves (BOE) (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: Net quantities of an enterprise's interests in proved undeveloped reserves of either crude oil (including condensate and natural gas liquids), natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other nonrenewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas as of the beginning and the end of the year. "Net" quantities of reserves include those relating to the enterprise's operating and nonoperating interests in properties. Quantities of reserves relating to royalty interests owned are included in "net" quantities if the necessary information is available to the enterprise. "Net" quantities do not include reserves relating to interests of others in properties owned by the enterprise. Measured in barrel of oil equivalent (BOE).

elementLabel: Proved Undeveloped Reserves (Volume) (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: Net quantities of an enterprise's interests in proved undeveloped reserves of either crude oil (including condensate and natural gas liquids), natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other renewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas as of the beginning and the end of the year. "Net" quantities of reserves include those relating to the enterprise's operating and nonoperating interests in properties. Quantities of reserves relating to royalty interests owned are included in "net" quantities if the necessary information is available to the enterprise. "Net" quantities does not include reserves relating to interests of others in properties owned by the enterprise. The unit of measure for reserve quantities is defined as "barrels" for oil and synthetic oil reserves or "cubic feet" or "cubic meters" for natural gas and synthetic gas reserves.

elementLabel: Proved Undeveloped Reserve (Volume)
definition: Net quantities of an enterprise's interests in proved undeveloped reserves of either crude oil (including condensate and natural gas liquids), natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other renewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas as of the beginning and the end of the year. "Net" quantities of reserves include those relating to the enterprise's operating and nonoperating interests in properties. Quantities of reserves relating to royalty interests owned are included in "net" quantities if the necessary information is available to the enterprise. "Net" quantities does not include reserves relating to interests of others in properties owned by the enterprise. The unit of measure for reserve quantities is defined as "barrels" for oil and synthetic oil reserves or "cubic feet" or "cubic meters" for natural gas and synthetic gas reserves.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Amount of Allowance for Funds Used During Construction, Equity Costs Capitalized Only for Rate-making Purposes
definition: Amount of costs of debt and equity financing capitalized for setting rates but not capitalized for financial statement purposes.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Approved Debt Capital Structure, Percentage
definition: Percentage of public utility's approved debt to capital, including debt and equity.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Approved Equity Capital Structure, Percentage
definition: Percentage of public utility's approved equity to capital, including debt and equity.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Approved Return on Equity, Percentage
definition: Percentage of public utility's approved return on equity.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Inventory
definition: The period end amount for a type of inventory held by the utility in a schedule of inventories.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Accumulated Depreciation
definition: Period end book value of accumulated depreciation on property, plant and equipment (PPE) that is owned by the regulated operations of the public utility.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Amortization of Present Value of Regulated Asset for Plant Abandonment
definition: Amortization of the present value amount of future cost recoveries related to plant abandonment in regulated industries.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Common
definition: Period end amount of property, plant and equipment (PPE) related to regulated assets common to business units.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Construction Work in Progress
definition: Period end amount of construction work in progress in public utility.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Distribution
definition: Period end amount of property, plant and equipment (PPE) related to utility distribution.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Equipment
definition: Period end book value of equipment owned (but not classified elsewhere) by the public utility.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Fuel
definition: Period end amount of property, plant and equipment (PPE) related to fuels owned by the public utility.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Generation or Processing
definition: Period end amount of property, plant and equipment (PPE) related to generation or processing owned by public utility.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Land
definition: Period end book value of land owned by the public utility.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Net
definition: Period end amount of total net PPE.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Other Property, Plant and Equipment
definition: Period end book value of other property, plant and equipment (PPE) owned (but not classified elsewhere) by the public utility.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Plant in Service
definition: Period end amount of total gross PPE.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Transmission
definition: Period end amount of property, plant and equipment (PPE) related to utility transmission owned by public utility.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Transmission and Distribution
definition: Period end amount of property, plant and equipment (PPE) related to transmission and distribution owned by public utility.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Vehicles
definition: Period end book value of vehicles owned by the public utility.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Requested Debt Capital Structure, Percentage
definition: Percentage of public utility's requested debt to capital, including debt and equity.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Requested Equity Capital Structure, Percentage
definition: Percentage of public utility's requested equity to capital, including debt and equity.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Requested Return on Equity, Percentage
definition: Percentage of public utility's requested return on equity.

elementLabel: Purchase Obligation
definition: Minimum amount of purchase arrangement in which the entity has agreed to expend funds to procure goods or services from a supplier.

elementLabel: Purchase Obligation, Due after Fifth Year
definition: Minimum amount of purchase arrangement maturing after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Includes, but not limited to, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, long-term purchase commitments, and short-term purchase commitments.

elementLabel: Purchase Obligation, Due in Fifth Year
definition: Minimum amount of purchase arrangement maturing in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Includes, but not limited to, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, long-term purchase commitments, and short-term purchase commitments.

elementLabel: Purchase Obligation, Due in Fourth and Fifth Year
definition: Minimum amount of purchase arrangement maturing in the fourth and fifth fiscal years following the latest fiscal year. Includes, but not limited to, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, long-term purchase commitments, and short-term purchase commitments.

elementLabel: Purchase Obligation, Due in Fourth Year
definition: Minimum amount of purchase arrangement maturing in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Includes, but not limited to, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, long-term purchase commitments, and short-term purchase commitments.

elementLabel: Purchase Obligation, Due in Next Twelve Months
definition: Minimum amount of purchase arrangement maturing in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Includes, but not limited to, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, long-term purchase commitments, and short-term purchase commitments.

elementLabel: Purchase Obligation, Due in Second and Third Year
definition: Minimum amount of purchase arrangement maturing in the second and third fiscal years following the latest fiscal year. Includes, but not limited to, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, long-term purchase commitments, and short-term purchase commitments.

elementLabel: Purchase Obligation, Due in Second Year
definition: Minimum amount of purchase arrangement maturing in the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Includes, but not limited to, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, long-term purchase commitments, and short-term purchase commitments.

elementLabel: Purchase Obligation, Due in Third Year
definition: Minimum amount of purchase arrangement maturing in the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Includes, but not limited to, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, long-term purchase commitments, and short-term purchase commitments.

elementLabel: Ratio of Indebtedness to Net Capital
definition: Indebtedness divided by net capital.

elementLabel: Real Estate Accumulated Depreciation, Depreciation Expense (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of depreciation expense for the period.

elementLabel: Real Estate and Accumulated Depreciation, Accumulated Depreciation (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The amount of accumulated depreciation for the property as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate and Accumulated Depreciation, Amount of Encumbrances
definition: Amount of lien or mortgage outstanding on real estate investment properties for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate and Accumulated Depreciation, Carrying Amount of Buildings and Improvements
definition: Amount before accumulated depreciation of buildings and improvements for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate. Excludes real estate not held as an investment or interest.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate and Accumulated Depreciation, Carrying Amount of Land
definition: Amount of land for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate. Excludes real estate not held as an investment or interest.

elementLabel: Real Estate and Accumulated Depreciation, Carrying Amount of Land and Buildings and Improvements (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Gross amount at which land and buildings and improvements are carried at the end of the period for each property.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate and Accumulated Depreciation, Initial Cost of Buildings and Improvements
definition: Initial cost of buildings and improvements for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate. Excludes real estate not held as an investment or interest.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate and Accumulated Depreciation, Initial Cost of Land
definition: Initial cost of land for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate. Excludes real estate not held as an investment or interest.

elementLabel: Real Estate and Accumulated Depreciation, Life Used for Depreciation (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The estimated economic life on which depreciation in the latest income statement was computed, typically stated in number of years (such as 5 or 4.5).

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate, Improvements
definition: Amount of increase in real estate investments related to improvements for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: Real Estate Investment Partnership Cost of Sales
definition: Amount of cost of sales related to investments in real estate partnerships and variable interest entities.

elementLabel: Real Estate Investment Partnership Revenue
definition: Amount of revenue recognized from investments in real estate partnerships and variable interest entities.

elementLabel: Real Estate Owned, Amount of Loss at Acquisition
definition: Amount of reduction to fair value of loan related to real estate owned (REO) at time of acquisition.

elementLabel: Real Estate Owned, Valuation Allowance, Provision
definition: Amount of expense recognized in the income statement for a decrease in valuation of real estate owned (REO).

elementLabel: Real Estate Owned, Valuation Allowance, Valuation Increase
definition: Amount of gain recognized in the income statement for an increase in valuation of real estate owned (REO).

elementLabel: Real Estate, Write-down or Reserve, Amount (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The amount of any write-down or reserve provided in the period on a real estate investment.

elementLabel: Receivables, Change in Method of Calculating Impairment, Recorded Investment
definition: Amount of receivables for which the allowance for credit losses had previously been measured under a general allowance for credit losses methodology, and are now identified as troubled debt restructurings.

elementLabel: Reclassification to Wells, Facilities, and Equipment Based on Determination of Proved Reserves (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Previously capitalized costs of the drilling of wells that were reclassified as part of the costs of the enterprise's wells and related equipment and facilities at the time that proved reserves were found.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Rolling after Year Five
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock, Value of Shares Subscribed but Unissued (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Value of a new issue of convertible redeemable preferred stock that has been applied for by investors. The shares have not yet been issued.

elementLabel: Redeemable Preferred Stock, Value Shares Subscribed but Unissued (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Value of a new issue of redeemable preferred stock applied for by investors. The shares have not yet been issued.

elementLabel: Reduction of Short-term Capital Lease Obligations
definition: The cash outflow for a borrowing recorded for a lease meeting the criteria for capitalization (with maturities within one year or the normal operating cycle of the entity, if longer).

elementLabel: Regulatory Assets
definition: The amount for the individual regulatory asset as itemized in a table of regulatory assets as of the end of the period.

elementLabel: Regulatory Assets, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of capitalized costs of regulated entities that are not expected to be recovered through revenue sources.

elementLabel: Regulatory Liabilities
definition: The amount for the individual regulatory liability as itemized in a table of regulatory liabilities as of the end of the period.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Effect on Claims and Benefits Incurred, Net Amount (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The net amount of the provision for the period for claims and benefits incurred on contracts directly written, assumed, and ceded.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Premiums for Insurance Companies, by Product Segment, Amount Assumed from Other Companies (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of premiums assumed from other companies.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Premiums for Insurance Companies, by Product Segment, Amount Ceded to Other Companies (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of premiums ceded to other companies.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Premiums for Insurance Companies, by Product Segment, Gross Amount (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Gross amount of premium revenue.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Premiums for Insurance Companies, by Product Segment, Net Amount (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Net amount of gross premiums, less premiums ceded to other companies, plus premiums assumed from other companies; which represents the net amount of premium revenue on the income statement.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Premiums for Insurance Companies, by Product Segment, Percentage of Amount Assumed to Net (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Percentage of amount of premiums assumed from other companies to net amount of premiums.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverable for Unpaid Claims and Claims Adjustments
definition: Amount after valuation allowance recoverable under reinsurance contracts for claims and claims adjustments.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverables, Allowance
definition: Amount of valuation allowance for reinsurance recoverables. Examples include, but are not limited to, settled and unsettled claims, incurred but not reported losses, loss adjustment expense, premium paid, policy benefits and policy reserves.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverables, Gross
definition: Amount before valuation allowance recoverable under reinsurance contracts. Examples include, but are not limited to, settled and unsettled claims, incurred but not reported losses, loss adjustment expense, premium paid, policy benefits and policy reserves.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverables on Paid and Unpaid Losses
definition: Amount after valuation allowance recoverable under reinsurance contracts, including, but not limited to, settled and unsettled claims, incurred but not reported losses, loss adjustment expense, policy benefits and policy reserves.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverables on Paid Losses
definition: Amount after valuation allowance of reinsurance recoverables on paid losses.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverables on Paid Losses, Allowance
definition: Amount of valuation allowance for reinsurance recoverables on paid losses.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverables on Paid Losses, Gross
definition: Amount before valuation allowance of reinsurance recoverables on paid losses.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverables on Unpaid Losses
definition: Amount after valuation allowance of reinsurance recoverables for losses reported to the ceding insurer but not yet paid, amounts expected of incurred losses and settlement expenses, which have not yet been reported to the ceding insurer.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverables on Unpaid Losses, Allowance
definition: Amount of valuation allowance for reinsurance recoverables for losses reported to the ceding insurer but not yet paid, and for amounts expected based upon statistical projections and other measures of incurred losses and loss settlement expenses which have not yet been reported to the ceding insurer.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverables on Unpaid Losses, Gross
definition: Amount before valuation allowance of reinsurance recoverables for losses reported to the ceding insurer but not yet paid, and for amounts expected based upon statistical projections and other measures of incurred losses and loss settlement expenses which have not yet been reported to the ceding insurer.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Recoverables, Percentage of Total (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Percentage of total reinsurance recoverables.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Retention Policy, Excess Retention, Amount Reinsured
definition: Amount of risk reinsured in excess of stated retention per company policy.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Retention Policy, Excess Retention, Percentage
definition: Percentage of risk reinsured in excess of stated retention per entity policy.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Retention Policy, Reinsured Risk, Percentage
definition: Percentage of risk reinsured on insurance products per entity policy.

elementLabel: Related Party Deposit Liabilities
definition: Amount of deposits held by the entity for a related party (entity, shareholder, employee).

elementLabel: Related Party Tax Expense, Due from Affiliates, Current
definition: The amount of any current tax-related balances due from affiliates as of the date of each statement of financial position presented.

elementLabel: Related Party Tax Expense, Due from Affiliates, Deferred
definition: The amount of any deferred tax-related balances due from affiliates as of the date of each statement of financial position presented.

elementLabel: Related Party Tax Expense, Due to Affiliates, Current
definition: The amount of any current tax-related balances due to affiliates as of the date of each statement of financial position presented.

elementLabel: Related Party Tax Expense, Due to Affiliates, Deferred
definition: The amount of any deferred tax-related balances due to affiliates as of the date of each statement of financial position presented.

elementLabel: Related Party Transaction, Expenses from Transactions with Related Party
definition: Expenses recognized resulting from transactions (excluding transactions that are eliminated in consolidated or combined financial statements) with related party.

elementLabel: Related Party Transaction, Purchases from Related Party
definition: Purchases during the period (excluding transactions that are eliminated in consolidated or combined financial statements) with related party.

elementLabel: Related Party Transaction, Rate
definition: Identify the stated interest rate per the agreement, for example, leasing and debt arrangements between related parties.

elementLabel: Related Party Transaction, Revenues from Transactions with Related Party (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Revenues, net of returns and allowances, realized from sales and other transactions (excluding transactions that are eliminated in consolidated or combined financial statements) with related party during the period.

elementLabel: Related Party Transaction, Selling, General and Administrative Expenses from Transactions with Related Party
definition: Amount of selling, general and administrative expenses resulting from transactions, excluding transactions that are eliminated in consolidated or combined financial statements, with related party.

elementLabel: Repayments of Annuities and Investment Certificates
definition: The cash outflow for an insurance contract under which the policy holder make a lump sum payment or a series of payments in exchange for periodic payments to the policyholder beginning immediately or at some future date.

elementLabel: Repayments of Construction Loans Payable
definition: The cash outflow from repayment of borrowings to finance the cost of construction.

elementLabel: Repayments of Federal Home Loan Bank Borrowings
definition: The cash outflow for the payment of loan drawn from Federal Home Loan.

elementLabel: Repayments of Financial Services Obligations
definition: The cash used to settle the borrowing issued by the entity involved in financial services operations.

elementLabel: Repayments of Notes Payable
definition: The cash outflow for a borrowing supported by a written promise to pay an obligation.

elementLabel: Repayments of Related Party Debt
definition: The cash outflow for the payment of a long-term borrowing made from a related party where one party can exercise control or significant influence over another party; including affiliates, owners or officers and their immediate families, pension trusts, and so forth. Alternate caption: Payments for Advances from Affiliates.

elementLabel: Reporting Unit, Amount of Fair Value in Excess of Carrying Amount
definition: Amount of fair value of reporting unit in excess of carrying amount.

elementLabel: Reporting Unit, Percentage of Fair Value in Excess of Carrying Amount
definition: Percentage of fair value of reporting unit in excess of carrying amount.

elementLabel: Repurchase Agreement Counterparty, Amount at Risk
definition: The amount at risk under repurchase agreements is defined as the excess of carrying amount (or market value, if higher than the carrying amount or if there is no carrying amount) of the securities or other assets sold under agreement to repurchase, including accrued interest plus any cash or other assets on deposit to secure the repurchase obligation, over the amount of the repurchase liability (adjusted for accrued interest).

elementLabel: Repurchase Agreement Counterparty, Weighted Average Maturity of Agreements (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: This equals the weighted average maturity (weighted by amount of the agreement) of all repurchase agreements with this counterparty.

elementLabel: Required Net Capital under Commodity Exchange Act
definition: Amount of net capital required to be maintained under the Commodity Futures Trading Commission's (CFTC) minimum financial requirements, pursuant to the Commodity Exchange Act, less the market value of certain commodity options.

elementLabel: Resale Agreement Counterparty, Amount at Risk
definition: The amount at risk under resale agreements (reverse repurchase agreements) is defined as the excess of the carrying amount of the resale agreements over the market value of assets delivered pursuant to the agreements by the counterparty to the registrant (or to a third party agent that has affirmatively agreed to act on behalf of the registrant) and not returned to the counterparty, except in exchange for their approximate market value in a separate transaction.

elementLabel: Resale Agreement Counterparty, Weighted Average Maturity of Agreements (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: This equals the weighted average maturity (weighted by amount of the agreement) of all resale agreements with this counterparty.

elementLabel: Reserves, Proportional Interest of Net Proved Reserve Quantities of Proportionately Consolidated Investees (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The proportional interest of net proved oil reserve quantities of proportionately consolidated investees.

elementLabel: Reserves, Proportional Interest of Net Proved Reserve Quantities of Proportionately Consolidated Investees
definition: Proportional interest of net proved oil reserve quantities of consolidated investees.

elementLabel: Reserves, Share of Equity Method Investee's Net Proved Oil and Gas Reserves
definition: The proportional interest of net proved oil reserve quantities of equity investees.

elementLabel: Restricted Investments, at Fair Value
definition: The aggregate value of all restricted investments.

elementLabel: Restricted Investments Exempt from Registration, at Fair Value
definition: The aggregate value of all restricted investments which are exempt from registration pursuant to Rule 144A.

elementLabel: Restricted Investments Exempt from Registration, Percent of Net Assets
definition: The percent of net assets of the aggregate value of all restricted investments exempt from registration pursuant to Rule 144A.

elementLabel: Restricted Investments Not Exempt from Registration, at Fair Value
definition: The aggregate value of all restricted investments which are not exempt from registration pursuant to Rule 144A.

elementLabel: Restricted Investments Not Exempt from Registration, Percent of Net Assets
definition: The percent of net assets of the aggregate value of all restricted investments not exempt from registration pursuant to Rule 144A.

elementLabel: Restricted Investments, Percent of Net Assets
definition: The percent of net assets of the aggregate value of all restricted investments.

elementLabel: Restructuring and Related Cost, Cost Incurred to Date
definition: Amount of costs incurred to date for the specified restructuring cost.

elementLabel: Restructuring and Related Cost, Expected Cost
definition: Amount expected to be recognized in earnings for the specified restructuring cost.

elementLabel: Restructuring and Related Cost, Expected Cost Remaining (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of expected cost remaining for the specified type of restructuring cost.

elementLabel: Restructuring and Related Cost, Expected Cost Remaining
definition: Amount of expected cost remaining for the specified restructuring cost.

elementLabel: Restructuring and Related Cost, Accelerated Depreciation
definition: Amount of accelerated depreciation charged against earnings associated with exit from or disposal of business activities or restructuring plan.

elementLabel: Restructuring Reserve, Settled without Cash
definition: Amount of consideration other than cash used to fully or partially settle an accrued restructuring cost.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Accretion of Asset Retirement Obligations
definition: Accretion expense of asset retirement obligations related to oil and gas producing activities.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Depreciation, Depletion and Amortization, and Valuation Provisions
definition: Depreciation, depletion and amortization, and valuation provisions (impairments) related to oil and gas producing activities.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Dry Hole Costs
definition: Dry hole costs from oil and gas producing activities.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Expense, Other
definition: Other costs for oil and gas producing activities.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Exploration Expense
definition: Exploration costs from oil and gas producing activities.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, General and Administrative Related to Oil and Gas Producing Activities
definition: General and administrative costs from oil & gas producing activities.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Impairment of Oil and Gas Properties
definition: Costs related to the impairment of oil and gas properties.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Production or Lifting Costs
definition: Production (lifting) costs from oil and gas producing activities, including but not limited to lease operating expense, production and ad valorem taxes, and transportation expense.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Revenue from Oil and Gas Producing Activities
definition: Total revenues from oil and gas producing activities.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Revenue, Other
definition: Other revenues from oil and gas producing activities.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Sales or Transfers to Entity's Other Operations
definition: Sales or transfers to the enterprises other operations from oil and gas producing activities.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Sales Revenue to Unaffiliated Enterprises
definition: Sales revenue to unaffiliated enterprises from oil and gas producing activities.

elementLabel: Results of Operations, Transportation Costs
definition: Includes the cost to prepare and move liquid hydrocarbons and natural gas to their points of sale.

elementLabel: Retail Land Sales, Maturity of Accounts Receivable, Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of accounts receivable from retail land sales to be collected in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retail Land Sales, Maturity of Accounts Receivable, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of accounts receivable from retail land sales to be collected in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retail Land Sales, Maturity of Accounts Receivable, Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of accounts receivable from retail land sales to be collected in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retail Land Sales, Maturity of Accounts Receivable, Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of accounts receivable from retail land sales to be collected in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retail Land Sales, Maturity of Accounts Receivable, Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of accounts receivable from retail land sales to be collected in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retail Land Sales, Maturity of Accounts Receivable, Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of accounts receivable from retail land sales to be collected in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retained Patronage Allocations
definition: Amount of patronage earnings retained within the agricultural cooperative.

elementLabel: Retention Payable, Due after Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amounts owed to vendors and subcontractors that have been withheld because of retainage provisions in a contract to be paid after the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retention Payable, Due after Rolling Year Five
definition: Amounts owed to vendors and subcontractors that have been withheld because of retainage provisions in a contract to be paid after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retention Payable, Due in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amounts owed to vendors and subcontractors that have been withheld because of retainage provisions in a contract to be paid in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retention Payable, Due in Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amounts owed to vendors and subcontractors that have been withheld because of retainage provisions in a contract to be paid in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year.
