Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retention Payable, Due in Rolling Year Five
definition: Amounts owed to vendors and subcontractors that have been withheld because of retainage provisions in a contract to be paid in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retention Payable, Due in Rolling Year Four
definition: Amounts owed to vendors and subcontractors that have been withheld because of retainage provisions in a contract to be paid in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retention Payable, Due in Rolling Year Three
definition: Amounts owed to vendors and subcontractors that have been withheld because of retainage provisions in a contract to be paid in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Retention Payable, Due in Rolling Year Two
definition: Amounts owed to vendors and subcontractors that have been withheld because of retainage provisions in a contract to be paid in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Revolving Loan Facility to Finance Leveraged Buyout (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Borrowings from a revolving loan facility used to finance leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Risk Weighted Assets
definition: Amount of risk-weighted assets as calculated in accordance with U.S. Federal regulatory capital standards.

elementLabel: Salaries, Wages and Officers' Compensation
definition: Expenditures for salaries for officers and non-officers. Does not include allocated share-based compensation, pension and post-retirement benefit expense or other labor-related non-salary expense. For commercial and industrial companies, excludes any direct and overhead labor that is included in cost of goods sold.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Accumulated Depreciation
definition: The accumulated depreciation and amortization related to the asset(s) sold in connection with the property sold to another party and leased back to the seller.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Amount Due under Financing Arrangement
definition: The liability due as of the balance sheet date for leasebacks accounted for using the deposit method.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Annual Rental Payments
definition: The yearly payments due under the lease entered into in connection with the transaction involving the sale of property to another party and the lease of the property back to the seller.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Cumulative Gain Recognized (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Represents the cumulative amount of the gain that has been recognized (out of the total deferred gain) as income or a reduction in rent expense through the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Cumulative Gain Recognized
definition: Cumulative amount of gain recognized (out of deferred gain) as income or a reduction in rent expense.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Current Period Gain Recognized
definition: The portion of the deferred gain that was recognized in the current period.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Deferred Gain, Gross
definition: The amount of the gain recorded in connection with the transaction involving the sale of property to another party and the lease of the property back to the seller to be recognized in future periods.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Deferred Gain, Net
definition: The portion of the gain that will be recorded as income or a reduction in rent expense in future periods less amounts recognized in the current period.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Gross Proceeds (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: The gross proceeds received from the asset(s) sold in connection with the transaction involving the sale of property to another party and the lease back to the seller.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Gross Proceeds, Financing Activities
definition: Amount of cash inflow before closing and deferred financing costs received by a seller-lessee in a sale-leaseback recognized in financing activities.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Gross Proceeds, Investing Activities
definition: Amount of cash inflow before closing and deferred financing costs received by a seller-lessee in a sale-leaseback recognized in investing activities.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Historical Cost
definition: The historical cost of the asset(s) sold in connection with the sale of the property to another party and the lease of the property back to the seller.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Imputed Interest Rate
definition: The financing cost related to leases that have been recorded under the deposit method, as a financing or as a capital leases in connection with the transaction involving the sale of property to another party and the lease of the property back to the seller.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Monthly Rental Payments
definition: The amount of the monthly rental payments due under the lease entered into in connection with the transactions involving the sale of property to another party and the lease of the property back to the seller.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Net Book Value
definition: The net book value of the asset(s) sold in connection with the sale of the property to another party and lease back to the seller.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Net Proceeds (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: The gross proceeds received from the asset(s) sold in connection with the transaction involving the sale of property to another party and the lease of the property back to the seller less the costs incurred in connection with the transaction, such as closing and deferred financing costs.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Net Proceeds, Financing Activities
definition: Amount of cash inflow after closing and deferred financing costs received by a seller-lessee in a sale-leaseback recognized in financing activities.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Net Proceeds, Investing Activities
definition: Amount of cash inflow after closing and deferred financing costs received by a seller-lessee in a sale-leaseback recognized in investing activities.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Other Payments Required
definition: Other amounts the seller-lessee is required to pay under the terms of the transaction involving the sale of property to another party and lease of the property back to the seller, including reimbursements for such items, as utilities, taxes, insurance and common area maintenance.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Quarterly Rental Payments
definition: The amount of the quarterly rental payments due under the lease entered into in connection with the transactions involving the sale of property to another party and the lease of the property back to the seller.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Rent Expense
definition: The amount of the current period expense recorded for use of the property in connection with the transaction involving the sale of property to another party and the lease of the property back to the seller.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Transaction Costs, Financing Activities
definition: Amount of cash outflow for transaction costs in a sale-leaseback recognized in financing activities. For example, but not limited to, closing and deferred financing costs.

elementLabel: Sale Leaseback Transaction, Transaction Costs, Investing Activities
definition: Amount of cash outflow for transaction costs in a sale-leaseback recognized in investing activities. For example, but not limited to, closing and deferred financing costs.

elementLabel: Sale of Trust Assets to Pay Expenses
definition: Amount of sale of trust assets (includes, but is not limited to, gold and silver) to pay trust expenses.

elementLabel: Sales of Equity to Finance Leveraged Buyout (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Amount of proceeds received from sale of common stock and other forms of equity used to finance a leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Schedule of Fair Value of Separate Accounts by Major Category of Investment, Fair Value
definition: Fair value amount of the specified investment category of assets maintained in separate accounts as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Gross Claim Liability
definition: This element represents the gross claim liability for financial guarantee insurance contracts presented in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Insured Contractual Payments Outstanding
definition: This element represents the amount of insured contractual payments outstanding on the underlying insured obligations for financial guarantee insurance contracts presented in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Insured Contractual Payments Outstanding, Interest
definition: This element represents the amount of insured contractual payments outstanding attributable to interest accrued on the underlying insured obligations for financial guarantee insurance contracts presented in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Insured Contractual Payments Outstanding, Principal
definition: This element represents the amount of insured contractual payments outstanding attributable to the principal of the underlying insured obligations for financial guarantee insurance contracts presented in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Net Claim Liability
definition: This element represents the net claim liability related to financial guarantee insurance contracts presented in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Number of Contracts Issued and Outstanding
definition: This element represents the number of issued and outstanding contracts for each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Reductions of Gross Claim Liability
definition: This element represents the aggregate reductions related to financial guarantee insurance contracts presented in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Reductions of Gross Claim Liability, Gross Potential Recoveries
definition: This element represents the gross potential recoveries against the gross claim liability for financial guarantee insurance contracts presented in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Reductions of Gross Claim Liability, Net Discount
definition: This element represents the net discount consisting of the difference between the discount related to the claim liability for and potential recoveries thereof related to financial guarantee insurance contracts presented in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Remaining Weighted Average Contract Period (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: This element represents the remaining weighted average contract period of financial guarantee insurance contracts for each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Statement of Financial Position, Claim Liability
definition: This element represents the claim liability, reported on or included in the statement of financial position, related to financial guarantee insurance contracts and presented in the schedule of insured financial obligations with credit deterioration in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Statement of Financial Position, Reinsurance Recoverable
definition: This element represents the amount of reinsurance recoverable, reported on or included in the statement of financial position, related to financial guarantee insurance contracts and presented in the schedule of insured financial obligations with credit deterioration in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: Schedule of Insured Financial Obligations with Credit Deterioration, Statement of Financial Position, Unearned Premium Revenue
definition: This element represents the amount of unearned premium revenue, reported on or included in the statement of financial position, related to financial guarantee insurance contracts and presented in the schedule of insured financial obligations with credit deterioration in the context of each surveillance grouping or category used by management to monitor and track potential deterioration in the credit worthiness of the insured party's ability to meet its financial obligations related to the contracts underlying financial guarantee insurance contracts the entity has issued.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate Accumulated Depreciation, Depreciation Expense
definition: Amount of depreciation expense of real estate investments for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate Investment Property, Net
definition: Amount after accumulated depreciation of real estate held for investment for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate, Number of Units
definition: Number of units of real estate held for investment for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate, Write-down or Reserve, Amount
definition: Amount of write-down or reserve recognized in the income statement on real estate investments for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Amount Offset Against Collateral
definition: Amount, after effects of master netting arrangements, of securities borrowed from entities in exchange for collateral offset against an obligation to return collateral under a master netting arrangement. Includes assets not subject to a master netting arrangement and not elected to be offset.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Collateral, Obligation to Return Cash
definition: Amount of obligation to return cash collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against securities borrowed.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Collateral, Obligation to Return Securities
definition: Amount of obligation to return securities collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against securities borrowed.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Fair Value of Collateral
definition: Fair value of the securities received as collateral against securities borrowed.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Gross
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of securities borrowed from entities in exchange for collateral. Includes assets elected not to be offset. Excludes assets not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Gross Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of securities borrowed from entities in exchange for collateral. Includes assets not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Liability
definition: Amount of liability associated with securities borrowed from entities in exchange for collateral.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Not Offset, Policy Election Deduction
definition: Amount of securities borrowed from entities in exchange for collateral, elected not to be offset, deducted from securities borrowed.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount of securities borrowed from entities in exchange for collateral, not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement Deduction
definition: Amount of securities borrowed from entities in exchange for collateral, not subject to a master netting arrangement, deducted from securities borrowed.

elementLabel: Securities Borrowed, Offset Against Collateral, Net of Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement, Policy Election
definition: Amount, after effects of master netting arrangements, deduction of assets not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset, of securities borrowed from entities in exchange for collateral, offset against an obligation to return collateral under a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities for Reverse Repurchase Agreements
definition: The carrying value of securities purchased to be resold in reverse repurchase transactions as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Amount Offset Against Collateral
definition: Amount, after effects of master netting arrangements, of securities loaned to entities in exchange for collateral offset against a right to receive collateral. Includes liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement and not elected to be offset.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Asset
definition: Amount of asset associated with securities loaned to entities in exchange for collateral.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Collateral, Right to Reclaim Cash
definition: Amount of right to receive cash collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against securities loaned.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Collateral, Right to Reclaim Securities
definition: Amount of right to receive securities collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against securities loaned.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Fair Value of Collateral
definition: Fair value of the securities pledged as collateral against securities loaned.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Gross
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of securities loaned to entities in exchange for collateral. Includes liabilities elected not to be offset. Excludes liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Gross Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of securities loaned to entities in exchange for collateral. Includes liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Not Offset, Policy Election Deduction
definition: Amount of securities loaned to entities in exchange for collateral, elected not to be offset, deducted from securities loaned.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount of securities loaned to entities in exchange for collateral, not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement Deduction
definition: Amount of securities loaned to entities in exchange for collateral, not subject to a master netting arrangement, deducted from securities loaned.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Offset Against Collateral, Net of Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement, Policy Election
definition: Amount, after effects of master netting arrangements, deduction of liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset, of securities loaned to entities in exchange for collateral, offset against a right to receive collateral.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell
definition: Amount, after the effects of master netting arrangements, of funds outstanding loaned in the form of a security resale agreement between the entity and another party for the purchase and resale of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price. Includes purchases of participations in pools of securities that are subject to a resale agreement, assets not subject to a master netting arrangement and not elected to be offset.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Collateral, Obligation to Return Cash
definition: Amount of obligation to return cash collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against securities purchased under agreement to resell.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Collateral, Obligation to Return Securities
definition: Amount of obligation to return securities collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against securities purchased under agreement to resell.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Fair Value of Collateral
definition: Fair value of securities received as collateral against securities purchased under agreement to resell.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Gross
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of funds outstanding loaned in the form of a security resale agreement between the entity and another party for the purchase and resale of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price. Includes assets elected not to be offset. Excludes assets not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Gross Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of funds outstanding loaned in the form of a security resale agreement between the entity and another party for the purchase and resale of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price. Includes assets not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Liability
definition: Amount of liability associated with funds outstanding loaned in the form of a security resale agreement between the entity and another party for the purchase and resale of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Not Offset, Policy Election Deduction
definition: Amount of funds outstanding loaned in the form of a security resale agreement between the entity and another party for the purchase and resale of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price, elected not to be offset, deducted from securities purchased under agreements to resell.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount of funds outstanding loaned in the form of a security resale agreement between the entity and another party for the purchase and resale of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price, not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement Deduction
definition: Amount of funds outstanding loaned in the form of a security resale agreement between the entity and another party for the purchase and resale of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price, not subject to a master netting arrangement, deducted from securities purchased under agreements to resell.

elementLabel: Securities Purchased under Agreements to Resell, Offset Against Collateral, Net of Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement, Policy Election
definition: Amount, after effects of master netting arrangements, deduction of assets not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset, of funds outstanding loaned in the form of a security resale agreement between the entity and another party for the purchase and resale of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price, offset against an obligation to return collateral.

elementLabel: Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Asset
definition: Amount of asset associated with funds outstanding borrowed in the form of a security repurchase agreement between the entity and another party for the sale and repurchase of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price.

elementLabel: Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Collateral, Right to Reclaim Cash
definition: Amount of right to receive cash collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against securities sold under agreement to repurchase.

elementLabel: Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Collateral, Right to Reclaim Securities
definition: Amount of right to receive securities collateral under master netting arrangements that have not been offset against securities sold under agreement to repurchase.

elementLabel: Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Fair Value of Collateral
definition: Fair value of securities pledged as collateral against securities sold under agreement to repurchase.

elementLabel: Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Gross
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of funds outstanding borrowed in the form of a security repurchase agreement between the entity and another party for the sale and repurchase of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price. Includes liabilities elected not to be offset. Excludes liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Gross Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of funds outstanding borrowed in the form of a security repurchase agreement between the entity and another party for the sale and repurchase of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price. Includes liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset.

elementLabel: Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount of funds outstanding borrowed in the form of a security repurchase agreement between the entity and another party for the sale and repurchase of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price, not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement Deduction
definition: Amount of funds outstanding borrowed in the form of a security repurchase agreement between the entity and another party for the sale and repurchase of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price, not subject to a master netting arrangement, deducted from securities sold under agreements to repurchase.

elementLabel: Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Offset Against Collateral, Net of Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement, Policy Election
definition: Amount, after effects of master netting arrangements, deduction of liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement and elected not to be offset, of funds outstanding borrowed in the form of a security repurchase agreement between the entity and another party for the sale and repurchase of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price, offset against a right to receive collateral.

elementLabel: Securities Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Not Offset, Policy Election Deduction
definition: Amount of funds outstanding borrowed in the form of a security repurchase agreement between the entity and another party for the sale and repurchase of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price, elected not to be offset, deducted from securities sold under agreements to repurchase.

elementLabel: Assets that Continue to be Recognized, Securitized or Asset-backed Financing Arrangement Assets and any Other Financial Assets Managed Together, Average Balance During Period (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: This is the average principal amount (during the year) of the securitized and unsecuritized financial assets.

elementLabel: Assets that Continue to be Recognized, Securitized or Asset-backed Financing Arrangement Assets and any Other Financial Assets Managed Together, Delinquent Amount at End of Period
definition: This is the amount of the financial instruments that are considered delinquent (past due) at the end of the period.

elementLabel: Assets that Continue to be Recognized, Securitized or Asset-backed Financing Arrangement Assets and any Other Financial Assets Managed Together, Net Credit Losses During Period (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Net credit losses are charge-offs and are based on total loans outstanding during the period.

elementLabel: Continuing Involvement with Continued to be Recognized Transferred Financial Assets, Amount Outstanding
definition: Amount of transferred financial assets in which the transferor has continuing involvement with the assets underlying the transaction that continue to be recognized in the statement of financial position. Includes, but is not limited to, servicing, recourse, and restrictions on transferor's interests in transferred financial assets.

elementLabel: Security Owned and Pledged as Collateral, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of financial instrument held by the entity for its own account (proprietary securities) for trading or investment purposes that are carried at fair value and pledged to counterparties as collateral for financing transactions.

elementLabel: Security Owned and Sold, Not yet Purchased Fair Value, Security Owned
definition: Fair value of financial instruments held by a broker-dealer for their own account (proprietary securities) for trading or investment purposes determined by management based upon quoted prices of a financial instrument with similar characteristics or on a valuation technique or model.

elementLabel: Security Owned and Sold, Not yet Purchased Fair Value, Security Sold, Not yet Purchased
definition: Fair value of financial instruments sold short by a broker-dealer for their own account (proprietary securities) for trading or investment purposes determined by management based upon quoted prices of a financial instrument with similar characteristics or on a valuation technique or model.

elementLabel: Security Owned Not Readily Marketable, Fair Value
definition: Value of the not readily marketable security or category which has been determined by management based upon fair value methods, including pricing of similar securities and valuation techniques and is included in the schedule of financial condition or the balance sheet.

elementLabel: Security Owned Not Readily Marketable, Quoted Price
definition: Amount of not readily marketable security or investment measured by quoted price.

elementLabel: Selling, General and Administrative Expense
definition: The aggregate total costs related to selling a firm's product and services, as well as all other general and administrative expenses. Direct selling expenses (for example, credit, warranty, and advertising) are expenses that can be directly linked to the sale of specific products. Indirect selling expenses are expenses that cannot be directly linked to the sale of specific products, for example telephone expenses, Internet, and postal charges. General and administrative expenses include salaries of non-sales personnel, rent, utilities, communication, etc.

elementLabel: Sensitivity Analysis of Fair Value, Transferor's Interests in Transferred Financial Assets, Impact of Other than 10 or 20 Percent Adverse Change in Discount Rate, Percent
definition: A specified percentage variance in the discount rate assumption in the determination of fair value of transferor's interests in transferred financial assets (including any servicing assets or servicing liabilities) as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Sensitivity Analysis of Fair Value, Transferor's Interests in Transferred Financial Assets, Impact of Other than 10 or 20 Percent Adverse Change in Other Assumption, Percent
definition: A specified percentage variance in a specified key assumption in the determination of fair value of transferor's interests in transferred financial assets (including any servicing assets or servicing liabilities).

elementLabel: Sensitivity Analysis of Fair Value, Transferor's Interests in Transferred Financial Assets, Impact of Other than 10 or 20 Percent Adverse Change in Prepayment Speed, Percent
definition: A specified percentage variance in the prepayment speed assumption in the determination of fair value of transferor's interests in transferred financial assets (including any servicing assets or servicing liabilities).

elementLabel: Sensitivity Analysis of Fair Value, Transferor's Interests in Transferred Financial Assets, Impact Other than 10 or 20 Percent Adverse Change in Expected Credit Loss, Percent
definition: A specified percentage variance in the expected credit losses assumption, including static pool losses, in the determination of fair value of transferor's interests in transferred financial assets (including any servicing assets or servicing liabilities).

elementLabel: Servicing Asset
definition: Aggregate amount of servicing assets that are subsequently measured at fair value and servicing assets that are subsequently measured using the amortization method.

elementLabel: Servicing Asset at Amortized Cost, Other than Temporary Impairments
definition: Amount of other-than-temporary impairment (OTTI) applied to contract to service financial assets under which the benefits of servicing are expected to more than adequately compensate the servicer.

elementLabel: Servicing Asset at Amortized Cost, Additions
definition: Amount of additions from purchases, assumption or transfer to contract to service financial assets under which the benefits of servicing are expected to more than adequately compensate the servicer.

elementLabel: Servicing Asset at Amortized Value, Amortization (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Decreases in the value of servicing assets due to the periodic amortization in proportion to and over the period of estimated net servicing income.

elementLabel: Servicing Asset at Amortized Cost, Amortization
definition: Amount of amortization of contract to service financial assets under which the benefits of servicing are expected to more than adequately compensate the servicer.

elementLabel: Servicing Asset at Amortized Cost, Disposals
definition: Amount conveyed to unrelated parties of contract to contract to service financial assets under which the benefits of servicing are expected to more than adequately compensate the servicer.

elementLabel: Servicing Asset at Amortized Cost, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of contract to service financial assets under which the benefits of servicing are expected to more than adequately compensate the servicer.

elementLabel: Servicing Asset at Amortized Value, Other than Temporary Impairments (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Adjustment made to the carrying value of servicing assets measured using the amortization method related to an other-than-temporary impairment, for example, due to a decrease in future servicing income or an increase in servicing costs.

elementLabel: Servicing Asset at Fair Value, Additions
definition: The value of new servicing assets, subsequently measured at fair value, acquired or created during the current period through purchases or from transfers of financial assets.

elementLabel: Servicing Asset at Fair Value, Disposals
definition: Decrease in servicing assets subsequently measured at fair value resulting from conveyance of servicing rights to unrelated parties.

elementLabel: Servicing Fees
definition: Amount of fees from providing shareholder services, including, but not limited to, answering shareholder inquiries and providing shareholders with information about their investments.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability
definition: Aggregate amount of servicing liabilities that are subsequently measured at fair value and servicing liabilities that are subsequently measured using the amortization method.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Amortized Cost, Amortization
definition: Amount of amortization of contract to service financial assets under which estimated future revenue from contractually specified servicing fees, late charges, and other ancillary revenues are not expected to adequately compensate the servicer for performing the servicing.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Amortized Cost, Additions
definition: Amount of additions from purchases, assumption or transfer to contract to service financial assets under which estimated future revenues from contractually specified servicing fees, late charges, and other ancillary revenue are not expected to adequately compensate the servicer for performing the servicing.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Amortized Value, Amortization (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Decreases in the value of a servicing liability due to amortization, the periodic mark down in value in proportion to and over the period of estimated net servicing income.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Amortized Cost, Balance
definition: Amortized amount of contract to service financial assets under which estimated future revenues from contractually specified servicing fees, late charges, and other ancillary revenue are not expected to adequately compensate the servicer for performing the servicing.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Amortized Cost, Disposals
definition: Amount conveyed to unrelated parties of contract to service financial assets under which estimated future revenue from contractually specified servicing fees, late charges, and other ancillary revenues are not expected to adequately compensate the servicer for performing the servicing.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Amortized Value, Fair Value (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Fair value of the servicing liability that has been amortized as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Amortized Cost, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of the servicing liability that has been amortized.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Amortized Value, Increase in Obligation (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: Adjustment made to carrying value of a servicing liability related to an increase in the fair value of the liability as are result of, for example: a significant change in the amount and timing of actual or expected future cash flows relative to the cash flows previously projected.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Amortized Value, Valuation Allowance (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The amount of valuation allowance applied to adjust the carrying value of a servicing liability.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Fair Value, Additions
definition: The value of new servicing liabilities, that are subsequently measured at fair value, acquired or created during the current period through assumptions of servicing obligations and servicing obligations that result from transfers of financial assets.

elementLabel: Servicing Liability at Fair Value, Disposals
definition: Decreases in fair value of servicing liabilities resulting from conveyance of servicing rights to unrelated parties.

elementLabel: Settlement of Asset Retirement Obligations Through Noncash Payments, Amount
definition: Amount of asset retirement obligations settled through noncash transactions. An asset retirement obligation is a legal obligation associated with the disposal or retirement from service of a tangible long-lived asset.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award Accelerated Compensation Cost
definition: Additional share-based compensation cost recognized as a result of an occurrence of an event that accelerates its recognition.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Accelerated Vesting, Number
definition: Number of shares for which recognition of compensation cost was accelerated.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Award Vesting Rights, Percentage
definition: Percentage of vesting of share-based compensation awards.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Equity Instruments Other than Options, Aggregate Intrinsic Value, Nonvested
definition: Intrinsic value of equity-based compensation awards not vested. Excludes stock and unit options.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Equity Instruments Other than Options, Aggregate Intrinsic Value, Outstanding
definition: Intrinsic value of equity-based compensation awards outstanding. Excludes stock and unit options.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Equity Instruments Other than Options, Aggregate Intrinsic Value, Vested
definition: Intrinsic value of equity-based compensation awards vested. Excludes stock and unit options.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Equity Instruments Other than Options, Forfeited in Period
definition: The number of equity-based payment instruments, excluding stock (or unit) options, that were forfeited during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Equity Instruments Other than Options, Forfeitures, Weighted Average Grant Date Fair Value
definition: Weighted average fair value as of the grant date of equity-based award plans other than stock (unit) option plans that were not exercised or put into effect as a result of the occurrence of a terminating event.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Equity Instruments Other than Options, Share-based Liabilities Paid
definition: Amount of cash paid related to share-based compensation liabilities.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Equity Instruments Other than Options, Vested in Period
definition: The number of equity-based payment instruments, excluding stock (or unit) options, that vested during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Fair Value Assumptions, Discount for Postvesting Restrictions
definition: Restrictions on equity-based instruments during the vesting period, such as the inability to transfer unvested awards, are not taken into account in estimating the fair value of the award. However, restrictions that remain in effect after an award is vested, such as the inability to transfer or hedge vested options or a prohibition on the sale of outstanding vested shares (or other type of equity) for a period of time, affect the estimate of an award's fair value.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Fair Value Assumptions, Exercise Price
definition: Agreed-upon price for the exchange of the underlying asset relating to the share-based payment award.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Fair Value Assumptions, Expected Volatility Rate
definition: The estimated measure of the percentage by which a share price is expected to fluctuate during a period. Volatility also may be defined as a probability-weighted measure of the dispersion of returns about the mean. The volatility of a share price is the standard deviation of the continuously compounded rates of return on the share over a specified period. That is the same as the standard deviation of the differences in the natural logarithms of the stock prices plus dividends, if any, over the period.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Fair Value Assumptions, Weighted Average Volatility Rate
definition: Weighted average expected volatility rate of share-based compensation awards.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Non-Option Equity Instruments, Exercised
definition: Number of non-option equity instruments exercised by participants.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Non-Option Equity Instruments, Expirations
definition: Number of shares under non-option equity instrument agreements for which rights to exercise lapsed.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Non-Option Equity Instruments, Forfeitures
definition: Number of shares under non-option equity instrument agreements that were cancelled as a result of occurrence of a terminating event.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Non-Option Equity Instruments, Forfeitures and Expirations
definition: Number of shares under non-option equity instrument agreements that were either cancelled or expired.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Non-Option Equity Instruments, Granted
definition: Net number of non-option equity instruments granted to participants.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Non-Option Equity Instruments, Outstanding, Number
definition: Number of equity instruments other than options outstanding, including both vested and non-vested instruments.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Number of Additional Shares Authorized
definition: Number of additional shares authorized for issuance under an established share-based compensation plan.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Exercises in Period (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The decrease in the number of reserved shares that could potentially be issued attributable to the exercise or conversion during the reporting period of previously issued stock options under the option plan.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Expirations in Period
definition: Number of options or other stock instruments for which the right to exercise has lapsed under the terms of the plan agreements.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Forfeitures and Expirations in Period
definition: For presentations that combine terminations, the number of shares under options that were cancelled during the reporting period as a result of occurrence of a terminating event specified in contractual agreements pertaining to the stock option plan or that expired.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Forfeitures and Expirations in Period, Weighted Average Intrinsic Value
definition: The combined weighted average of the accumulated differences between the fair values on underlying shares and exercises prices to acquire such shares as of the grant date on options that were either forfeited or lapsed.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Forfeitures in Period
definition: The number of shares under options that were cancelled during the reporting period as a result of occurrence of a terminating event specified in contractual agreements pertaining to the stock option plan.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Nonvested, Number of Shares
definition: Number of non-vested options outstanding.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Nonvested Options Forfeited, Number of Shares
definition: Number of non-vested options forfeited.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Nonvested Options Forfeited, Weighted Average Grant Date Fair Value
definition: Weighted average grant-date fair value of non-vested options forfeited.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Nonvested, Weighted Average Grant Date Fair Value
definition: Weighted average grant-date fair value of non-vested options outstanding.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Other Share Increase (Decrease) in Period, Weighted Average Exercise Price (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: The weighted average price at which grantees could acquire or could have acquired the underlying shares with respect to any other type of change in shares reserved for issuance under the stock option plan during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Vested in Period, Fair Value (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Fair value of options vested. Excludes equity instruments other than options, for example, but not limited to, share units, stock appreciation rights, restricted stock.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Vested in Period, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of options vested. Excludes equity instruments other than options, for example, but not limited to, share units, stock appreciation rights, restricted stock.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Vested, Number of Shares
definition: Number of options vested.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Vested, Weighted Average Grant Date Fair Value
definition: Weighted average grant-date fair value of options vested.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Percentage of Outstanding Stock Maximum
definition: Maximum number of shares that may be issued in accordance with the plan as a proportion of outstanding capital stock.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Purchase Price of Common Stock, Percent
definition: Purchase price of common stock expressed as a percentage of its fair value.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangements by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Exercises in Period, Weighted Average Exercise Price
definition: Weighted average price at which option holders acquired shares when converting their stock options into shares.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangements by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Expirations in Period, Weighted Average Exercise Price
definition: Weighted average price at which grantees could have acquired the underlying shares with respect to stock options of the plan that expired.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangements by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Forfeitures in Period, Weighted Average Exercise Price
definition: Weighted average price at which grantees could have acquired the underlying shares with respect to stock options that were terminated.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangements by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Grants in Period, Weighted Average Exercise Price
definition: Weighted average per share amount at which grantees can acquire shares of common stock by exercise of options.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangements by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Other Share Increase (Decrease) in Period, Weighted Average Exercise Price
definition: Weighted average price at which grantees could acquire or could have acquired the underlying shares with respect to any other type of change in shares reserved for issuance.

elementLabel: Shareholder Loans to Finance Leveraged Buyout (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Proceeds from shareholder loans used to finance leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Share of Equity Method Investees Net Capitalized Costs Relating to Oil and Gas Producing Activities (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The enterprise's share of the investees' net capitalized costs relating to oil and gas producing activities, if the enterprise's financial statements include investments that are accounted for by the equity method.

elementLabel: Share of Equity Method Investees' Property Acquisition, Exploration, and Development Costs Incurred in Oil and Gas Producing Activities (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The enterprise's share of the investees' property acquisition, exploration, and development costs incurred in oil and gas producing.

elementLabel: Share Price
definition: Price of a single share of a number of saleable stocks of a company.

elementLabel: Shares Issued, Price Per Share
definition: Per share or per unit amount of equity securities issued.

elementLabel: Short-term and Long-term Debt, Defaulted, Amount (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Amount of outstanding debt associated with any securities or credit agreement for which there has been a default in principal, interest, sinking fund, or redemption provisions, or any breach of covenant that existed at the end of the period and subsequently has not been cured.

elementLabel: Short-term Debt, Amount (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Reflects the total carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of debt having initial terms less than one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Short-term Debt, Interest Rate Increase
definition: Percentage increase in the stated interest rate on a short-term debt instrument.

elementLabel: Short-term Debt, Percentage Bearing Fixed Interest Rate
definition: The portion of the carrying amount of short-term borrowings outstanding as of the balance sheet date which accrues interest at a set, unchanging rate.

elementLabel: Short-term Debt, Percentage Bearing Variable Interest Rate
definition: The portion of the carrying amount of short-term borrowings outstanding as of the balance sheet date, which accrues interest at a rate subject to change from time to time.

elementLabel: Significant Commitment, Remaining Minimum Amount Committed (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The floor amount as of the balance sheet date that the entity must expend to satisfy the terms of the disclosed arrangements (excluding long-term commitments) in which the entity has agreed to expend funds to procure goods or services from a supplier, or to commit resources to supply goods or services to a customer.

elementLabel: Purchase Commitment, Remaining Minimum Amount Committed (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The floor amount as of the balance sheet date that the entity must expend to satisfy the terms of disclosed arrangements (excluding long-term commitments) in which the entity has agreed to expend funds to procure goods or services from one or more suppliers, other than under a long-term purchase commitment or an unconditional purchase obligation.

elementLabel: Supply Commitment, Remaining Minimum Amount Committed
definition: The floor amount as of the balance sheet date that the entity must expend to satisfy the terms of disclosed arrangements (excluding long-term commitments) in which the entity must commit resources to supply goods or services to one or more customers.

elementLabel: Single Employer Plans Accounted for as Multi-Employer, Plan Contributions
definition: Amount of contributions to a pension or other postretirement plan which is not defined as a multiemployer plan but is accounted for as a multiemployer plan.

elementLabel: Statutory Accounting Practices, Dividends Paid with Approval of Regulatory Agency
definition: Amount of dividends paid subject to regulatory approval.

elementLabel: Statutory Accounting Practices, Statutory Amount Available for Dividend Payments without Regulatory Approval
definition: Amount of dividends that can be declared or paid without approval of regulatory agency.

elementLabel: Statutory Accounting Practices, Statutory Amount Available for Dividend Payments with Regulatory Approval
definition: Amount of dividends that can be declared or paid with approval of regulatory agency.

elementLabel: Stockholders' Equity Attributable to Parent, Not Allowable for Net Capital (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Deduct stockholders' equity not allowable for net capital.

elementLabel: Stockholders' Equity Note, Stock Split, Conversion Ratio
definition: Ratio applied to the conversion of stock split, for example but not limited to, one share converted to two or two shares converted to one.

elementLabel: Stock Issued (Deprecated 2011-01-31)
definition: The fair value of stock issued in noncash financing activities.

elementLabel: Development Stage Entities, Stock Issued, Shares, Issued for Cash (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Number of shares issued as consideration for cash for development stage entities.

elementLabel: Development Stage Entities, Stock Issued, Shares, Issued for Noncash Consideration (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Number of shares issued for noncash consideration for development stage entities.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Issued for Services
definition: Number of shares issued in lieu of cash for services contributed to the entity. Number of shares includes, but is not limited to, shares issued for services contributed by vendors and founders.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Shares Held in Trust of Employee Stock Ownership Plan (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Number of shares issued during the period and held in trust for Employee Stock Ownership Plan (ESOP).

elementLabel: Development Stage Entities, Stock Issued, Value, Issued for Cash (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Value of shares issued as consideration for cash for development stage entities.

elementLabel: Development Stage Entities, Stock Issued, Value, Issued for Noncash Consideration (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Value of shares issued for noncash consideration for development stage entities.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Value, Issued for Services
definition: Value of stock issued in lieu of cash for services contributed to the entity. Value of the stock issued includes, but is not limited to, services contributed by vendors and founders.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Value, Shares Held in Trust of Employee Stock Ownership Plan (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Value of stock issued during the period and held in trust for Employee Stock Ownership Plan (ESOP) or cost of compensation committed to employee's trust but not yet earned. The consideration to be received by the employer for placing the shares in the ESOP trust is future employee services. That is, this consideration is the cost of compensation.

elementLabel: Stock or Units Available for Distributions
definition: Number of stock or units eligible for distribution to members or limited partners of the limited liability company (LLC) or limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Stock Repurchase Program, Authorized Amount
definition: Amount of stock repurchase plan authorized.

elementLabel: Stock Repurchase Program, Remaining Authorized Repurchase Amount
definition: Amount remaining of a stock repurchase plan authorized.

elementLabel: Subadvisory Fees for Mutual Funds
definition: Subadvisory fees that the funds adviser pays for out of the management fee, which it receives from the fund.

elementLabel: Subordinated Borrowing, Interest Rate
definition: Stated interest rate of the subordinated debt.

elementLabel: Subordinated Borrowing with Six Month Notice of Intent to Withdraw (Deprecated 2015-01-31)
definition: Amount of subordinated debt for which six months notice of intent to withdraw has been provided.

elementLabel: Subordinated Liabilities, Additions
definition: New liabilities assumed during the reporting period that are subordinated to claims of general creditors.

elementLabel: Subordinated Liabilities, Extinguished
definition: Liabilities that are subordinated to claims of general creditors and were paid or extinguished during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Subordinated Notes to Finance Leveraged Buyout (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Issuance of subordinated notes to finance leveraged buyout transaction.

elementLabel: Subsequent Event, Amount (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Reflects the known or estimated financial effect of the event, or transaction that occurred between the balance sheet date and the date the financial statements are issued or available to be issued.

elementLabel: Subsequent Event, Amount, Higher Range (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The highest estimated amount of the financial effect of the event or transaction that occurred between the balance sheet date and the date the financial statements are issued or available to be issued.

elementLabel: Subsequent Event, Amount, Lower Range (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: The lowest estimated amount of the financial effect of the event or transaction that occurred between the balance sheet date and the date the financial statements are issued or available to be issued.

elementLabel: Subsidiary or Equity Method Investee, Noncontrolling Interest in Income of Subsidiary
definition: The dividends from redeemable preferred stock of a subsidiary that are accounted for as a noncontrolling interest in income of a subsidiary in a parent's consolidated financial statements.

elementLabel: Summary of Investments, Other than Investments in Related Parties, Carrying Amount
definition: This element represents the carrying (reported) amount of the entity's investments as of the balance sheet date. This amount may represent the individual investment's or group of similar investments' original cost, fair value, or such other amount at which the investment is shown in the entity's balance sheet.

elementLabel: Summary of Investments, Other than Investments in Related Parties, Cost
definition: This item represents the original cost of the entity's investments including investments in equity securities and, as to fixed maturities, original cost reduced by repayments and adjusted for amortization of premiums or accrual of discounts.

elementLabel: Summary of Investments, Other than Investments in Related Parties, Fair Value
definition: This item represents the reported amount of the entity's investments measured at fair value. Fair value is the price that would be received to sell an investment in an orderly transaction between market participants at the balance sheet [measurement] date.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Amortization of Deferred Policy Acquisition Costs
definition: Amount of amortization expense on deferred policy acquisition cost.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Deferred Policy Acquisition Costs
definition: Amount of deferred policy acquisition cost related to property-casualty insurance policy written.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Discount Deducted from Reserves
definition: The amount of discount that may be deducted from the reserve for unpaid claims and claims adjustment expense.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Earned Premiums
definition: Amount of property-casualty insurance premium revenue earned on insurance policies.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Interest Rate at which Discount Computed
definition: The rate at which the discount was computed for each business segment reported.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Maximum Interest Rate in Range
definition: The maximum interest rate in the range of rates estimated at which the discount was computed for each business segment reported.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Minimum Interest Rate in Range
definition: The minimum interest rate in the range of rates estimated at which the discount was computed for each business segment reported.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Net Investment Income
definition: Amount of net investment income earned by property-casualty insurance underwriter.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Paid Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense
definition: Payments of claims and claims adjustment expenses during the period of a property-casualty insurance entity.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Premiums Written
definition: Amount of actual premium written by property-casualty insurance underwriter.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Reserves for Unpaid Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense
definition: The amount of reserve, policy claim payable and loss expense incurred by property-casualty insurance underwriter.

elementLabel: Supplemental Information for Property, Casualty Insurance Underwriters, Unearned Premiums
definition: Amount of property-casualty insurance premium revenue not yet earned on insurance policies.

elementLabel: Supplementary Insurance Information, Amortization of Deferred Policy Acquisition Costs
definition: Amount of amortization of deferred policy acquisition costs recognized.

elementLabel: Supplementary Insurance Information, Benefits, Claims, Losses and Settlement Expense
definition: Amount of insurance benefits, claims, losses and settlement expenses incurred.

elementLabel: Supplementary Insurance Information, Deferred Policy Acquisition Costs
definition: Net amount of deferred policy acquisition costs capitalized on contracts remaining in force on the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Supplementary Insurance Information, Liability for Future Policy Benefits, Losses, Claims and Loss Expense Reserves
definition: Amount of reserves for future policy claims payable and loss expenses to be incurred.

elementLabel: Supplementary Insurance Information, Net Investment Income
definition: Amount of net investment income earned.

elementLabel: Supplementary Insurance Information, Other Operating Expense
definition: Amount of other operating expense incurred.

elementLabel: Supplementary Insurance Information, Other Policy Claims and Benefits Payable
definition: Amount of claims and benefits payable not included within other categories.

elementLabel: Supplementary Insurance Information, Premium Revenue
definition: Amount of premium revenue earned.

elementLabel: Supplementary Insurance Information, Premiums Written
definition: Amount of actual written premiums, including, as applicable, premiums from reinsurance assumed and net of premiums on reinsurance ceded.

elementLabel: Supplementary Insurance Information, Unearned Premiums
definition: Amount of premiums not yet earned.

elementLabel: Supplies and Postage Expense
definition: The aggregate amount of expenses directly related to the supplies and postage.

elementLabel: Supplies Expense
definition: Amount of expense associated with supplies that were used during the current accounting period.

elementLabel: Tangible Capital
definition: Tangible capital as defined in the regulations (generally includes outstanding stock plus retained earnings) for banking institutions subject to Office of Thrift Supervision (OTS) capital requirements.

elementLabel: Tangible Capital Required for Capital Adequacy
definition: The minimum amount of tangible capital required under the regulatory framework for prompt corrective action.

elementLabel: Tangible Capital Required for Capital Adequacy to Tangible Assets
definition: The minimum amount of Tangible Capital divided by tangible assets (Tangible Capital Ratio) as defined in the regulations.

elementLabel: Tangible Capital to Tangible Assets
definition: Tangible Capital divided by Tangible assets as defined in the regulations.

elementLabel: Tax Basis of Investments, Cost for Income Tax Purposes
definition: The aggregate cost of investments for Federal income tax purposes.

elementLabel: Tax Basis of Investments, Gross, Unrealized Appreciation
definition: Aggregate gross unrealized appreciation for all Investments in which there is an excess of value over tax cost.

elementLabel: Tax Basis of Investments, Gross, Unrealized Depreciation
definition: The aggregate gross unrealized depreciation for all Investments in which there is an excess of tax cost over value.

elementLabel: Tax Benefit from Stock Options Exercised (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Tax benefits realized from the exercise of stock options resulting in reductions in the entity's income taxes, which increases net cash provided by operating activities.

elementLabel: Taxes and Licenses
definition: Amount of tax expense, excluding income, excise, production and property taxes, and licenses and fees not related to production.

elementLabel: Taxes, Miscellaneous
definition: All taxes not related to income of the entity or excise or sales taxes levied on the revenue of the entity that are not reported elsewhere. These taxes could include production, real estate, personal property, and pump tax.

elementLabel: Taxes, Other
definition: Taxes, excluding payroll, income and excise taxes, if not included elsewhere, that could include production, real and personal property, and other selling and distribution-related taxes.

elementLabel: Temporary Equity, Carrying Amount, Attributable to Noncontrolling Interest (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Carrying amount, attributable to noncontrolling interests, of an entity's issued and outstanding stock which is not included within permanent equity. Temporary equity is a security with redemption features that are outside the control of the issuer, is not classified as an asset or liability in conformity with GAAP, and is not mandatorily redeemable. Includes any type of security that is redeemable at a fixed or determinable price or on a fixed or determinable date or dates, is redeemable at the option of the holder, or has conditions for redemption which are not solely within the control of the issuer. Includes stock with a put option held by an ESOP and stock redeemable by a holder only in the event of a change in control of the issuer.

elementLabel: Temporary Equity, Carrying Amount, Attributable to Parent
definition: Carrying amount, attributable to parent, of an entity's issued and outstanding stock which is not included within permanent equity. Temporary equity is a security with redemption features that are outside the control of the issuer, is not classified as an asset or liability in conformity with GAAP, and is not mandatorily redeemable. Includes any type of security that is redeemable at a fixed or determinable price or on a fixed or determinable date or dates, is redeemable at the option of the holder, or has conditions for redemption which are not solely within the control of the issuer. Includes stock with a put option held by an ESOP and stock redeemable by a holder only in the event of a change in control of the issuer.

elementLabel: Temporary Equity, Carrying Amount, Including Portion Attributable to Noncontrolling Interests
definition: Carrying amount, attributable to parent and noncontrolling interests, of an entity's issued and outstanding stock which is not included within permanent equity. Temporary equity is a security with redemption features that are outside the control of the issuer, is not classified as an asset or liability in conformity with GAAP, and is not mandatorily redeemable. Includes any type of security that is redeemable at a fixed or determinable price or on a fixed or determinable date or dates, is redeemable at the option of the holder, or has conditions for redemption which are not solely within the control of the issuer. Includes stock with a put option held by an ESOP and stock redeemable by a holder only in the event of a change in control of the issuer.

elementLabel: Threshold Percentage of Value Decline in Equity Securities to be considered Other than Temporary Impairment
definition: Threshold percentage by which investments in equity securities have declined in value to be considered other than temporary impairment (OTTI).

elementLabel: Tier One Leverage Capital
definition: Tier 1 Leverage Capital as defined in the regulations. Also called Core Capital.

elementLabel: Tier One Leverage Capital Required for Capital Adequacy
definition: The minimum amount of Tier 1 Leverage Capital required for capital adequacy purposes under the regulatory framework for prompt corrective action.

elementLabel: Tier One Leverage Capital Required for Capital Adequacy to Average Assets
definition: The minimum amount of Tier 1 Leverage Capital for capital adequacy purposes divided by average assets as defined in the regulations.

elementLabel: Tier One Leverage Capital Required to be Well Capitalized
definition: The amount of Tier 1 Leverage Capital required to be categorized as well capitalized under the regulatory framework for prompt corrective action.

elementLabel: Tier One Leverage Capital Required to be Well Capitalized to Average Assets
definition: The amount of Tier 1 Leverage Capital required to be categorized as well capitalized divided by average assets as defined in the regulatory framework for prompt corrective action.

elementLabel: Tier One Leverage Capital to Average Assets
definition: Tier 1 Leverage Capital divided by average assets as defined in the regulations.

elementLabel: Tier One Risk Based Capital
definition: Tier 1 Risk Based Capital as defined in the regulations.

elementLabel: Tier One Risk Based Capital Required for Capital Adequacy
definition: The minimum amount of Tier 1 Risk Based Capital required for capital adequacy purposes under the regulatory framework for prompt corrective action.

elementLabel: Tier One Risk Based Capital Required for Capital Adequacy to Risk Weighted Assets
definition: The minimum Tier One Capital Ratio (Tier one capital divided by risk-weighted assets) required for capital adequacy purposes under the regulatory framework for prompt corrective action.

elementLabel: Tier One Risk Based Capital Required to be Well Capitalized
definition: The amount of Tier 1 Risk Based Capital required to be categorized as well capitalized under the regulatory framework for prompt corrective action.

elementLabel: Tier One Risk Based Capital Required to be Well Capitalized to Risk Weighted Assets
definition: The Tier 1 capital ratio (Tier 1 capital divided by risk weighted assets) required to be categorized as "well capitalized" under the regulatory framework for prompt corrective action.

elementLabel: Tier One Risk Based Capital to Risk Weighted Assets
definition: Tier 1 capital divided by risk weighted assets as defined by regulations.

elementLabel: Tier Two Risk Based Capital
definition: Tier 2 risk-based capital as defined in the regulations.

elementLabel: Time Deposit Maturities, after Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of time deposits maturing after the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. Time deposits include, but are not limited to, certificates of deposits.
