For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Time Deposit Maturities, after Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of time deposits maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. Time deposits include, but are not limited to, certificates of deposits. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Time Deposit Maturities, Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of time deposits maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. Time deposits include, but are not limited to, certificates of deposits. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Time Deposit Maturities, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of time deposits maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Time deposits include, but are not limited to, certificates of deposits. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Time Deposit Maturities, Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of time deposits maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. Time deposits include, but are not limited to, certificates of deposits. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Time Deposit Maturities, Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of time deposits maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. Time deposits include, but are not limited to, certificates of deposits. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Time Deposit Maturities, Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of time deposits maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. Time deposits include, but are not limited to, certificates of deposits. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Time Deposit Maturities, Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of time deposits maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. Time deposits include, but are not limited to, certificates of deposits. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Time Sharing Transactions, Additions to Allowance for Current-Period Sales (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Additions to the allowance for uncollectible accounts for current-period sales.

elementLabel: Time Sharing Transactions, Additions to Allowance for Current-Period Sales
definition: Amount of expense related to the additions to the allowance for uncollectible accounts for current-period sales.

elementLabel: Time Sharing Transactions, Additions to Allowance for Current Period Sales on Receivables Sold with Recourse (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: Additions to the allowance for uncollectible accounts for current-period sales on receivables sold with recourse. This may include a deduction from notes receivables for any profit deferred based on reduced profit calculations.

elementLabel: Time Sharing Transactions, Additions to Allowance for Current Period Sales on Receivables Sold with Recourse
definition: Amount of expense related to the additions to the allowance for uncollectible accounts for current-period sales on receivables sold with recourse.

elementLabel: Time Sharing Transactions, Estimated Cost to Complete Improvements and Promised Amenities
definition: Estimated cost to complete improvements and promised amenities.

elementLabel: Time Sharing Transactions, Stated Interest Rates for Notes Receivable, Maximum
definition: Maximum end of range of stated interest rates of notes receivable.

elementLabel: Time Sharing Transactions, Stated Interest Rates for Notes Receivable, Minimum
definition: Minimum end of range of stated interest rates of notes receivable.

elementLabel: Time Sharing Transactions, Weighted Average of Stated Interest Rates for Notes Receivable
definition: Weighted average of stated interest rates of notes receivable.

elementLabel: Trade Receivables Held-for-sale, Reconciliation to Cash Flow, Additions to Held-for-sale
definition: Reconcile the changes in trade receivables held for sale balances to the amounts presented in the consolidated statement of cash flows. Enter the additions to trade accounts that will be sold to other entities for the period.

elementLabel: Trade Receivables Held-for-sale, Reconciliation to Cash Flow, Deductions from Held-for-sale
definition: Reconcile the changes in trade receivables that will be sold to other entities balances to the amounts presented in the consolidated statement of cash flows. Enter the deductions to trade accounts that will be sold to other entities for the period.

elementLabel: Trading Securities, Debt, Amortized Cost
definition: Amortized cost of investments in debt securities classified as trading.

elementLabel: Trading Securities, Equity, Cost
definition: Cost of investments in equity securities and other forms of securities that provide ownership interests classified as trading.

elementLabel: Trading Securities, Short-term Investments, Amortized Cost
definition: Amortized cost of short-term investments in debt and equity securities and other forms of securities that provide ownership interests classified as trading.

elementLabel: Transfer from Investments
definition: Value of investments transferred from the entity's investments in noncash transactions.

elementLabel: Transfer of Loans Held-for-sale to Portfolio Loans
definition: Value of loans held-for-sale transferred to loans held in the entity's portfolio in noncash transactions.

elementLabel: Real Estate Owned, Transfer from Real Estate Owned
definition: Value transferred out of real estate owned (REO) in noncash transactions.

elementLabel: Transfer of Portfolio Loans and Leases to Held-for-sale
definition: Value of loans and leases held in the entity's portfolio transferred to loans and leases held-for-sale in noncash transactions.

elementLabel: Transfers Accounted for as Secured Borrowings, Assets, Carrying Amount
definition: Carrying amount of financial assets accounted for as secured borrowings recognized in the transferor's statement of financial position at the end of each period presented.

elementLabel: Transfers Accounted for as Secured Borrowings, Associated Liabilities, Carrying Amount
definition: Carrying amount of liabilities associated with financial assets accounted for as secured borrowings recognized in the transferor's statement of financial position at the end of each period presented.

elementLabel: Transfer to Investments
definition: Value of investments transferred to the entity's investments in noncash transactions.

elementLabel: Real Estate Owned, Transfer to Real Estate Owned
definition: Value transferred from mortgage loans to real estate owned (REO) in noncash transactions.

elementLabel: Two Percent of Debit Items
definition: This element represents the amount of net capital of a broker or dealer that has elected not to be subject to the Aggregate Indebtedness Standard (as defined). The amount of net capital represented by this element is the greater of $250,000 or two percent of aggregate debit items computed in accordance with the Formula for Determination of Reserve Requirements for Brokers and Dealers (as defined).

elementLabel: Unbilled Receivables, Not Billable, Amount Expected to be Collected after Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of receivables under long-term contracts that have not been billed and were not billable that are expected to be collected after the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unbilled Receivables, Not Billable, Amount Expected to be Collected in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of receivables under long-term contracts that have not been billed and were not billable that are expected to be collected in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unbilled Receivables, Not Billable, Amount Expected to be Collected in Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of receivables under long-term contracts that have not been billed and were not billable that are expected to be collected in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Underlying, Derivative
definition: Specified interest rate, security price, commodity price, foreign exchange rate, index of prices or rates for a derivative contract but not the derivative contract itself.

elementLabel: Underlying, Derivative Asset
definition: Specified interest rate, security price, commodity price, foreign exchange rate, index of prices or rates for a derivative asset contract but not the derivative contract itself.

elementLabel: Underlying, Derivative Energy Measure
definition: Specified interest rate, security price, commodity price, foreign exchange rate, index of prices or rates for a derivative contract measured in energy volume but not the derivative contract itself.

elementLabel: Underlying, Derivative Flow Rate
definition: Specified interest rate, security price, commodity price, foreign exchange rate, index of prices or rates for a derivative contract measured in flow rate but not the derivative contract itself.

elementLabel: Underlying, Derivative Liability
definition: Specified interest rate, security price, commodity price, foreign exchange rate, index of prices or rates for a derivative liability contract but not the derivative contract itself.

elementLabel: Underlying, Derivative Mass
definition: Specified interest rate, security price, commodity price, foreign exchange rate, index of prices or rates for a derivative contract measured in mass but not the derivative contract itself.

elementLabel: Underlying, Derivative Volume
definition: Specified interest rate, security price, commodity price, foreign exchange rate, index of prices or rates for a derivative contract measured in volume but not the derivative contract itself.

elementLabel: Underwriting Expense Ratio
definition: Ratio of non-life acquisition expenses and certain non-life general and administrative expenses, to non-life net premiums earned.

elementLabel: Undistributed Earnings of Domestic Subsidiaries
definition: Amount of undistributed earnings of domestic subsidiaries or domestic joint ventures intended to be permanent.

elementLabel: Undistributed Earnings of Foreign Subsidiaries
definition: Amount of undistributed earnings of foreign subsidiaries intended to be permanently reinvested outside the country of domicile.

elementLabel: Unrecognized Tax Benefits, Decrease Resulting from Acquisition
definition: Amount of decrease in unrecognized tax benefits resulting from acquisitions.

elementLabel: Unrecognized Tax Benefits, Decrease Resulting from Foreign Currency Translation
definition: Amount of decrease in unrecognized tax benefits resulting from foreign currency translation.

elementLabel: Unrecognized Tax Benefits, Increase Resulting from Acquisition
definition: Amount of increase in unrecognized tax benefits resulting from acquisitions.

elementLabel: Unrecognized Tax Benefits, Increase Resulting from Foreign Currency Translation
definition: Amount of increase in unrecognized tax benefits resulting from foreign currency translation.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Rolling after Year Five
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Rolling Year Five
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Rolling Year Four
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Rolling Year Three
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Rolling Year Two
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unsolicited Tender Offer Costs
definition: Costs incurred in connection with an unsolicited tender offer (one where the Entity being sought has not requested the offer). These would include costs relating to evaluation and dissemination of information regarding an unsolicited tender offer. A tender offer is a broad solicitation by an Entity or a third party to purchase a substantial percentage of another entity's shares or units for a limited period of time. The offer is at a fixed price, usually at a premium over the current market price, and is contingent on shareholders' tendering a fixed number of their shares or units.

elementLabel: Unused Commitments to Extend Credit
definition: Unused amount of commitments to extend credit to customers.

elementLabel: Unusual or Infrequent Item, Gain, Gross
definition: Amount of gain recognized in the income statement for an event or transaction, that is unusual in nature or occurs infrequently, but not both.

elementLabel: Unusual or Infrequent Item, Loss, Gross
definition: Amount of loss recognized in the income statement for an event or transaction, that is unusual in nature or occurs infrequently, but not both.

elementLabel: Valuation Allowance for Impairment of Recognized Servicing Assets, Aggregate Write-Downs
definition: The charge against the valuation allowance related to a servicing asset that is subsequently measured using the amortization method.

elementLabel: Valuation Allowance for Impairment of Recognized Servicing Assets, Balance
definition: Reflects the estimated amount of impairment as of the balance sheet date of recognized servicing assets that are being amortized in proportion to and over the period of estimated net servicing income or loss.

elementLabel: Valuation Allowance for Impairment of Recognized Servicing Assets, Sales and Disposals
definition: Reduction in valuation allowance of servicing assets based on sales and disposals.

elementLabel: Valuation Allowances and Reserves, Balance
definition: Total of allowances and reserves, the valuation and qualifying accounts that are either netted against the cost of an asset (in order to value it at its carrying value) or that reflect a liability established to represent expected future costs.

elementLabel: Valuation Allowances and Reserves, Recoveries
definition: Total of recoveries of amounts due the Entity that had previously been written off as uncollectible using allowances (the valuation accounts that are netted against the cost of an asset to value it at its carrying value) and total of reestablishments of reserves (liabilities established to represent expected future costs) that had previously been utilized.

elementLabel: Valuation Allowances and Reserves, Reserves of Businesses Acquired
definition: Total of allowances and reserves, the valuation and qualifying accounts that are either netted against the cost of an asset (in order to value it at its carrying value) or that reflect a liability established to represent expected future costs, acquired in a business combination.

elementLabel: Variable Interest Entity, Nonconsolidated, Comparison of Carrying Amount of Assets and Liabilities to Maximum Loss Exposure, Explanation, Quantitative Information, Advantageous (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Quantitative information provided in explanation of the differences between the carrying amounts of assets and liabilities in the reporting entity's statement of financial position that relate to the reporting entity's variable interest in the Variable Interest Entity (VIE) and the reporting entity's maximum exposure to loss as a result of its involvement with the VIE which information is favorable to the reporting entity.

elementLabel: Variable Interest Entity, Nonconsolidated, Comparison of Carrying Amount of Assets and Liabilities to Maximum Loss Exposure, Explanation, Quantitative Information, Disadvantageous (Deprecated 2012-01-31)
definition: Quantitative information provided in explanation of the differences between the carrying amounts of assets and liabilities in the reporting entity's statement of financial position that relate to the reporting entity's variable interest in the Variable Interest Entity (VIE) and the reporting entity's maximum exposure to loss as a result of its involvement with the VIE which information is unfavorable to the reporting entity.

elementLabel: Warrants Not Settleable in Cash, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of warrants not settleable in cash classified as equity.

elementLabel: Water floods in Process of Installation
definition: The number of water floods in process of installation in each geographic area as of the date listed.

elementLabel: Weighted Average Discount Rate, Percent
definition: The average discount rate applied to insurance contracts to determine future policy benefits to be paid to or on behalf of policyholders.

elementLabel: Weighted Average Interest Rate on Overdrawn Demand Deposit
definition: Weighted average interest rate on overdrawn demand deposit.

elementLabel: Weighted Average Limited Partnership Units Outstanding, Diluted
definition: Weighted average number of limited partnership units outstanding determined by relating the portion of time within a reporting period that limited partnership units have been outstanding to the total time in that period. Used in the calculation of diluted net income or loss per limited partnership unit.

elementLabel: Weighted Average Number of Shares Outstanding, Basic and Diluted
definition: Average number of shares or units issued and outstanding that are used in calculating basic and diluted earnings per share (EPS).

elementLabel: Weighted Average Number Diluted Limited Partnership Units Outstanding Adjustment
definition: The sum of dilutive potential limited partnership units used in the calculation of the diluted per-unit computation.

elementLabel: Wells in Process of Drilling
definition: The number of wells in the process of being drilled in each geographic area as of the date listed.

elementLabel: Wells Temporarily Suspended
definition: The number of wells temporarily suspended in each geographic area as of the date listed.

elementLabel: Withdrawal from Contract Holders Funds
definition: The cash outflow for a segregated fund account during the period.

elementLabel: Workers' Compensation Liability (Deprecated 2009-01-31)
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations and payables pertaining to claims incurred of a workers compensation nature. For classified balance sheets, used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer); for unclassified balance sheets, used to reflect the total liabilities (regardless of due date).

elementLabel: Accumulated Depreciation, Depletion and Amortization, Reclassifications from Property, Plant and Equipment
definition: Amount of decrease in accumulated depreciation, depletion and amortization as a result of reclassifications from property, plant and equipment.

elementLabel: Accumulated Depreciation, Depletion and Amortization, Sale or Disposal of Property, Plant and Equipment
definition: Amount of decrease in accumulated depreciation, depletion and amortization as a result of sale or disposal of property, plant and equipment.

elementLabel: Affordable Housing Project Investment, Write-down, Amount
definition: Amount of write-down from impairment of an investment in a qualified affordable housing project.

elementLabel: Affordable Housing Tax Credits and Other Tax Benefits, Amount
definition: Amount of affordable housing tax credits and other tax benefits recognized.

elementLabel: Amortization Method Qualified Affordable Housing Project Investments
definition: Amount of investment in qualified affordable housing projects.

elementLabel: Amortization Method Qualified Affordable Housing Project Investments, Amortization
definition: Amount of amortization expense of investment in qualified affordable housing projects.

elementLabel: Assets Held-for-sale, Not Part of Disposal Group
definition: Amount of assets held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group.

elementLabel: Assets Held-for-sale, Not Part of Disposal Group, Current
definition: Amount of assets held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group, expected to be sold within a year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Assets Held-for-sale, Not Part of Disposal Group, Current, Other
definition: Amount of other assets held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group, expected to be sold within a year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Assets Held-for-sale, Not Part of Disposal Group, Other
definition: Amount of other assets held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group.

elementLabel: Average Collected Cash Balances with Commercial Banks, Federal Home Loan Bank
definition: Average amount of collected cash balances with commercial banks the Federal Home Loan Banks (FHLBanks) maintain in return for certain services.

elementLabel: Capital Expenditure, Discontinued Operations
definition: Amount of capital expenditure attributable to discontinued operations.

elementLabel: Cash Pass-through Reserve, Federal Home Loan Bank
definition: Amount of pass-through reserves deposited with Federal Reserve Banks from member institutions of Federal Home Loan Banks (FHLBanks).

elementLabel: Decrease in Unrecognized Tax Benefits is Reasonably Possible
definition: Amount of decrease reasonably possible in the next twelve months for the unrecognized tax benefit.

elementLabel: #NAME?
definition: #NAME?

elementLabel: #NAME?
definition: #NAME?

elementLabel: Discontinued Operation, Equity Method Investment Retained after Disposal, Ownership Interest after Disposal
definition: Percent, after disposal, of ownership interest of a discontinued operation in which an equity method investment is retained.

elementLabel: Discontinued Operation, Equity Method Investment Retained after Disposal, Ownership Interest Prior to Disposal
definition: Percent, prior to disposal, of ownership interest of a discontinued operation in which an equity method investment is retained.

elementLabel: Discontinued Operation, Intra-Entity Amounts, Discontinued Operation after Disposal, Expense
definition: Amount of expense in continuing operations related to continuing involvement in a discontinued operation after the disposal that before the disposal was eliminated as intra-entity transactions.

elementLabel: Discontinued Operation, Intra-Entity Amounts, Discontinued Operation after Disposal, Revenue
definition: Amount of revenue in continuing operations related to continuing involvement in a discontinued operation after disposal that before the disposal was eliminated as intra-entity transactions.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Capital Leased Assets
definition: Amount classified as capital leased assets attributable to disposal group.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Capital Leased Assets, Current
definition: Amount classified as capital leased assets attributable to disposal group, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Capital Leased Assets, Noncurrent
definition: Amount classified as capital leased assets attributable to disposal group, expected to be disposed of after one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Disposal Group, Including Discontinued Operation, Inventory, Current
definition: Amount classified as inventory attributable to disposal group, expected to be disposed of within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Financial Assets Sold under Agreements to Repurchase, Gross Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of funds outstanding borrowed in the form of a financial asset repurchase agreement between the entity and another party for the sale and repurchase of identical or substantially the same financial asset at a date certain for a specified price. Includes repurchase-to-maturity transactions and liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Nonaccrual, Percent Past Due
definition: Percent of nonaccrual financing receivable balances outstanding that are past due.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Percent Past Due
definition: Percent of financing receivables past due.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Next Rolling Twelve Months, Amortized Cost
definition: Amortized cost of held-to-maturity debt securities maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Rolling after Ten Years, Amortized Cost
definition: Amortized cost of held-to-maturity debt securities maturing after the tenth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Rolling Year Six Through Ten, Amortized Cost
definition: Amortized cost of held-to-maturity debt securities maturing in the sixth through tenth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, Rolling Year Two Through Five, Amortized Cost
definition: Amortized cost of held-to-maturity debt securities maturing in the second through fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Increase in Unrecognized Tax Benefits is Reasonably Possible
definition: Amount of increase reasonably possible in the next twelve months for the unrecognized tax benefit.

elementLabel: Loan Restructuring, Trial Modifications, Amount
definition: Amount of loan receivable in which the terms of the loan agreement have been modified on a trial basis.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable Held-for-sale, Net, Not Part of Disposal Group
definition: Amount, after allowance for bad debt, of loan receivables held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans classified as debt securities.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable Held-for-sale, Net, Not Part of Disposal Group, Commercial and Industrial
definition: Amount, after allowance for bad debt, of commercial and industrial loan receivables held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans classified as debt securities.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable Held-for-sale, Net, Not Part of Disposal Group, Commercial, Real Estate
definition: Amount, after allowance for bad debt, of commercial mortgage loan receivables held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans classified as debt securities.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable Held-for-sale, Net, Not Part of Disposal Group, Consumer, Credit Card
definition: Amount, after allowance for bad debt, of credit card loan receivables held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans classified as debt securities.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable Held-for-sale, Net, Not Part of Disposal Group, Consumer, Home Equity
definition: Amount, after allowance for bad debt, of home equity loan receivables held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans classified as debt securities.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable Held-for-sale, Net, Not Part of Disposal Group, Consumer, Student
definition: Amount, after allowance for bad debt, of student loan receivables held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans classified as debt securities.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable Held-for-sale, Net, Not Part of Disposal Group, Mortgage
definition: Amount, after allowance for bad debt, of mortgage loan receivables held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans classified as debt securities.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable Held-for-sale, Net, Not Part of Disposal Group, Other
definition: Amount, after allowance for bad debt, of other loan receivables held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans classified as debt securities.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans in Process of Foreclosure, Amount
definition: Recorded investment of consumer mortgage loan receivables secured by residential real estate properties for which formal foreclosure proceedings are in process.

elementLabel: Net Amount at Risk by Product and Guarantee, Guaranteed Minimum Return Rate
definition: Rate of guaranteed minimum return on deposits made to contracts reported in separate accounts maintained by an insurance entity.

elementLabel: Previously Estimated Development Costs Incurred
definition: Amount of increase in standardized measure of discounted future net cash flow as a result of previously estimated development costs incurred.

elementLabel: Qualified Affordable Housing Project Investments, Commitment
definition: Amount of commitment or contingent commitments to qualified affordable housing project investments.

elementLabel: Redeemable Noncontrolling Interest, Equity, Common, Redemption Value
definition: Redemption value, as if currently redeemable, of redeemable noncontrolling interest for common shares, units or ownership interests classified as temporary equity and the election has been made to accrete changes in redemption value to the earliest redemption date.

elementLabel: Redeemable Noncontrolling Interest, Equity, Other, Redemption Value
definition: Redemption value, as if currently redeemable, of redeemable noncontrolling interest for other shares, units or ownership interests classified as temporary equity and the election has been made to accrete changes in redemption value to the earliest redemption date.

elementLabel: Redeemable Noncontrolling Interest, Equity, Preferred, Redemption Value
definition: Redemption value, as if currently redeemable, of redeemable noncontrolling interest for preferred shares, units or ownership interests classified as temporary equity and the election has been made to accrete changes in redemption value to the earliest redemption date.

elementLabel: Redeemable Noncontrolling Interest, Equity, Redemption Value
definition: Redemption value, as if currently redeemable, of redeemable noncontrolling interest classified as temporary equity and the election has been made to accrete changes in redemption value to the earliest redemption date.

elementLabel: Secured Borrowings, Gross Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of financial assets loaned to entities in exchange for collateral and funds outstanding borrowed in the form of a financial asset repurchase agreement between the entity and another party for the sale and repurchase of identical or substantially the same financial assets at a date certain for a specified price. Includes liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned and Securities Sold under Agreement to Repurchase, Gross Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of securities loaned to entities in exchange for collateral and funds outstanding borrowed in the form of a security repurchase agreement between the entity and another party for the sale and repurchase of identical or substantially the same securities at a date certain for a specified price. Includes liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement.

elementLabel: Securities Loaned, Including Not Subject to Master Netting Arrangement and Assets other than Securities Transferred
definition: Amount, before effects of master netting arrangements, of financial assets loaned to entities in exchange for collateral. Includes liabilities not subject to a master netting arrangement and financial assets transferred other than securities that qualify as secured borrowings.

elementLabel: Trade and Loans Receivables Held-for-sale, Net, Not Part of Disposal Group
definition: Amount, after allowance for bad debt, of trade and loan receivables held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans classified as debt securities.

elementLabel: Trade Receivables Held-for-sale, Net, Not Part of Disposal Group
definition: Amount, after allowance for bad debt, of trade receivables held-for-sale that are not part of a disposal group.

elementLabel: Transfer of Financial Assets Accounted for as Sales, Amount Derecognized
definition: Amount of derecognized financial assets from transactions which comprise an initial transfer and an agreement entered into in contemplation of the initial transfer resulting in retention of substantially all of the exposure to the economic return throughout the term of the transaction, at the date of derecognition.

elementLabel: Transfer of Financial Assets Accounted for as Sales, Cash Proceeds Received for Assets Derecognized, Amount
definition: Amount, before counterparty netting, of cash proceeds received in transfers of derecognized financial assets from transactions which comprise an initial transfer and an agreement entered into in contemplation of the initial transfer resulting in retention of substantially all of the exposure to the economic return throughout the term of the transaction.

elementLabel: Transfer of Financial Assets Accounted for as Sales, Fair Value of Derecognized Assets
definition: Fair value of derecognized financial assets from transactions which comprise an initial transfer and an agreement entered into in contemplation of the initial transfer resulting in retention of substantially all of the exposure to the economic return throughout the term of the transaction.

elementLabel: Accretion Expense
definition: Amount recognized for the passage of time, typically for liabilities, that have been discounted to their net present values. Excludes accretion associated with asset retirement obligations.

elementLabel: Allowance for Doubtful Accounts Receivable
definition: For an unclassified balance sheet, a valuation allowance for receivables due a company that are expected to be uncollectible.

elementLabel: Amortization of Deferred Charges
definition: The amount of amortization of deferred charges applied against earnings during the period.

elementLabel: Amortization of Financing Costs
definition: Amount of noncash expense included in interest expense to issue debt and obtain financing associated with the related debt instruments. Alternate captions include noncash interest expense.

elementLabel: Asset Retirement Obligation, Accretion Expense
definition: Amount of accretion expense recognized during the period that is associated with an asset retirement obligation. Accretion expense measures and incorporates changes due to the passage of time into the carrying amount of the liability.

elementLabel: Asset Retirement Obligation, Liabilities Settled
definition: Amount of asset retirement obligations settled, or otherwise disposed of, during the period. This may include asset retirement obligations transferred to third parties associated with the sale of a long-lived asset.

elementLabel: Assets
definition: Sum of the carrying amounts as of the balance sheet date of all assets that are recognized. Assets are probable future economic benefits obtained or controlled by an entity as a result of past transactions or events.

elementLabel: Assets, Current
definition: Sum of the carrying amounts as of the balance sheet date of all assets that are expected to be realized in cash, sold, or consumed within one year (or the normal operating cycle, if longer). Assets are probable future economic benefits obtained or controlled by an entity as a result of past transactions or events.

elementLabel: Available-for-sale Securities, Gross Unrealized Losses (Deprecated 2013-01-31)
definition: This item represents the gross unrealized losses for securities, at a point in time, which are categorized neither as held-to-maturity nor trading securities.

elementLabel: Cash Acquired from Acquisition
definition: The cash inflow associated with the acquisition of business during the period (for example, cash that was held by the acquired business).

elementLabel: Cash and Cash Equivalents, at Carrying Value
definition: Amount of currency on hand as well as demand deposits with banks or financial institutions. Includes other kinds of accounts that have the general characteristics of demand deposits. Also includes short-term, highly liquid investments that are both readily convertible to known amounts of cash and so near their maturity that they present insignificant risk of changes in value because of changes in interest rates. Excludes cash and cash equivalents within disposal group and discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Common Stock, Share Subscribed but Unissued, Subscriptions Receivable
definition: Amount of subscription receivable from investors who have been allocated common stock.

elementLabel: Convertible Notes Payable, Current
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of the portion of long-term debt due within one year or the operating cycle if longer identified as Convertible Notes Payable. Convertible Notes Payable is a written promise to pay a note which can be exchanged for a specified amount of another, related security, at the option of the issuer and the holder.

elementLabel: Cost of Goods and Services Sold
definition: The aggregate costs related to goods produced and sold and services rendered by an entity during the reporting period. This excludes costs incurred during the reporting period related to financial services rendered and other revenue generating activities.

elementLabel: Cost of Goods Sold
definition: Total costs related to goods produced and sold during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Cost of Revenue
definition: The aggregate cost of goods produced and sold and services rendered during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Debt Conversion, Converted Instrument, Amount
definition: The value of the financial instrument(s) that the original debt is being converted into in a noncash (or part noncash) transaction. "Part noncash" refers to that portion of the transaction not resulting in cash receipts or cash payments in the period.

elementLabel: Deferred Policy Acquisition Costs, Additions
definition: Total amount of policy acquisition costs capitalized during the income statement period.

elementLabel: Deferred Tax Assets, Gross
definition: Amount before allocation of valuation allowances of deferred tax asset attributable to deductible temporary differences and carryforwards.

elementLabel: Deferred Tax Assets, Net of Valuation Allowance
definition: Amount after allocation of valuation allowances of deferred tax asset attributable to deductible temporary differences and carryforwards.

elementLabel: Deferred Tax Assets, Net of Valuation Allowance, Current
definition: Amount after allocation of valuation allowances of deferred tax asset attributable to deductible temporary differences and carryforwards expected to be realized or consumed within one year or operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Benefit Obligation
definition: 1) For defined benefit pension plans, the benefit obligation is the projected benefit obligation, which is the actuarial present value as of a date of all benefits attributed by the pension benefit formula to employee service rendered prior to that date. 2) For other postretirement defined benefit plans, the benefit obligation is the accumulated postretirement benefit obligation, which is the actuarial present value of benefits attributed to employee service rendered to a particular date.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Interest Cost
definition: The increase in a defined benefit pension plan's projected benefit obligation or a defined benefit postretirement plan's accumulated postretirement benefit obligation due to the passage of time.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Service Cost
definition: The actuarial present value of benefits attributed by the pension benefit formula to services rendered by employees during the period. The portion of the expected postretirement benefit obligation attributed to employee service during the period. The service cost component is a portion of the benefit obligation and is unaffected by the funded status of the plan.

elementLabel: Depreciation
definition: The amount of expense recognized in the current period that reflects the allocation of the cost of tangible assets over the assets' useful lives. Includes production and non-production related depreciation.

elementLabel: Derivative Instruments, Loss Reclassified from Accumulated OCI into Income, Effective Portion
definition: The effective portion of loss reclassified from accumulated other comprehensive income into income on derivative instruments designated and qualifying as hedging instruments.

elementLabel: Dividends, Common Stock
definition: Amount of paid and unpaid common stock dividends declared with the form of settlement in cash, stock and payment-in-kind (PIK).

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Gross
definition: Amount before amortization of assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Intangible Assets, Net
definition: Amount after amortization of assets, excluding financial assets and goodwill, lacking physical substance with a finite life.

elementLabel: General and Administrative Expense
definition: The aggregate total of expenses of managing and administering the affairs of an entity, including affiliates of the reporting entity, which are not directly or indirectly associated with the manufacture, sale or creation of a product or product line.

elementLabel: Goodwill, Impaired, Accumulated Impairment Loss
definition: Amount of accumulated impairment loss for an asset representing future economic benefits arising from other assets acquired in a business combination that are not individually identified and separately recognized.

elementLabel: Goodwill, Impairment Loss
definition: Amount of loss from the write-down of an asset representing the future economic benefits arising from other assets acquired in a business combination that are not individually identified and separately recognized.

elementLabel: Effective Income Tax Rate Reconciliation, Deduction, Dividends, Amount
definition: Amount of the difference between reported income tax expense (benefit) and expected income tax expense (benefit) computed by applying the domestic federal statutory income tax rates to pretax income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to deduction for dividend.

elementLabel: Effective Income Tax Rate Reconciliation, Nondeductible Expense, Life Insurance, Amount
definition: Amount of the difference between reported income tax expense (benefit) and expected income tax expense (benefit) computed by applying the domestic federal statutory income tax rates to pretax income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to nondeductible life insurance expense.

elementLabel: Interest Costs Capitalized
definition: Amount of interest capitalized during the period.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Debt
definition: Amount of the cost of borrowed funds accounted for as interest expense for debt.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Other
definition: Interest expense on all other items not previously classified. For example, includes dividends associated with redeemable preferred stock of a subsidiary that is treated as a liability in the parent's consolidated balance sheet.

elementLabel: Interest Paid, Net
definition: The amount of cash paid for interest during the period net of cash paid for interest that is capitalized.

elementLabel: Inventory Valuation Reserves
definition: Amount of valuation reserve for inventory.

elementLabel: Investment Income, Nonoperating
definition: The aggregate amount of income from investments (for example, dividends) not considered a component of the entity's core operations.

elementLabel: Investments in and Advance to Affiliates, Subsidiaries, Associates, and Joint Ventures
definition: Total investments in (A) an entity in which the entity has significant influence, but does not have control, (B) subsidiaries that are not required to be consolidated and are accounted for using the equity and or cost method, and (C) an entity in which the reporting entity shares control of the entity with another party or group. Includes long-term advances receivable from a party that is affiliated with the reporting entity by means of direct or indirect ownership.

elementLabel: Liabilities
definition: Sum of the carrying amounts as of the balance sheet date of all liabilities that are recognized. Liabilities are probable future sacrifices of economic benefits arising from present obligations of an entity to transfer assets or provide services to other entities in the future.

elementLabel: Liabilities and Equity
definition: Amount of liabilities and equity items, including the portion of equity attributable to noncontrolling interests, if any.

elementLabel: Liabilities, Current
definition: Total obligations incurred as part of normal operations that are expected to be paid during the following twelve months or within one business cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt
definition: Carrying amount of long-term debt, net of unamortized discount or premium, including current and noncurrent amounts. Includes, but not limited to, notes payable, bonds payable, debentures, mortgage loans and commercial paper. Excludes capital lease obligations.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Current Maturities
definition: Amount of long-term debt, after unamortized discount or premium, scheduled to be repaid within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer. Includes, but not limited to, notes payable, bonds payable, debentures, mortgage loans and commercial paper. Excludes capital lease obligations.

elementLabel: Noncontrolling Interest, Decrease from Distributions to Noncontrolling Interest Holders
definition: Decrease in noncontrolling interest balance from payment of dividends or other distributions by the non-wholly owned subsidiary or partially owned entity, included in the consolidation of the parent entity, to the noncontrolling interest holders.

elementLabel: Operating Loss Carryforwards, Valuation Allowance
definition: The portion of the valuation allowance pertaining to the deferred tax asset representing potential future taxable deductions from net operating loss carryforwards for which it is more likely than not that a tax benefit will not be realized.

elementLabel: Amortization of Other Deferred Charges
definition: Amount of amortization of other deferred costs recognized in the income statement.

elementLabel: Other Cost and Expense, Operating
definition: The total amount of other operating cost and expense items that are associated with the entity's normal revenue producing operation.

elementLabel: Other Noncash Expense
definition: Other expenses or losses included in net income that result in no cash outflows or inflows in the period and are not separately disclosed.

elementLabel: Other Operating Income
definition: The total amount of other operating income, the components of which are not separately disclosed on the income statement, from items that are associated with the entity's normal revenue producing operation.

elementLabel: Payments for Repurchase of Common Stock
definition: The cash outflow to reacquire common stock during the period.

elementLabel: Payments for Restructuring
definition: Amount of cash payments made as the result of exit or disposal activities. Excludes payments associated with a discontinued operation or an asset retirement obligation.

elementLabel: Payments of Debt Issuance Costs
definition: The cash outflow paid to third parties in connection with debt origination, which will be amortized over the remaining maturity period of the associated long-term debt.

elementLabel: Payments of Distributions to Affiliates
definition: The distributions of earnings to an entity that is affiliated with the reporting entity by means of direct or indirect ownership.

elementLabel: Payments of Dividends
definition: Cash outflow in the form of capital distributions and dividends to common shareholders, preferred shareholders and noncontrolling interests.

elementLabel: Payments of Financing Costs
definition: The cash outflow for loan and debt issuance costs.

elementLabel: Payments of Stock Issuance Costs
definition: The cash outflow for cost incurred directly with the issuance of an equity security.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Intangible Assets
definition: The cash outflow to acquire asset without physical form usually arising from contractual or other legal rights, excluding goodwill.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Interest in Subsidiaries and Affiliates
definition: The cash outflow associated with the acquisition of or advances to an entity that is related to it but not strictly controlled (for example, an unconsolidated subsidiary, affiliate, and joint venture or equity method investment) or the acquisition of an additional interest in a subsidiary (controlled entity).

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Productive Assets
definition: The cash outflow for purchases of and capital improvements on property, plant and equipment (capital expenditures), software, and other intangible assets.

elementLabel: Pension and Other Postretirement Defined Benefit Plans, Current Liabilities
definition: For a classified balance sheet, the amount recognized in balance sheet as a current liability associated with an underfunded defined benefit plan.

elementLabel: Pension and Other Postretirement Defined Benefit Plans, Liabilities
definition: This represents the entire liability recognized in the balance sheet that is associated with the defined benefit plans.

elementLabel: Pension and Other Postretirement Defined Benefit Plans, Liabilities, Noncurrent
definition: This represents the noncurrent liability for underfunded plans recognized in the balance sheet that is associated with the defined benefit pension plans and other postretirement defined benefit plans.

elementLabel: Policyholder Benefits and Claims Incurred, Net
definition: Amount, after effects of policies assumed or ceded, of expense related to the provision for policy benefits and costs incurred.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Contributions from Affiliates
definition: The cash inflow from an entity that is affiliated with the entity by means of direct or indirect ownership.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Contributions from Parent
definition: The cash inflow from parent as a source of financing that is recorded as additional paid in capital.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Lines of Credit
definition: Amount of cash inflow from contractual arrangement with the lender, including but not limited to, letter of credit, standby letter of credit and revolving credit arrangements.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Notes Payable
definition: The cash inflow from a borrowing supported by a written promise to pay an obligation.

elementLabel: Product Warranty Accrual, Payments
definition: Represents the aggregate decrease in the liability related to payments to satisfy claims for standard and extended product warranties.

elementLabel: Allowance for Funds Used During Construction, Capitalized Interest
definition: Amount capitalized of allowance for funds used during construction.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate Accumulated Depreciation
definition: Amount of accumulated depreciation pertaining to real estate investments for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: Repayment of Notes Receivable from Related Parties
definition: The cash inflow from a loan, supported by a promissory note, granted to related parties where one party can exercise control or significant influence over another party; including affiliates, owners or officers and their immediate families, pension trusts, and so forth.

elementLabel: Repayments of Debt
definition: The cash outflow during the period from the repayment of aggregate short-term and long-term debt. Excludes payment of capital lease obligations.

elementLabel: Repayments of Lines of Credit
definition: Amount of cash outflow for payment of an obligation from a lender, including but not limited to, letter of credit, standby letter of credit and revolving credit arrangements.

elementLabel: Repayments of Long-term Debt
definition: The cash outflow for debt initially having maturity due after one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Repayments of Other Debt
definition: The cash outflow for the payment of other borrowing not otherwise defined in the taxonomy.

elementLabel: Research and Development Expense
definition: The aggregate costs incurred (1) in a planned search or critical investigation aimed at discovery of new knowledge with the hope that such knowledge will be useful in developing a new product or service, a new process or technique, or in bringing about a significant improvement to an existing product or process; or (2) to translate research findings or other knowledge into a plan or design for a new product or process or for a significant improvement to an existing product or process whether intended for sale or the entity's use, during the reporting period charged to research and development projects, including the costs of developing computer software up to the point in time of achieving technological feasibility, and costs allocated in accounting for a business combination to in-process projects deemed to have no alternative future use.

elementLabel: Revenue, Net
definition: Total revenue from sale of goods and services rendered during the reporting period, in the normal course of business, reduced by sales returns and allowances, and sales discounts.

elementLabel: Shares, Outstanding
definition: Number of shares issued which are neither cancelled nor held in the treasury.

elementLabel: Standard Product Warranty Accrual, Payments
definition: Represents the aggregate decrease in the liability for payments made (in cash or in kind) to satisfy claims under the terms of the standard product warranty. Does not include any Increase or Decrease in the liability for payments related to extended product warranties.

elementLabel: Stock Repurchased During Period, Value
definition: Equity impact of the value of stock that has been repurchased during the period and has not been retired and is not held in treasury. Some state laws may mandate the circumstances under which an entity may acquire its own stock and prescribe the accounting treatment therefore. This element is used when state law does not recognize treasury stock.

elementLabel: Temporary Equity, Accretion to Redemption Value
definition: Value of accretion of temporary equity to its redemption value during the period.

elementLabel: Treasury Stock, Value
definition: The amount allocated to treasury stock. Treasury stock is common and preferred shares of an entity that were issued, repurchased by the entity, and are held in its treasury.

elementLabel: Treasury Stock, Value, Acquired, Cost Method
definition: Equity impact of the cost of common and preferred stock that were repurchased during the period. Recorded using the cost method.

elementLabel: Unrecognized Tax Benefits, Decrease Resulting from Prior Period Tax Positions
definition: Amount of decrease in unrecognized tax benefits resulting from tax positions taken in prior period tax returns.

elementLabel: Unrecognized Tax Benefits, Decrease Resulting from Settlements with Taxing Authorities
definition: Amount of decrease in unrecognized tax benefits resulting from settlements with taxing authorities.

elementLabel: Unrecognized Tax Benefits, Reduction Resulting from Lapse of Applicable Statute of Limitations
definition: Amount of decrease in unrecognized tax benefits resulting from lapses of applicable statutes of limitations.

elementLabel: Deferred Tax Assets, Net of Valuation Allowance, Noncurrent
definition: Amount after allocation of valuation allowances of noncurrent deferred tax asset attributable to deductible temporary differences and carryforwards. Noncurrent assets are expected to be realized or consumed after one year (or the normal operating cycle, if longer).

elementLabel: Notes Payable, Current
definition: Sum of the carrying values as of the balance sheet date of the portions of long-term notes payable due within one year or the operating cycle if longer.

elementLabel: Deferred Tax Assets, Valuation Allowance, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of deferred tax assets for which it is more likely than not that a tax benefit will not be realized expected to be realized or consumed after one year (or the normal operating cycle, if longer).

elementLabel: Management Fees Revenue
definition: Revenue, comprised of base and incentive revenue derived from the management of joint ventures, managing third-party properties, or another entity's operations.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Stock Options Exercised
definition: The cash inflow associated with the amount received from holders exercising their stock options. This item inherently excludes any excess tax benefit, which the entity may have realized and reported separately.

elementLabel: Accrued Income Taxes, Current
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the unpaid sum of the known and estimated amounts payable to satisfy all currently due domestic and foreign income tax obligations.

elementLabel: Effective Income Tax Rate Reconciliation, Deduction, Other, Amount
definition: Amount of the difference between reported income tax expense (benefit) and expected income tax expense (benefit) computed by applying the domestic federal statutory income tax rates to pretax income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to other deductions.

elementLabel: Liabilities Assumed
definition: The fair value of liabilities assumed in noncash investing or financing activities.

elementLabel: #NAME?
definition: The cash outflow from advancing money to an affiliate (an entity that is related but not strictly controlled by the entity).

elementLabel: Property, Plant and Equipment, Net
definition: Amount after accumulated depreciation, depletion and amortization of physical assets used in the normal conduct of business to produce goods and services and not intended for resale. Examples include, but are not limited to, land, buildings, machinery and equipment, office equipment, and furniture and fixtures.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of Long-term Debt
definition: The cash inflow from a debt initially having maturity due after one year or beyond the operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Foreign Currency Transaction Gain, before Tax
definition: Amount before tax of foreign currency transaction realized and unrealized gain recognized in the income statement.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Machinery and Equipment
definition: The cash outflow for acquisition of machinery and equipment.

elementLabel: Derivative, Cash Received on Hedge
definition: The amount of cash received during the period on settlement of a hedge.

elementLabel: Noncash or Part Noncash Acquisition, Fixed Assets Acquired
definition: The amount of fixed assets that an Entity acquires in a noncash (or part noncash) acquisition. Noncash is defined as information about all investing and financing activities of an enterprise during a period that affect recognized assets or liabilities but that do not result in cash receipts or cash payments in the period. "Part noncash" refers to that portion of the transaction not resulting in cash receipts or cash payments in the period.

elementLabel: Payments of Ordinary Dividends, Common Stock
definition: Amount of cash outflow in the form of ordinary dividends to common shareholders of the parent entity.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Investments
definition: The cash outflow associated with the purchase of all investments (debt, security, other) during the period.

elementLabel: Real Estate Owned, Valuation Allowance, Provision (Deprecated 2014-01-31)
definition: Amount of the increase in the real estate owned valuation allowance that is charged against earnings in the period.

elementLabel: Allowance for Doubtful Accounts Receivable, Current
definition: A valuation allowance for trade and other receivables due to an Entity within one year (or the normal operating cycle, whichever is longer) that are expected to be uncollectible.

elementLabel: Dividends, Preferred Stock, Stock
definition: Amount of paid and unpaid preferred stock dividends declared with the form of settlement in stock.

elementLabel: Issuance of Stock and Warrants for Services or Claims
definition: Fair value of share-based compensation granted to nonemployees as payment for services rendered or acknowledged claims.

elementLabel: Other General Expense
definition: Amount of general expenses not normally included in Other Operating Costs and Expenses.

elementLabel: Derivative Asset, Notional Amount
definition: Nominal or face amount used to calculate payments on the derivative asset.

elementLabel: Effective Income Tax Rate Reconciliation, Repatriation of Foreign Earnings, Amount
definition: Amount of the difference between reported income tax expense (benefit) and expected income tax expense (benefit) computed by applying the domestic federal statutory income tax rates to pretax income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to repatriation of foreign earnings.

elementLabel: Stock Issued
definition: The fair value of stock issued in noncash financing activities.

elementLabel: Municipal Debt Securities, at Carrying Value
definition: Bonds or similar securities issued by state, city, or local governments or the agencies operated by state, city, or local governments which are short-term, highly liquid investments that are both readily convertible to known amounts of cash and so near their maturity that they present insignificant risk of changes in value because of changes in interest rates. Generally, only investments with original maturities of three months or less qualify under that definition. Original maturity means original maturity to the entity holding the investment. For example, both a three-month US Treasury bill and a three-year Treasury note purchased three months from maturity qualify as cash equivalents. However, a Treasury note purchased three-years ago does not become a cash equivalent when its remaining maturity is three months.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Equity Method Investments
definition: The cash outflow associated with the purchase of or advances to an equity method investments, which are investments in joint ventures and entities in which the entity has an equity ownership interest normally of 20 to 50 percent and exercises significant influence.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Operating
definition: Amount of operating interest income, including, but not limited to, amortization and accretion of premiums and discounts on securities.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Notes Receivable
definition: The cash outflow to acquire an agreement for an unconditional promise by the maker to pay the entity (holder) a definite sum of money at a future date. Such amount may include accrued interest receivable in accordance with the terms of the note. The note also may contain provisions including a discount or premium, payable on demand, secured, or unsecured, interest bearing or noninterest bearing, among myriad other features and characteristics.

elementLabel: Noncontrolling Interest, Increase from Business Combination
definition: Increase in noncontrolling interest balance because of a business combination that occurred during the period.

elementLabel: Payments for Rent
definition: Cash payments to lessor's for use of assets under operating leases.

elementLabel: Product Warranty Expense
definition: The expense charged against earnings for the period pertaining to standard and extended warranties on the entity's goods and services granted to customers.

elementLabel: Certain Loans Acquired in Transfer Not Accounted for as Debt Securities, Accretable Yield, Reclassifications from Nonaccretable Difference
definition: Amount of increase of reclassification from nonaccretable difference to the excess of a loan's cash flows expected to be collected over the investor's initial investment in acquired loans not accounted for as debt securities with evidence of deterioration of credit quality.

elementLabel: Debt, Current
definition: Amount of short-term debt and current maturity of long-term debt and capital lease obligations due within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Repayments of Short-term Debt
definition: The cash outflow for a borrowing having initial term of repayment within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Capitalized Computer Software, Additions
definition: Additions made to capitalized computer software costs during the period.

elementLabel: Payments of Capital Distribution
definition: Cash outflow to owners or shareholders, excluding ordinary dividends. Includes special dividends.

elementLabel: Capital Lease Obligations, Current
definition: Amount of capital lease obligation due within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Mineral Rights
definition: The cash outflow from the acquisition of a mineral right which is the right to extract a mineral from the earth or to receive payment, in the form of royalty, for the extraction of minerals.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Other Property, Plant, and Equipment
definition: The cash outflow for acquisition of or capital improvements of property, plant and equipment, used to produce goods or deliver services, and not otherwise defined in the taxonomy.

elementLabel: Derivative Instruments, Gain Reclassified from Accumulated OCI into Income, Effective Portion
definition: The effective portion of gain reclassified from accumulated other comprehensive income into income on derivative instruments designated and qualifying as hedging instruments.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross
definition: Amount before allowance of loans and leases held in portfolio, including but not limited to, commercial and consumer loans. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Contributed Capital
definition: The cash inflow associated with the amount received by a corporation from a shareholder during the period.

elementLabel: Property, Plant and Equipment, Other, Accumulated Depreciation
definition: The cumulative amount of depreciation (related to capitalized assets classified as property, plant and equipment not otherwise defined in the taxonomy) that has been recognized in the income statement.

elementLabel: Convertible Preferred Dividends, Net of Tax
definition: The after-tax amount of any dividends on convertible preferred stock.

elementLabel: Effective Income Tax Rate Reconciliation, Tax Credit, Foreign, Amount
definition: Amount of the difference between reported income tax expense (benefit) and expected income tax expense (benefit) computed by applying the domestic federal statutory income tax rates to pretax income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to foreign tax credit.

elementLabel: Deposits
definition: The aggregate of all deposit liabilities held by the entity, including foreign and domestic, interest and noninterest bearing; may include demand deposits, saving deposits, Negotiable Order of Withdrawal (NOW) and time deposits among others.

elementLabel: Due to Related Parties, Current
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of obligations due all related parties. For classified balance sheets, represents the current portion of such liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer).

elementLabel: Payments to Noncontrolling Interests
definition: Amount of cash outflow to a noncontrolling interest. Includes, but not limited to, reduction of noncontrolling interest ownership. Excludes dividends paid to the noncontrolling interest.

elementLabel: Repayments of Long-term Capital Lease Obligations
definition: The cash outflow for the obligation for a lease meeting the criteria for capitalization (with maturities exceeding one year or beyond the operating cycle of the entity, if longer).

elementLabel: Convertible Notes Payable
definition: Including the current and noncurrent portions, carrying value as of the balance sheet date of a written promise to pay a note, initially due after one year or beyond the operating cycle if longer, which can be exchanged for a specified amount of one or more securities (typically common stock), at the option of the issuer or the holder.

elementLabel: Other Noncash Income
definition: Other income or gains included in net income that result in no cash inflows or outflows in the period and are not separately disclosed.

elementLabel: Payments of Ordinary Dividends, Preferred Stock and Preference Stock
definition: Amount of cash outflow in the form of ordinary dividends to preferred shareholders of the parent entity.

elementLabel: Temporary Equity, Accretion of Dividends
definition: Value of accretion of temporary equity during the period due to unpaid dividends.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, Related Allowance
definition: Amount of allowance for credit losses related to recorded investment.

elementLabel: Convertible Debt, Fair Value Disclosures
definition: Fair value portion of borrowing which can be exchanged for a specified number of another security at the option of the issuer or the holder, for example, but not limited to, the entity's common stock.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Net Amount
definition: Amount after allowance and deduction of deferred interest and fees, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts, of loans and leases held in portfolio, including but not limited to, commercial and consumer loans. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements and loans held for sale.

elementLabel: Notes Payable
definition: Including the current and noncurrent portions, aggregate carrying amount of all types of notes payable, as of the balance sheet date, with initial maturities beyond one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Liabilities
definition: The aggregate carrying amount, as of the balance sheet date, of liabilities not separately disclosed in the balance sheet.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Available-for-sale Securities
definition: The cash outflow to acquire debt and equity securities not classified as either held-to-maturity securities or trading securities which would be classified as available-for-sale securities and reported at fair value, with unrealized gains and losses excluded from earnings and reported in a separate component of shareholders' equity.

elementLabel: #NAME?
definition: #NAME?

elementLabel: Derivative Instruments Not Designated as Hedging Instruments, Liability, at Fair Value
definition: Fair value as of the balance sheet date of derivative instrument not designated as hedging instrument and classified as a liability.

elementLabel: Certain Loans Acquired in Transfer Not Accounted for as Debt Securities, Accretable Yield, Reclassifications to Nonaccretable Difference
definition: Amount of decrease from reclassification to nonaccretable difference of the excess of a loan's cash flows expected to be collected over the investor's initial investment in acquired loans not accounted for as debt securities with evidence of deterioration of credit quality.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Businesses, Gross
definition: The cash outflow associated with the acquisition of business during the period. The cash portion only of the acquisition price.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Marketable Securities
definition: Cash outflow for purchase of trading, available-for-sale securities and held-to-maturity securities.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Noncontrolling Interests
definition: Amount of cash inflow from a noncontrolling interest. Includes, but is not limited to, purchase of additional shares or other increase in noncontrolling interest ownership.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock Redemption Discount
definition: The excess of (1) the carrying amount of the preferred stock in the registrant's balance sheet over (2) the fair value of the consideration transferred to the holders of the preferred stock, during the accounting period, which will be added to net earnings to arrive at net earnings available to common shareholders in the calculation of earnings per share.

elementLabel: Accumulated Amortization, Debt Issuance Costs
definition: Amount of accumulated amortization of debt issuance costs.

elementLabel: Repayments of Convertible Debt
definition: The cash outflow from the repayment of a long-term debt instrument which can be exchanged for a specified amount of another security, typically the entity's common stock, at the option of the issuer or the holder.

elementLabel: Debt and Capital Lease Obligations
definition: Sum of the carrying values as of the balance sheet date of all debt, including all short-term borrowings, long-term debt, and capital lease obligations.

elementLabel: Exploration Expense, Mining
definition: Exploration expenses (including prospecting) related to the mining industry would be included in operating expenses. Exploration costs include costs incurred in identifying areas that may warrant examination and in examining specific areas that are considered to have prospects of mineral reserves.

elementLabel: Other Noncash Income Tax Expense
definition: The portion of the noncash component of income tax expense for the period other than the portion from the net change in the entity's deferred tax assets and liabilities.

elementLabel: Preferred Units, Preferred Partners' Capital Accounts
definition: The amount of the preferred partners' ownership interests.

elementLabel: Due from Related Parties
definition: For an unclassified balance sheet, amounts due from related parties including affiliates, employees, joint ventures, officers and stockholders, immediate families thereof, and pension funds.

elementLabel: Asset-Backed Securities, at Carrying Value
definition: Investments in notes or bonds that are collateralized by a specific group of underlying assets owned by the issuer of the notes or bonds which are short-term, highly liquid investments that are both readily convertible to known amounts of cash and so near their maturity that they present insignificant risk of changes in value because of changes in interest rates. Generally, only investments with original maturities of three months or less qualify under that definition. Original maturity means original maturity to the entity holding the investment. For example, both a three-month US Treasury bill and a three-year Treasury note purchased three months from maturity qualify as cash equivalents. However, a Treasury note purchased three-years ago does not become a cash equivalent when its remaining maturity is three months.

elementLabel: Due from Related Parties, Current
