definition: Fair value of obligations arising from state and municipal debt obligations sold short.

elementLabel: Financial Services Liabilities
definition: For entities that provide full or partial financing and servicing for customers supplementary to its major operations (such as a manufacturer or a homebuilder providing and servicing loans to buyers), represents the liabilities associated with such activities, including accounts payable and accrued liabilities.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Recorded Investment, 90 Days Past Due and Still Accruing
definition: Recorded investment in financing receivables that are 90 days or more past due and still accruing.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Significant Purchases
definition: The amount of any significant purchases of financing receivables during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Significant Sales
definition: The amount of any significant sales of financing receivables during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Core Deposits, Gross
definition: Bank deposits belonging to an acquired bank that can be counted on as a stable source of lending funds. These deposits have the following attributes: predictable costs and low sensitivity to interest rates. This intangible asset is usually amortized over its estimated useful life.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Customer Lists, Gross
definition: Gross carrying amount before accumulated amortization as of the balance sheet date of an asset comprised of customer information, acquired in a business combination or other transaction, having a finite beneficial life.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Noncompete Agreements, Gross
definition: Gross carrying amount before accumulated amortization as of the balance sheet date of payments made to third parties in exchange for their agreement not to engage in specified competitive practices in specified geographic territories for a specified period of time.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Trademarks, Gross
definition: Gross carrying amount before accumulated amortization as of the balance sheet date for the rights acquired through registration of a trademark to gain or protect exclusive use of a business name, symbol or other device or style for a specified period of time.

elementLabel: Finite-Lived Trade Names, Gross
definition: Gross carrying amount before accumulated amortization as of the balance sheet date of the rights acquired through registration of a trade name to gain or protect exclusive use thereof for a reasonably expected period of economic benefit.

elementLabel: Fixtures and Equipment, Gross
definition: Amount before accumulated depreciation of fixtures and equipment. Includes, but is not limited to, machinery, equipment, and engines.

elementLabel: Flight Equipment, Gross
definition: The gross amount of long-lived, depreciable flight assets used in the entity's principle business operations, including owned aircraft and on capital lease, as well as capitalized improvements.

elementLabel: Flight Equipment, Net
definition: The net amount of long-lived, depreciable flight assets used in the entity's principle business operations, including owned aircraft and on capital lease, as well as capitalized improvements.

elementLabel: Food and Beverage Revenue
definition: Revenue from sale of food (prepared and cooked-to-order foodstuffs, as well as snack items) and beverages (bottled or on-tap alcoholic beverages, as well as nonalcoholic beverages like carbonated drinks, juices, energy/sports drinks, water, coffee, and tea).

elementLabel: Foreign Currency Fair Value Hedge Asset at Fair Value
definition: Fair value as of the balance sheet date of all derivative assets designated as foreign currency fair value hedging instruments.

elementLabel: Foreign Financial Institutions, Actual Deposits
definition: The amount of deposits held by branches of foreign institutions.

elementLabel: Foreign Financial Institutions, Actual Reserve Amount
definition: The amount of reserves held by branches of foreign institutions.

elementLabel: Foreign Financial Institutions, Mandated Deposits
definition: The amount of mandated deposits required of branches of foreign institutions.

elementLabel: Foreign Financial Institutions, Mandated Reserve Amount
definition: The mandated reserve amounts required of branches of foreign institutions.

elementLabel: Foreign Reinsurance Transactions, Claims Additions to Underwriting Balances
definition: The amount for insured risks paid or due and owing to the ceding entity, recorded as additions to net premiums written minus net losses paid minus the sum of loss adjustment expenses and underwriting costs and expenses on insurance ceded to companies outside the United States.

elementLabel: Foreign Reinsurance Transactions, Claims Recognized as Income
definition: Amounts for insured risks on policies that have been ceded to entities outside the United States and for which claims income is paid or due and owing to the ceding entity.

elementLabel: Foreign Reinsurance Transactions, Expense Additions to Underwriting Balances
definition: The amount of expenses on insured risks paid or due and owing to the ceding entity, recorded as additions to net premiums written minus net losses paid minus the sum of loss adjustment expenses and underwriting costs and expenses on insurance ceded to companies outside the United States.

elementLabel: Foreign Reinsurance Transactions, Expense Recognized as Income
definition: The amount of insurance policy expenses on insurance that has been ceded to companies outside the United States and for which amounts are paid or due and owing from those foreign companies.

elementLabel: Foreign Reinsurance Transactions, Premium Additions to Underwriting Balances
definition: The amount recorded as additions to net premiums written minus net losses paid minus the sum of loss adjustment expenses and underwriting costs and expenses on insurance ceded to companies outside the United States.

elementLabel: Foreign Reinsurance Transactions, Premiums Recognized as Income
definition: The amount recorded as income on insurance ceded to companies outside the United States.

elementLabel: Foreign Reinsurance under Open Year Method, Claims
definition: Amount of foreign reinsurance claims accounted for under the open year method in the underwriting account.

elementLabel: Foreign Reinsurance under Open Year Method, Expense
definition: Amount of foreign reinsurance expenses accounted for under the open year method in the underwriting account.

elementLabel: Foreign Reinsurance under Open Year Method, Premiums
definition: Amount of foreign reinsurance premiums accounted for under the open year method in the underwriting account.

elementLabel: Forward Contract Indexed to Issuer's Equity, Forward Rate Per Share
definition: The per share price of the Company's stock at which the contract holder of the freestanding contract has the right to purchase or sell the Company's stock at a future date.

elementLabel: Forward Contract Indexed to Issuer's Equity, Indexed Shares
definition: The number of issuer's shares to which the forward contract is indexed.

elementLabel: Forward Contract Indexed to Issuer's Equity, Shares
definition: The maximum number of shares that could be issued to net share settle a contract, if applicable. If a contract does not have a fixed or determinable maximum number of shares that may be required to be issued, disclose the fact that a potentially infinite number of shares could be issued to settle the contract.

elementLabel: Franchise Costs
definition: Costs incurred and are directly related to generating franchise revenues.

elementLabel: Franchisor Costs
definition: Aggregate costs incurred that are directly related to activities, including but not limited to, generating franchise revenues from franchisor owned outlets and franchised outlets.

elementLabel: Franchisor Revenue
definition: Amount of revenue earned from franchisor owned outlets and franchised outlets.

elementLabel: Freight Costs
definition: Cost of freight-in, whether based on weight, negotiated freight rates and method of transportation (that is, rail, barge, truck, and so forth).

elementLabel: Frequent Flier Liability, Current
definition: Value of revenue deferred or cost to provide future products or services, primarily air transportation, associated with programs used by airlines to encourage passenger loyalty by providing rewards geared to the frequency of travel on the sponsoring airline, typically in the form of frequent flyer miles, points, or segments that can be accumulated and converted into free or discounted travel or other redemption options. Used to reflect the current portion of the liability (within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer).

elementLabel: Frequent Flier Liability, Noncurrent
definition: Value of revenue deferred or cost to provide future products or services, primarily air transportation, associated with programs used by airlines to encourage passenger loyalty by providing rewards geared to the frequency of travel on the sponsoring airline, typically in the form of frequent flyer miles, points, or segments that can be accumulated and converted into free or discounted travel or other redemption options. Used to reflect the noncurrent portion of the liability.

elementLabel: Fuel Costs, Gross of Hedging
definition: The cost for fuel, incurred during the period, before considering the impacts of any related hedging activities.

elementLabel: Funds Held for Clients
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the funds held on behalf of others and that are expected to be liquidated within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer. This does not include funds held under reinsurance agreements.

elementLabel: Funds Held under Reinsurance Agreements, Asset
definition: Amount of the reinsurer's funds held on its behalf by the ceding insurer, including funds held in trust, under reinsurance treaties or contracts with the assuming insurer as security for the payment of the obligations thereunder.

elementLabel: Funds Held under Reinsurance Agreements, Liability
definition: Amount of funds held as security for payments to be received under reinsurance contracts.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Thereafter
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, within Five Years
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, within Four Years
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Future Minimum Sublease Rentals, Sale Leaseback Transactions, within Three Years
definition: Amount of minimum sublease rentals for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing to be received by the seller-lessee in the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Gain from Components Excluded from Assessment of Cash Flow Hedge Effectiveness
definition: The gain relating to components of the gain (loss) on the cash flow hedging instrument excluded from the assessment of cash flow hedge effectiveness. Recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Gain from Components Excluded from Assessment of Fair Value Hedge Effectiveness
definition: Gain relating to components of the gain (loss) on the fair value hedging instrument excluded from the assessment of fair value hedge effectiveness. Recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Gain from Hedged Firm Commitment Not Qualifying as Fair Value Hedge
definition: Amount of gain recognized in earnings when a hedged firm commitment no longer qualifies as a fair value hedge.

elementLabel: Gain on Discontinuation of Cash Flow Hedge Due to Forecasted Transaction Probable of Not Occurring
definition: The amount of gain reclassified into earnings in the period when cash flow hedge is discontinued because it is probable that the original forecasted transactions will not occur by the end of the original period or an additional two month time period.

elementLabel: Gain on Fair Value Hedge Ineffectiveness
definition: Amount of gain recognized in the income statement from the hedging ineffectiveness of a fair value hedge.

elementLabel: Gain Recognized on Assets Transferred to Separate Account, Gross
definition: Amount of gain recognized during the reporting period on assets that were transferred into separate accounts.

elementLabel: Gas Balancing Payable, Current
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred and payable to an underproduced working interest owner when an overproduced working interest owner has sold gas in excess of the party's ownership percentage. Used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer).

elementLabel: Gas Balancing Payable
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred and payable to an underproduced working interest owner when an overproduced working interest owner has sold gas in excess of the party's ownership percentage.

elementLabel: Gas Purchase Payable, Current
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred and payable for purchases of natural gas. Used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer).

elementLabel: Gas Purchase Payable
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred and payable for purchases of natural gas.

elementLabel: General and Administrative Costs in Inventory, Amount Incurred
definition: Aggregate amount of general and administrative costs incurred in each period and charged to inventory.

elementLabel: General and Administrative Costs in Inventory, Amount Remaining
definition: Actual or estimated amount of general and administrative costs remaining in inventory.

elementLabel: General Contractor Revenue
definition: The aggregate revenue from general contracting services, which may include directly performed or subcontracted plumbing, electrical work, drywall and plaster installation, steel erection, painting, glass work, utility line construction, and other specialty trade services.

elementLabel: General Partners' Capital Account, Units Authorized
definition: The number of general partner units authorized to be issued.

elementLabel: General Partners' Capital Account, Units Issued
definition: The number of general partner units issued.

elementLabel: General Partners' Capital Account, Units Outstanding
definition: The number of general partner units outstanding.

elementLabel: General Partners' Contributed Capital
definition: The amount of capital contributed by the general partner.

elementLabel: General Partners' Cumulative Cash Distributions
definition: Aggregate cumulative cash distributions made to the general partner.

elementLabel: Gold Products and Services Revenue
definition: Revenue derived from sale of gold and related products. Also includes rendering of services and selling of products for exploration, development, mining, and processing, as well as supporting activities.

elementLabel: Good Faith and Margin Deposits with Broker-Dealers
definition: Amount of right to receive cash and securities on deposit with broker-dealers to demonstrate an intention to complete a purchase (good faith deposit) and collateral deposited by counterparty to cover the credit risk assumed (margin deposit).

elementLabel: Goodwill, Not Allocated, Amount
definition: Portion of goodwill not yet allocated to reportable segments.

elementLabel: Government Contract Receivable
definition: The amount of receivables that are derived from government contracts.

elementLabel: Government Contract Receivable, Progress Payments Offset
definition: The amount of progress payments offset against unbilled government contract receivables.

elementLabel: Grandfathered ESOP Expense Recognition, Actual Interest Incurred on ESOP Debt
definition: For grandfathered ESOP shares acquired prior to January 1, 1993, the actual interest incurred on debt for obligations that the employer may secure on behalf of the ESOP.

elementLabel: Grandfathered ESOP Expense Recognition, Cash Contributions to ESOP
definition: For grandfathered ESOP shares acquired prior to January 1, 1993, the amount of cash contributions made to the ESOP.

elementLabel: Grandfathered ESOP Expense Recognition, Dividends Paid to ESOP
definition: For grandfathered ESOP shares acquired prior to January 1, 1993, the dividends paid to the ESOP.

elementLabel: Grandfathered ESOP Expense Recognition, Dividends Used by ESOP for Debt Service
definition: For grandfathered ESOP shares acquired prior to January 1, 1993, the amount of ESOP dividends used to pay debt service by the sop.

elementLabel: Grants Receivable
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of amounts due under the terms of governmental, corporate, or foundation grants.

elementLabel: Grants Receivable, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying amount due after one year of the balance sheet date (or one operating cycle, if longer) of amounts due under the terms of governmental, corporate, or foundation grants.

elementLabel: Gross Billings
definition: Disclosure of gross transaction volume for revenues which are reported net.

elementLabel: Guaranteed Interest Contracts
definition: The amount of the liability as of the balance sheet date pertaining to the guarantee given by the insurance entity to contract holders of a specified rate of return (a guaranteed yield) on their investments for a specified period.

elementLabel: Guarantees, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of guarantee, including, but not limited to, financial standby letter of credit, fair value guarantee, guarantee of collection of scheduled contractual cash flows from financial assets, and contracts that contingently require the guarantor to make payments or perform services.

elementLabel: Guaranty Assets
definition: The carrying amount of the contractual right to receive fees, as compensation in exchange for providing a guarantee to a third party, over life of the guarantee.

elementLabel: Guaranty Liabilities
definition: This item represents a non-contingent liability for the fair value of an obligation to stand ready to perform over the term of a guaranty issued in the event that specified triggering events or conditions occur.

elementLabel: Haircuts on Bankers' Acceptances, Certificates of Deposit and Commercial Paper
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on Bankers' Acceptances, Certificates of Deposit and Commercial Paper.

elementLabel: Haircuts on Contractual Securities Commitments
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on security collateral commitments.

elementLabel: Haircuts on Corporate Obligations
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on corporate obligations.

elementLabel: Haircuts on Options
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on options.

elementLabel: Haircuts on Securities
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on securities.

elementLabel: Haircuts on Securities Collateralizing Secured Demand Notes
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on securities collateralizing secured demand notes.

elementLabel: Haircuts on State and Municipal Government Obligations
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on State and Municipal Government Obligations.

elementLabel: Haircuts on Stocks and Warrants
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on stocks and warrants.

elementLabel: Haircuts on Trading and Investment Securities
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on trading and investment securities.

elementLabel: Haircuts on Undue Concentrations
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on undue concentrations.

elementLabel: Haircuts on US and Canadian Government Obligations
definition: Percentage deduction to take into account portfolio and market risk on US and Canadian Government Obligations.

elementLabel: Haircuts, Other
definition: Amount of deduction to take into account portfolio and market risks on securities, classified as other.

elementLabel: Health Care Organization, Capitation Revenue
definition: Amount of revenue recognized based on fees charged on a per capita basis.

elementLabel: Health Care Organization, Contract Acquisition Expense
definition: Costs associated with marketing of subscriber contracts and member enrollments. For example, commissions paid to agents or brokers and incentive compensation based on new enrollments. Includes also salaries of the marketing director and staff, general marketing brochures, and general advertising and promotion expenses.

elementLabel: Health Care Organization, Expenses, Gross
definition: Total expenses of a HCO before stop-loss insurance recoveries. Costs of services rendered (including costs of services rendered but not yet reported).

elementLabel: Health Care Organization, Medical Supplies and Drugs Expense
definition: Amount of medical supplies consumed, for example, but not limited to, bandages, syringes and drugs, for patient care.

elementLabel: Health Care Organization, Resident Service Revenue
definition: Amount of revenues recognized from services provided to residents in facilities owned or operated by the health care organization (not including patient service revenue), which may be based on contractual rates set forth in agreements with third-party payers.

elementLabel: Health Care Organization, Stop Loss Insurance Premium Expense
definition: Stop-loss insurance premiums recognized as expense. In stop-loss insurance, prepaid health care providers or associated entities transfer portions of their financial risks to other companies. A provider typically contracts to recover health care costs in excess of stated amounts during the contract periods.

elementLabel: Health Care Organization, Stop Loss Insurance Recoveries
definition: Amount of stop-loss insurance recoveries. In stop-loss insurance, prepaid health care providers or associated entities transfer portions of their financial risks to other companies. A provider typically contracts to recover health care costs in excess of stated amounts during the contract periods.

elementLabel: Health Care Trust Fund, Assets Limited as to Use, Current
definition: The portion of trust fund assets classified as current assets because they are expected to be liquidated to pay current liabilities as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Health Care Trust Fund, Assets Limited as to Use, Noncurrent
definition: Total trust fund assets, excluding those classified as current assets because they are expected to be liquidated to pay current liabilities as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Hedging Assets, Current
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the asset arising from a financial instrument or a contract used to mitigate a specified risk (hedge), and which are expected to be converted into cash or otherwise disposed of within a year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Hedging Assets, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the asset arising from a financial instrument or a contract used to hedge price changes in underlying assets, and which are expected to be converted into cash or otherwise disposed of after a year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Hedging Liabilities, Current
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the liability arising from a financial instrument or a contract used to mitigate a specified risk (hedge), and which are expected to be converted into cash or otherwise disposed of within a year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Amortized Cost before Other than Temporary Impairment
definition: Amount before other than temporary impairment (OTTI) accretion, of investments in debt securities classified as held-to-maturity.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Current
definition: Amount after other than temporary impairment (OTTI) accretion, of investments in debt securities classified as held-to-maturity, expected to be converted to cash, sold or exchanged within one year or the normal operating cycle.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, without Single Maturity Date, Fair Value
definition: Amount of held-to-maturity debt securities at fair value that do not have a single maturity date and which the entity has decided to disclose separately rather than allocating the fair value over several maturity groupings.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Debt Maturities, without Single Maturity Date, Net Carrying Amount
definition: Carrying amount of debt securities accounted for as held-to-maturity, net of adjustments including, but not limited to, accretion, amortization, collection of cash, previous other-than-temporary impairments (OTTI) recognized, and fair value hedge accounting adjustments, over several maturity groupings.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of investments in debt securities classified as held-to-maturity.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Gross Gains, Derivatives
definition: This item represents, as of the balance sheet date, the gross gains in accumulated other comprehensive income, a separate component of shareholders' equity, for any derivatives that hedged the forecasted acquisition of held-to-maturity securities.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Gross Losses, Derivatives
definition: This item represents, as of the balance sheet date, the gross losses in accumulated other comprehensive income, a separate component of shareholders' equity, for any derivatives that hedged the forecasted acquisition of held-to-maturity securities.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity, Securities in Unrealized Loss Positions, Qualitative Disclosure, Number of Positions
definition: Disclosure regarding factors used to determine that the impairment of securities categorized as held-to-maturity where cost exceeds fair value is not an other than temporary impairment (OTTI). This item contains disclosure of the number of investment positions in the held-to-maturity investments determined to be temporarily impaired.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity, Securities in Unrealized Loss Positions, Qualitative Disclosure, Other, Default Rate
definition: This item represents the default rate of the underlying assets in the security that were considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are not other-than-temporarily impaired.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity, Securities in Unrealized Loss Positions, Qualitative Disclosure, Other, Delinquency Rate
definition: This item represents the delinquency rate of the underlying assets in the security that were considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are not other-than-temporarily impaired.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity, Securities in Unrealized Loss Positions, Qualitative Disclosure, Other, Fair Value Volatility, Rate
definition: This item represents the volatility rate related to the fair value of the underlying assets in the security, represented as a percentage, which was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are not other-than-temporarily impaired.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity, Securities in Unrealized Loss Positions, Qualitative Disclosure, Other, Level of Subordination
definition: This item represents the current level of subordination of the entity's receipt of consideration should the assets underlying the security be liquidated when the level of subordination was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are not other-than-temporarily impaired.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity, Securities in Unrealized Loss Positions, Qualitative Disclosure, Other, Percentage of Nonperforming Assets
definition: This item represents the percentage of nonperforming assets that the underlying assets in the security represent and which were considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are not other-than-temporarily impaired.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity, Securities in Unrealized Loss Positions, Qualitative Disclosure, Other, Third Party Guarantees, Amount
definition: Amount of third party guarantees against loss of value in the underlying assets of a held-to-maturity security in an unrealized loss position and for which other-than-temporary impairments (OTTI) have not been recognized.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Noncurrent
definition: Amount after other than temporary impairment (OTTI) accretion, of investments in debt securities classified as held-to-maturity, not expected to be converted to cash, sold or exchanged within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities Pledged as Collateral
definition: The carrying amount of held-to-maturity securities that serve as collateral for borrowings.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Restricted
definition: The carrying amount of securities categorized as held-to-maturity which serve as security for borrowings or other arrangements.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Restricted, Current
definition: This item represents investments in debt securities which are categorized as held-to-maturity and that have scheduled maturities within one year of the balance sheet date or the normal operating cycle, whichever is longer, and that are pledged to one or more secured parties who have the right to buy, sell, or re-pledge the collateral.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Restricted, Noncurrent
definition: This item represents investments in debt securities which are categorized as held-to-maturity and that have scheduled maturities more than one year from the balance sheet date or operating cycle, if longer, and that are pledged to one or more secured parties who have the right to buy, sell, or re-pledge the collateral.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Sold at Par
definition: The aggregate value of securities held, which were categorized as held-to-maturity, for which the interest rate reset through an auction process, that failed to be liquidated through auction, and which were sold at par value during the period.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Sold Security, at Carrying Value
definition: For any sales of securities categorized as held-to-maturity, this item represents the net carrying amount of the sold security.

elementLabel: Held-to-maturity Securities, Transferred Security, at Carrying Value
definition: For any transfer of securities categorized as held-to-maturity, this item represents the net carrying amount of the transferred security to another category of investments in debt and equity securities (trading or available-for-sale).

elementLabel: Home Building Revenue
definition: Revenue related to the sale of homes and home building activities including design, development, general contracting, and renovation services for residential buildings, including single-family houses, multifamily housing, townhouses, apartments, and modular housing.

elementLabel: Impaired Financing Receivable, Unpaid Principal Balance
definition: Amount of unpaid principal balance of impaired financing receivables with related allowance for credit losses and without related allowance for credit losses.

elementLabel: Impairment of Retained Interest
definition: The charge against earnings to reduce the carrying value of an interest continued to be held by the transferor in a securitized financial instrument.

elementLabel: Incentive Distribution, Distribution Per Unit
definition: Per-share or per-unit amount of incentive dividend declared and paid to managing member or general partner.

elementLabel: Incentive from Lessor
definition: This item represents the deferred credit for an incentive or inducement received by a lessee from a lessor, in order to motivate the lessee to enter the lease agreement, which incentive or inducement is to be recognized as a reduction of rental expense over the lease term.

elementLabel: Incentive to Lessee
definition: This item represents the deferred charge for an incentive or inducement granted by a lessor to a lessee, in order to motivate the lessee to enter the lease agreement, which incentive or inducement is to be recognized as a reduction of rental revenue over the lease term.

elementLabel: Income Taxes Receivable, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying amount due after one year of the balance sheet date (or one operating cycle, if longer) from tax authorities as of the balance sheet date representing refunds of overpayments or recoveries based on agreed-upon resolutions of disputes.

elementLabel: Incremental Common Shares Attributable to Dilutive Effect of Conversion of Debt Securities
definition: Additional shares included in the calculation of diluted EPS as a result of the potentially dilutive effect of convertible debt securities using the if-converted method.

elementLabel: Incremental Common Shares Attributable to Dilutive Effect of Equity Forward Agreements
definition: Additional shared included in the calculation of diluted EPS as a result of the potentially dilutive effect of equity forward arrangements using the reverse treasury stock method.

elementLabel: Incremental Common Shares Attributable to Dilutive Effect of Equity Unit Purchase Agreements
definition: Additional shares included in the calculation of diluted EPS as a result of the potentially dilutive effect of equity unit purchase agreements using the treasury stock method.

elementLabel: Incremental Common Shares Attributable to Dilutive Effect of Written Put Options
definition: Additional shares included in the calculation of diluted EPS as a result of the potentially dilutive effect of outstanding written put options using the reverse treasury stock method.

elementLabel: Indefinite-Lived Contractual Rights
definition: Carrying amount (original costs adjusted for previously recognized amortization and impairment) as of the balance sheet date of rights with an indefinite period of benefit that arose from a contractual arrangement with a third party (not including franchise rights and license agreements).

elementLabel: Indefinite-Lived Domestic Slots and Routes
definition: Carrying amount, (original cost adjusted for any previously recognized amortization and impairment) as of the balance sheet date, of domestic slots, route authorities, airport operating and gate lease rights and related intangibles.

elementLabel: Indefinite-Lived Franchise Rights
definition: Carrying amount (original costs adjusted for previously recognized amortization and impairment) as of the balance sheet date for the rights acquired through a franchise arrangement having an indefinite period of benefit.

elementLabel: Indefinite-Lived International Slots and Routes
definition: Carrying amount, (original cost adjusted for any previously recognized amortization and impairment) as of the balance sheet date, of international slots, route authorities, airport operating and gate lease rights and related intangibles.

elementLabel: Indefinite-Lived License Agreements
definition: Carrying amount (original costs adjusted for previously recognized amortization and impairment) as of the balance sheet date for the capitalized costs to acquire rights under a license arrangement (for example, to sell specified products in a specified territory) having an indefinite period of benefit.

elementLabel: Indefinite-Lived Slots and Routes
definition: Carrying amount, (original cost adjusted for any previously recognized amortization and impairment) as of the balance sheet date, of slots, route authorities, airport operating and gate lease rights and related intangibles.

elementLabel: Indefinite-Lived Trademarks
definition: Carrying amount (original costs adjusted for previously recognized amortization and impairment) as of the balance sheet date for the rights acquired through registration of a trademark to gain or protect exclusive use of a business name, symbol or other device or style for a projected indefinite period of benefit.

elementLabel: Indefinite-Lived Trade Names
definition: Carrying amount (original costs adjusted for previously recognized amortization and impairment) as of the balance sheet date for the rights acquired through registration of a trade name to gain or protect exclusive use thereof for a projected indefinite period of benefit.

elementLabel: Initial Franchise Fees
definition: The amount of initial franchise fees.

elementLabel: Insurance Agency Management Fee
definition: Fees earned during the period for providing management services.

elementLabel: Insurance Investment Income
definition: Investment income associated with the company's insurance services.

elementLabel: Insurance Receivable for Malpractice
definition: The amount receivable from insurance and similar arrangements for reimbursement and payment of malpractice claims and litigation costs.

elementLabel: Insurance Receivable for Malpractice, Current
definition: The current portion of the amount receivable from insurance and similar arrangements for reimbursement and payment of malpractice claims and litigation costs.

elementLabel: Insurance Receivable for Malpractice, Noncurrent
definition: The noncurrent portion of the receivable from insurance and similar arrangements for reimbursement and payment of malpractice claims and litigation costs.

elementLabel: Insurance Settlements Receivable
definition: Amount due in settlement of a claim for reimbursement from an insurance company when the Company has suffered a loss covered under an insurance policy.

elementLabel: Insurance Settlements Receivable, Current
definition: Amount due in settlement of a claim for reimbursement from an insurance company when the Company has suffered a loss covered under an insurance policy. For classified balance sheets, represents the current amount receivable, that is amounts expected to be collected within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Insurance Settlements Receivable, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying amount due after one year of the balance sheet date (or one operating cycle, if longer) of amount due in settlement of a claim for reimbursement from an insurance company when the Company has suffered a loss covered under an insurance policy.

elementLabel: Insurance Tax
definition: Represents total insurance tax expense reflected in the income statement for each period presented.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the intangible assets from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Additions
definition: Additions in intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination during the year.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Dispositions
definition: Amount of the decrease in the period in the intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination attributable to dispositions of the underlying insurance contracts.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Percentage of Amount Amortized, Year Five
definition: Estimated percentage of the remaining ending balance as of the most recent fiscal year-end of the intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination to be amortized in the fifth year following that balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Percentage of Amount Amortized, Year Four
definition: Estimated percentage of the remaining ending balance as of the most recent fiscal year-end of the intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination to be amortized in the fourth year following that balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Percentage of Amount Amortized, Year One
definition: Estimated percentage of the remaining balance as of the most recent fiscal year-end of the intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination to be amortized in the first year following that balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Percentage of Amount Amortized, Year Three
definition: Estimated percentage of the remaining ending balance as of the most recent fiscal year-end of the intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination to be amortized in the third year following that balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Intangible Assets Arising from Insurance Contracts Acquired in Business Combination, Percentage of Amount Amortized, Year Two
definition: Estimated percentage of the remaining ending balance as of the most recent fiscal year-end of the intangible assets arising from insurance contracts acquired in a business combination to be amortized in the second year following that balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Interest and Dividends Payable, Current
definition: Sum of the carrying values as of the balance sheet date of (a) interest payable on all forms of debt, including trade payables, that has been incurred, and (b) dividends declared but unpaid on equity securities issued by the entity and outstanding (also includes dividends collected on behalf of another owner of securities that are being held by the entity). Used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer).

elementLabel: Interest and Dividends Payable
definition: Sum of the carrying values as of the balance sheet date of (a) interest payable on all forms of debt, including trade payables, that has been incurred, and (b) dividends declared but unpaid on equity securities issued by the entity and outstanding (also includes dividends collected on behalf of another owner of securities that are being held by the entity).

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Deposit Liabilities
definition: The aggregate of all domestic and foreign interest-bearing deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Deposit Liabilities, Domestic
definition: Total amount of interest-bearing domestic deposit liabilities, which may include brokered, retail, demand, checking, notice of withdrawal, money market and other interest-bearing deposits.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Deposit Liabilities, Foreign
definition: Amount of foreign interest-bearing deposits held by the entity.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Brokered
definition: Amount of interest-bearing domestic third-party deposits placed by or through the assistance of a deposit broker, also known as brokered deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Certificates of Deposits
definition: Amount of interest-bearing domestic certificate of deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Money Market
definition: Amount of interest-bearing domestic money market demand account deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Negotiable Order of Withdrawal (NOW)
definition: Amount of interest-bearing domestic negotiable order of withdrawal (NOW) demand deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Other Time Deposit
definition: Amount of interest-bearing domestic deposit liabilities classified as other. Excludes certificates of deposit.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Retail
definition: Amount of interest-bearing domestic retail deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Savings
definition: Amount of interest-bearing domestic savings deposit liabilities. Saving deposits bear interest and have no stated maturity.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Foreign Deposit, Brokered
definition: Amount of interest-bearing foreign third-party deposits placed by or through the assistance of a deposit broker, also known as brokered deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Foreign Deposit, Certificates of Deposits
definition: Amount of interest-bearing certificates of deposit liabilities in foreign banking offices.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Foreign Deposit, Checking
definition: Amount of interest-bearing checking deposit liabilities in foreign banking offices.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Foreign Deposit, Demand
definition: Amount of money in interest-bearing foreign accounts that entitle the depositor to withdraw funds at any time without prior notice, also known as demand deposits. Checking and negotiable order withdrawals (NOW) are the most common forms of demand deposits.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Foreign Deposit, Money Market
definition: Amount of interest-bearing money market demand account deposit liabilities in foreign banking offices.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Foreign Deposit, Negotiable Order of Withdrawal (NOW)
definition: Amount of interest-bearing negotiable order of withdrawal (NOW) deposit liabilities in foreign banking offices.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Foreign Deposit, Other Time Deposits
definition: Amount of interest-bearing time deposit liabilities other than certificates of deposit in foreign banking offices.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Foreign Deposit, Retail
definition: Amount of interest-bearing retail deposit liabilities in foreign banking offices.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Foreign Deposit, Savings
definition: Amount of interest-bearing savings deposit liabilities in foreign banking offices.

elementLabel: Interest-bearing Foreign Deposit, Time Deposits
definition: Amount of interest-bearing time deposits in foreign banking offices. Time deposits bear interest for a fixed, stated period of time and include certificate of deposits and individual retirement accounts.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Deposits from Other Federal Home Loan Banks
definition: Amount of interest expense on interest-bearing deposits from another Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities
definition: Aggregate amount of all interest expense on domestic deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Brokered
definition: Amount of interest expense on domestic brokered deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Certificates of Deposit
definition: Amount of interest expense on domestic certificates of deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Checking
definition: Amount of interest expense on domestic checking deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Demand
definition: Amount of interest expense on domestic demand deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Money Market
definition: Amount of interest expense on domestic money market demand account deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Other Time Deposit
definition: Amount of interest expense on domestic time deposit liabilities other than certificates of liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Retail
definition: Amount of interest expense on domestic retail deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Savings
definition: Amount of interest expense on domestic savings deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense Domestic Deposit Liabilities, Time Deposit
definition: Amount of interest expense on time deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Interest Expense, Loans from Other Federal Home Loan Banks
definition: Amount of interest expense on loans received from another Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLB).

elementLabel: Interest Income, Deposits with Other Federal Home Loan Banks
definition: Amount of interest income from interest-bearing funds deposited into another Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Interest Income, Loans to Other Federal Home Loan Banks
definition: Amount of interest income from loans to another Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Interest Paid, Discontinued Operations
definition: The amount of cash paid during the current period for interest owed on debt associated with discontinued operations.

elementLabel: Interest Receivable, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of noncurrent interest earned but not received. Also called accrued interest or accrued interest receivable.

elementLabel: Transferor's Interests in Transferred Financial Assets, Fair Value
definition: The carrying amount (fair value) as of the balance sheet date of the transferor's interests in transferred financial assets (typically securitized receivables, generally not involved in the collection of principal) following transfer of significant portions of such financial instruments to other parties. Such interests could be ancillary cash flows and interest-only strips.

elementLabel: Interim Period, Costs Not Allocable Amount, First Item
definition: The amount of the cost or expense incurred during an interim period that cannot be readily identified with the activities or benefits of other interim periods and are charged to the interim period in which incurred.

elementLabel: Interim Period, Costs Not Allocable Amount, Second Item
definition: The amount of the cost or expense incurred during an interim period that cannot be readily identified with the activities or benefits of other interim periods and are charged to the interim period in which incurred.

elementLabel: Interim Period, Costs Not Allocable Amount, Third Item
definition: The amount of the cost or expense incurred during an interim period that cannot be readily identified with the activities or benefits of other interim periods and are charged to the interim period in which incurred.

elementLabel: Intermediate-life Plants, Accumulated Costs
definition: The amount of accumulated costs related to intermediate-life plants.

elementLabel: Inventory Amount, Unpriced Change Orders for Long-term Contracts or Programs
definition: Amount of unpriced change orders or other similar items subject to uncertainty concerning their determination or ultimate realization included in inventory as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Inventory, Buildings and Improvements
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of building structures held as inventory including any additions, improvements, or renovations to those structures.

elementLabel: Energy Related Inventory, Crude Oil, Products and Merchandise
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of finished goods inventories for petroleum products, crude oil, petrochemical products, and other oil and gas inventories.

elementLabel: Inventory, Finished Goods and Work in Process, Gross
definition: Amount before valuation reserves of merchandise or goods held by the entity that are readily available for sale and items held by the entity which are partially complete or in the process of being readied for sale.

elementLabel: Inventory, Finished Goods and Work in Process, Net of Reserves
definition: The aggregated amount of merchandise or goods held by the entity and readily available for future sale plus items held by the entity which are partially complete or in the process of being readied for future sale. This amount is net of valuation reserves and adjustments.

elementLabel: Inventory, Finished Homes
definition: The carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of homes that have been finished and are ready for sale, net of valuation allowance and impairment loss.

elementLabel: Inventory for Long-term Contracts or Programs, Gross
definition: Amount before valuation and LIFO reserves, and progress payments, of inventory associated with long-term contracts, expected to be sold, or consumed within one year or operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Inventory for Long-term Contracts or Programs, General and Administrative Costs Included in Inventory
definition: The actual or estimated amount of general and administrative expense remaining in inventory as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Inventory for Long-term Contracts or Programs, General and Administrative Expense Incurred
definition: Amount of general and administrative costs charged to inventory.

elementLabel: Inventory, Gas in Storage Underground, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of natural gas stored underground in depleted gas reservoirs, aquifers, or salt caverns to meet future seasonal and peak load demands and also as insurance against unforeseen supply disruptions, and deemed to be a noncurrent asset because it is not expected to be used within 12 months or in the normal operating cycle.

elementLabel: Inventory, Homes under Construction
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of capitalized construction costs of homes for future sale.

elementLabel: Inventory, Land Held for Development and Sale
definition: Carrying amount net of impairment reserves as of the balance sheet date primarily consisting of deposits for land purchases (including option payments), related acquisition costs, and land which is not expected to be developed in the next two years.

elementLabel: Inventory, Land Held-for-sale
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of parcels of land held for sale, and on which the entity has no intention or no further intention to perform construction activities.

elementLabel: Inventory, Operative Builders
definition: The net carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the sum of the various components of an operative builder's inventory, including finished homes. Operative builders primarily consist of entities that develop land, construct residential homes and commercial and industrial buildings thereon, and sell them to home buyers and operators of the commercial and industrial properties.

elementLabel: Inventory, Operative Builders, Other
definition: Amount of inventory used in the development of real estate classified as other.

elementLabel: Inventory, Ore Stockpiles on Leach Pads, Gross
definition: Amount before last-in first-out (LIFO) and valuation reserves of ore stockpile material contained on a leach pad, for example, but not limited to, copper or gold ore.

elementLabel: Inventory, Parts and Components, Net of Reserves
definition: Carrying amount, net of valuation reserves and adjustments, as of the balance sheet date for elements of machinery or equipment held for the purpose of replacing similar parts in the course of repair or maintenance.

elementLabel: Inventory, Raw Materials and Purchased Parts, Net of Reserves
definition: Carrying amount, net of valuation reserves and adjustments, as of the balance sheet date of items purchased for use as components of a finished product or pieces of machinery and equipment plus any items in their natural and unrefined state. This element may be used when the reporting entity combines raw materials and purchased parts into an aggregate amount.

elementLabel: Inventory, Raw Materials and Supplies, Gross
definition: Gross amount of unprocessed materials to be used in manufacturing or production process and supplies that will be consumed.

elementLabel: Inventory, Raw Materials and Supplies, Net of Reserves
definition: Aggregated amount of unprocessed materials to be used in manufacturing or production process and supplies that will be consumed. This amount is net of valuation reserves and adjustments.

elementLabel: Inventory, Raw Materials, Net of Reserves
definition: Carrying amount, net of valuation reserves and adjustments, as of the balance sheet date of unprocessed items to be consumed in the manufacturing or production process.

elementLabel: Inventory, Real Estate
definition: Total of (1) improvements, (2) held-for-sale, (3) land and land under development, (4) construction-in-process, (5) mortgage loans held-in-inventory, and (6) other real estate investments which are considered inventory due to being held for sale or disposition.

elementLabel: Inventory, Real Estate, Construction in Process
definition: Cost of real estate projects incurred for projects for eventual sale or transfer (condominium or time share projects, vacation clubs).

elementLabel: Inventory, Real Estate, Held-for-sale
definition: Represents properties which were acquired directly or through foreclosure for which a committed plan to sell exists and an active program to market such properties has been initiated.

elementLabel: Inventory, Real Estate, Improvements
definition: Represents improvements to real estate during development for ultimate sale to third parties. Improvements may consist of project infrastructure and other expenditures necessary to completion of the development project which is generally of a long-term nature.

elementLabel: Inventory, Real Estate, Land and Land Development Costs
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date, net of valuation allowances and impairment losses, of costs of land expected to be developed in the near term plus capitalized costs of development, for purposes of selling completed units to home buyers or commercial or industrial entities..

elementLabel: Inventory, Real Estate, Mortgage Loans Held in Inventory
definition: Represents mortgage loans held in inventory primarily for sale to others (third parties, businesses, legal entities) in the ordinary course of business.

elementLabel: Inventory, Real Estate, Other
definition: Amount of investment in certain other real estate investments not specifically identified elsewhere in the existing taxonomy.

elementLabel: Inventory, Real Estate, Timeshare Available-for-sale
definition: Amount of real estate which is available for sale in the form of shared property ownership in which rights vest in several owners (buyers, timeshare holders) to use the property for a specified period each year (timeshare). Included in this item would be real estate assets in which timeshares are for sale, such as in condominiums at timeshare resorts. Excluded from this item would be assets, other than real estate, in which the Entity has sold or intends to sell timeshares, such as for cruises, recreational vehicles, campgrounds, aircraft (fractional ownership) and other types of rights.

elementLabel: Investment in Federal Home Loan Bank Stock, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of investments in Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) stock.

elementLabel: Investment in Physical Commodities
definition: Investments held in physical commodities, such as gold, silver, platinum, crude oil, coal, sugar, rice, wheat.

elementLabel: Investment-related Liabilities
definition: The aggregate amount of liabilities as of the balance sheet date for obligations incurred in connection with the entity's investments.

elementLabel: Investments and Other Noncurrent Assets
definition: Amount of investments, and noncurrent assets classified as other.

elementLabel: Investments in Power and Distribution Projects
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of investments in power and distribution projects that are expected to be realized after one year or beyond the operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Items Included in Consolidated Statement of Financial Condition
definition: Total indebtedness included on the balance sheet.

elementLabel: Items Not Included in Consolidated Statement of Financial Condition
definition: Indebtedness not included on the balance sheet.

elementLabel: Japanese Welfare Pension Insurance Law, Government Subsidies
definition: The amount of the subsidy from the transfer of employee pension fund liabilities to the Japanese government. The amount of this subsidy excludes any amounts related to previously accrued salary progression.

elementLabel: Japanese Welfare Pension Insurance Law, Previously Accrued Salary Progression Derecognition
definition: The amount of the derecognition of previously accrued salary progression.

elementLabel: Junior Subordinated Debenture Owed to Unconsolidated Subsidiary Trust
definition: Including the current and noncurrent portions, the carrying value of junior subordinated long-term debt owed to unconsolidated subsidiary trusts as of the balance sheet date. Such debt places a lender in a lien position behind debt having a higher priority of repayment in liquidation of the entity's assets and was initially scheduled to be repaid after one year or beyond the normal operating cycle if longer.

elementLabel: Junior Subordinated Debenture Owed to Unconsolidated Subsidiary Trust, Noncurrent
definition: The noncurrent portion of the carrying value of junior subordinated long-term debt owed to unconsolidated subsidiary trusts as of the balance sheet date. Such debt places a lender in a lien position behind debt having a higher priority of repayment in liquidation of the entity's assets and was initially scheduled to be repaid after one year or beyond the normal operating cycle if longer.

elementLabel: Junior Subordinated Notes, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of long-term debt (with maturities initially due after one year or beyond the operating cycle if longer) identified as Junior Subordinated Notes, which have a lower priority than senior instruments, excluding current portion.

elementLabel: Junior Subordinated Notes, Current
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of portion of long-term debt due within one year or the operating cycle if longer identified as Junior Subordinated Notes, which have a lower priority than senior instruments.

elementLabel: Land Available for Development
definition: Carrying amount of land available for development.

elementLabel: Land Available-for-sale
definition: Carrying value of land held for sale.

elementLabel: Land Improvements
definition: Amount before accumulated deprecation and depletion of additions or improvements to real estate held for productive use. Examples include, but are not limited to, walkways, driveways, fences, and parking lots.

elementLabel: Landing Fees and Other Rentals
definition: Direct costs incurred at airports in which the entity conducts flight operations. The costs primarily consist of fees paid to the airport authority for takeoff and landing, gate space and facilities, allocations of common space such as security and other terminal costs and fuel storage facilities.

elementLabel: Land under Purchase Options, Not Recorded
definition: Discloses the total purchase price of land option agreements that were not recorded.

elementLabel: Land under Purchase Options, Recorded
definition: The carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of land not owned but under a contract in which the entity has an option to purchase the land.

elementLabel: Late Fee Income Generated by Servicing Financial Assets, Amount
definition: All amounts that are due to the servicer of a financial asset as a result of the debt holder not meeting the monthly payment terms.

elementLabel: Lease Incentive, Payable, Current
definition: This item represents an incentive or inducement contractually stipulated between parties to a lease whereby the lessor has committed to provide the entity (lessee) with a cash payment as inducement to enter the lease. Used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer).

elementLabel: Lease Incentive, Payable
definition: This item represents an incentive or inducement contractually stipulated between parties to a lease whereby the lessor has committed to provide the entity (lessee) with a cash payment as inducement to enter the lease.

elementLabel: Lease Incentive Receivable
definition: This item represents a receivable for an incentive or inducement contractually stipulated between parties to a lease whereby the lessor has committed to provide the entity (lessee) with a cash payment as inducement to enter the lease.

elementLabel: Lease Incentive Receivable, Current
definition: This item represents the current receivable for an incentive or inducement contractually stipulated between parties to a lease whereby the lessor has committed to provide the entity (lessee) with a cash payment as inducement to enter the lease. The receivable is due within one year. For classified balance sheets, this element represents the current amount receivable, that is amounts expected to be collected within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Lease Incentive Receivable, Noncurrent
definition: Noncurrent portion of receivables for an incentive or inducement contractually stipulated between parties to a lease whereby the lessor has committed to provide the entity (lessee) with a cash payment as inducement to enter the lease.

elementLabel: Leases Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Lease Financing
definition: Amount before allowance of commercial leases and leveraged lease transactions where the entity is long-term creditor. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Leveraged Lease Investment
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of leveraged lease investments which represent the aggregate amount of the estimated residual value of the lease assets and lease payments receivables, net of unearned and deferred income to be allocated over the lease term and non-recourse debt.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Balance Sheet, Deferred Taxes Arising from Leveraged Leases
definition: The liability for taxes payable in the future as a result of temporary differences in treatment of certain items in the current year arising from the net investment in arrangements meeting the criteria for classification as a leveraged lease.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Balance Sheet, Investment in Leveraged Leases
definition: The net investment in arrangements meeting the criteria to be classified as leveraged excluding deferred taxes.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Balance Sheet, Investment in Leveraged Leases, Net
definition: The net investment in arrangements meeting the criteria to be classified as leveraged.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Income Statement, Investment Tax Credit Recognized on Leveraged Leases
definition: The receivable for the amount of investment tax credit to be realized on the transaction as part of the net investment allocated in proportionate amounts to income.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Net Investment in Leveraged Leases Disclosure, Deferred Income
definition: The estimated portion of pretax income and investment tax credit remaining to be allocated to income over the lease term.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Net Investment in Leveraged Leases Disclosure, Investment Tax Credit Receivable
definition: This element represents the receivable for the amount of the investment tax credit to be realized on the leveraged lease transaction.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Net Investment in Leveraged Leases Disclosure, Rental Receivables, Gross
definition: The gross rentals receivable equal to the future cash flows from the lessee.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Net Investment in Leveraged Leases Disclosure, Rental Receivables, Net
definition: This element represents leveraged lease rentals receivable, net of that portion of the rental applicable to principal and interest on the nonrecourse debt.

elementLabel: Leveraged Leases, Net Investment in Leveraged Leases Disclosure, Residual Value of Leased Assets
definition: The estimate of the value of the leased asset at the end of the lease term.

elementLabel: Liabilities of Business Transferred under Contractual Arrangement, Current
definition: The current carrying amount, due within one year or one operating cycle, if longer, of liabilities resulting from the transfer of a business segment under contractual arrangement where the transferor maintains certain risks, obligations or liabilities.

elementLabel: Liabilities of Business Transferred under Contractual Arrangement, Noncurrent
definition: The noncurrent portion, due in greater than one year or one operating cycle, if longer, of liabilities resulting from the transfer of a business segment under contractual arrangement where the transferor maintains certain risks, obligations, or liabilities.

elementLabel: Liability for Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense, Disability, Accident and Health
definition: The amount needed to reflect the estimated ultimate cost of settling claims relating to disability, accident and health insurance insured events that have occurred on or before a particular date (ordinarily, the balance sheet date) and the amount needed to provide for the estimated ultimate cost required to investigate and settle claims relating to insured events that have occurred on or before a particular date (ordinarily, the balance sheet date), whether or not reported to the insurer at that date.

elementLabel: Liability for Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense, Property Casualty Liability
definition: The amount needed to reflect the estimated ultimate cost of settling claims relating to casualty insurance insured events that have occurred on or before a particular date (ordinarily, the balance sheet date) and the amount needed to provide for the estimated ultimate cost required to investigate and settle claims relating to insured events that have occurred on or before a particular date (ordinarily, the balance sheet date), whether or not reported to the insurer at that date.

elementLabel: Liability for Future Policy Benefits and Unpaid Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense
definition: The aggregate amount of policy reserves (provided for future obligations including unpaid claims and claims adjustment expenses) and policy benefits (liability for future policy benefits) as of the balance sheet date; grouped amount of all the liabilities associated with the company's insurance policies.

elementLabel: Liability for Unpaid Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense, Incurred but Not Reported (IBNR) Claims, Amount
definition: Estimated costs as of the balance sheet date of settling insured claims and costs incurred in the claims settlement process for claims that have not yet been submitted to the insurance company for reimbursement.

elementLabel: Liability for Unpaid Claims and Claims Adjustment Expense, Reported Claims, Amount
definition: Costs of settling insured claims and costs incurred in the claims settlement process for the specified year specifically for claims that have already been submitted to the insurance company for reimbursement.

elementLabel: Liability, Reporting Currency Denominated, Value
definition: The reporting currency-denominated liability value.

elementLabel: License and Maintenance Revenue
definition: Revenue from multiple-deliverable arrangements that include licensing fees and maintenance revenue. Licensing revenue is consideration received from another party for the right to use, but not own, certain of the entity's intangible assets. Licensing arrangements include, but are not limited to, rights to use a patent, copyright, technology, manufacturing process, software or trademark. Licensing fees are generally, but not always, fixed as to amount and not dependent upon the revenue generated by the licensing party. An entity may receive licensing fees for licenses that also generate royalty payments to the entity. Maintenance revenue is derived from maintenance services provided under contracts or arrangements with clients. Services may include the maintenance of software, plant and equipment, and facilities.

elementLabel: Life Insurance Assumed Ratio
definition: Ratio of life insurance assumed from another insurer to gross life insurance in force.

elementLabel: Life Insurance, Corporate or Bank Owned, Amount
definition: This item represents the amount that could be realized under a life insurance contract or contracts owned by the Entity as of the date of the statement of financial position. Such Entity-owned life insurance policies are commonly known as corporate-owned life insurance (COLI) or bank-owned life insurance (BOLI).

elementLabel: Life Premiums as Percentage of Gross Premiums
definition: Ratio with total life insurance premiums in numerator and total GAAP premiums in the denominator.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing after Rolling Year Five
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing after Year Five
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Next Twelve Months
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Rolling Year Five
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Rolling Year Four
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Rolling Year Three
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Rolling Year Two
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Year Five
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Year Four
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Year Three
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value, Maturing in Year Two
definition: Fair value of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value
definition: Fair value amount of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value
