definition: Face value (death benefits) of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing after Rolling Year Five
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing after Year Five
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Next Twelve Months
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Rolling Year Five
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Rolling Year Four
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Rolling Year Three
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Rolling Year Two
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Year Five
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Year Four
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Year Three
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Face Value, Maturing in Year Two
definition: Face value of the life insurance policies underlying the life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing after Rolling Year Five
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing after the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing after Year Five
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Next Rolling Twelve Months
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the next rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Next Twelve Months
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Rolling Year Five
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fifth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Rolling Year Four
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fourth rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Rolling Year Three
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the third rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Rolling Year Two
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the second rolling twelve months following the latest balance sheet. For interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Year Five
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Year Four
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Year Three
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Life Settlement Contracts, Fair Value Method, Number of Contracts, Maturing in Year Two
definition: Number of life settlement contracts accounted for under the fair value method maturing in the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Limited Liability Company (LLC) or Limited Partnership (LP), Managing Member or General Partner, Ownership Interest
definition: Percentage investment held by the managing member or general partner of the limited liability company (LLC) or limited partnership (LP).

elementLabel: Limited Liability Company (LLC) or Limited Partnership (LP), Members or Limited Partners, Ownership Interest
definition: The number of units or percentage investment held by one or more members or limited partners of the LLC or LP.

elementLabel: Limited Partners' Capital Account, Units Authorized
definition: The number of limited partner units authorized to be issued.

elementLabel: Limited Partners' Cumulative Cash Distributions
definition: Aggregate cumulative cash distributions made to the limited partners.

elementLabel: Limited Partners' Offering Costs
definition: The cumulative amount of offering costs allocated to the limited partners.

elementLabel: Line of Credit Assumed
definition: The fair value of line of credit assumed in noncash investing or financing activities.

elementLabel: Line of Credit Facility, Capacity Available for Specific Purpose Other than for Trade Purchases
definition: The maximum amount of borrowing capacity under a line of credit that is available as of the balance sheet date for a specific purpose other than for financing goods acquired for inventory or imminent delivery to a customer.

elementLabel: Line of Credit Facility, Capacity Available for Trade Purchases
definition: The maximum amount of borrowing capacity under a line of credit that is available as of the balance sheet date for financing purchases of goods acquired for inventory or imminent delivery to a customer.

elementLabel: Line of Credit Facility, Collateral Fees, Amount
definition: Amount of the fees associated with providing collateral for the credit facility.

elementLabel: Line of Credit Facility, Commitment Fee Percentage
definition: The fee, expressed as a percentage of the line of credit facility, for the line of credit facility regardless of whether the facility has been used.

elementLabel: Line of Credit Facility, Unused Capacity, Commitment Fee Percentage
definition: The fee, expressed as a percentage of the line of credit facility, for available but unused credit capacity under the credit facility.

elementLabel: Estimated Litigation Liability, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying amount of estimated litigation liability for known or estimated probable loss from litigation, which may include attorneys' fees and other litigation costs, which is expected to be paid after one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Loan Portfolio Expense
definition: The loan servicing fees paid to third parties that relate to loan expenses for a portfolio containing the entire group of loans owned by the company.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Collateral for Secured Borrowings
definition: Reflects the aggregate value of loans, trade receivables, securities and financial instruments that serve as collateral for obligations arising from a transfer of financial assets recorded as a secured borrowing.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Governments
definition: Amount before allowance of loans and leases issued to a unit or agency of a federal, state or local jurisdiction within the country of domicile of the reporting entity. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Commitments, Fixed Rates
definition: Reflects the amount of cash required to fully fund agreements to provide advances to borrowers and lessees at stated interest rates.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Commitments, Variable Rates
definition: Reflects the amount of cash required to fully fund agreements to provide advances to borrowers and lessees at interest rates that increase or decrease depending on certain facts or circumstances.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Construction
definition: Amount before allowance of loans issued to build, improve or remodel a residential home. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Home Equity
definition: Amount before allowance of revolving, open-end loan, extended under a line of credit and secured by the borrower's residential property. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Installment and Revolving
definition: Amount before allowance of installment and revolving loans issued to individuals, including, but not limited to credit card, automobile, boat, student, durable home appliance loans. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Installment, Durable Goods
definition: Amount before allowance of consumer loans to acquire durable goods, including, but not limited to, automobiles, recreational vehicles, boats, refrigerators, washers and dryers. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Installment, Other
definition: Amount before allowance of other consumer installment loans. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Installment, Student
definition: Amount before allowance of higher education or qualifying vocational and professional schools loans. Includes federally subsidized and personal loans and deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Lease Financing
definition: Amount before allowance of consumer lease agreements. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Mortgage
definition: Amount before allowance of consumer mortgage. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes subordinated loans such as home equity lines of credit and loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Other
definition: Amount before allowance of consumer loans and leases not otherwise specified in the taxonomy. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Real Estate
definition: Amount before allowance of consumer real estate loans. Includes, but not limited to, construction financing, residential mortgage loans, and home equity lines of credit. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Revolving, Credit Card
definition: Amount before allowance of credit card loans issued to individuals. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Gross, Consumer, Revolving, Other
definition: Amount before allowance of other revolving credit arrangements, for example, but not limited to, personal lines of credit. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes home equity lines of credit and credit cards and loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Fees Earned but Excluded from Yield
definition: Reflects the amount of fees recognized as income related to loan originations, commitments or servicing which are not included in interest income and that exceed one percent of the aggregate of total interest income and other income.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Impaired, Commitment to Lend
definition: Reflects the unfunded portion of contractual agreements to lend funds to borrowers for loans whose terms have been modified by troubled debt restructuring.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Impaired, Interest Income Recognized, Change in Present Value Attributable to Passage of Time
definition: The amount of interest income on impaired and nonperforming loans that is due to the change in present value attributable to the passage of time.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Impaired, Interest Lost on Nonaccrual Loans
definition: Reflects the amount of additional interest income that would have been recorded if impaired or nonperforming loans were instead current, in compliance with their original terms, and outstanding throughout the reporting period or since origination (if held for part of the period).

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Nonperforming, Accrual of Interest
definition: Reflects the carrying amount of loans deemed to be questionable as to collection on which interest is continuing to be earned or accrued.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Nonperforming, Nonaccrual of Interest
definition: Reflects the carrying amount of loans deemed to be questionable as to collection on which no interest is continuing to be recognized.

elementLabel: Loans and Leases Receivable, Ratio of Nonperforming Loans to All Loans
definition: Reflects the percentage derived from dividing impaired loans on which interest has ceased to be accrued by total loans.

elementLabel: Loans from Other Federal Home Loan Banks
definition: Amount of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) loans from another FHLBank.

elementLabel: Loans, Gross, Insurance Policy
definition: Amount before allowance of loans made to policy and contract holders using their life insurance contracts' cash value or separate accounts as collateral. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums over and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans and leases covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Pledged as Collateral
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of loans that have been pledged as collateral for borrowings. If the secured party has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge the collateral, then the debtor reclassifies that asset and report that asset in its statement of financial position separately from other assets not so encumbered.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Basis Spread on Variable Rate
definition: The percentage points (also referred to as 'margin') added to the reference rate as stated in the loan agreement and used to compute the variable rate on the loans receivable. For instance, the loan agreement might state that the interest rate the borrower is obligated to pay is the London Interbank Offered Rate (LIBOR) plus three quarters (3/4) of a percentage point adjusted quarterly (each three months). LIBOR in this example is the index or reference rate, 3/4 percentage point is the margin, the reference rate plus the margin is the fully indexed rate. This element would be used to report separately the margin.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Basis Spread on Variable Rate, During Period
definition: The percentage points added to the reference rate or index during the adjustment period to compute the variable [fully indexed] rate on the loans receivable realized during the reporting period. This may be an effective margin for the period depending on the specific terms of the underlying loan agreement (for example, an annual disclosure for a loan with a quarterly adjustment period).

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Acquisition
definition: Amount before allowance of commercial loans to acquire real property. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Agricultural
definition: Amount before allowance of loans issued to agricultural institutions. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Commercial and Industrial
definition: Amount before allowance of loans issued to commercial and industrial institutions. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes real estate loans and loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Construction
definition: Amount before allowance of commercial construction loans. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Development
definition: Amount before allowance of commercial loans to develop land for sale or construction thereon. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Financial and Agricultural
definition: Amount before allowance of loans issued to agricultural, commercial and industrial, and financial institutions. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Financial Institutions
definition: Amount before allowance of loans issued to financial institutions, including, but not limited to, real estate investment trusts, mortgage companies, and banks. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Mortgage
definition: Amount before allowance of mortgage loans on existing land or building. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Real Estate
definition: Amount before allowance of commercial loans issued to businesses to acquire, develop, construct, improve, or refinance land or building. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Commercial, Trade Financing
definition: Amount before allowance of commercial loans, including, but not limited to, letters of credit, bankers' acceptances, receivables factoring, open account financing, for international trade activities. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable Held-for-sale, Amount
definition: The face amount of loans that will be sold to other entities.

elementLabel: Loans Receivable, Gross, Mortgage Warehouse Lending
definition: Amount before allowance of revolving credit lines for to originate and purchase financial assets including, but not limited to, mortgage loans. Includes deferred interest and fees, undisbursed portion of loan balance, unamortized costs and premiums and discounts from face amounts. Excludes loans covered under loss sharing agreements.

elementLabel: Loans to Other Federal Home Loan Banks
definition: Amount of Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) loans to another FHLBank.

elementLabel: Accounts, Notes, Loans and Financing Receivable, Net, Noncurrent
definition: The aggregate of amounts due from customers or clients more than one year from the balance sheet date, for goods or services that have been delivered or sold in the normal course of business and an amount representing an agreement for an unconditional promise by the maker to pay the Company (holder) a definite sum of money at a future date more than one year from the balance sheet date, reduced to their estimated net realizable fair value by an allowance established by the Company of the amount it deems uncertain of collection and net of any write-downs taken for collection uncertainty on the part of the holder, respectively.

elementLabel: Long-term Commercial Paper, Current
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of the current portion of long-term unsecured obligations issued by corporations and other borrowers to investors (with maturities initially due after one year or beyond the operating cycle if longer).

elementLabel: Long-term Construction Loan, Current
definition: This element represents the current portion of a long-term real estate loan to finance building costs. The funds are disbursed as needed or in accordance with a prearranged plan; generally, a portion of the funds is disbursed at inception and the remainder as construction progresses. The money is repaid on completion of the project (generally one to seven years), usually from the proceeds of a mortgage loan. The rate is normally higher than the prime rate, and there is usually an origination fee. The effective yield on these loans tends to be high, and the lender has a security interest in the real property.

elementLabel: Long-term Construction Loan
definition: This element represents the current and noncurrent portions of a long-term real estate loan with an initial maturity beyond one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer, to finance building costs. The funds are disbursed as needed or in accordance with a prearranged plan; generally, a portion of the funds is disbursed at inception and the remainder as construction progresses. The money is repaid on completion of the project (generally one to seven years), usually from the proceeds of a mortgage loan. The rate is normally higher than the prime rate, and there is usually an origination fee. The effective yield on these loans tends to be high, and the lender has a security interest in the real property.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Maturing in Years Four and Five
definition: Amount of long-term debt payable, sinking fund requirements, and other securities issued that are redeemable by holder at fixed or determinable prices and dates maturing in the fourth and fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Maturing in Years Two and Three
definition: Amount of long-term debt payable, sinking fund requirements, and other securities issued that are redeemable by holder at fixed or determinable prices and dates maturing in the second and third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Percentage Bearing Fixed Interest, Amount
definition: The portion of the carrying amount of long-term borrowings outstanding as of the balance sheet date, including current maturities, which accrues interest at a set, unchanging rate.

elementLabel: Long-term Debt, Percentage Bearing Variable Interest, Amount
definition: The portion of the carrying amount of long-term borrowings outstanding as of the balance sheet date, including current maturities, which accrues interest at a rate subject to change from time to time.

elementLabel: Long-term Federal Home Loan Bank Advances, Noncurrent
definition: The noncurrent portion of Federal Home Loan Bank borrowings initially due beyond one year or beyond the normal operating cycle if longer.

elementLabel: Loans Payable to Bank, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of loans from a bank with maturities initially due after one year or beyond the operating cycle if longer, excluding current portion.

elementLabel: Loans Payable, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of loans payable (with maturities initially due after one year or beyond the operating cycle if longer), excluding current portion.

elementLabel: Notes and Loans, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of all notes and loans payable (with maturities initially due after one year or beyond the operating cycle if longer), excluding current portion.

elementLabel: Long-term Pollution Control Bond, Current
definition: Current portion of a debt security issued by a state, certain agencies or authorities, a local government, or development corporation to finance the construction of air- or water-pollution control facilities or sewage or solid waste disposal facilities pursuant to federal law. The bonds are backed by the credit of the beneficiary of the financing rather than the credit of the issuer.

elementLabel: Long-term Pollution Control Bond
definition: Represents the current and noncurrent portions of a debt security issued by a state, certain agencies or authorities, a local government, or development corporation to finance the construction of air- or water-pollution control facilities or sewage or solid waste disposal facilities pursuant to federal law. The bonds are backed by the credit of the beneficiary of the financing rather than the credit of the issuer.

elementLabel: Long-term Transition Bond, Noncurrent
definition: Long-Term transition bonds are bonds under the Competition Act in which the proceeds of Transition Bonds are required to be used principally to reduce qualified stranded costs and the related capitalization of the utility. This represents the noncurrent portion.

elementLabel: Long-term Transition Bond, Current
definition: Long-Term transition bonds are bonds under the Competition Act in which the proceeds of Transition Bonds are required to be used principally to reduce qualified stranded costs and the related capitalization of the utility. This represents the current portion.

elementLabel: Long-term Transition Bond
definition: Long-Term transition bonds are bonds under the Competition Act in which the proceeds of Transition Bonds are required to be used principally to reduce qualified stranded costs and the related capitalization of the utility. This represents the current and noncurrent portions. The initial maturity is beyond one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Loss from Components Excluded from Assessment of Cash Flow Hedge Effectiveness
definition: The loss relating to components of the gain (loss) on the cash flow hedging instrument excluded from the assessment of cash flow hedge effectiveness. Recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Loss from Components Excluded from Assessment of Fair Value Hedge Effectiveness
definition: Loss relating to components of the gain (loss) on the fair value hedging instrument excluded from the assessment of fair value hedge effectiveness. Recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Loss from Hedged Firm Commitment Not Qualifying as Fair Value Hedge
definition: Amount of loss recognized in earnings when a hedged firm commitment no longer qualifies as a fair value hedge.

elementLabel: Loss on Contract Termination
definition: The loss recognized on termination of a contract.

elementLabel: Loss on Contract Termination for Default
definition: The amount of the loss on termination of a contract for default.

elementLabel: Machinery and Equipment, Gross
definition: Amount before accumulated depreciation of tangible personal property used to produce goods and services, including, but is not limited to, tools, dies and molds, computer and office equipment.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Accrual, Discounted
definition: Amount of the accrued liability on a discounted basis for malpractice claims (including general and professional liability).

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Accrual, Discounted, Current
definition: Amount of the current portion of the accrued liability on a discounted basis for malpractice claims (including general and professional liability).

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Accrual, Discounted, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of the noncurrent portion of the accrued liability on a discounted basis for malpractice claims (including general and professional liability).

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Accrual, Undiscounted
definition: Amount of the accrued liability on an undiscounted basis for malpractice claims (including general and professional liability) at the end of the accounting period.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Accrual, Undiscounted, Current
definition: Amount of the current portion of the accrued liability on an undiscounted basis for malpractice claims (including general and professional liability).

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Accrual, Undiscounted, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of the noncurrent portion of the accrued liability on an undiscounted basis for malpractice claims (including general and professional liability).

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Claims Incurred in Period
definition: Amount of loss recognized for asserted and unasserted malpractice claims.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Claims Incurred in Prior Periods
definition: Amount of increase in asserted and unasserted malpractice claims that were originally recognized in a prior period.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Claims Incurred, Net
definition: Amount of costs associated with malpractice claims and insurance premiums incurred during an accounting period, less insurance recoveries and returns of previously paid premiums.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Discount Rate
definition: The interest rate used to discount the estimated cash flows associated with the payment of malpractice claims.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Insurance Recoveries
definition: Amount of insurance recoveries recognized from insurance and similar arrangements for reimbursement and payment of malpractice claims recognized during an accounting period.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Letters of Credit and Surety Bonds
definition: Amount of letters of credit and other surety bonds that are available for the future payment of malpractice claims.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Number of Claims
definition: Number of malpractice claims outstanding at the end of the accounting period.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Period Cost
definition: Amount of costs associated with malpractice claims, including costs associated with litigating and settling claims, incurred during an accounting period.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Premium Costs
definition: Amount of costs incurred that are associated with obtaining malpractice insurance and other risk transferring arrangements during an accounting period.

elementLabel: Malpractice Loss Contingency, Return of Premiums
definition: Amount received during the period representing a return of premiums previously paid, generally under a retrospectively rated policy.

elementLabel: Managing Member or General Partner, Subsequent Distribution Amount
definition: Amount of cash or stock or unit payment to a limited liability corporation managing member or limited partnership general partner after the end of the accounting period.

elementLabel: Marine Services Revenue
definition: Revenue from marine-related services and products such as lubricants for offshore drilling, and retail or wholesale sales in a marina.

elementLabel: Marketable Securities, Equity Securities, Current
definition: Amount of investments in equity securities and other forms of securities that provide ownership interests expected to be converted to cash, sold or exchanged within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Marketable Securities, Noncurrent
definition: Total debt and equity financial instruments including: (1) securities held-to-maturity and (2) securities available-for-sale that will be held for the long-term.

elementLabel: Marketable Securities, Restricted
definition: Total debt and equity financial instruments including: (1) securities held-to-maturity, (2) trading securities, and (3) securities available-for-sale that are pledged to one or more secured parties who have the right to buy, sell, or re-pledge the collateral.

elementLabel: Marketable Securities, Restricted, Current
definition: Total debt and equity financial instruments including: (1) securities held-to-maturity, (2) trading securities, and (3) securities available-for-sale which are intended to be held for less than one year or the normal operating cycle, whichever is longer and that are pledged to one or more secured parties who have the right to buy, sell, or re-pledge the collateral.

elementLabel: Marketable Securities, Restricted, Noncurrent
definition: Total debt and equity financial instruments including: (1) securities held-to-maturity, (2) trading securities, and (3) securities available-for-sale which are intended to be held for greater than one year or the normal operating cycle, whichever is longer and that are pledged to one or more secured parties who have the right to buy, sell, or re-pledge the collateral.

elementLabel: Market Value of Stock Dividends Outstanding over Thirty Days
definition: The market value of stock dividends outstanding over thirty days at the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Medium-term Notes
definition: Including the current and noncurrent portions, carrying value at the balance sheet date of a financial instrument used to receive debt funding on a regular basis with original maturities ranging from 5-10 years.

elementLabel: Medium-term Notes, Current
definition: Carrying value at the balance sheet date of the current portion of a financial instrument used to receive debt funding on a regular basis with original maturities ranging from 5-10 years.

elementLabel: Medium-term Notes, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying value at the balance sheet date of the noncurrent portion of a financial instrument used to receive debt funding on a regular basis with original maturities ranging from 5-10 years.

elementLabel: Membership Dues Revenue, On-going
definition: Revenue earned during the period from periodic fees charged to existing members of an association or club. An example would be the monthly/annual dues paid to a gym or workout facility. This element excludes the initial membership fees received on enrollment or registration.

elementLabel: Memberships in Exchanges Owned
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the capitalized costs of obtaining memberships that provide the entity, typically a broker-dealer, with the right to do business on trading exchanges (such as stock or commodity exchanges) in which the entity or its employees are members. Memberships are usually registered in the names of individuals who are affiliated with the broker-dealer. A membership held in the name of an individual is considered to be an asset of the broker-dealer if it is held by the broker-dealer under an agreement (such as an ABC agreement) that would require the member, upon leaving the broker-dealer, to do one of the following: a) Pay the member organization the amount necessary to purchase another membership (if the named individual wished to retain the membership); b) Sell the membership and pay the proceeds over to the member organization; or, c) Transfer the membership for a nominal consideration to a person designated by the member organization and satisfactory to the exchange.

elementLabel: Mineral Properties, Gross
definition: Carrying amount at the balance sheet date of mineral properties, gross of adjustments.

elementLabel: Mineral Properties, Net
definition: Mineral properties, net of adjustments.

elementLabel: Mineral Rights
definition: Carrying amount at the balance sheet date of mineral rights, or rights to extract a mineral from the earth or to receive payment in the form of a royalty for the extraction of minerals, net of amortization.

elementLabel: Mine Reclamation and Closing Liability, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of a reclamation and mine closing liability that is associated with a legal obligation for the closure and reclamation of a mine including the removal of buildings, equipment, machinery and other physical remnants of mining, closure of tailings impoundments, leach pads and other mine features, and contouring, covering and revegetation of waste rock piles and other disturbed areas.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Thereafter
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, within Five Years
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, within Four Years
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, Next Twelve Months
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, within Three Years
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions, within Two Years
definition: Amount of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing due in the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Noncontrolling Interest, Amount Represented by Preferred Stock
definition: The amount of noncontrolling interest in subsidiary represented by preferred securities issued by the subsidiary.

elementLabel: Mortgage-backed Securities Held-to-maturity, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value of securitized, pay-through debt securities collateralized by real estate mortgage loans classified as held-to-maturity.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Intercompany Profits in Carrying Amount of Loans
definition: Amount of any intercompany profits included in the carrying amount of mortgage loans on real estate.

elementLabel: Mortgages Held-for-sale, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of mortgage loans held-for-sale.

elementLabel: Multiemployer Plan, Period Contributions
definition: Amount of contributions made to multiemployer plans by the employer. A multiemployer plan is a pension or postretirement benefit plan to which two or more unrelated employers contribute where assets contributed by one participating employer may be used to provide benefits to employees of other participating employers.

elementLabel: Municipal Investment Agreements
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of the obligations arising from contracts specifying rights and responsibilities of a host municipality in the structure or operation of an investment project. For example, proceeds from a revenue bond may be invested temporarily in contracts until disbursements are required for construction of a major project. There is little or no insurance risk for the entity.

elementLabel: Natural Gas Liquid Reserves Not Clearly Attributable to Leasehold Interests, Proved and Unproved Reserves
definition: The quantity of proved and unproved reserves not clearly attributable to leasehold interests ownership.

elementLabel: Natural Gas Midstream Costs
definition: Midstream costs of residue gas, natural gas liquids and condensate. Midstream is a term sometimes used to identify those industry activities that fall between exploration and production (upstream) and refining and marketing (downstream). The term is most often applied to pipeline transportation of crude oil and natural gas.

elementLabel: Natural Gas Production Revenue
definition: Revenue from natural gas production during the reporting period. Natural gas consists largely of the hydrocarbon methane, and is found in underground formations either by itself or with crude oil.

elementLabel: Net Capital in Excess of Five Percent of Debit Items
definition: Net capital less five percent of aggregate debit items.

elementLabel: Net Capital in Excess of Four Percent of Debit Items
definition: Net capital less four percent of aggregate debit items.

elementLabel: Noncash or Part Noncash Acquisition, Employee Benefit Liabilities Assumed
definition: The amount of employee benefit liabilities that an Entity assumes in acquiring a business or in consideration for an asset received in a noncash (or part noncash) acquisition. Noncash is defined as transactions during a period that affect recognized assets or liabilities but that do not result in cash receipts or cash payments in the period. "Part noncash" refers to that portion of the transaction not resulting in cash receipts or cash payments in the period.

elementLabel: Noncash or Part Noncash Acquisition, Interest Acquired
definition: The level of ownership or equity interest acquired in a noncash (or part noncash) transaction. "Part noncash" refers to that portion of the transaction not resulting in cash receipts or cash payments in the period.

elementLabel: Noncash or Part Noncash Acquisition, Inventory Acquired
definition: The amount of inventory that an Entity acquires in a noncash (or part noncash) acquisition. Noncash is defined as information about all investing and financing activities of an enterprise during a period that affect recognized assets or liabilities but that do not result in cash receipts or cash payments in the period. "Part noncash" refers to that portion of the transaction not resulting in cash receipts or cash payments in the period.

elementLabel: Noncash or Part Noncash Acquisition, Noncash Financial or Equity Instrument Consideration, Rate
definition: Dividend or interest rate associated with the financial or equity instrument issued as noncash or part noncash consideration for a business or asset acquired. Noncash are transactions that affect recognized assets or liabilities but that do not result in cash receipts or cash payments. Part noncash refers to that portion of the transaction not resulting in cash receipts or cash payments.

elementLabel: Noninterest-bearing Deposit Liabilities
definition: The aggregate amount of all domestic and foreign noninterest-bearing deposits liabilities held by the entity.

elementLabel: Noninterest-bearing Deposit Liabilities, Domestic
definition: Amount of domestic noninterest-bearing deposits held by the entity, which may include demand deposits, checking, brokered and retail deposits.

elementLabel: Noninterest-bearing Deposit Liabilities, Foreign
definition: Amount of foreign noninterest-bearing deposits held by the entity which may include demand deposits, checking, brokered and retail deposits.

elementLabel: Noninterest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Brokered
definition: Amount of noninterest-bearing domestic third-party deposits placed by or through the assistance of a deposit broker, also known as brokered deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Noninterest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Checking
definition: Amount of noninterest-bearing domestic checking deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Noninterest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Demand
definition: Amount of money in noninterest-bearing domestic accounts that entitle the depositor to withdraw funds at any time without prior notice, also known as demand deposits.

elementLabel: Noninterest-bearing Domestic Deposit, Retail
definition: Amount of noninterest-bearing domestic retail deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Nonmonetary Transaction, Gross Operating Revenue Recognized
definition: The amount of gross operating revenue recognized in a nonmonetary transaction.

elementLabel: Nonpatronage Source Earnings
definition: The excess or revenues over costs resulting from transactions that do not relate to patrons.

elementLabel: Nontrade Receivables
definition: Carrying amounts due as of the balance sheet date of the sum of amounts receivable other than from customers.

elementLabel: Nontrade Receivables, Noncurrent
definition: The noncurrent portion of the receivable other than from customers, that is amounts expected to be collected after one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Notes, Loans and Financing Receivable, Net, Noncurrent
definition: An amount representing an agreement for an unconditional promise by the maker to pay the Entity (holder) a definite sum of money at a future date more than one year from the balance sheet date, net of any write-downs taken for collection uncertainty on the part of the holder. Such amount may include accrued interest receivable in accordance with the terms of the debt. The debt also may contain provisions and related items including a discount or premium, payable on demand, secured, or unsecured, interest bearing or noninterest bearing, among a myriad of other features and characteristics. This amount does not include amounts related to receivables held-for-sale.

elementLabel: Notes Payable to Bank
definition: Including the current and noncurrent portions, the carrying value as of the balance sheet date of notes payable to banks, excluding mortgage notes, initially due beyond one year or beyond the operating cycle if longer.

elementLabel: Notes Payable to Bank, Noncurrent
definition: The total amount due within more than 12 month, or the operating cycle if longer, on all notes payable to banks paid on an installment. This can include the amount of any loans from the applicant firm. This does not, however, include any mortgage balances.

elementLabel: Notes Receivable, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of an agreement for an unconditional promise by the maker to pay the holder a definite sum of money at a future date.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Net
definition: Net amount of the investment in a contractual right to receive money on demand or on fixed or determinable dates that is recognized as an asset in the creditor's statement of financial position. Examples include, but are not limited to, credit card receivables, notes receivable and receivables relating to lessor's rights to payments from leases other than operating leases that have been recorded as assets. Excludes trade accounts receivable with contractual maturity of one year or less and arose from the sale of goods or services.

elementLabel: Qualitative and Quantitative Information, Transferor's Continuing Involvement, Not Previously Required Financial Support Provided, Amount
definition: The amount of the support provided by the transferor with a continuing involvement that was not previously contractually required to provide to the transferee or its beneficial interest holders.

elementLabel: Number of Businesses Acquired
definition: The number of businesses acquired by the entity during the period.

elementLabel: Number of Countries in which Entity Operates
definition: The number of countries in which the entity operates as of balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Number of Credit Risk Derivatives Held
definition: Number of credit risk derivative instruments held.

elementLabel: Number of Foreign Currency Derivatives Held
definition: Number of foreign currency exchange rate derivatives held by the entity at the reporting date.

elementLabel: Number of Interest Rate Derivatives Held
definition: Number of interest rate derivative instruments held by the entity at the reporting date.

elementLabel: Number of Price Risk Derivatives Held
definition: Number of price risk derivative instruments held by the entity at the reporting date.

elementLabel: Number of Real Estate Properties
definition: The number of real estate properties owned as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Number of Real Estate Properties, Fee Simple
definition: The number of real estate properties owned as of the statement of financial position to which the entity has fee simple title.

elementLabel: Number of States in which Entity Operates
definition: The number of states the entity operates in as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Number of Stores
definition: Represents the number of stores.

elementLabel: Number of Units in Real Estate Property
definition: The number of units in a real estate property owned as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Occupancy Revenue
definition: Revenue derived from the provision of short term lodging; it does not apply to lease or rental income. Includes hotel rooms, cruise revenue, and other revenue related to lodgings.

elementLabel: Office of Finance, Cost Assessed on Federal Home Loan Bank
definition: Amount of a Federal Home Loan Bank's (FHLBank) proportionate share of the costs of operating the Office of Finance.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Joint Interest Billing Receivables, Current
definition: Current portion of accounts receivable attributable to joint interest partners in oil and gas properties. These are billings to the non-operators associated with the operation of wells and are based on those owners' working interests in the wells. For classified balance sheets, represents the current amount receivable, that is amounts expected to be collected within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Joint Interest Billing Receivables, Noncurrent
definition: Noncurrent portion of accounts receivable attributable to joint interest partners in oil and gas properties. These are billings to the non-operators associated with the operation of wells and are based on those owners' working interests in the wells.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Producing Properties of Rate Regulated Companies, Proved and Unproved Reserves
definition: The quantity of proved and unproved reserves related to properties subject to cost-of-service ratemaking.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Producing Properties of Rate Regulated Companies, Unamortized Cost
definition: The amount of unamortized cost related to properties subject to cost-of-service ratemaking.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Property, Successful Effort Method, Gross
definition: Oil and Gas properties, gross, carried under the successful effort method.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Reclamation Liability, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of a reclamation liability that is associated with a legal obligation for the closure and reclamation of oil and gas properties.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Sales Payable, Current
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred and payable to third parties for oil and gas that has been sold but not delivered. Used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer).

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Sales Payable
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred and payable to third parties for oil and gas that has been sold but not delivered.

elementLabel: Operating Insurance and Claims Costs, Production
definition: Insurance and claims costs directly related to goods produced and sold, or services rendered, during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Income Statement, Carrying Amount at Lease Inception Exceeds Fair Value
definition: This element represents the loss resulting from the amount by which the cost or carrying amount, if different, of an asset subject to an agreement classified as an operating lease, at the inception of a lease involving real estate, exceeds the fair value of the leased property.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Income Statement, Contingent Revenue
definition: Amount of contingent rental revenue recognized for the period under lease, based on the occurrences of an event or condition.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Income Statement, Minimum Lease Revenue
definition: The total amount of lease revenue recognized for the period for which the lessee was obligated under leasing arrangements regardless of any other events or conditions. This amount excludes contingent revenue and sublease revenue.

elementLabel: Operating Leases of Lessee, Contingent Rentals, Basis Spread on Variable Rate
definition: The percentage points added to the reference rate to compute the variable rate on the lessee's operating lease.

elementLabel: Operating Leases of Lessor, Contingent Rentals, Basis Spread on Variable Rate
definition: The percentage points added to the reference rate to compute the variable rate on the lessor's operating lease.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Rent Expense, Minimum Rentals
definition: This element represents the payments that the lessee is obligated to make or can be required to make in connection with a property under the terms of an agreement classified as an operating lease, excluding contingent rentals and a guarantee by the lessee of the lessor's debt and the lessee's obligation to pay (apart from the rental payments) executory costs such as insurance, maintenance, and taxes.

elementLabel: Operating Support from Adviser, Amount
definition: The amount of the support provided by the Adviser to help the REIT achieve a certain return for the period.

elementLabel: Option Indexed to Issuer's Equity, Indexed Shares
definition: The number of issuer's shares to which the option contract is indexed.

elementLabel: Option Indexed to Issuer's Equity, Shares
definition: The maximum number of shares that could be issued to net share settle a contract, if applicable. If a contract does not have a fixed or determinable maximum number of shares that may be required to be issued, disclose the fact that a potentially infinite number of shares could be issued to settle the contract.

elementLabel: Origination of Loans to Employee Stock Ownership Plans
definition: The cash outflow to finance the entity's defined contribution plan to acquire shares of the entity. The plan initially holds the shares in a suspense account, which is collateral for the loan. As the plan makes payment on the debt, the shares are released from the suspense account and become available to be allocated to participant accounts.

elementLabel: Other Assets, Miscellaneous, Current
definition: Amount of other miscellaneous assets expected to be realized or consumed within one year or operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Assets, Miscellaneous, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of other miscellaneous assets expected to be realized or consumed after one year or normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Assets Not Allowed
definition: Other assets not readily convertible into cash, such as prepaid expenses, intangible assets, and unsecured receivables net of any reserves.

elementLabel: Other Borrowings
definition: The carrying amount as of the balance sheet date for the aggregate of other miscellaneous borrowings owed by the reporting entity.

elementLabel: Other Cash Equivalents, at Carrying Value
definition: Amount of short-term, highly liquid investments that are both readily convertible to known amounts of cash and so near their maturity that they present insignificant risk of changes in value because of changes in interest rates, classified as other. Excludes cash and cash equivalents within disposal group and discontinued operation.

elementLabel: Other Construction Costs
definition: Other costs incurred and are directly related to construction and development services.

elementLabel: Other Deductions and Charges
definition: Other deductions and charges as defined.

elementLabel: Other Deferred Compensation Arrangements, Liability, Classified, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of the liabilities, classified as other, for deferred compensation arrangements payable after one year or the operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Deferred Compensation Arrangements, Liability, Current and Noncurrent
definition: Amount of the liabilities for deferred compensation arrangements classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Deferred Costs, Gross
definition: Gross amount of other deferred costs capitalized at the end of the reporting period. Does not include deferred finance costs or deferred acquisition costs of insurance companies.

elementLabel: Other Deferred Costs, Net
definition: Net amount of other deferred costs capitalized at the end of the reporting period. Does not include deferred finance costs or deferred acquisition costs of insurance companies.

elementLabel: Other Deferred Credits, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of unearned revenue or income classified as other, expected to be taken into income after one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Direct Costs of Hotels
definition: Other costs incurred and are directly related to hotel operations.

elementLabel: Other Employee-related Liabilities, Current
definition: Amount of obligations incurred for employer-related costs classified as other, payable within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Employee-related Liabilities
definition: Amount of obligations incurred for employer-related costs classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Hotel Operating Revenue
definition: Amount of revenue, generated from managing and operating hotels, classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Indefinite-lived Intangible Assets
definition: Amount after impairment of indefinite-lived intangible assets classified as other. Excludes financial assets and goodwill.

elementLabel: Other Interest Earning Assets
definition: Amount of interest earning assets classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Inventories, Spare Parts, Gross
definition: Gross amount of components of assembled products that can be sold directly or indirectly through sales of assembled products.

elementLabel: Other Inventory, Gross
definition: Amount before valuation and LIFO reserves of other inventory expected to be sold, or consumed within one year or operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Inventory, Demo, Gross
definition: Gross amount of merchandise, goods, commodities, or supplies to which the entity holds the title and uses for the specific purpose of showing the benefits and features of the entity's products to existing or potential customers.

elementLabel: Other Inventory, in Transit, Gross
definition: Gross amount of merchandise or supplies to which the entity holds the title but does not hold physical possession because the goods are currently being transported.

elementLabel: Other Inventory, Inventory at off Site Premises, Gross
definition: Gross amount of merchandise or materials to which the entity holds the title, but physically at another entity's facilities (for example, but not limited to, work in process may be temporarily at the site of a subcontractor).

elementLabel: Other Inventory, Materials, Supplies and Merchandise under Consignment, Gross
definition: Gross amount of inventory owned by the entity but in the hands of a customer, typically a reseller.

elementLabel: Other Inventory, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of inventories not expected to be converted to cash, sold or exchanged within the normal operating cycle (such as inventory related to long-term contracts or program rights).

elementLabel: Other Inventory, Purchased Goods, Gross
definition: Gross amount of components used by the entity which are bought from another entity rather than produced by the entity.

elementLabel: Other Inventory, Scrap, Gross
definition: Gross amount of residue from manufacturing or production process that has recovery value.

elementLabel: Other Inventory, Supplies, Gross
definition: Amount before valuation and LIFO reserves of other supplies used within the manufacturing or production process expected to be consumed within one year or operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Inventory, Warehouse, Gross
definition: Gross amount of merchandise, goods, commodities, or supplies held by the entity in a building or part of a building for future sale.

elementLabel: Other Investments and Securities, at Cost
definition: Includes other investments and securities that are not at fair value as of the balance sheet date and those that are not accounted for under the equity method.

elementLabel: Other Liabilities and Deferred Revenue, Noncurrent
definition: Aggregate carrying amount, as of the balance sheet date, of noncurrent obligations and noncurrent portion of deferred revenue not separately disclosed in the balance sheet. Noncurrent liabilities are expected to be paid after one year (or the normal operating cycle, if longer). Deferred revenue is a liability related to a revenue producing activity for which revenue has not yet been recognized, and is not expected to be recognized in the next twelve months.

elementLabel: Other Loans Payable
definition: Amount of long-term loans payable classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Loans Payable, Current
definition: Amount of long-term loans classified as other, payable within one year or the operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Loans Payable, Long-term, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of long-term loans classified as other, payable after one year or the operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Long-term Debt, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of long-term debt classified as other, payable after one year or the operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Notes Payable, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of long-term notes classified as other, payable after one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Marketable Securities, Current
definition: Amount of other investments not classified as trading, available-for-sale or held-to-maturity, expected to be converted to cash, sold or exchanged within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Other Marketable Securities, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of debt and equity financial instruments classified as other and noncurrent.

elementLabel: Other Notes Payable
definition: Amount of long-term notes payable classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Oil and Gas Property, Successful Effort Method
definition: Amount of oil and gas properties accounted for using the successful effort method, classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Ownership Interests, Cumulative Cash Distributions
definition: Aggregate cumulative cash distributions made to the other unit holders in a limited partnership or master limited partnership. Does not include limited or general partners' ownership interests.

elementLabel: Other Ownership Interests, Offering Costs
definition: The cumulative amount of offering costs allocated to the other unit holders.

elementLabel: Other Ownership Interests, Units Authorized
definition: The number of units of other ownership interest authorized to be issued in a limited partnership or master limited partnership. Does not include limited or general partners' ownership interests.

elementLabel: Other Ownership Interests, Units Issued
definition: The number of units of other ownership interests issued in a limited partnership or master limited partnership. Does not include limited or general partners' ownership interests.

elementLabel: Other Ownership Interests, Units Outstanding
definition: The number of units of other ownership interests outstanding in a limited partnership or master limited partnership. Does not include limited or general partners' ownership interests.

elementLabel: Other Ownership Interests, Contributed Capital
definition: The amount of capital contributed by other unit holders.

elementLabel: Other Payables to Broker-Dealers and Clearing Organizations
definition: Amount of other payables due to broker-dealers or clearing organizations.

elementLabel: Other Policyholder Funds
definition: Amount due to policyholders for funds held that are returnable under the terms of insurance contracts, classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Postretirement Benefits Payable
definition: The total amount of the entity's obligation as of the balance sheet date under any other retirement plan(s), such as one or more defined contribution plans.

elementLabel: Other Postretirement Benefits Payable, Noncurrent
definition: The total amount of the entity's noncurrent obligation as of the balance sheet date under any other retirement plan(s), such as one or more defined contribution plans.

elementLabel: Other Recurring Income
definition: Amount of recurring income classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Restricted Assets
definition: Total assets that cannot be used for operating purposes because of contract or regulatory requirements that are in effect for a period that extends beyond one year.

elementLabel: Other Restricted Assets, Current
definition: Amount of current assets that are pledged or subject to withdrawal restrictions, classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Restricted Assets, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of noncurrent assets that are pledged or subject to withdrawal restrictions, classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Secured Financings
definition: Secured financing other than securities sold under agreements to repurchase and securities loaned.

elementLabel: Other Short-term Investments
definition: Amount of short-term investments classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Sundry Liabilities, Current
definition: Obligations not otherwise itemized or categorized in the footnotes to the financial statements that are due within one year or operating cycle, if longer, from the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Available-for-sale Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Default Rate
definition: This item represents the default rate of the underlying assets in the security that was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the available-for-sale investments are other than temporarily impaired and the amount of such impairment determined to be related to credit loss recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Available-for-sale Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Delinquency Rate
definition: This item represents the delinquency rates of the underlying assets in the security that was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the available-for-sale investments are other than temporarily impaired and measure the amount of impairment related to credit loss recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Available-for-sale Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Level of Subordination
definition: This item represents the current level of subordination of the entity's receipt of consideration should the assets underlying the security be liquidated when the level of subordination was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the available-for-sale investments are other than temporarily impaired and the amount of such impairment determined to be related to credit loss recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Available-for-sale Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Percentage of Nonperforming Assets
definition: This item represents the percentage of nonperforming assets underlying the security which were considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the available-for-sale investments are other than temporarily impaired and the amount of such impairment determined to be related to credit loss recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Available-for-sale Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Third Party Guarantees, Amount
definition: Amount of third party guarantees against loss of value in the underlying assets of an available-for-sale security for which only the portion of an other-than-temporary impairment (OTTI) related to a credit loss was recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Held-to-maturity Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Default Rate
definition: This item represents the default rate of the underlying assets in the security that was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are other than temporarily impaired and only the amount of impairment related to credit loss was recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Held-to-maturity Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Delinquency Rate
