definition: This item represents the delinquency rate of the underlying assets in the security that was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are other than temporarily impaired and only the amount of impairment related to credit loss was recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Held-to-maturity Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Level of Subordination
definition: This item represents the current level of subordination of the entity's receipt of consideration should the assets underlying the security be liquidated when the level of subordination was considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are other than temporarily impaired and only the amount of impairment related to credit loss was recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Held-to-maturity Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Percentage of Nonperforming Assets
definition: This item represents the percentage of nonperforming assets that the underlying assets in the security represent and which were considered as one of the potential factors in reaching a conclusion that the held-to-maturity investments are other than temporarily impaired and only the amount of impairment related to credit loss was recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Held-to-maturity Securities, Portion Recognized in Earnings, Net, Qualitative Disclosures, Third Party Guarantees, Amount
definition: Amount of third party guarantees against loss of value in the underlying assets of a held-to-maturity security for which only the portion of an other-than-temporary impairment (OTTI) related to a credit loss was recognized in earnings.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Portion in Other Comprehensive Loss, before Tax, Portion Attributable to Noncontrolling Interest, Held-to-maturity Securities
definition: Amount before tax of other than temporary impairment (OTTI) on investment in held-to-maturity debt security, recognized in other comprehensive loss, attributable to noncontrolling interest.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Portion in Other Comprehensive Loss, Net of Tax, Portion Attributable to Noncontrolling Interest
definition: Amount after tax of other than temporary impairment loss (OTTI) on investments in available-for-sale and held-to-maturity debt securities, recognized in other comprehensive loss and attributable to noncontrolling interest.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Portion in Other Comprehensive Loss, Net of Tax, Portion Attributable to Noncontrolling Interest, Available-for-sale Securities
definition: Amount after tax of other than temporary impairment (OTTI) on investment in available-for-sale debt security, recognized in other comprehensive loss, attributable to noncontrolling interest.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Portion in Other Comprehensive Loss, Net of Tax, Portion Attributable to Noncontrolling Interest, Held-to-maturity Securities
definition: Amount after tax of other than temporary impairment (OTTI) on investment in held-to-maturity debt security, recognized in other comprehensive income loss, attributable to noncontrolling interest.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Portion in Other Comprehensive Loss, Tax, Portion Attributable to Noncontrolling Interest, Available-for-sale Securities
definition: Amount of tax (expense) benefit of other than temporary impairment (OTTI) on investment in available-for-sale debt security, recognized in other comprehensive loss, attributable to noncontrolling interest.

elementLabel: Other than Temporary Impairment Losses, Investments, Portion in Other Comprehensive Loss, Tax, Portion Attributable to Noncontrolling Interest, Held-to-maturity Securities
definition: Amount of tax (expense) benefit of other than temporary impairment (OTTI) on investment in held-to-maturity debt security, recognized in other comprehensive loss, attributable to noncontrolling interest.

elementLabel: Other Unrecorded Amounts
definition: Amount of unrecorded indebtedness classified as other.

elementLabel: Other Utility Costs
definition: Other utility cost incurred related to oil and gas produced and sold during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Own-share Lending Arrangement, Collateral
definition: The amount of collateral required to be received or received by the entity from the counterparty (share borrower) in connection with an own-share lending arrangement entered into by the entity, in contemplation of a convertible debt offering or other financing.

elementLabel: Own-share Lending Arrangement, Counterparty Default, Earnings Per Share, Shares
definition: In periods in which default, by a counterparty (share borrower) to a share-lending arrangement, is probable, but has not yet occurred, this item represents the number of the entity's shares related to the share-lending arrangement that will be reflected in basic and diluted earnings per share when the counterparty (share borrower) default does occur.

elementLabel: Own-share Lending Arrangement, Counterparty Default, Period of Default, Expense
definition: The amount of default related expense recognized in earnings in the period in which the entity concludes it is probable that the counterparty (share borrower) to a share-lending arrangement will default.

elementLabel: Own-share Lending Arrangement, Dividends, Not Reimbursed
definition: The amount of dividends paid to holders of record of shares of the entity's stock associated with an own-share lending arrangement in contemplation of a convertible debt offering or other financing, which will not be reimbursed by the counterparty (share borrower) to the arrangement.

elementLabel: Own-share Lending Arrangement, Shares, Outstanding
definition: The number of shares outstanding as of the date of the statement of financial position in connection with an own-share lending arrangement entered into by the entity, in contemplation of a convertible debt offering or other financing.

elementLabel: Own-share Lending Arrangement, Shares, Outstanding, Value
definition: The fair value as of the date of the statement of financial position of shares outstanding in connection with an own-share lending arrangement, in contemplation of a convertible debt offering or other financing.

elementLabel: Participating Mortgage Loans, Mortgage Obligations, Amount
definition: The aggregate amount of the participating mortgage obligation at the end of the accounting period.

elementLabel: Participating Mortgage Loans, Participation Liabilities, Amount
definition: The aggregate amount of the participation liability at the end of the accounting period.

elementLabel: Participating Mortgage Loans, Unamortized Debt Discount, Amount
definition: The amount of the related debt discount at the end of the accounting period.

elementLabel: Participating Policies, Additional Income Allocated
definition: Amount of additional income allocated to policy holders whose contracts entitle them to a portion of the entity's earnings or surplus, paid through dividends.

elementLabel: Participating Policies as Percentage of Gross Insurance in Force
definition: This percent places participating policies in the numerator and insurance contracts in force in the denominator. Participating insurance contracts allow policyholders to share in the experience of the entity, primarily through policy dividends.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital Allocated for Income Tax and Other Withdrawals
definition: Amount of partnership capital allocated for income tax and other withdrawals.

elementLabel: Partners' Capital, Distribution Amount Per Share
definition: The distribution amount per share for all classes of units.

elementLabel: Passenger Revenue
definition: A transportation (plane, train, ship) carrier's fare revenue recognized in the period from carrying passengers between destinations.

elementLabel: Passenger Revenue, Mainline
definition: Amount of a transportation carrier's mainline fare revenue recognized in the period from carrying passengers between destinations.

elementLabel: Passenger Revenue, Regional
definition: Amount of a transportation carrier's regional affiliates' fare revenue recognized in the period from carrying passengers between destinations.

elementLabel: Payables for Congressionally Mandated Assessments
definition: Amount payable for Congressionally mandated Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank) assessments, for example, but not limited to, Resolution Funding Corporation (REFCORP) assessments.

elementLabel: Payables to Customers
definition: Amounts payable to customers at the balance sheet date. The term customers generally excludes other broker-dealers; persons who are principal officers, directors, and stockholders; and persons whose securities or funds are part of the regulatory net capital of the broker-dealer. Another broker-dealer's account can be classified as a customer if the account is carried as an omnibus account in compliance with certain regulations. The accounts of principal officers, directors and stockholders may be combined in the customer captions if they are not material and the combination is disclosed in the oath that is required to accompany the annual audited FOCUS Report.

elementLabel: Payments for Bonds Transferred to Other Federal Home Loan Banks
definition: Amount of cash outflow from transfers and assumptions of primary liability of consolidated obligations to another Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Payments for Delayed Tax Exempt Exchange
definition: Cash outflow related to a property which is traded for the promise to provide a replacement like-kind property in the near future also known as a tax deferred exempt exchange.

elementLabel: Payments for Deposits Applied to Debt Retirements
definition: Cash outflow during the period as a deposit on account for application (deposits to retire or pay down) against an amount of debt owed by the entity.

elementLabel: Payments for Flight Equipment
definition: The cash outflow for acquisition of long-lived depreciable flight assets, including owned aircraft or capital improvements.

elementLabel: Payments for Hedge, Investing Activities
definition: The cash outflow for a financial contract that meets the hedge criteria as either a cash flow hedge, fair value hedge, or hedge of a net investment in a foreign operation.

elementLabel: Payments for Investment in Restricted Cash from Pollution Control Bond
definition: The cash outflow for investments in restricted cash from pollution control bond, which is a debt security issued by a state, certain agencies or authorities, a local government, or development corporation to finance the construction of air- or water-pollution control facilities or sewage or solid waste disposal facilities pursuant to federal law. The bonds are backed by the credit of the beneficiary of the financing rather than the credit of the issuer.

elementLabel: Payments for Mortgage Deposits
definition: outflow associated with an amount paid in advance to show an intention to complete a mortgage financing.

elementLabel: Payments for Nuclear Fuel
definition: Cash outflow associated with the purchase of any material that is commonly used in the generation of nuclear energy.

elementLabel: Payments for Operating Activities
definition: Total amount of cash paid for operating activities during the current period.

elementLabel: Payments for Removal Costs
definition: Cash outflow related to disposal costs of plants, whether by demolishing, dismantling, abandoning, sale, and so forth during the period.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Loans and Leases Held-for-investment
definition: The cash outflow from (a) purchases of loans held-for-investment, (b) purchases of leases held-for-investment, and (c) both.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Loans and Leases Held-for-investment, Credit Card Securitizations
definition: The cash outflow from the purchase of securitized credit card receivables which are held for investment purposes. Securitization is the structured process whereby interests in loans and other receivables are packaged, underwritten, and sold in the form of asset-backed securities.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Real Estate and Real Estate Joint Ventures
definition: The cash outflow associated with the purchase of real estate held-for-investment and real estate joint ventures.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Retained Interest in Securitized Receivables
definition: The cash outflow for the purchase of a retained interest in a receivable securitized via a structured process whereby interests in loans and other receivables are packaged, underwritten, and sold in the form of asset-backed securities.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Timberlands
definition: The cash outflow for acquisition of timber and timberlands during the period.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Waste Water Systems
definition: The cash outflow for the purchase of waste water systems which includes the waste treatment and disposal facility and equipment to households and industry.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Water and Waste Water Systems
definition: The cash outflow for the purchase of a facility and equipment that provides water supply which includes wells, reservoirs, pumping stations, and control facilities; and waste water systems which includes the waste treatment and disposal facility and equipment to households and industry.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Water Systems
definition: The cash outflow for the purchase of a facility and equipment that provides water supply which includes wells, reservoirs, pumping stations, and control facilities.

elementLabel: Payments to Acquire Investments to be Held in Decommissioning Trust Fund
definition: The cash outflow for the purchase of investments that will be held in a decommissioning trust fund.

elementLabel: Payments to Suppliers and Employees
definition: Cash payments to suppliers for goods and services provided and to employees for services provided.

elementLabel: Pension and Other Postretirement and Postemployment Benefit Plans, Liabilities
definition: This represents the entire liability recognized in the balance sheet that is associated with the defined benefit pension plans and other postretirement and postemployment benefit plans.

elementLabel: Pension and Other Postretirement and Postemployment Benefit Plans, Liabilities, Noncurrent
definition: This represents the noncurrent liability recognized in the balance sheet that is associated with the defined benefit pension plans and other postretirement and postemployment benefit plans.

elementLabel: Percentage of Amount Amortized of Ending Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Year Five
definition: Estimated percentage of the ending balance of the present value of the future insurance profits asset acquired in the purchase of an insurance entity to be amortized in the fifth year after the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Percentage of Amount Amortized of Ending Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Year Four
definition: Estimated percentage of the ending balance of the present value of the future insurance profits asset acquired in the purchase of an insurance entity to be amortized in the fourth year after the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Percentage of Amount Amortized of Ending Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Year One
definition: Estimated percentage of the ending balance of the present value of future profits asset acquired in the purchase of an insurance entity to be amortized in the first year after the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Percentage of Amount Amortized of Ending Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Year Three
definition: Estimated percentage of the ending balance of the present value of the future insurance profits asset acquired in the purchase of an insurance entity to be amortized in the third year after the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Percentage of Amount Amortized of Ending Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Year Two
definition: Estimated percentage of the ending balance of the present value of the future insurance profits asset acquired in the purchase of an insurance entity to be amortized in the second year after the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Percentage of Debt Hedged by Interest Rate Derivatives
definition: Percentage of an entity's outstanding debt that is designated as a hedged item in cash flow, fair value, or net investment hedge.

elementLabel: Percentage of FIFO Inventory
definition: The percentage of FIFO (first in first out) inventory to total inventory as of the balance sheet date if other than 100 percent.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits, Brokered
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic brokered deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits, Certificates of Deposit
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic certificates of deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits, Checking
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic checking demand deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits, Demand
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic demand deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits, Money Market
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic money market demand account deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits, Notice of Withdrawal
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic notice of withdrawal demand deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits, Other Time Deposit
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic time deposit liabilities other than certificates of deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits, Retail
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic retail deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits, Savings
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic savings deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of Interest-bearing Domestic Deposits to Deposits, Time Deposits
definition: Percentage of interest-bearing domestic time deposit liabilities to total deposit liabilities.

elementLabel: Percentage of LIFO Inventory
definition: The percentage of LIFO (last in first out) inventory to total inventory as of the balance sheet date if other than 100 percent.

elementLabel: Percentage of Unamortized Film Costs
definition: The percentage of unamortized film costs for released films, excluding acquired film libraries, that it expects to amortize within three years from the date of the balance sheet.

elementLabel: Percentage of Weighted Average Cost Inventory
definition: The percentage of weighted average cost inventory present at the reporting date when inventory is valued using different valuation methods.

elementLabel: Operating Leases, Income Statement, Percentage Revenue
definition: This element represents the rental revenue earned during the period from lessee-operators based on revenues generated in their operations, generally in excess of a base amount. Such rental revenue is generally stipulated in the lease agreement, usually will provide for a fixed percentage of revenue to be paid as additional (or possibly only) rent due the lessor, and may be based on gross revenues, net revenues, or multiple variations thereof. Percentage rent is often required under leases with retail outlets located on premises owned by hoteliers, cruise lines, others in the hospitality industry, and shopping mall operators, among others.

elementLabel: Phase-in Plan, Amount of Capitalized Costs Recovered
definition: The sum total amount of allowable costs capitalized in the period pertaining to a phase-in plan and previously capitalized costs that were recovered (recognized in earnings) during the period through rates.

elementLabel: Phase-in Plan, Amount of Costs Deferred for Rate-making Purposes
definition: The total amount of allowable costs capitalized during the period by the entity pertaining to Phase-In plans which were deferred on the expectation of future recovery.

elementLabel: Plant Held for Future Use Amount
definition: Discloses the period end amount of plants held for future use and whether such amount is included in the utility's rate base.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets, Not Separately Reported, Finance Receivables
definition: The carrying amount, as of the date of the latest financial statement presented, of finance receivables which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation, primarily a secured borrowing or repurchase agreement, and for which the transferee is not permitted to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets, Not Separately Reported, Nonsecuritized Investments
definition: The carrying amount, as of the date of the latest financial statement presented, of investments which are not evidenced by ownership of securities, such as interests in partnerships or other forms of unincorporated entities, but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation, primarily a secured borrowing or repurchase agreement, and for which the transferee is not permitted to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets, Other, Not Separately Reported on Statement of Financial Position
definition: The carrying amount, as of the date of the latest financial statement presented, of all assets that are pledged as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation primarily arising from secured borrowings, repurchase agreements or other current or potential obligations, where the secured party does not have the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge the collateral and therefore are not reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets, Not Separately Reported, Other
definition: The carrying amount, as of the date of the latest financial statement presented, of other assets which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation, primarily a secured borrowing or repurchase agreement, and for which the transferee is not permitted to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets, Not Separately Reported, Real Estate
definition: The carrying amount, as of the date of the latest financial statement presented, of real estate owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation, primarily a secured borrowing or repurchase agreement, and for which the transferee is not permitted to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Finance Receivables Pledged as Collateral, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of finance receivables which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Loans Pledged for Federal Home Loan Bank, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of loans that are restricted as collateral for the payment of the FHLB debt obligations, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Loans Pledged for Other Debt Obligations, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of loans which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of other debt obligations, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Loans Pledged for Repurchase Agreements, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of loans that are restricted as collateral for the payment of repurchase agreements, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Mortgage-Related Securities Available-for-sale or Held-for-investment
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of mortgage-related securities, classified as available for sale or held for investment, which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation, primarily a secured borrowing or repurchase agreement, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Nonsecuritized Investments Pledged as Collateral, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of investments which are not evidenced by ownership of securities, such as interests in partnerships or other forms of unincorporated entities, which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation, and that is reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge such ownership interests.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Other, on Statement of Financial Position, at Fair Value
definition: The sum of the fair values, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of assets which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of debt obligations, primarily secured borrowings, repurchase agreements or other current or potential obligations, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Other Assets Pledged as Collateral, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of other assets which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Other Debt Securities Available-for-sale or Held-for-investment
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of other securities, classified as available for sale or held for investment, which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation, primarily a secured borrowing or repurchase agreement, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Real Estate Pledged as Collateral, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of real estate which is owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the related debt obligation, and that is reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge it.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Securities Pledged as Collateral, at Fair Value
definition: The sum of the fair values, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of securities that are restricted as collateral for the payment of related debt obligations, primarily secured borrowings and repurchase agreements, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Securities Pledged for Federal Home Loan Bank, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of securities which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of the FHLB debt obligations, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Securities Pledged for Other Debt Obligations, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of securities that are restricted as collateral for the payment of other debt obligations, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Securities Pledged for Repurchase Agreements, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of securities which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of repurchase agreements, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Assets Separately Reported, Securities Pledged under Letter of Credit Facilities, at Fair Value
definition: The fair value, as of the date of each statement of financial position presented, of securities that are restricted as collateral under letter of credit agreements, and that are reclassified and separately reported in the statement of financial position because the transferee has the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Loans Receivable Pledged as Collateral
definition: The sum of the carrying amounts, as of the date of the latest financial statement presented, of loans receivable which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of related debt obligations, primarily secured borrowings and repurchase agreements, and for which the transferees are not permitted to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Loans Receivable, for Federal Home Loan Bank Debt
definition: The carrying amount, as of the date of the latest financial statement presented, of loans receivable which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of FHLB debt obligations, and for which the transferee is not permitted to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Loans Receivable, for Other Arrangements
definition: The carrying amount, as of the date of the latest financial statement presented, of loans receivable which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of other debt obligations, and for which the transferee is not permitted to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Loans Receivable, for Repurchase Agreements
definition: The carrying amount, as of the date of the latest financial statement presented, of loans receivable which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for the payment of repurchase obligations, and for which the transferee is not permitted to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Mortgage-Related Securities Available-for-sale or Held-for-investment
definition: The carrying amount as of the date of the latest financial statement presented of mortgage-related securities classified as available for sale or held for investment which are owned but transferred to another party to serve as collateral to partially or fully secure a debt obligation, repurchase agreement or other current or potential obligation, and for which the transferee does not have the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Mortgage-Related Securities Held-to-maturity
definition: The carrying amount as of the date of the latest financial statement presented of mortgage-related securities classified as held to maturity which are owned but transferred to another party to serve as collateral to partially or fully secure a debt obligation, repurchase agreement or other current or potential obligation, and for which the transferee does not have the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Other Debt Securities Available-for-sale or Held-for-investment
definition: The carrying amount as of the date of the latest financial statement presented of other securities classified as available for sale or held for investment which are owned but transferred to another party to serve as collateral to partially or fully secure a debt obligation, repurchase agreement or other current or potential obligation, and for which the transferee does not have the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Other Debt Securities Held-to-maturity
definition: The carrying amount as of the date of the latest financial statement presented of other debt securities classified as held to maturity which are owned but transferred to another party to serve as collateral to partially or fully secure a debt obligation, repurchase agreement or other current or potential obligation, and for which the transferee does not have the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Securities for Federal Home Loan Bank
definition: The carrying amount as of the date of the latest financial statement presented of securities which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for FHLB debt obligations, and for which the transferee does not have the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Securities for Letter of Credit Facilities
definition: The carrying amount as of the date of the latest financial statement presented of securities which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for letter of credit arrangements, and for which the transferee does not have the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Securities for Other Debt Facilities
definition: The carrying amount as of the date of the latest financial statement presented of securities which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for debt facilities other than FHLB loans, repurchase agreements and letter of credit arrangements, and for which the transferee does not have the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Securities for Repurchase Agreements
definition: The carrying amount as of the date of the latest financial statement presented of securities which are owned but transferred to serve as collateral for repurchase agreements, and for which the transferee does not have the right by contract or custom to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Pledged Financial Instruments, Not Separately Reported, Securities
definition: Sum of the carrying amounts as of the date of the latest financial statement presented of securities which are owned but transferred to another party to serve as collateral to partially or fully secure a debt obligation, repurchase agreement or other current or potential obligation, and for which the transferee is not permitted to sell or re-pledge them to an unrelated party.

elementLabel: Policyholder Dividends Payable
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of the liability for dividends that are payable to the policyholders based upon the terms of the underlying insurance contracts.

elementLabel: Policyholder Dividends, Rate on Policy Earnings
definition: The percentage of earnings allocable to participating policyholders based on earnings of such policies for payment of dividends.

elementLabel: Policyholder Funds
definition: The total liability as of the balance sheet date of amounts due policy holders, excluding future policy benefits and claims, including unpaid policy dividends, retrospective refunds, and undistributed earnings on participating business.

elementLabel: Policy Loans Receivable
definition: Carrying amount of loans made to policyholders against the cash surrender value (CSV) or other policyholder funds, and secured by the CSV, policyholder funds or the death benefit provided by the insurance contracts.

elementLabel: Portion of Future Oil and Gas Production Being Hedged
definition: The quantity of future oil and gas production being hedged.

elementLabel: Postemployment Benefits Liability, Current
definition: For a classified balance sheet, the carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the portion of the obligations recognized for the various benefits provided to former or inactive employees, their beneficiaries, and covered dependents after employment but before retirement that is payable within one year of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Postemployment Benefits Liability, Noncurrent
definition: For a classified balance sheet, the carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the portion of the obligations recognized for the various benefits provided to former or inactive employees, their beneficiaries, and covered dependents after employment but before retirement that is payable after one year (or beyond the operating cycle if longer).

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Dividend Rate, Per-Dollar-Amount
definition: The amount per share used to calculated dividend payments on preferred stock.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock Dividends, Shares
definition: Number of shares of preferred stock issued as dividends during the period. Excludes stock splits.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Including Additional Paid in Capital
definition: Aggregate issuance value of nonredeemable preferred stock (or preferred stock redeemable solely at the option of the issuer) issued and outstanding.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Including Additional Paid in Capital, Net of Discount
definition: Aggregate par value plus amounts in excess of par or issuance value (in cases of no-par value stock) for nonredeemable preferred stock (or preferred stock redeemable solely at the option of the issuer) issued and outstanding, net of discount on shares. Aggregate for preferred stock issued and outstanding.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Liquidation Preference Per Share
definition: The per share liquidation preference (or restrictions) of nonredeemable preferred stock (or preferred stock redeemable solely at the option of the issuer) that has a preference in involuntary liquidation considerably in excess of the par or stated value of the shares. The liquidation preference is the difference between the preference in liquidation and the par or stated values of the share.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, No Par Value
definition: Face amount per share of no-par value preferred stock nonredeemable or redeemable solely at the option of the issuer.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Per Share Amounts of Preferred Dividends in Arrears
definition: Per share amount of cumulative preferred dividends in arrears.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Redemption Amount, Future Redeemable Securities
definition: The redemption (or callable) amount of redeemable preferred stock, excluding currently redeemable preferred stock. Includes amounts representing dividends not declared or paid but which will be payable under the redemption features or for which ultimate payment is solely within the control of the issuer.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Redemption Price Per Share
definition: The price per share at which the preferred stock of an entity that has priority over common stock in the distribution of dividends and in the event of liquidation of the entity is redeemed or may be called at. The redemption features of this preferred stock are solely within the control of the issuer.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Shares Outstanding
definition: Aggregate share number for all nonredeemable preferred stock (or preferred stock redeemable solely at the option of the issuer) held by stockholders. Does not include preferred shares that have been repurchased.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Value, Subscriptions
definition: Amount of subscription received from investors who have been allocated nonredeemable preferred stock or preferred stock redeemable solely at the option of the issuer.

elementLabel: Preferred Units, Authorized
definition: The number of preferred units authorized to be issued.

elementLabel: Preferred Units, Contributed Capital
definition: The amount of capital contributed by the preferred partners.

elementLabel: Preferred Units, Cumulative Cash Distributions
definition: Aggregate cumulative cash distributions made to the preferred partners.

elementLabel: Preferred Units, Issued
definition: The number of preferred units issued.

elementLabel: Preferred Units, Outstanding
definition: The number of preferred units outstanding.

elementLabel: Premiums and Other Receivables, Net
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date, net of allowance for doubtful accounts, of all premiums and other types of receivables due from other persons or entities.

elementLabel: Premiums Receivable, Allowance for Doubtful Accounts
definition: The carrying value as of the balance sheet date of the estimated valuation allowance to reduce gross premiums receivable to net realizable value.

elementLabel: Premiums Receivable, Net
definition: The carrying amount as of the balance sheet date due the entity from (a) agents and insureds, (b) uncollected premiums and (c) others, net of the allowance for doubtful accounts.

elementLabel: Premiums Receivable, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of amount receivable on insurance policies.

elementLabel: Premiums Receivable, Gross
definition: Gross amount, as of the balance sheet date, due the entity from (a) agents and insureds, (b) uncollected premiums and (c) others, before deducting the allowance for doubtful accounts.

elementLabel: Premiums Receivable, Proceeds from Sale of Receivables
definition: The amount of proceeds from the transfer of premium receivables reported as sales by an insurance entity.

elementLabel: Prepaid Advertising
definition: Amount of consideration paid in advance for advertising that provides economic benefits within a future period of one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Prepaid Expense Other, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of amounts paid in advance which will be charged against earnings in periods after one year or beyond the operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Prepaid Interest
definition: Amount of asset related to consideration paid in advance for interest that provides economic benefits within a future period of one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Prepaid Mineral Royalties, Noncurrent
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of capitalized amounts paid for mineral royalties which will be charged against earnings after one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Prepaid Reinsurance Premiums
definition: The unexpired portion of premiums ceded on policies in force as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Prepaid Royalties
definition: Amount of asset related to consideration paid in advance for royalties that provide economic benefits within a future period of one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

elementLabel: Preproduction Costs Related to Long-term Supply Arrangements, Asset for Molds Dies and Tools Not Owned
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of capitalized costs of molds, dies, and other tools that the entity does not own which are or will be used in producing goods under a long-term supply arrangement, and for which there is a noncancelable right of use during such arrangement.

elementLabel: Preproduction Costs Related to Long-term Supply Arrangements, Asset for Molds Dies and Tools Owned
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of capitalized costs of molds, dies, and other tools that will be used in producing products under a long-term supply arrangement.

elementLabel: Preproduction Costs Related to Long-term Supply Arrangements, Costs Capitalized
definition: The carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of capitalized preproduction costs incurred on long-term supply arrangements, including recoverable costs to design and develop products.

elementLabel: Present Value of Future Insurance Profits, Additions from Acquisitions
definition: Additions in present value of future profits asset during the year arising from acquisitions of insurance entities.

elementLabel: Present Value of Future Minimum Lease Payments, Sale Leaseback Transactions
definition: Present value of minimum lease payments for sale-leaseback transactions accounted for using the deposit method or as a financing.

elementLabel: Price Risk Cash Flow Hedge Asset, at Fair Value
definition: Fair value as of the balance sheet date of all price risk derivative assets designated as cash flow hedging instruments.

elementLabel: Price Risk Cash Flow Hedge Liability, at Fair Value
definition: Fair value as of the balance sheet date of all price risk derivative liabilities designated as cash flow hedging instruments.

elementLabel: Price Risk Derivative Instruments Not Designated as Hedging Instruments Asset, at Fair Value
definition: Fair value as of the balance sheet date of all price risk derivative assets not designated as hedging instruments.

elementLabel: Price Risk Fair Value Hedge Asset, at Fair Value
definition: Fair value as of the balance sheet date of all price risk derivative assets designated as fair value hedging instruments.

elementLabel: Price Risk Fair Value Hedge Liability, at Fair Value
definition: Fair value as of the balance sheet date of all price risk derivative liabilities designated as fair value hedging instruments.

elementLabel: Principal Amount Outstanding of Loans Held-in-portfolio
definition: This is the result of the principal amount outstanding of total loans managed or securitized less securitized loans and loans that are in the process of being securitized.

elementLabel: Principal Amount Outstanding on Loans Held-for-sale or Securitization or Asset-backed Financing Arrangement
definition: This is the principal amount outstanding for loans which are in the process of being securitized as of the date of the statement of financial position (across all types of loans).

elementLabel: Principal Amount Outstanding on Loans Securitized or Asset-backed Financing Arrangement
definition: This is the principal amount outstanding for securitized loans only (across all types of loans).

elementLabel: Proceeds from Bonds Transferred from Other Federal Home Loan Banks
definition: Amount of cash inflow from transfers and assumptions of primary liability for consolidated obligations of another Federal Home Loan Bank (FHLBank).

elementLabel: Proceeds from Collection of Retained Interest in Securitized Receivables
definition: The cash inflow from the collection of a retained interest in a receivable securitized via a structured process whereby interests in loans and other receivables are packaged, underwritten, and sold in the form of asset-backed securities.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Commissions Received
definition: Cash received for commissions during the current period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Customers
definition: Cash receipts from customers during the current period which are usually for sales of goods and services.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Customers for Progress Payments
definition: Cash received from customers as progress payments on projects that have been partially completed.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Debt, Maturing in More than Three Months
definition: The cash inflow from a borrowing having initial term of repayment of more than three months. Includes proceeds from long-term and short-term debt.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Delayed Tax Exempt Exchange
definition: Cash inflow related to a property which is traded for the promise to provide a replacement like-kind property in the near future also known as a tax deferred exempt exchange.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Deposits Applied to Debt Retirements
definition: Cash inflow received during the period as a deposit on account for application (deposits to retire or pay down) against an amount of debt owed to the entity.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Distribution of Restricted Cash from Pollution Control Bond
definition: The cash inflow from amounts received from distributions of restricted cash from pollution control bond, which is a debt security issued by a state, certain agencies or authorities, a local government, or development corporation to finance the construction of air- or water-pollution control facilities or sewage or solid waste disposal facilities pursuant to federal law. The bonds are backed by the credit of the beneficiary of the financing rather than the credit of the issuer.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Financing Revenue Received under Leases
definition: Financing revenue received under leases during the current period by an entity that provides financial services.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Grantors
definition: Cash received from grantors during the current period related to operating activities. This element represents receipts from a guarantor for the amount of guarantee provided.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of First Mortgage Bond
definition: The cash inflow from amounts received from a long-term debt instrument secured by a first mortgage deed of trust, containing a pledge of real property. The lender has the highest claim on the property in case of default.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of Mandatory Redeemable Capital Securities
definition: The cash inflow from issuance of an equity security that embodies an unconditional obligation requiring the issuer to redeem the security by transferring the assets at a specified or determinable date (or dates) that is (or are) initially more than one year (or the normal operating cycle, if longer) from the issuance date, or upon an event that is certain to occur beyond one year (or the normal operating cycle, if longer) from the issuance date.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of Secured Tax Exempt Debt
definition: The cash inflow from amounts received from issuance of long-term tax exempt debt that is wholly or partially secured by collateral.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of Unsecured Tax Exempt Debt
definition: The cash inflow from the issuance of long-term tax exempt debt that is not secured by collateral.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Leases Held-for-investment
definition: The cash inflow from the sale of a lease held for investment, which may be a lease of real estate, equipment or other fixed assets for a specified time in exchange for payment, usually in the form of rent.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Maturities, Prepayments and Calls of Long-term Investments
definition: The cash inflow from maturities, prepayments, calls and collections of all investments, including securities and other assets, having ready marketability and intended by management to be liquidated, if necessary, beyond the current operating cycle.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Maturities, Repayments and Calls of Trading Securities Held-for-investment
definition: The cash inflow associated with maturities (principal being due), repayments and calls (payments before maturities) of securities classified as trading securities and held for investment purposes. Excludes proceeds from trading securities purchased and held principally for the purpose of selling them in the near term (thus held for only a short period of time).

elementLabel: Proceeds from Mortgage Deposits
definition: Cash inflow received in association with a commitment to issue a mortgage.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Nuclear Fuel
definition: Cash inflow resulting from the sale of any material that is commonly used in the generation of nuclear energy.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Pollution Control Bond
definition: The cash inflow from amounts received from a long-term debt security issued by a state, certain agencies or authorities, a local government, or development corporation to finance the construction of air- or water-pollution control facilities or sewage or solid waste disposal facilities pursuant to federal law. The bonds are backed by the credit of the beneficiary of the financing rather than the credit of the issuer.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Refunds from Suppliers of Material
definition: Cash received for refunds from suppliers during the current period. This element includes refunds from suppliers of materials; it excludes refunds from providers of fixed assets.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Removal Costs
definition: Cash inflow resulting from recoveries, by any means, against the cost of disposing of plant, whether by demolishing, dismantling, abandoning, sale, and so forth during the period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Rents Received
definition: Cash received for rents during the current period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Royalties Received
definition: Cash received for royalties during the current period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale and Collection of Finance Receivables
definition: The cash inflow associated with the sale or collection of receivables arising from the financing of goods and services.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale and Collection of Lease Receivables
definition: The cash inflow associated with the sale or collection of receivables arising from the lease of real estate, equipment or other fixed assets for a specified time in exchange for payment, usually in the form of rent; excludes proceeds from sales-type lease transactions, which are classified as operating activities.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale and Collection of Loans Receivable
definition: The cash inflow associated with the sale and collection of loans receivables arising from the financing of goods and services.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale and Collection of Other Receivables
definition: Amount of cash inflow from the sale and collection of receivables classified as other.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale, Maturity and Collection of Long-term Investments
definition: The cash inflow from sales, maturities, prepayments, calls and collections of all investments, including securities and other assets, having ready marketability and intended by management to be liquidated, if necessary, beyond the current operating cycle.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Buildings
definition: The cash inflow from sale of buildings.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Flight Equipment
definition: Cash received from sales of long-lived depreciable flight assets, including owned aircraft or capital improvements.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Furniture and Fixtures
definition: The cash inflow from sale of furniture and fixtures.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Insurance Investments
definition: The cash inflow associated with the sale of insurance policy investment assets during the period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Interest in Corporate Unit
definition: The cash inflow resulting from the sale of an interest in a corporate unit during the period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Land Held-for-use
definition: The cash inflow from the sale of land held for use; excludes sales of land held as inventory or investments.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Loans and Leases Held-for-investment
definition: The net cash inflow from (a) sales of loans held-for-investment, (b) sales of leases held-for-investment, and (c) both. Includes proceeds from securitizations of loans.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Water Systems
definition: The cash inflow from sale of a facility and equipment that provides water supply which includes wells, reservoirs, pumping stations, and control facilities.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Sale of Wholly Owned Real Estate and Real Estate Acquired in Settlement of Loans
definition: The cash inflow from proceeds From Sales of Wholly Owned Real Estate and Real Estate Acquired in Settlement of Loans.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Securitizations of Consumer Loans
definition: The cash inflow from the securitization of receivables for loans to consumers. Securitization is the structured process whereby interests in loans and other receivables are packaged, underwritten, and sold in the form of asset-backed securities.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Securitizations of Loans Held-for-investment
definition: The cash inflow from the securitization of loans held for investment. Securitization is the structured process whereby interests in loans and other receivables are packaged, underwritten, and sold in the form of asset-backed securities.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Short-term Debt, Maturing in Three Months or Less
definition: The cash inflow from a borrowing having initial term of repayment within three months.

elementLabel: Proceeds of Other Loans and Leases Held-for-investment
definition: Amount of cash inflow from loans and leases held-for-investment, classified as other.

elementLabel: Production Costs, Cumulative
definition: The capitalized costs incurred (excluded from amortization), as of the date of the balance sheet, to operate and maintain wells and related equipment and facilities, including depreciation and applicable operating costs of support equipment and facilities and other costs of operating and maintaining those wells and related equipment and facilities. They become part of the cost of oil and gas produced. Examples of production costs (sometimes called lifting costs) are: costs of labor to operate the wells and related equipment and facilities; repairs and maintenance; materials, supplies, and fuel consumed and supplies utilized in operating the wells and related equipment and facilities; property taxes and insurance applicable to proved properties and wells and related equipment and facilities; severance taxes; some support equipment or facilities may serve two or more oil and gas producing activities and may also serve transportation, refining, and marketing activities. To the extent that the support equipment and facilities are used in oil and gas producing activities, their depreciation and applicable operating costs become exploration, development or production costs, as appropriate. Depreciation, depletion, and amortization of capitalized acquisition, exploration, and development costs are not production costs but also become part of the cost of oil and gas produced along with production (lifting) costs identified above.

elementLabel: Product Liability Contingency, Third Party Recovery
definition: Amount of the estimated recovery from third parties recorded in the period pertaining to product liability damages from specified products.

elementLabel: Product Liability Contingency, Third Party Recovery, Percentage
definition: Percentage of the estimated recovery from third parties recorded in the period pertaining to product liability damages from specified products.

elementLabel: Standard and Extended Product Warranty Accrual
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred through that date and payable for estimated claims under standard and extended warranty protection rights granted to customers.

elementLabel: Product Warranty Accrual, Current
definition: Carrying value as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred through that date and payable for estimated claims under standard and extended warranty protection rights granted to customers. For classified balance sheets, represents the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer).

elementLabel: Pro Forma Weighted Average Shares Outstanding, Diluted
definition: The weighted average number of shares or units and dilutive common stock or unit equivalents outstanding in the calculation of proforma diluted earnings per share (earnings per unit), which is commonly presented in initial public offerings based on the terms of the offering.

elementLabel: Projects that have Exploratory Well Costs that have been Capitalized for Period Greater than One Year, Number of Projects
definition: The number of projects for which exploratory well costs have been capitalized for a period of greater than one year after the completion of drilling.

elementLabel: Propane Costs
definition: Cost incurred related to propane gas during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Propane Revenue
definition: Revenue from sale of propane gas, a product derived from other petroleum products during oil or natural gas processing.

elementLabel: Property Management Fee, Percent Fee
definition: The percentage charged for managing real estate properties.

elementLabel: Property, Plant and Equipment, Number of Aircraft Sold
definition: The number of aircraft sold by the entity during the period.

elementLabel: Property, Plant, and Equipment, Owned, Gross
definition: Gross amount of long-lived, depreciable flight assets owned by the entity and used in the entity's principle business operations (owned aircraft and capitalized improvements) and capitalized assets classified as property, plant and equipment that are owned by the entity. Excludes assets subject to a capital lease.

elementLabel: Property, Plant, and Equipment, Owned, Net
definition: The net amount of long-lived, depreciable flight assets owned by the entity and used in the entity's principle business operations (owned aircraft and capitalized improvements) and capitalized assets classified as property, plant and equipment that are owned by the entity. Excludes assets subject to a capital lease.

elementLabel: Property, Plant, and Equipment, Salvage Value
definition: The estimated or actual value of the asset at the end of its useful life or when it is no longer serviceable (cannot be used for its original purpose).

elementLabel: Property, Plant and Equipment, Salvage Value, Percentage
definition: Stated as a percentage, the estimated or actual value of the asset at the end of its useful life or when it is no longer serviceable (cannot be used for its original purpose) divided by its [historical] capitalized cost.

elementLabel: Property Subject to or Available for Operating Lease, Number of Units
definition: The number of units (items of property) under operating lease arrangements.

elementLabel: Proved Oil and Gas Property, Successful Effort Method
definition: Oil and Gas properties with proved reserves under the successful effort method.

elementLabel: Proved Oil and Gas Reserve Quantities Applicable to Long-term Supply Agreements with Governments or Authorities
definition: Reserve quantities of oil and/or gas subject to purchase under long-term supply, purchase, or similar agreements and contracts with governments or authorities, as of the end of the period if the enterprise participates in the operation of the properties in which the oil or gas is located or otherwise serves as the producer of those reserves, as opposed, for example, to being an independent purchaser, broker, dealer or importer.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Allowance for Funds Used During Construction, Rate
definition: Effective rate, including composite rate, of cost of financing additions to qualifying regulated assets, commonly called allowance for funds used during construction.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Amount of Allowance for Earnings on Equity Capitalized for Rate Making Purposes
definition: Discloses the amount of any allowance for earnings on shareholders' investment capitalized for rate making purposes but not for the financial statements.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Amount of Construction Work in Process Included in Rate Base
definition: Discloses the amount of construction work in process that is included in the rate making process at period end.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Amount of Disallowed Costs for Recently Completed Plant
definition: Amount of disallowed costs for rate making purposes for recently completed plants in regulated industries.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Amount of Interest Incurred on Intermediary Debt for Electric Utility Plant Construction
definition: Amount of interest cost incurred for plant construction by an electric utility using a construction intermediary.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Amount of Remainder of Costs of Disallowed Assets for Recently Completed Plant
definition: The remaining amount of assets disallowed from inclusion in the rate making process pertaining to recently completed plants in regulated industries.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Disclosure of Composite Depreciation Rate for Plants in Service
definition: Composite depreciation rate for public utility plants in service.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Interest Rate on Intermediary Debt for Electric Utility Plant Construction
definition: Discloses the interest rate related to debt for plant construction for an electric utility using an intermediary for each period for which an income statement is presented.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Original Cost of Intangible Utility Plants
definition: Original cost of establishing intangible utility plants.

elementLabel: Public Utilities, Property, Plant and Equipment, Present Value of Regulated Asset for Plant Abandonment
definition: The present value amount of future cost recoveries that are probable and estimable related to plant abandonment's for regulated industries.

elementLabel: Pump Taxes
definition: Pump tax, commonly known as a Replenishment assessment. A charge on each acre-foot of groundwater extracted from the basin. Income from the pump taxes finances the replenishment of the basin and projects for water recycling and water quality improvements.

elementLabel: Purchase Options, Land
definition: Carrying amount of an option or options to acquire real property.

elementLabel: Real Estate Held for Development and Sale
definition: For banks, amount of real estate assets held for development or sale by the consolidated entity.

elementLabel: Real Estate Held for Development and Sale, Net
definition: For banks, amount of real estate assets held for development or sale, net of associated liabilities.

elementLabel: Real Estate Held for Development and Sale, Subsidiary
definition: For banks, amount of real estate assets held for development or resale by subsidiary entities which hold such assets in the course of business.

elementLabel: Real Estate Insurance
definition: A contract to provide coverage or protection in exchange for a payment or "premium". Examples of insurance protection include liability and property insurance. The entity paying the premiums for the protection will have insurance expense and possibly an asset, Prepaid Insurance (if the premiums are paid in advance).

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate, Intercompany Profits Included in Carrying Amount
definition: Amount of intercompany profits included in the amount, before accumulated depreciation, of real estate investments for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: Real Estate Inventory, Construction Materials
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of unprocessed goods that will be used in the course of a construction project which will become a part of the finished inventory.

elementLabel: Real Estate Investments, Net
definition: Amount of real estate investments, net of accumulated depreciation, which may include the following: (1) land available-for-sale; (2) land available-for-development; (3) investments in building and building improvements; (4) tenant allowances; (5) developments in-process; (6) rental properties; (7) other real estate investments; (8) real estate joint ventures; and (9) unconsolidated real estate and other joint ventures not separately presented.

elementLabel: Real Estate Investment Subsidiaries, Cash and Other Assets
definition: For banks, amount of assets of real estate investments of a financial institution which are not land, buildings, or leasehold improvements.

elementLabel: Real Estate Liabilities Associated with Assets Held for Development and Sale
definition: For banks, amount of all liabilities for which a financial institution is required to include in its calculation of net investment in real estate assets held for development or sale.

elementLabel: Real Estate Owned, Accumulated Depreciation
definition: Amount of accumulated depreciation for real estate owned (REO).

elementLabel: Real Estate Subsidiary Liabilities
definition: For banks, amount of liabilities for which a financial institution is required to include in its calculation of net investment in real estate assets held for development or sale.

elementLabel: Real Estate Variable Interest Entity Borrowings
definition: For banks, amount of liabilities in variable interest entities for which a financial institution is required to include in its calculation of net investment in real estate assets held for development or sale.

elementLabel: Receivable for Recovery of Import Duties, Net
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of tariffs due either from customers or suppliers arising from sales or purchases, or as previously overpaid to tax authorities or vendors.

elementLabel: Receivables, Fair Value Disclosure
definition: Fair value portion of receivables, including, but not limited to, trade account receivables, note receivables, and loan receivables.

elementLabel: Receivables Held-for-sale, Amount
definition: The face amount of all receivables that will be sold to other entities, including trade and loan receivables.

elementLabel: Receivables, Long-term Contracts or Programs
definition: Amount to be collected within one year of the balance sheet date (or one operating cycle, if longer) from customers in accordance with the contractual provisions of long-term contracts or programs including amounts billed and unbilled as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Receivables with Imputed Interest, Amortization Amount
definition: The amount of amortization of the discount or premium on the note or receivable which was the result of the determination of present value in cash or noncash transactions, recognized in the statement of operations for the period.

elementLabel: Receivable with Imputed Interest, Effective Yield (Interest Rate)
definition: Yield on the receivable, on which interest has been imputed, as calculated from its issuance value or purchase price. The calculated effective interest rate considers factors such as the issued face value or price paid for the receivable, the time period between payments, and the time until maturity [full receipt] of the receivable.

elementLabel: Receivable with Imputed Interest, Face Amount
definition: The principal amount of the receivable or note before consideration of the discount or premium.

elementLabel: Receivable with Imputed Interest, Premium
definition: Disclosure of the unamortized amount of the premium on the note or receivable which is added to the face amount of the receivable or loan. The discount or premium is defined as the difference between the present value and the face amount.

elementLabel: Recorded Third-Party Environmental Recoveries, Amount
definition: Recorded amount of the individual components comprising the asset for third-party recoveries related to environmental remediation obligations.

elementLabel: Recorded Third-Party Environmental Recoveries, Current
definition: Cumulative amount of the asset for third-party recoveries related to environmental remediation obligations that is recoverable within one year of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Third-Party Environmental Recoveries, Discount
definition: The amount of imputed interest necessary to reduce the expected aggregate undiscounted amount of the asset for third-party recoveries related to environmental remediation obligations to the present value recognized on the balance sheet (if the receivable is discounted).

elementLabel: Recorded Third-Party Environmental Recoveries, Discount Rate
definition: Rate applied to the undiscounted amount of the asset for third-party recoveries related to environmental remediation obligations to arrive at the present value recorded as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Third-Party Environmental Recoveries, Noncurrent
definition: Cumulative amount of the asset for third-party recoveries related to environmental remediation obligations that is recoverable after one year from the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Third-Party Environmental Recoveries Receivable
definition: Carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of known and reasonably estimable amounts of recoveries from third-parties pertaining to an entity's environmental remediation obligations. An entity's balance sheet may include several assets that relate to an environmental remediation obligation. Among them are the following: a. Receivables from other potentially responsible parties that are not providing initial funding; b. anticipated recoveries from insurers; and c. anticipated recoveries from prior owners as a result of indemnification agreements.

elementLabel: Recorded Third-Party Environmental Recoveries, Undiscounted
definition: Aggregate undiscounted amount of the asset for third-party recoveries related to environmental remediation obligations as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Minimum Quantity Required
definition: The minimum number of units that must be purchased, in connection with an unconditional purchase obligation that has been recognized for financial reporting purposes.

elementLabel: Recovery Stranded Costs
definition: Revenue from billings to utility customers to recover what are also referred to as stranded assets or stranded investments. These are assets that formerly regulated utilities with monopolies on local service are allowed to recover during their transition to deregulated suppliers in competitive markets. Essentially, these investments are sunk costs, made by utilities under the old regulated system, which might not be recovered in a truly competitive marketplace. However, since they were valid investments at the time, the utilities are allowed to recover these costs from customers (for example, an investment in electrical generation assets that may not be recouped if customers are now allowed to purchase electricity from another utility).

elementLabel: Recycling Revenue
definition: Revenue from collecting, reselling and reprocessing used or waste materials into new products or materials.

elementLabel: Redeemable Noncontrolling Interest, Equity, Common, Fair Value
definition: The fair value as of the reporting date of noncontrolling interests which are redeemable by the (parent) entity (1) at a fixed or determinable price on a fixed or determinable date, (2) at the option of the holder of the noncontrolling interest, or (3) upon occurrence of an event that is not solely within the control of the (parent) entity. The noncontrolling interest holder's ownership (or holders' ownership) may be in the form of common shares (regardless of class), limited partnership units (regardless of class), non-preferential membership interests, or any other form of common equity regardless of investee entity legal form.

elementLabel: Redeemable Noncontrolling Interest, Equity, Other, Carrying Amount
definition: Amount of noncontrolling interests which are redeemable by the parent entity, classified as other equity.

elementLabel: Redeemable Noncontrolling Interest, Equity, Other, Fair Value
definition: Fair value of noncontrolling interests which are redeemable by the parent entity and classified as other equity.

elementLabel: Redeemable Noncontrolling Interest, Equity, Preferred, Carrying Amount
definition: As of the reporting date, the carrying amount of noncontrolling interests which are redeemable by the (parent) entity (1) at a fixed or determinable price on a fixed or determinable date, (2) at the option of the holder of the noncontrolling interest, or (3) upon occurrence of an event that is not solely within the control of the (parent) entity. The noncontrolling interest holder's ownership (or holders' ownership) may be in the form of preferred shares (regardless of class), preferred partnership units (regardless of class), preferential membership interests, or any other form of preferred equity regardless of investee entity legal form.

elementLabel: Redeemable Noncontrolling Interest, Equity, Preferred, Fair Value
