definition: Amount of accumulated depreciation and amortization at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Property and Equipment, Net
definition: Total property and equipment, net at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Short-term Borrowings
definition: Amount of short-term borrowings at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Other Postretirement Obligations
definition: Amount of noncurrent other postretirement obligations at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Other Property and Equipment
definition: Amount of other property and equipment at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Other Assets, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of other noncurrent assets at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Preferred Stock
definition: Amount of preferred stock at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Preferred and Common Stock Held in Treasury
definition: Amount of preferred and common stock held in treasury at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Amortizable Intangible Assets, Net
definition: Amount of intangible assets subject to amortization at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Goodwill
definition: Amount of goodwill at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Inventories
definition: Amount of inventories at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Prepaid and Other Current Assets
definition: Amount of prepaid and other current assets at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Accounts Payable
definition: Amount of accounts payable at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Accrued Liabilities
definition: Amount of accrued liabilities at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Pension Obligations
definition: Amount of noncurrent pension obligations at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Leasehold Improvements
definition: Amount of leasehold improvements at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Liabilities Subject to Compromise
definition: Amount of liabilities subject to compromise at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Debt Issuance Costs
definition: Amount of debt issuance costs before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Noncurrent Other Obligations
definition: Amount of other noncurrent obligations at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Current Liabilities
definition: Total current liabilities at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Current Assets
definition: Total current assets at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Debtor-in-Possession Financing
definition: Amount of long-term debt related to debtor-in-possession financing at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Restricted Cash and Cash Equivalents, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of noncurrent restricted cash and cash equivalents at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Long-term Debt
definition: Total long-term debt at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Other Current Liabilities
definition: Amount of other current liabilities at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Other Long-term Debt
definition: Amount of other long-term debt at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Investments
definition: Amount of investments at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Liabilities
definition: Total liabilities at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Liabilities and Stockholders' Equity
definition: Total liabilities and stockholders' equity at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Other Assets
definition: Total other assets at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Restricted Cash and Cash Equivalents, Current
definition: Amount of current restricted cash and cash equivalents at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Furniture and Fixtures
definition: Amount of furniture and fixtures at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Other Noncurrent Obligations
definition: Total other noncurrent obligations at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Nonamortizable Intangible Assets
definition: Amount of intangible assets not subject to amortization at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Receivables, Net
definition: Amount of receivables, net at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Short-term Investments
definition: Amount of short-term investments at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Cash and Cash Equivalents
definition: Amount of cash and cash equivalents at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Current Maturities of Long-term Debt
definition: Amount of current maturities of long-term debt at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Assets
definition: Total assets at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Common Stock
definition: Amount of common stock at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Current Maturities of Capital Lease Obligations
definition: Amount of current maturities of capital lease obligations at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Buildings and Improvements
definition: Amount of buildings and improvements at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Land
definition: Amount of land at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Postconfirmation Credit Facility
definition: Amount of long-term postconfirmation date credit facility at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Equipment
definition: Amount of equipment at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preconfirmation, Capital Lease Obligations, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of noncurrent capital lease obligations at the balance sheet date before fresh-start adjustments.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Liquidation Preference, Value
definition: Value of the difference between preference in liquidation and the par or stated values of the preferred shares.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Accretion of Redemption Discount
definition: The amount of accretion of the preferred stock redemption discount during the period.

elementLabel: Proceeds from Issuance of Shares under Incentive and Share-based Compensation Plans, Excluding Stock Options
definition: Amount of cash inflow from issuance of shares under share-based compensation arrangement, excluding stock option exercises.

elementLabel: Product Liability Contingency, Loss Exposure in Excess of Accrual, Best Estimate
definition: Best estimate of the reasonably possible loss exposure in excess of the amount accrued for damages pertaining to a specified product.

elementLabel: Product Liability Contingency, Accrual, Present Value
definition: Present value of the accrual for product liability loss contingencies as of the balance sheet date (if the accrual qualifies for discounting).

elementLabel: Product Liability Contingency, Accrual, Discount Rate
definition: Rate applied to the undiscounted amount of estimated damages for product liability to arrive at the present value recorded as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Product Liability Contingency, Loss Exposure Not Accrued, Best Estimate
definition: Best estimate of the loss exposure for a reasonably possible liability for product liability damages for which no accrual has been recorded.

elementLabel: Product Liability Accrual, Component Amount
definition: Recorded amount of the accrual for a material component of a product liability contingency.

elementLabel: Property, Plant and Equipment, Disposals
definition: Amount of divestiture of long-lived, physical assets used in the normal conduct of business and not intended for resale. Examples include, but are not limited to, land, buildings, machinery and equipment, office equipment, furniture and fixtures, and computer equipment.

elementLabel: Purchase Commitment, Remaining Minimum Amount Committed
definition: Minimum amount to be expended to satisfy the terms of arrangements in which the entity has agreed to expend funds to procure goods or services, excluding long-term purchase commitments or unconditional purchase obligations.

elementLabel: Purchase Obligation, Future Minimum Payments, Remainder of Fiscal Year
definition: Minimum amount of purchase arrangement maturing in the remainder of the fiscal year following the latest fiscal year ended. Includes, but is not limited to, recorded and unrecorded purchase obligations, long-term purchase commitments, and short-term purchase commitments.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Amount of Maturities and Sinking Fund Requirements
definition: States the combined aggregate amount of maturities and sinking fund requirements for a long-term unconditional purchase obligation that has been recognized on the balance sheet.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Nonfinancial Assets Pledged as Security, Value
definition: The value of assets other than financial instruments pledged to provide security to a suppler under a recorded unconditional purchase obligation arrangement.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation Due in Second Year
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation Due in Fourth Year
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation Due in Fifth Year
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation Due after Fifth Year
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing after the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation
definition: Amount of the recorded obligation to transfer funds in the future for fixed or minimum amounts or quantities of goods or services at fixed or minimum prices (for example, as in take-or-pay contracts or throughput contracts).

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation Due in Next Twelve Months
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Recorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation Due in Third Year
definition: Amount of the recorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Registration Payment Arrangement, Accrual Carrying Value
definition: The carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the liability representing the obligation under the registration payment arrangement.

elementLabel: Registration Payment Arrangement, Maximum Potential Consideration
definition: Describes the maximum potential amount of consideration, undiscounted, that could be transferred under the registration payment arrangement.

elementLabel: Regulated Operating Revenue, Exploration and Production
definition: The amount of regulated exploration and production operating revenues recognized during the period.

elementLabel: Reinsurance, Loss on Uncollectible Accounts in Period, Amount
definition: Amount of the write-down or write-off of a receivable from a reinsurer.

elementLabel: Reinsurance Retention Policy, Amount Retained
definition: Stated amount that is the upper retention limit per entity policy.

elementLabel: Reorganization Value, Net Realizable Value of Asset Dispositions
definition: Amount of reorganization value related to estimated net realizable value of asset dispositions. Reorganization value is the amount attributed to the reconstituted entity, as well as the expected net realizable value of those assets that will be disposed before reconstitution occurs.

elementLabel: Reorganization Value, Cash in Excess of Normal Operating Needs
definition: Amount of reorganization value related to cash in excess of normal operating requirements generated by operations. Reorganization value is the amount attributed to the reconstituted entity, as well as the expected net realizable value of those assets that will be disposed before reconstitution occurs.

elementLabel: Research and Development Asset Acquired Other than Through Business Combination, Fair Value Acquired
definition: The fair value of capitalized costs of a research and development nature that were acquired during the period in a transaction other than a business combination.

elementLabel: Short-term Debt, Maximum Amount Outstanding During Period
definition: For the form of debt having an initial term of less than one year or less than the normal operating cycle, if longer, the maximum amount borrowed at any time during the period.

elementLabel: Short-term Debt, Average Outstanding Amount
definition: For the form of debt having an initial term of less than one year or less than the normal operating cycle, if longer, average borrowings during the period.

elementLabel: Short-term Debt, Maximum Month-end Outstanding Amount
definition: For the form of debt having an initial term of less than one year or less than the normal operating cycle, if longer, maximum month-end borrowings during the period.

elementLabel: Shares, Issued
definition: Number of shares of stock issued as of the balance sheet date, including shares that had been issued and were previously outstanding but which are now held in the treasury.

elementLabel: Short-term Debt, Refinanced, Amount
definition: Amount of a short-term obligation that has been excluded from current liabilities in the balance sheet because of a refinancing of the obligation.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Value, Employee Stock Ownership Plan
definition: Aggregate value of stock issued during the period as a result of employee stock ownership plan (ESOP).

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Treasury Stock Reissued
definition: Number of treasury shares (units) reissued during the period, excluding reissuance of shares (units) held in treasury used to satisfy equity-based compensation obligations exercised by the holders of such rights. Upon reissuance of shares (units) from treasury, either the common or preferred stock (unit) reissued is outstanding.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Acquisitions
definition: Number of shares of stock issued during the period pursuant to acquisitions.

elementLabel: Stock Redeemed or Called During Period, Shares
definition: Number of stock bought back by the entity at the exercise price or redemption price.

elementLabel: Stock Repurchased and Retired During Period, Shares
definition: Number of shares that have been repurchased and retired during the period.

elementLabel: Stock Repurchased During Period, Shares
definition: Number of shares that have been repurchased during the period and have not been retired and are not held in treasury. Some state laws may govern the circumstances under which an entity may acquire its own stock and prescribe the accounting treatment therefore. This element is used when state law does not recognize treasury stock.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Stock Splits
definition: Number of shares issued during the period as a result of a stock split.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Employee Stock Ownership Plan
definition: Number of shares of capital stock issued (purchased by employees) in connection with an employee stock ownership plan.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Reverse Stock Splits
definition: Reduction in the number of shares during the period as a result of a reverse stock split.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Restricted Stock Award, Forfeited
definition: Number of shares related to Restricted Stock Award forfeited during the period.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Employee Stock Purchase Plans
definition: Number of shares issued during the period as a result of an employee stock purchase plan.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Value, Stock Dividend
definition: Value of stock issued to shareholders as a dividend during the period.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Value, Employee Stock Purchase Plan
definition: Aggregate change in value for stock issued during the period as a result of employee stock purchase plan.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Value, Restricted Stock Award, Forfeitures
definition: Value of stock related to Restricted Stock Awards forfeited during the period.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Restricted Stock Award, Gross
definition: Total number of shares issued during the period, including shares forfeited, as a result of Restricted Stock Awards.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, New Issues
definition: Number of new stock issued during the period.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Value, Dividend Reinvestment Plan
definition: Value of stock issued during the period from a dividend reinvestment plan (DRIP). A dividend reinvestment plan allows the holder of the stock to reinvest dividends paid to them by the entity on new issues of stock by the entity.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Value, Acquisitions
definition: Value of stock issued pursuant to acquisitions during the period.

elementLabel: Share-based Compensation Arrangement by Share-based Payment Award, Options, Exercises in Period
definition: Number of share options (or share units) exercised during the current period.

elementLabel: Stock and Warrants Issued During Period, Value, Preferred Stock and Warrants
definition: Value of preferred stock and warrants for common stock issued.

elementLabel: Stock Issued During Period, Shares, Dividend Reinvestment Plan
definition: Number of shares issued during the period from a dividend reinvestment plan (DRIP). A dividend reinvestment plan allows the shareholders to reinvest dividends paid to them by the entity on new issues of stock by the entity.

elementLabel: Subsidiary of Limited Liability Company or Limited Partnership, Ownership Interest
definition: The number of units or percentage investment held in the subsidiary by the limited liability company or limited partnership.

elementLabel: Trading Securities, Unrealized Holding Gain
definition: Amount of unrealized holding gain before loss recognized in the income statement for investments in trading securities.

elementLabel: Trading Securities, Realized Gain
definition: This item represents the gain realized during the period from the sale of trading securities.

elementLabel: Trading Securities, Realized Loss
definition: This item represents the loss realized during the period from the sale of trading securities.

elementLabel: Trading Securities, Restricted
definition: Total of all securities that are purchased with the intent to be sold in the short-term and that are pledged to one or more secured parties who have the right to buy, sell, or re-pledge the collateral.

elementLabel: Trading Securities, Unrealized Holding Loss
definition: Amount of unrealized holding loss before gain recognized in the income statement for investments in trading securities.

elementLabel: Treasury Stock, Retired, Par Value Method, Amount
definition: Amount of decrease of par value, additional paid in capital (APIC) and retained earnings of common and preferred stock retired from treasury when treasury stock is accounted for under the par value method.

elementLabel: Treasury Stock, Shares, Acquired
definition: Number of shares that have been repurchased during the period and are being held in treasury.

elementLabel: Treasury Stock, Retired, Cost Method, Amount
definition: Amount of decrease of par value, additional paid in capital (APIC) and retained earnings of common and preferred stock retired from treasury when treasury stock is accounted for under the cost method.

elementLabel: Treasury Stock, Shares, Retired
definition: Number of shares of common and preferred stock retired from treasury during the period.

elementLabel: Unrecognized Tax Benefits, Increase Resulting from Current Period Tax Positions
definition: Amount of increase in unrecognized tax benefits resulting from tax positions that have been or will be taken in current period tax return.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation
definition: Amount of the unrecorded obligation to transfer funds in the future for fixed or minimum amounts or quantities of goods or services at fixed or minimum prices (for example, as in take-or-pay contracts or throughput contracts).

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Imputed Interest
definition: If disclosed, the amount of imputed interest necessary to reduce an unconditional purchase obligation to present value on an unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due in Next Twelve Months
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the next fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due within Four Years
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the fourth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due within Five Years
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the fifth fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Purchases
definition: The amount purchased during the period under an unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation (for example, under the take-or-pay or throughput contract).

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due within Three Years
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the third fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Unrecorded Unconditional Purchase Obligation, Due within Two Years
definition: Amount of the fixed and determinable portion of the unrecorded unconditional purchase obligation maturing in the second fiscal year following the latest fiscal year. Excludes interim and annual periods when interim periods are reported on a rolling approach, from latest balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Variable Interest Entity, Qualitative or Quantitative Information, Ownership Percentage
definition: Percentage of the Variable Interest Entity's (VIE) voting interest owned by (or beneficial interest in) the reporting entity (directly or indirectly).

elementLabel: Weighted Average Number of Shares, Restricted Stock
definition: Number of shares of restricted stock determined by relating the portion of time within a reporting period that restricted shares have been outstanding to the total time in that period. Restricted shares are subject to sales, contractual, regulatory or other restrictions that prevent or inhibit the holder from freely disposing of them before the restriction ends.

elementLabel: Beneficial Interest, Secured by Prepayable Financial Instruments, Last-of-Layer, Amortized Cost
definition: Amortized cost of beneficial interest secured by prepayable financial instrument, used to designate hedging relationship in which hedged item is last layer expected to be remaining at end of hedging relationship.

elementLabel: Capitalized Contract Cost, Net, Current
definition: Amount, after accumulated amortization and accumulated impairment loss, of asset recognized from cost incurred to obtain or fulfill contract with customer; classified as current.

elementLabel: Capitalized Contract Cost, Net, Noncurrent
definition: Amount, after accumulated amortization and accumulated impairment loss, of asset recognized from cost incurred to obtain or fulfill contract with customer; classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Continuing Care Retirement Communities, Obligation for Future Service, Amount
definition: Present value of liability to provide future service and use of facility related to continuing-care contract.

elementLabel: Continuing Care Retirement Communities, Obligation for Future Service, Interest Rate
definition: Interest rate used to discount liability to provide future service related to continuing-care contract.

elementLabel: Common Stock, Convertible, Conversion Price, Increase
definition: Per share increase in conversion price of convertible common stock. Excludes change due to standard antidilution provision.

elementLabel: Closed Portfolio and Beneficial Interest, Last-of-Layer, Amortized Cost
definition: Amortized cost of closed portfolio of prepayable financial asset and beneficial interest secured by prepayable financial instrument, used to designate hedging relationship in which hedged item is last layer expected to be remaining at end of hedging relationship.

elementLabel: Compensation Expense, Excluding Cost of Good and Service Sold
definition: Amount of expense for salary, wage, profit sharing; incentive and equity-based compensation; and other employee benefit. Other employee benefit expense includes, but is not limited to, service component of net periodic benefit cost for defined benefit plan. Excludes compensation cost in cost of good and service sold.

elementLabel: Cost, Depletion
definition: Cost of reduction in quantity of natural resource due to consumption directly related to good produced and service rendered.

elementLabel: Cost, Maintenance
definition: Cost of maintenance incurred and directly related to good produced and service rendered.

elementLabel: Cost, Direct Material
definition: Cost of material used for good produced and service rendered.

elementLabel: Cost, Direct Labor
definition: Cost of labor directly related to good produced and service rendered. Includes, but is not limited to, payroll cost and equity-based compensation.

elementLabel: Cost, Depreciation, Amortization and Depletion
definition: Amount of expense for allocation of cost of tangible and intangible assets over their useful lives, and reduction in quantity of natural resource due to consumption directly used in production of good and rendering of service.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, Less than 12 Months, Accumulated Loss
definition: Amount of accumulated unrealized loss on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), in continuous unrealized loss position for less than 12 months.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Held-to-maturity, Derivative, Cumulative Loss
definition: Amount of loss in accumulated other comprehensive income (AOCI) for derivative hedging forecasted acquisition of investment in debt security measured at amortized cost (held-to-maturity).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Held-to-maturity, Derivative, Cumulative Gain
definition: Amount of gain in accumulated other comprehensive income (AOCI) for derivative hedging forecasted acquisition of investment in debt security measured at amortized cost (held-to-maturity).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Held-to-maturity, Transfer, Amount
definition: Amount of investment in debt security, measured at amortized cost, transferred to investment in debt security, measured at fair value, with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale) and net income (trading).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Trading and Available-for-sale
definition: Amount of investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading) and investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale and Held-to-maturity
definition: Amount of investment in debt security measured at amortized cost (held-to-maturity) and investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Trading, and Equity Securities, FV-NI, Cost
definition: Cost of investment in debt investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading) and investment in equity security with change in fair value recognized in net income (FV-NI). Excludes equity method investment and investment in equity security without readily determinable fair value.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Unrealized Loss Position, Number of Positions
definition: Number of investments in debt securities measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), in unrealized loss position.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Unrealized Loss Position
definition: Amount of investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), in unrealized loss position.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Unrealized Loss Position, Accumulated Loss
definition: Amount of accumulated unrealized loss on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), in unrealized loss position.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, 12 Months or Longer, Number of Positions
definition: Number of investments in debt securities measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), in continuous unrealized loss position for 12 months or longer.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Trading, Realized Gain
definition: Amount of realized gain on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Realized Loss, Excluding Other-than-temporary Impairment
definition: Amount of realized loss on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), excluding other-than-temporary impairment (OTTI).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Restricted
definition: Amount of restricted investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale).

elementLabel: Debt Securities
definition: Amount of investment in debt security measured at amortized cost (held-to-maturity), investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale) and investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Held-to-maturity, Sold, Amount
definition: Amount of investment in debt security, measured at amortized cost, sold.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, 12 Months or Longer, Accumulated Loss
definition: Amount of accumulated unrealized loss on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), in continuous unrealized loss position for 12 months or longer.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, Less than 12 Months
definition: Amount of investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), in continuous unrealized loss position for less than 12 months.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, Less than 12 Months, Number of Positions
definition: Number of investments in debt securities measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), in continuous unrealized loss position for less than 12 months.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Trading, Unrealized Loss
definition: Amount of unrealized loss on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading).

elementLabel: Debt Instrument, Convertible, Conversion Price, Decrease
definition: Per share decrease in conversion price of debt instrument. Excludes change due to standard antidilution provision.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Trading, Realized Loss
definition: Amount of realized loss on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Current
definition: Amount of investment in debt security measured at amortized cost (held-to-maturity), investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale) and investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading); classified as current.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Realized Gain
definition: Amount of realized gain on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Transfer to Trading, Gain
definition: Amount of unrealized gain recognized in earnings from transfer of investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale) to investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale) and investment in debt security measured at amortized cost (held-to-maturity), classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Trading, Restricted
definition: Amount of restricted investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Transfer to Trading, Loss
definition: Amount of unrealized loss recognized in earnings from transfer of investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale) to investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading).

elementLabel: Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Continuous Unrealized Loss Position, 12 Months or Longer
definition: Amount of investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), in continuous unrealized loss position for more than 12 months.

elementLabel: Debt Instrument, Convertible, Conversion Price, Increase
definition: Per share increase in conversion price of debt instrument. Excludes change due to standard antidilution provision.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Pension Plan with Projected Benefit Obligation in Excess of Plan Assets, Plan Assets
definition: Amount of plan asset for defined benefit pension plan with projected benefit obligation in excess of plan assets.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Pension Plan with Projected Benefit Obligation in Excess of Plan Assets, Accumulated Benefit Obligation
definition: Amount of accumulated benefit obligation for defined benefit pension plan with projected benefit obligation in excess of plan assets.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Pension Plan with Projected Benefit Obligation in Excess of Plan Assets, Projected Benefit Obligation
definition: Amount of projected benefit obligation for defined benefit pension plan with projected benefit obligation in excess of plan assets.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Plan Assets, Investment within Plan Asset Category, Amount
definition: Amount of investment within defined benefit plan asset category.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Plan Assets, Investment within Plan Asset Category, Percentage
definition: Percentage of investment to total investment within defined benefit plan asset category.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Plan Assets Level 3 Reconciliation, Decrease for Sale
definition: Amount, measured using unobservable input, of decrease in plan asset of defined benefit plan from sale.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Plan Assets Level 3 Reconciliation, Decrease for Settlement
definition: Amount, measured using unobservable input, of decrease in plan asset of defined benefit plan from settlement of trade associated with underlying investment.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Plan Assets Level 3 Reconciliation, Increase for Purchase
definition: Amount, measured using unobservable input, of increase in plan asset of defined benefit plan from purchase.

elementLabel: Derivative, Excluded Component, Gain, Recognized in Earnings
definition: Amount of gain from excluded component of derivative hedge, recognized in earnings. Excludes recognition under systematic and rational method.

elementLabel: Derivative, Excluded Component, Loss, Recognized in Earnings
definition: Amount of loss from excluded component of derivative hedge, recognized in earnings. Excludes recognition under systematic and rational method.

elementLabel: Dividend Income, Equity Securities, Operating
definition: Amount of dividend income on investment in equity security, classified as operating.

elementLabel: Equity Securities, FV-NI
definition: Amount of investment in equity security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (FV-NI).

elementLabel: Equity Securities, FV-NI and without Readily Determinable Fair Value
definition: Amount of investment in equity security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (FV-NI) and investment in equity security without readily determinable fair value.

elementLabel: Equity Securities, FV-NI, Cost
definition: Cost of investment in equity security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (FV-NI). Excludes equity method investment and investment in equity security without readily determinable fair value.

elementLabel: Equity Securities, FV-NI, Realized Gain
definition: Amount of realized gain from sale of investment in equity security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (FV-NI).

elementLabel: Equity Securities, FV-NI, Realized Loss
definition: Amount of realized loss from sale of investment in equity security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (FV-NI).

elementLabel: Equity Securities, FV-NI, Restricted
definition: Amount of restricted investment in equity security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (FV-NI).

elementLabel: Equity Securities, FV-NI, Unrealized Gain
definition: Amount of unrealized gain on investment in equity security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (FV-NI).

elementLabel: Equity Securities, FV-NI, Unrealized Loss
definition: Amount of unrealized loss on investment in equity security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (FV-NI).

elementLabel: Equity Securities without Readily Determinable Fair Value, Amount
definition: Amount of investment in equity security without readily determinable fair value.

elementLabel: Equity Securities without Readily Determinable Fair Value, Downward Price Adjustment, Annual Amount
definition: Amount of loss from downward price adjustment on investment in equity security without readily determinable fair value.

elementLabel: Equity Securities without Readily Determinable Fair Value, Downward Price Adjustment, Cumulative Amount
definition: Amount of cumulative loss from downward price adjustment on investment in equity security without readily determinable fair value.

elementLabel: Equity Securities without Readily Determinable Fair Value, Impairment Loss, Cumulative Amount
definition: Amount of cumulative impairment loss on investment in equity security without readily determinable fair value.

elementLabel: Equity Securities without Readily Determinable Fair Value, Upward Price Adjustment, Annual Amount
definition: Amount of gain from upward price adjustment on investment in equity security without readily determinable fair value.

elementLabel: Equity Securities without Readily Determinable Fair Value, Upward Price Adjustment, Cumulative Amount
definition: Amount of cumulative gain from upward price adjustment on investment in equity security without readily determinable fair value.

elementLabel: Financial Instrument Subject to Mandatory Redemption, Par Value Per Share
definition: Par value per share of mandatory redeemable financial instrument classified as liability.

elementLabel: Health Care Organization, Accounts Receivable Due from Third-Party Payor, Retroactive Adjustment
definition: Amount of receivable from retroactive adjustment for final settlement or appeal due from third-party payor.

elementLabel: Hedged Asset, Fair Value Hedge
definition: Amount of asset hedged in fair value hedging relationship.

elementLabel: Hedged Asset, Fair Value Hedge, Last-of-Layer, Amount
definition: Amount of asset hedged in last of layer, expected to be remaining at end of hedging relationship.

elementLabel: Hedged Liability, Fair Value Hedge
definition: Amount of liability hedged in fair value hedging relationship.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Debt Securities, Available-for-sale, Operating
definition: Amount of interest income, amortization of premium and accretion of discount on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale); classified as operating.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Debt Securities, Operating
definition: Amount of interest income, amortization of premium and accretion of discount, on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in other comprehensive income (available-for-sale), investment in debt security measured at amortized cost (held-to-maturity) and investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading); classified as operating.

elementLabel: Interest Income, Debt Securities, Trading, Operating
definition: Amount of interest income, amortization of premium and accretion of discount, on investment in debt security measured at fair value with change in fair value recognized in net income (trading); classified as operating.

elementLabel: Merchant Marine, Operating-differential Subsidy
definition: Amount of operating-differential subsidy received pursuant to Merchant Marine Act of 1936.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Convertible, Conversion Price, Decrease
definition: Per share decrease in conversion price of convertible preferred stock. Excludes change due to standard antidilution provision.

elementLabel: Preferred Stock, Convertible, Conversion Price, Increase
definition: Per share increase in conversion price of convertible preferred stock. Excludes change due to standard antidilution provision.

elementLabel: Prepayable Financial Asset Closed Portfolio, Last-of-Layer, Amortized Cost
definition: Amortized cost of closed portfolio of prepayable financial asset, used to designate hedging relationship in which hedged item is last layer expected to be remaining at end of hedging relationship.

elementLabel: Reserve Quantity Attributable to Consolidated Subsidiary, Noncontrolling Interest, Volume
definition: Volume of reserve quantity of oil and gas attributable to consolidated subsidiary with noncontrolling interest.

elementLabel: Short-duration Insurance Contract, Discounted Liability, Discount for Reinsurance
definition: Amount of cumulative discount for reinsurance related to time value of money deducted from short-duration insurance contract liability reported at present value.

elementLabel: Short-duration Insurance Contract, Discounted Liability, Discount, Net of Reinsurance
definition: Amount of cumulative discount, after effect of reinsurance, related to time value of money deducted from short-duration insurance contract liability reported at present value.

elementLabel: Stock Option, Exercise Price, Decrease
definition: Per share decrease in exercise price of stock option. Excludes change due to standard antidilution provision and stock option granted for share-based compensation.

elementLabel: Stock Option, Exercise Price, Increase
definition: Per share increase in exercise price of stock option. Excludes change due to standard antidilution provision and stock option granted for share-based compensation.

elementLabel: Warrant, Exercise Price, Decrease
definition: Per share decrease in exercise price of warrant. Excludes change due to standard antidilution provision.

elementLabel: Warrant, Exercise Price, Increase
definition: Per share increase in exercise price of warrant. Excludes change due to standard antidilution provision.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Production
definition: Production of proved reserves.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Sales of Minerals in Place
definition: Sales of minerals in place.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate and Accumulated Depreciation, Amount of Encumbrances
definition: Amount of lien or mortgage outstanding on real estate investment properties for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserve, Production (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of decrease in quantity of proved reserve of oil and gas resulting from production, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Sale of Mineral in Place (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of decrease in quantity of proved reserve of oil and gas resulting from sale of mineral in place, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Extensions, Discoveries, and Additions
definition: Additions to proved reserves that result from (1) extension of the proved acreage of previously discovered (old) reservoirs through additional drilling in periods after discovery and (2) discovery of new fields with proved reserves or of new reservoirs of proved reserves in old fields.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Purchases of Minerals in Place
definition: Purchase of minerals in place.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Net
definition: The net quantity of proved reserves as of the balance sheet date. Proved oil reserves are the estimated quantities of crude oil and natural gas liquids which geological and engineering data demonstrate with reasonable certainty to be recoverable.

elementLabel: Proved Developed Reserves (Volume)
definition: Net quantities of an enterprise's interests in proved developed reserves of either crude oil (including condensate and natural gas liquids), natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other nonrenewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas as of the beginning and the end of the year. "Net" quantities of reserves include those relating to the enterprise's operating and nonoperating interests in properties. Quantities of reserves relating to royalty interests owned are included in "net" quantities if the necessary information is available to the enterprise. "Net" quantities does not include reserves relating to interests of others in properties owned by the enterprise. The unit of measure for reserve quantities is defined as "barrels" for oil and synthetic oil reserves or "cubic feet" or "cubic meters" for natural gas and synthetic gas reserves.

elementLabel: Proved Undeveloped Reserve (Volume)
definition: Net quantities of an enterprise's interests in proved undeveloped reserves of either crude oil (including condensate and natural gas liquids), natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other renewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas as of the beginning and the end of the year. "Net" quantities of reserves include those relating to the enterprise's operating and nonoperating interests in properties. Quantities of reserves relating to royalty interests owned are included in "net" quantities if the necessary information is available to the enterprise. "Net" quantities does not include reserves relating to interests of others in properties owned by the enterprise. The unit of measure for reserve quantities is defined as "barrels" for oil and synthetic oil reserves or "cubic feet" or "cubic meters" for natural gas and synthetic gas reserves.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserves, Improved Recovery
definition: Changes in proved reserve estimates resulting from application of improved recovery techniques.

elementLabel: Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Production Costs
definition: Amount of estimated future accumulated cash outflow for costs to be incurred in producing proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Development Costs
definition: Amount of estimated future accumulated cash outflow for costs to be incurred in developing proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Periodic Payment Terms, Balloon Payment to be Received
definition: Amount of large payment to be received at final maturity date of mortgage loans.

elementLabel: Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Cash Inflows
definition: Amount of estimated future accumulated cash inflow from the sale of proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force, Assumed
definition: Amount of life insurance issued and outstanding assumed from other entities. Includes, but not limited to, dividends and adjustments to face value.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force, Ceded
definition: Amount of life insurance issued and outstanding ceded to other entities. Includes, but not limited to, dividends and adjustments to face value.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force, Gross
definition: Amount before contracts ceded to other entities and contracts assumed by the entity of life insurance issued and outstanding. Includes, but not limited to, dividends and adjustments to face value.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force, Net
definition: Amount after contracts ceded to other entities and contracts assumed by the entity of life insurance issued and outstanding. Includes, but not limited to, dividends and adjustments to face value.

elementLabel: Life Insurance in Force, Percentage Assumed to Net
definition: Percentage of assumed life insurance issued and outstanding contracts to life insurance issued and outstanding after contracts ceded to other entities and contracts assumed by the entity. Includes, but not limited to, dividends and adjustments to face value.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Delinquent Principal or Interest, Acquired from Affiliates
definition: Amount of principal due on loans that have been delinquent, which may exclude loans having interest delinquent for three months or less, as of the balance sheet date that were acquired from controlled and other affiliates.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Face Amount of Mortgages
definition: Amount of the contractual principal due at the origination of the mortgage loan (face amount).

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Federal Income Tax Basis
definition: Amount of the federal income tax basis of mortgage loans on real estate.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Interest Rate
definition: The stated interest rate on the mortgage loan receivable or the weighted average interest rate on a group of loans.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Number of Loans
definition: Indicates the number of mortgages under each classification.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Principal Amount of Delinquent Loans
definition: Amount of principal due on loans that have been delinquent, which may exclude loans having interest delinquent for three months or less, as of the balance sheet date.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Prior Liens
definition: Amount of prior lien on the real estate that secures the mortgage loan.

elementLabel: Oil and Gas Quantities Received under Long-term Supply Agreements with Governments or Authorities
definition: The net quantity of oil and/or gas received under long-term supply, purchase, or similar agreements and contracts, including such agreements with governments or authorities, as of the end of the period if the enterprise participates in the operation of the properties in which the oil or gas is located or otherwise serves as the "producer" of those reserves, as opposed, for example, to being an independent purchaser, broker, dealer or importer.

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserve, Extension and Discovery (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of increase in quantity of proved reserve of oil and gas resulting from the extension of the proved acreage of previously discovered reservoir or discovery of new field with proved reserve or of new reservoir of proved reserve in old field, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserve, Improved Recovery (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of increase in quantity of proved reserve of oil and gas resulting from application of improved recovery techniques, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserve, Net (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of proved reserve of oil and gas, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed and Undeveloped Reserve, Purchase of Mineral in Place (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of increase in quantity of proved reserve of oil and gas resulting from purchase of mineral in place, stated in a unit of energy. For example, but not limited to, barrel of oil equivalents (BOE) or one thousand cubic feet of natural gas equivalent (Mcfe).

elementLabel: Proved Developed Reserves (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of interests in proved developed reserves of crude oil, including condensate and natural gas liquids, natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other nonrenewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas.

elementLabel: Proved Undeveloped Reserves (Energy)
definition: Energy measure of proved undeveloped reserves of crude oil, including condensate and natural gas liquids, natural gas, synthetic oil and gas, or other nonrenewable natural resource that is intended to be upgraded into synthetic oil and gas.

elementLabel: Reserves, Share of Equity Method Investee's Net Proved Oil and Gas Reserves
definition: The proportional interest of net proved oil reserve quantities of equity investees.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate, Number of Units
definition: Number of units of real estate held for investment for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: Previously Estimated Development Costs Incurred
definition: Amount of increase in standardized measure of discounted future net cash flow as a result of previously estimated development costs incurred.

elementLabel: Mortgage Loans on Real Estate, Collections of Principal
definition: The amount of principal collected on mortgage loans on real estate during the reporting period.

elementLabel: Decrease Due to Sales of Minerals in Place
definition: Amount of decrease in standardized measure of discounted future net cash flow as a result of sales of minerals in place.

elementLabel: Standardized Measure of Discounted Future Net Cash Flow Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves, Accretion of Discount
definition: Amount of accretion of discount for the standardized measure of discounted future net cash flow related to proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: Proved Oil and Gas Reserve Quantities Applicable to Long-term Supply Agreements with Governments or Authorities
definition: Reserve quantities of oil and/or gas subject to purchase under long-term supply, purchase, or similar agreements and contracts with governments or authorities, as of the end of the period if the enterprise participates in the operation of the properties in which the oil or gas is located or otherwise serves as the producer of those reserves, as opposed, for example, to being an independent purchaser, broker, dealer or importer.

elementLabel: Increase Due to Purchases of Minerals in Place
definition: Amount of increase in standardized measure of discounted future net cash flow as a result of purchases of minerals in place.

elementLabel: Standardized Measure of Discounted Future Net Cash Flows Relating to Proved Oil and Gas Reserves
definition: Amount of discounted future accumulated cash inflow relating to proved oil and gas reserves.

elementLabel: SEC Schedule III, Real Estate, Federal Income Tax Basis
definition: Cost basis of real estate investments for federal income tax purposes for entities with a substantial portion of business acquiring and holding investment real estate.

elementLabel: Earnings Per Share, Basic, Distributed
definition: Dividends declared in the period and the contractual amount of dividends (or interest on participating income bonds) that must be paid per security.

elementLabel: Accounts and Financing Receivable, Allowance for Credit Loss
definition: Amount of allowance for credit loss of accounts and financing receivables. Includes, but is not limited to, notes and loan receivable.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, 90 Days or More Past Due, Still Accruing
definition: Amount of accounts receivable, classified as noncurrent, 90 days or more past due and still accruing.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Nonaccrual
definition: Amount of accounts receivable, classified as noncurrent, on nonaccrual status.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Nonaccrual, Interest Income
definition: Amount of interest income on accounts receivable, classified as noncurrent, on nonaccrual status.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Nonaccrual, No Allowance
definition: Amount of accounts receivable, classified as noncurrent, on nonaccrual status with no allowance for credit loss.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Not Past Due
definition: Amount of accounts receivable not past due, classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Originated Five or More Years before Latest Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of accounts receivable originated five or more years prior to latest fiscal year, classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Originated Four Years before Latest Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of accounts receivable originated four years prior to latest fiscal year, classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Originated in Current Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of accounts receivable originated in current fiscal year, classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Originated in Fiscal Year before Latest Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of accounts receivable originated in fiscal year prior to latest fiscal year, classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Originated Three Years before Latest Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of accounts receivable originated three years prior to latest fiscal year, classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Originated Two Years before Latest Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of accounts receivable originated two years prior to latest fiscal year, classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Noncurrent, Past Due
definition: Amount of accounts receivable past due, classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Purchase
definition: Amount of increase from purchase of accounts receivable.

elementLabel: Accounts Receivable, Sale
definition: Amount of decrease from sale of accounts receivable.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, after Reinsurance
definition: Amount, after effect of reinsurance, of present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, before Reinsurance, after Discount Rate Change
definition: Amount, before effect of reinsurance and after current period update of cash flow assumption and discount rate change, of present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, Benefit Payment
definition: Amount of cash outflow to policyholder related to benefit payment for present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, Current Weighted-Average Discount Rate
definition: Current weighted-average discount rate used to measure present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, Derecognition
definition: Amount of decrease in present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment from derecognition of contract. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, Gross Premium Income
definition: Amount of gross premium income recognized for present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, Issuance
definition: Amount of increase in present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment from contract issuance. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, Net Premium Collected
definition: Amount of gross premium collected from policyholder to fund expected benefit payment for present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, Original Discount Rate, before Cash Flow and Reinsurance
definition: Amount, before effect of reinsurance and current period update of cash flow assumption, of present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment, discounted at original rate. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, Original Discount Rate, before Reinsurance, after Cash Flow Change
definition: Amount, before effect of reinsurance and after current period update of cash flow assumption, of present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment, discounted at original rate. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, Reinsurance Recoverable, after Allowance
definition: Amount, after allowance for credit loss, recoverable under reinsurance for present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Additional Liability, Long-Duration Insurance, Weighted-Average Interest Accretion Rate
definition: Original weighted-average discount rate at contract issue date used to measure present value of total expected payment to policyholder in excess of present value of total expected assessment. Excludes benefit classified as market risk benefit or under provisions of Topic 815 on derivative and hedging.

elementLabel: Contract with Customer, Asset, Allowance for Credit Loss, Recovery
definition: Amount of increase in allowance for credit loss on right to consideration in exchange for good or service transferred to customer when right is conditioned on something other than passage of time, from recovery.

elementLabel: Contract with Customer, Asset, Allowance for Credit Loss, Writeoff
definition: Amount of writeoff of right to consideration in exchange for good or service transferred to customer when right is conditioned on something other than passage of time, charged against allowance for credit loss.

elementLabel: Contract with Customer, Asset, Not Past Due
definition: Amount of right to consideration in exchange for good or service transferred to customer when right is conditioned on something other than passage of time, not past due.

elementLabel: Contract with Customer, Asset, Past Due
definition: Amount of right to consideration in exchange for good or service transferred to customer when right is conditioned on something other than passage of time, past due.

elementLabel: Contract with Customer, Asset, Purchase
definition: Amount of increase from purchase of right to consideration in exchange for good or service transferred to customer when right is conditioned on passage of time.

elementLabel: Contract with Customer, Asset, Sale
definition: Amount of decrease from sale of right to consideration in exchange for good or service transferred to customer when right is conditioned on something other than passage of time and other income.

elementLabel: Cost of Goods and Service, Excluding Depreciation, Depletion, and Amortization
definition: Cost of product sold and service rendered, excluding depreciation, depletion, and amortization.

elementLabel: Deferred Income
definition: Amount of deferred income excluding obligation to transfer product and service to customer for which consideration has been received or is receivable.

elementLabel: Deferred Income, Current
definition: Amount of deferred income excluding obligation to transfer product and service to customer for which consideration has been received or is receivable, classified as current.

elementLabel: Deferred Income, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of deferred income excluding obligation to transfer product and service to customer for which consideration has been received or is receivable, classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Deferred Policy Acquisition Cost and Present Value of Future Insurance Profit, Experience Adjustment
definition: Amount of expense for writeoff from unexpected insurance contract termination, charged against previously capitalized amount in deferred policy acquisition cost and present value of future profit from insurance contract acquired in business combination.

elementLabel: Deferred Policy Acquisition Cost, Experience Adjustment
definition: Amount of expense for writeoff from unexpected insurance contract termination, charged against previously capitalized deferred policy acquisition cost.

elementLabel: Deferred Sale Inducement Cost, Experience Adjustment
definition: Amount of expense for writeoff from unexpected insurance contract termination, charged against previously capitalized deferred sale inducement cost.

elementLabel: Deferred Tax Asset, Interest Carryforward
definition: Amount, before allocation of valuation allowance, of deferred tax asset attributable to deductible interest carryforward.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Assumptions Used Calculating Benefit Obligation, Weighted-Average Interest Crediting Rate
definition: Weighted-average interest crediting rate used to determine benefit obligation of defined benefit plan. Plan includes, but is not limited to, cash balance and other defined benefit plans with promised interest crediting rate.

elementLabel: Defined Benefit Plan, Assumptions Used Calculating Net Periodic Benefit Cost, Weighted-Average Interest Crediting Rate
definition: Weighted-average interest crediting rate used to determine net periodic benefit cost of defined benefit plan. Plan includes, but is not limited to, cash balance and other defined benefit plans with promised interest crediting rate.

elementLabel: Derivative, Nonmonetary Notional Amount
definition: Nominal number of units used to calculate payment on derivative.

elementLabel: Derivative, Notional Amount
definition: Nominal or face amount used to calculate payment on derivative.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, 90 Days or More Past Due, Still Accruing
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease, 90 days or more past due and still accruing.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Allowance for Credit Loss
definition: Amount of allowance for credit loss on net investment in direct financing lease.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Allowance for Credit Loss, Current
definition: Amount of allowance for credit loss on net investment in direct financing lease, classified as current.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Allowance for Credit Loss, Noncurrent
definition: Amount of allowance for credit loss on net investment in direct financing lease, classified as noncurrent.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Allowance for Credit Loss, Recovery
definition: Amount of increase in allowance for credit loss on net investment in direct financing lease, from recovery.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Allowance for Credit Loss, Writeoff
definition: Amount of writeoff of net investment in direct financing lease, charged against allowance for credit loss.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Change in Present Value, Interest Income
definition: Amount of interest income on net investment in direct financing lease, from change in present value of expected cash flows, attributable to passage of time.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Nonaccrual
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease on nonaccrual status.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Nonaccrual, Interest Income
definition: Amount of interest income on net investment in direct financing lease, on nonaccrual status.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Nonaccrual, No Allowance
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease on nonaccrual status with no allowance for credit loss.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Not Past Due
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease, not past due.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Originated Five or More Years before Latest Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease originated five or more years prior to latest fiscal year.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Originated Four Years before Latest Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease originated four years prior to latest fiscal year.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Originated in Current Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease originated in current fiscal year.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Originated in Fiscal Year before Latest Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease originated in fiscal year prior to latest fiscal year.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Originated Three Years before Latest Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease originated three years prior to latest fiscal year.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Originated Two Years before Latest Fiscal Year
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease originated two years prior to latest fiscal year.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Past Due
definition: Amount of net investment in direct financing lease, past due.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Purchase
definition: Amount of increase from purchase of net investment in direct financing lease.

elementLabel: Direct Financing Lease, Net Investment in Lease, Sale
definition: Amount of decrease from sale of net investment in direct financing lease.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, after Deferred Income Offset
definition: Amount, after fee received for commitment to originate or purchase, of financing receivable. Excludes financing receivable covered under loss sharing agreement.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Allowance for Credit Loss, Purchased with Credit Deterioration, Increase
definition: Amount of increase in allowance for credit loss on financing receivable purchased with credit deterioration.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Allowance for Credit Loss, Writeoff, after Recovery
definition: Amount, after recovery, of writeoff of financing receivable, charged against allowance for credit loss.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, before Allowance for Credit Loss and Fee
definition: Amount, before allowance for credit loss and fee, of financing receivable. Excludes financing receivable covered under loss sharing agreement.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Change in Present Value, Interest Income
definition: Amount of interest income on financing receivable, from change in present value of expected cash flows, attributable to passage of time.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Covered and Not Covered, after Allowance for Credit Loss, Fee, Premium, and Discount
definition: Amount, after allowance for credit loss and unamortized deferred fee, premium, and discount, of financing receivable covered under loss sharing agreement and financing receivable not covered under loss sharing agreement.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Covered, after Allowance for Credit Loss
definition: Amount, after allowance, of finance receivable covered by loss sharing agreement.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Covered, Allowance for Credit Loss
definition: Amount of allowance for finance receivable covered by loss sharing agreement.

elementLabel: Financing Receivable, Covered, before Allowance for Credit Loss
